name: Bon Ami
description:
Bon Ami- Bistro and Creperie, a restaurant in the West Washington Park neighborhood of Denver, offers authentic French cuisine in a casual bistro setting. The Dinner is served every night, and Brunch is served on Saturdays and Sundays.

Both Brunch and Dinner menus offer a variety of savory crepes and French bistro classics-Escargot, Mussels, Croque Monsieur, Crispy Chicken and Frites, Beef Bourguignon, Fish and chips, Steak and Frites…
Monday through Friday 4 pm till 6 pm join us for a Happy Hour, enjoy half price on all bottles of wine and stay for our intimate twilight lit patio.

topReview.highlightedText: crepe varieties are catering to everyone's tastes and salads are good. different wines from the usual and of course the garden eating area is wonderful

name: Carmine's On Penn
description: Carmine's on Penn was established in 1994 as a neighborhood, family-style Italian restaurant. Our atmosphere is casual, festive, and friendly. Our servers bring the menu to life, describing dishes and offering advice on selecting just the right combination of food and beverage. We are currently accepting reservations for up to 14 people. Please include persons of any age in the reservation. Carmine's on Penn is currently offering takeout and dining Tues/Wed/Thur/Sun 5-8pm  Fri/Sat 5-9 303-777-6443

topReview.highlightedText: Wonderful service from the hostesses to the bartender and waiters. All knowledgeable and friendly. And the food!!! Oh my! The seasonal ravioli with mushrooms and fontina! We also dined on baked ziti with bolognese and it was hearty and flavorful. Our server helped us pick a red blend wine that was perfect.

name: Odyssey Italian Restaurant & Wine Bar
description: Welcome to The "Old School" Odyssey Italian Restaurant. Come try our delicious Sicilian & Classic Italian dishes which are chef's recipes from back home in Palermo, Sicily. We are family operated & located in a 111 year old historical Victorian Mansion which is perfect for all occasions. You have definitely found a unique gem and an experience unlike no other.

topReview.highlightedText: Monday nights would not be complete without dining at the Odyssey!

name: Bruno's Italian Bistro
description: We believe Brunos Italian Bistro, could be just the thing you're looking for, offers a enjoyable meal from our pasta dishes, choice of chicken, seafood or steak. Please relax with your choice of a bottle of selected wine, chilled beer or a cocktail.

topReview.highlightedText: Food was out of this world!!  Best Italian I've ever had and Ive been to many places.  Service was off the charts fantastic!!  We will definitely be going back!

name: Go Fish - Denver
description: Go Fish Japanese restaurant fits right in amongst the trendy shopping, eating, and drinking destinations on South Broadway - packed with personality and local flavor, this well kept secret is a favorite of locals looking for some quality food to go with a night on the town. If sushi isn't your thing, Go Fish also has a whole menu of Asian goodness and a full bar, serving up traditional drinks as well as the occasional wasabi shot. A must-visit for anyone looking for quality Asian food in Denver.

topReview.highlightedText: First time there and will definitely be back.

name: True Food Kitchen - Cherry Creek
description: True Food Kitchen in Cherry Creek is currently open with dine-in and carry-out service. As always, we will continue to prioritize the health and safety of our guests by following the guidance of the CDC and local health officials. We appreciate your patience and understanding as we navigate this new normal together.

topReview.highlightedText: Food was wonderful, as always, with the exception of one of our favorite items (lettuce cups) no longer being available even though it was on the menu. We couldn't have asked for a better server - Christian was fantastic. Super attentive, good natured and professional.

name: Rioja
description: Chef Jennifer Jasinski's creatively inspired food is influenced by local seasonal products.  Rioja is simple, pure food that emphasizes bright flavors and textures. The wines are a collection of fun interesting varietals that complement the cuisine.

topReview.highlightedText: Had tasting menu. Everything was amazing, but I loved how vegetables were in every dish. I have been to several Top Chef restaurants and this is my favorite, hands down.

name: The Blue Bonnet Restaurant
description: When a family owned restaurant has been in business for almost 50 years, they must be doing something right. Recently expanded with a beautiful patio, the Blue Bonnet has become an institution in Denver. Handmade chips and salsa, specialty street tacos, fire roasted stuffed poblanos,  chimi changas, award-winning margaritas,  chile rellenos, pollo adovado, fish tacos, and carnitas are just a few items made from scratch along with many traditional favorites. Locals, tourists, and celebrities line up for some of the freshest and best tasting Mexican food in Denver. Casual atmosphere with friendly service. If you can't go South of the border... at least head South of Alameda. East availability for large parties even on the weekends.

topReview.highlightedText: As always, some of the best food in town!

name: Guard & Grace
description: Chef Troy Guard’s largest and most exciting concept, Guard and Grace, is a 9,000 square ft. modern American steakhouse located at 1801 California Street in downtown Denver. The sophisticated new space offers private dining areas, one of Denvers largest patios, an expansive raw bar, a wood burning oven and open kitchen.

topReview.highlightedText: Go, go now. We ordered the wagyu tomahawk and it was worth every bite. When you go to a steak house you expect a steak of good quality and to be cooked to perfection — you’ll definitely find that here. Personally, I would have to say the sides were the show stoppers. The gnocchi, which usually I don’t go for, was the show stopper plus the smoky, grilled carrots. Yum! The service was also what you would expect from a higher caliber restaurant — anticipation of needs, flawless service, and knowledgeable. First class!

name: Ocean Prime - Denver - Larimer Square
description:
Ocean Prime is a nationally acclaimed, modern American restaurant & lounge from the award-winning Cameron Mitchell Restaurants. There is a warm & vibrant energy, stunning settings, an impressive menu of seafood & steaks, and genuine hospitality making Ocean Prime the ideal place to socialize, talk business, celebrate & indulge. Made from scratch dishes showcase simple, pure & regional flavors. Our menu features an array of appetizers, salads, seafood, steaks, sides, house-made desserts & handcrafted cocktails.
Located at Denver's Historic Larimer Square, OP features a vibrant outdoor terrace & is open nightly for dinner. OP also features 5 stunning private dining rooms.

We are proud to announce our new, state-of-the-art Air Filtration and Air Purification system has been installed in our restaurant. Our NEW iWave Air Purification system, along with MERV Filters, will eliminate 99.4% of all airborne pathogens, including viruses and COVID

topReview.highlightedText: Best place! Food amazing great service! Always enjoy and love the atmosphere!

name: Table 6
description: Table 6 is a classic American bistro, offering a warm and inviting atmosphere. Chef Aniedra Nichols prepares succulent dishes, delivered with elegant style and complimented with a dynamic wine list, created by Owner/Sommelier Aaron Forman, which represents most of the flourishing wine districts from all over the world. Please visit us at the restaurant or call us at 303-831-8800.

topReview.highlightedText: Food was excellent. Service was great as well. I only wish they had a full bar!

name: North Italia – Denver
description: At North, we focus on what we do best: Italian from scratch. Enjoy any of our handmade pastas and pizzas, created with seasonal ingredients and inventive flavors.  Or, try a different signature dish, prepared with our fresh flavors from the garden, farm, and sea. We’ve hand crafted seasonal cocktails that pair great with our food, creating a real modern Italia experiences perfect for any occasion.

topReview.highlightedText: Delicious food and good service! We enjoyed it!

name: Satchel's on 6th
description:
Satchel's on 6th.

September UPDATE:

Satchel's will be close between September 7-15th for a much needed break. Please refer to our web page for all the details www.Satchelon6th.com

Named after the owner’s youngest son, Satchel’s on 6th is the place to eat and drink. Our Chef has created a contemporary, eclectic, New American neighborhood menu using seasonal ingredients that results in refined flavors and inspired plates. We've put our heart and soul into this place and it gives us great pleasure to serve you.
Warm wood tones and exposed brick highlight this cozy, 50 seat space that has made its home on East Denver reinvigorated 6th Avenue. Says Casalini, Our goal is to become the best go-to, indispensable restaurant in the neighborhood. Period. End of story.

topReview.highlightedText: LOVE THIS NEIGHBORHOOD GEM!!  I'm tempted not to tout this wonderful, delicious, friendly place b/c I don't want it to get so popular I can't find rezzos or just pop in...but...IT'S SO AWESOME!!  The staff is the best and their food is just so darn good.  Their wine selections and cocktails are creative and unique.  Just go and be a bar-fly; it's the perfect place for that.  But please...don't spread the word.  HA!

name: Blue Island Oyster Bar & Seafood
description: We’re more than oysters - we’re Denver's best seafood restaurant! Our approach is to create honest food and drinks, served in a comfortable, casual environment. The restaurant’s culture is inspired by memories of growing up in coastal towns with families of oyster farmers and fishermen. Like them, we strive to bring you superb hospitality and delicious food with a commitment to the freshest seafood at reasonable prices. To ensure this commitment of quality, we’ve partnered with Chris Quartuccio of Blue Island Shellfish Farms in Long Island, NY to bring you nearly daily shipments of seasonal oysters and seafood, offering favorites such as Steamed Mussels, Lobster Rolls, Clam Chowder, Crab Cakes, and fish like halibut, Icelandic cod, and salmon, to name a few. Our food items are complemented by a well-rounded bar menu with craft cocktails, a great wine list, and a thoughtful beer selection.

topReview.highlightedText:
The food was excellent. Did not love the curry cauliflower but i’m sure many do…
The craft cocktails were great but the bar service was very slow .
Obviously, it’s an oyster place and by the looks of the orders they have some great ones. We didn’t partake at this visit.
Truly super loud in there, if you’re looking for quiet/romantic. Not your spot, but definitely a good place to gather with friends. 
The sea bass was fantastic!!!

name: Afternoon Tea at the Brown Palace
description:
**Please note that all reservations after 4pm are for Jazz and cocktails not our afternoon tea service.

Afternoon Tea is a decades-long tradition at The Brown Palace. Set amid the historic grandeur of the Atrium Lobby with its serenade of the melodic piano, guests revel in the splendor as they escape from the city's bustle. Enjoy such signature items as a pot of properly brewed English tea accompanied by scones served with Devonshire cream and preserves, savory tea sandwiches, and a delightful array of classic tea pastries.

Sip on classic cocktails, a glass of wine, or a refreshing pint in our Lobby while digging into charcuterie and other inventive dishes at Atrium Cocktails on Friday & Saturday evenings from 4:30 to 7:30 pm. Live music by The John Kite Jazz Quartet will complete an unforgettable and lively experience.

topReview.highlightedText: The whole experience was great more than what I had imagined!

name: Quality Italian- Denver
description:
Quality Italian in Denver is open for indoor dining, outdoor patio dining with seating available in our covered and outdoor cabins,

Visit us at www.qualityitaliandenver.com for more information.

topReview.highlightedText: I choice this place for a first date because of reviews and pics.  It did not disappoint.  Beautiful decor, easy to get to and I choice the valet parking at hotel because I just didn't need extra stress and worries.  To be honest I don't remember what we ordered or even eating that much (it was first date and too much jitters and excitement ).  She liked it and that was all that mattered!  I was ready to spend a small fortune on dinner, we had appetizer, main course with some sides, no drinks, and it was not much worse than a night at any of the corp. box Italian places with a couple drinks.  Wait staff was friendly helpful and very knowledgeable.  Oh and the date went fantastic!  Thanks Quality Italian.

name: Elway's Cherry Creek
description: Elway's Cherry Creek Colorado Steakhouse offers 100% USDA Prime Beef steaks, hand-cut on the premises, as well as seasonal seafood selections, all in a contemporary and inviting atmosphere. Our fresh menu selections are accompanied by an extensive and reasonably priced wine list and delivered with genuine hospitality and attentive service. With private dining options to accommodate 6 to 65, Elway's Cherry Creek is always the perfect setting for any occasion.

topReview.highlightedText: Great service, waitress was very attentive. Food was excellent.

name: Ristorante Lo Stella
description:
"Lo Stella" Ristorante is the oldest and most successful family owned restaurant operation in Portofino, Italy. It is one of the country’s most renowned historic family owned and operated restaurants for more than 167 years. Now, downtown Denver is home to this historically famed Italian restaurant, led by the 8th generation family member, Alessandro Polo.
At " Lo Stella" Ristorante you will find the original recipes from previous generations like Pesto sauce, Bolognese sauce, marinara, fish ravioli, vegetable ravioli, pappardelle, tagliatelle, pizza and a lot of Colorado meat and fish products cooked in our "ligurian" style.
Lo Stella Ristorante has also had 25 years of great success in Tokyo, Japan until 2013 when Alessandro decided to move to Denver to open this authentic Italian Restaurant.

topReview.highlightedText: Awesome place! Quaint, great service! Top notch food!

name: Buckhorn Exchange
description:
Welcome to a taste of history!

Denver’s original steakhouse, The Buckhorn Exchange is located in the city’s oldest neighborhood, just 5-minutes from downtown Denver -- with a light-rail stop right across the street. This National Historic Landmark and Western Museum has been serving the finest in Old West fare since 1893.

Prime grade beef steaks, buffalo prime rib, elk, salmon, quail, game hen, and succulent baby-back pork ribs are just some of the marvelous offerings on the Buckhorn menu. Exotic appetizers such as alligator tail and buffalo sausage are available, and no dinner is complete without the house specialty, Rocky Mountain Oysters.

For lunch we serve up a lighter fare including our renowned Grandma Fanny’s pot roast sandwich, enormous beef and buffalo burgers and more!

topReview.highlightedText: Met Trace Adkins!!!

name: Matsuhisa Denver
description:
If your desired reservation time is not available online, please call the restaurant at 303-329-6628.

Featuring Chef Nobu Matsuhisa’s signature new-style Japanese cuisine, Matsuhisa Denver anchors the ground floor of the Steel Creek luxury apartment building in Cherry Creek, Denver’s premier shopping, restaurant, and entertainment district. Our 7,800 square foot dining room is open for dinner service from 5pm nightly. Takeout available nightly from 5-9pm.

To ensure we are adhering to the health and safety guidelines, and to reopen as safely and responsibly as possible, we are requiring guests entering our premises to wear protective face masks.

-----------------

Chef Nobu Matsuhisa’s fusion cuisine draws influence from his classical training in Tokyo and his life abroad in Peru, Argentina, and around the world, showcasing signature dishes such as Yellowtail Sashimi with Jalapeño, Black Cod Miso and White fish Tiradito.

topReview.highlightedText: Good, not great.  Especially for the relatively high cost ~$200/per person.

name: The Capital Grille - Denver
description:
OUR DINING ROOM IS OPEN. ONLINE ORDERING FOR TAKEOUT IS ALSO AVAILABLE.

Enjoy nationally renowned steaks—dry aged and hand-cut on premises by our in-house butchers—the freshest of seafood, creative sides, and irresistible desserts prepared on-site every day. All accompanied by an acclaimed wine list, carefully curated and featuring over 350 labels from around the world. Experience gracious, anticipatory service in our comfortable, sophisticated dining room.

Polite Notice – For the comfort of all guests and to better deliver on our promise of a refined atmosphere, proper dress is required. Thank you for not wearing: Gym attire, sweatpants, tank tops, hats, clothing with offensive language or images, exposed undergarments.

topReview.highlightedText: Never disappoints!   John is usually our server…he was not working so we had Natalie….she was awesome!    Thks!!!

name: Bistro Vendome
description: Bistro Vendome, designed to evoke the look and feel of a long-established, family-owned bistro plucked from a Parisian street corner, features a carefully crafted menu that contains a wealth of French flavors served in a comfortable and charming environment. Brought to you by the owners of nearby Rioja, Bistro Vendome is based a foundation of classical French with a lighter and more contemporary influence. This heartwarming bistro fare pairs well with the full service bar with more than 65 selections of French wine representing all regions of France. Every detail of the food, service and atmosphere guarantees a unique and authentic French dining experience.

topReview.highlightedText: Everything was great really enjoyed it! Will be back again.

name: Washington Park Grille
description:
The Zagat Survey says, "There's much to like about this Washington Park Italian-New American: "good food", a "great patio" & "cheerful" service & ambiance."
An upscale age-diverse crowd mingles at this popular neighborhood restaurant & gathering place east of Wash Park.
A covered strip on the south and west side with heat and misters makes for convivial outdoor seating (you just might see a neighbor). A beautiful lounge is off to the side. 11 beers on tap, 15 in bottles and an excellent wine list at the elegant U-shaped bar. A roomy & elegant banquet room with its own patio and a presentation compatible 80” HDTV complete this restaurant for every occasion.
Dinners are mid-priced, with a nice selection of grilled seafood & steaks & several fancy pasta dishes. The lunch offerings include sandwiches, pizza, salads & pasta.

topReview.highlightedText: End of summer date with friends. It was perfect!  I haven’t been there for years and the food was the best I’ve  had there.

name: La Merise
description:
La Merise is located in Denver, Colorado and offers authentic French cuisine in a bistro setting. The menu offers brunch selections including crepes, omelets, classic French toast, breakfast pancakes and much more. The brunch menu at La Merise also features a selection of sandwiches and entr�es including a croquet monsieur, chicken croquettes and steak frites.

The dinner menu at La Merise offers a selection of appetizers including oysters du jour and escargots de Bourgogne. The menu also has a selection of soups and salads available as well. Entr�es include lamb chops Proven�ale, beef bourguignon, steak au poivre, pork medallions and chicken coquettes.

topReview.highlightedText: Fantastic!

name: Le Bilboquet - Denver
description:
Le Bilboquet, bringing a premier French restaurant experience to Denver and Cherry Creek North.

This bistro is modeled after the Upper East Side original — a dining room dressed in white linens, with velvet seats, dark wood, and brass finishes. The Denver menu will include traditional and modern French fare, as well as the house special: Cajun Chicken.

Le Bilboquet is a 6,000-square-foot location at 3rd and Saint Paul has a premier 70 seat patio, a beautiful lounge, a 32 seat private dining room and a main dining room that can seat up to 110 guests.

topReview.highlightedText: Fish selections are excellent.  So is the risotto appetizer and creme brulee.  Extensive collection of excellent wines

name: Happy Camper
description:
A chic, outdoorsy pizza haven located in LoHI. Happy Camper boasts a décor that includes disco balls, neon lights, warm wooden accents, tire swings and a giant outdoor patio. We invite you to indulge in our creative cocktails and extensive beer selection; paired with specialty pizzas and mouth-watering appetizers. Come for the food.  Stay for the vibes.
*Unfortunately, at this time we are unable to accept pets on our patio. We look forward to meeting your furry friends soon!

topReview.highlightedText: We went for our son’s birthday and had a part of eight. The server was super accommodating and nice. Food was great and we had a fantastic time.

name: Steuben's
description: Steuben’s is named after a restaurant in Boston that my Great Uncles, Max and Joe, opened in 1945. Steuben's became a famous Boston restaurant, nightclub, and hotspot from the 1940’s to the 1960’s on Boylston Street. The Vienna Room, The Cave, and The Blue Room were all part of the Steuben's space and hosted Big Band, Jazz, and Swing groups with The Rat Pack, proms and sweet sixteens, and more. In its prime, Steuben’s was the center of the Boston dining and nightlife scene.

topReview.highlightedText: Customer service was stellar! Gyro was flavorful & filling. Gravy fries were delish. Chicken & waffles…eh. There’s an unusual spice in the chicken batter that didn’t mix with the other flavors going on.

name: Uchi Denver
description:
UPDATE 1.10.21
We are currently open for limited indoor dining, outdoor dining, and take-out. All of our outdoor dining options are currently tented. Although our tent is partially enclosed and heated, we recommend planning and dressing for the cold. We are currently able to take a very limited number of walk-ins. If you choose to walk in, please plan to sit outside. As seating is limited, we plan for two hours per reservation, but please let us know if more time is desired. Should you be running late please let us know, we will hold your reservation time for 15 minutes.

We are diligently following new service operations that go above and beyond government requirements. To stay safe during this time, we are requiring face coverings for all who enter the restaurant. For further information about our service operations, menus, or to place a to-go order, please visit our website at www.uchidenver.com.

Thank you for your patience and understanding!

topReview.highlightedText: Great bartender and great food

name: SOL Mexican Cocina - Denver
description: The Best of Baja in the heart of Cherry Creek, SOL Cocina offers an upscale, yet inviting dining experience. Executive Chef Deborah Schneider, a 2009 James Beard Foundation Book Award Nominee, has created a menu of contemporary and gourmet interpretations of Baja street cuisine, inlcuding antojitos, street tacos, cocktels de mariscos and main dishes made with fresh seafood, wood grilled meats, local produce and salsas that are all made fresh daily.

topReview.highlightedText: Great margaritas and Mexican food!

name: 801 Chophouse - Denver
description:
A classic American chophouse interior with signature leather booths, cherry wood furnishings, wooden floors, granite counter tops and high ceilings, accented with dramatic lighting. 801 Chophouse in Cherry Creek offers USDA Prime Beef, fresh seafood offerings, Duroc pork chops, and seasonal vegetables.

Our Executive Chef Kyle Viera creates a Fresh Sheet that highlights our unique weekly offerings. Seasonal fresh soups and salads, oysters on the half-shell, five species of fresh fish, live Maine lobsters and king crab legs. Make sure to save room for our made from scratch Grand Marnier Soufflé!

Serving Aged USDA Grade Prime Beef ONLY, and customizing menus for all private dining groups, our walls reconfigure for the perfect amount of space, our tables change for seating and conversation, and our custom menus range from cocktails and hors d"oeuvres to full course dining.

topReview.highlightedText: Great steakhouse with all the classics you would expect. Very nice place

name: Toro Latin Kitchen + Lounge
description: In the tradition of Central and South American convivial dining culture, Toro Denver features a ceviche bar, small plates, steaks and other family-style entrees, plus, hand-muddled cocktails and local beer and wine. Relaxed and inviting, Toro invites you to share in authentic Latin ingredients, international flavors, and artful dishes at our Cherry Creek Denver restaurant.

topReview.highlightedText: New Grand Baby-all Grand Parent celebrating

name: Corinne Restaurant
description: Corinne is downtown Denver’s neighborhood dining and cocktail spot serving classic, honest American comfort food with an emphasis on locally-sourced ingredients.

topReview.highlightedText: Superior device. Great biscuits, omelets, coffee.

name: STK – Denver
description: STK Denver artfully blends the modern steakhouse and a chic lounge into one, offering a dynamic fine dining experience with the superior quality of a traditional steakhouse. As one of the newest additions to the LoDo neighborhood of Denver, STK Denver distinguishes itself with a vibrant mix of stylish dining and lounge spaces, paired with a signature menu and world-class service.

topReview.highlightedText: Always an excellent experience!

name: Tupelo Honey - Denver
description:
Tupelo Honey is a revival of Southern food and traditions rooted in the Carolina Mountains we call home. Steps from historic Denver Union Station, we craft brunches, lunches and suppers that bring family and friends around the table and allow for conversations and cocktails to linger longer than usual. Always scratch-made, always responsibly-soured, and always Southern.

Reservations are strongly recommended, and we will accommodate walk-ins where possible.

topReview.highlightedText: Good food at a good price.   Fried chicken with Mac and Cheese was awesome!

name: Blackbird - Denver
description:
Blackbird - Denver is a neighborhood restaurant located at South Downing Street and Alameda Avenue in the Washington Park neighborhood of Denver. We are open 7 days a week for lunch and dinner with Brunch on the weekends form 10-3 featuring bottomless mimosas and one of Denver's top 10 Bloody Marys according to Westword readers.
Our menus feature fresh small plates, hand tossed pizzas, a wide variety of burgers, pasta and seafood as well as the area's freshest oysters and mussels.
The beverage offerings include a curated cocktail, wine and deep craft beer list to go with our always popular wine list. The bar area viewing options include International soccer leagues (Premier League, Champions League) as well as college and pro-football. Walk-ins are always welcome. Please call or stop in if reservations are unavailable. Come join us today.

topReview.highlightedText: The Seasonal Oysters were as fantastic as the service was

name: The Post Brewing Co - Rosedale
description:
The Post Chicken & Beer is open and ready to welcome you for dine-in, outdoor dining, curbside pick-up and our very own delivery service 7 days a week!

At The Post Chicken & Beer our motto is Hot Chicken Loves Cold Beer. Our brewers brew beers that are gosh darn delicious, memorable, and something you will want to put in your mouth repeatedly. Featured by Guy Fieri on Food Network's Diners Drive-Ins &; Dives, our bird is better than the rest--humanely raised, all natural chickens are brined for hours, dipped in buttermilk, seasoned with GLUTEN-FREE flour, and then fried to crispy golden perfection.

For curbside pick-up and delivery, order WeDeliver online anytime after 4pm until we close. It is easy-peasy!
Order Online: postchickenandbeer.com/rosedale/

topReview.highlightedText: For the price we felt the amount of chicken on the chicken and waffles was really small. This was disappointing as the last time dining here there we two pieces of chicken while yesterday there was only one.

name: Etc Eatery
description:
Located in the heart of the Platt Park neighborhood, Etc Eatery is your newest neighborhood spot! The menu features an eclectic and inclusive blend of fan-favorite comfort food from around the globe (and cocktails to pair). Perfect for #patioseason, the space boasts a massive outdoor dining area and a rooftop with views of Historic South Pearl Street. We're pretty positive that the restaurant's vibrant and unique interior will make you smile.

Come, eat, drink, enjoy, etc. etc. etc.

topReview.highlightedText: We tried etc eatery because it’s in our dining out passbook and while all of the food was good, all of the portions were so small! My husband and I ordered the beef satay appetizer, the tacos and the stuffed peppers as our entrees, and the peach pie as dessert and still left feeling hungry!

name: narrative.
description: Winner of Cherry Creek Food and Wine’s 2018 People’s Choice award and 2019's Best in Show! Delivering a new topic of conversation and a place to hold that exchange. Narrative offers storied food and drink under the direction of award-winning Executive Chef Paul Nagan. An approachable, modern American menu features global flavors, shareable plates, and a daily robust happy hour! An upscale cocktail menu and wine library with over 700 bottles and 90 labels await your entrée selection. A welcome ambiance is highlighted by floor to ceiling windows which offer wonderful natural light and an open-air feeling. Complimentary valet is included with your meal.

topReview.highlightedText: The food and service at Narrative were excellent.  We had an attentive but not overbearing waiter. We took his advice on a starter and main dish and both were excellent. The kitchen did a very nice job of splitting the entree for my husband and I to share.

name: Hapa Sushi Grill & Sake Bar - Cherry Creek
description: The name Hapa is derived from the Hawaiian term that describes a harmonious blend of Asian and American cultures. Like our name, our food reflects this dynamic combination. The menu is based on traditional Japanese cooking fundamentals which are then amplified, muted, or mixed with influences from many different styles of cooking until they are something completely new: they're Hapa. We have stretched the boundaries of creativity to develop dishes that defy all the rules while holding true to our roots. We hope you will find our menu innovative, uninhibited, and distinctly fun! Incomplete parties will not be sat until complete.

topReview.highlightedText: Yummy and great service as usual! Love Hapa!

name: Briar Common Brewery
description: An elevated brewery experience you will not find anywhere else! Ten of our own beers on tap along with an array of perfectly prepared dishes to satisfy the masses!

topReview.highlightedText: Great cocktails. Not overly sweet and not watered down so you can actually taste the booze. Highly recommend the burgers and the fried chicken sandwich.

name: EDGE Restaurant & Bar
description:
+Located inside Four Seasons Hotel Denver, EDGE Restaurant & Bar is a progressive American Steakhouse with global influences utilizing superior quality meats, locally sourced Colorado game, fresh seafood, vegetarian and vegan fare, and produce from nearby farms to cultivate dishes full of seasonal flavors. EDGE offers all day dining and weekend brunch throughout the contemporary restaurant, as well as three glass-enclosed private dining rooms including the Butcher's Room, which offers an exclusive look into the kitchen. The adjacent EDGE Bar is a dynamic see-and-be-seen lounge featuring expertly handcrafted cocktails, an award-winning wine list, a selection of local craft beers, and a menu of approachable fare.

Please see updated hours of operations for Edge and Edge bar.

topReview.highlightedText: We came to Edge to celebrate our 10th wedding anniversary and it was the perfect venue. Hip, fancy, approachable, and incredible food, this was a great location. My husband had the bone marrow appetizer which he swooned over after every bite. He followed that up with the scallops (which he enjoyed and the couple next to us had steaks during which point my husband said he wished he would have gotten one of those!). His dessert was the blackberry lemon sorbet. I tried it and it was absolutely fantastic. Creamy, delicious, and perfectly flavored. I started with the wedge salad (which could have easily been my meal), and moved onto the Whole striped bass. It was a bit of a monster to tackle but once I broke through the crispy, battered skin, the fish inside was warm, soft, and perfectly cooked. I finished with the sticky toffee pudding which was a great end to my meal. The whiskey wasn't overpowering and the ice cream was a nice addition to the pudding. We had a marvelous time and hope to return again soon!

name: ChoLon Modern Asian - Downtown
description: ChoLon, which translates to "big market,” is named after the largest Chinese-influenced market in Saigon, Vietnam. At ChoLon, Chef Lon Symensma brings to life his extensive culinary travels throughout Southeast Asia. ChoLon's menu features inspired interpretations of traditional dishes found across the region, with presentations ideal for sharing. From dim sum or "small bites" to large family style plates, ChoLon offers authentic flavors for the modern palate. The bar and lounge serves handcrafted, artisanal cocktails developed to complement Symensma’s cuisine. The venue is also ideal for business meetings, presentations, large parties and events. ChoLon’s professional staff will deliver top quality service and a memorable experience.

topReview.highlightedText: Great food! Good service!

name: El Five
description:
Hello!

We are open!

El Five and the Edible Beats Family (Root Down, Linger, Ophelias, Vital Root and El Five) are very grateful to welcome you back into our restaurant.

Our menu continues to feature our take on traditional Spanish and Mediterranean tapas with influences from North Africa and the Middle East.

Enjoy this underrepresented cuisine while overlooking spectacular unobstructed city views of the downtown Denver skyline and Rockies foothills.

We are open for inside dining and to-go. We are also offering limited enclosed and heated outdoor seating, on a first come, first serve basis. We sincerely apologize, enclosed outdoor seating is not available to be reserved ahead of time.

Please be aware that we continue to follow all state and city guidance regarding capacity and health practices, including temperature checks and the wearing of masks while moving around our space or engaging with staff.

We look

topReview.highlightedText: Amazing food, amazing views. Try to go before sunset to see the changing skyline of the city and don't miss the opposite side of the restaurant with gorgeous Mountain views as well. Carne paella is not to be missed as well as the pork loin tapa

name: Max Gill and Grill
description:
We are currently open for dine-in, patio seating, delivery, and take out.
Please visit our website for our updated menus and all additional information.
www.maxgillandgrill.com
Thank you so much for the continued support.
The Max Gill and Grill Family




Specializing in the freshest seafood and raw bar along with the finest spit roasted and grilled cuisine, Max Gill and Grill serves really great liquids amid praiseworthy food. Check out our website at www.MaxGillandGrill.com for all updates.
(Patio seating is on a first come/first serve basis, thank you!)

topReview.highlightedText: We love Max’s Gill am Grill - food is great, service is excellent. Fun atmosphere!

name: Urban Farmer
description:
Urban Farmer Denver’s seasonally-driven menu highlights nose-to-tail cuts of naturally raised meat, carefully curated by our culinary team. The restaurant focuses on in-house whole animal butchering and ways to use the entire animal throughout the menu.

The steakhouse is not entirely focused on meats alone, and also offers soul nurturing sides, soups, and salads inspired by each season’s abundance. Post-supper sweets are made in-house and include a variety of baked goods and selection of rotating ice creams and sorbets.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent atmosphere, food, and service.  It's expensive.  But for the overall experience, not outrageously so.

name: Hapa Sushi Grill and Sake Bar Lodo
description: The name Hapa is derived from the Hawaiian term that describes a harmonious blend of Asian and American cultures. Like our name, our food reflects this dynamic combination. The menu is based on traditional Japanese cooking fundamentals which are then amplified, muted, or mixed with influences from many different styles of cooking until they are something completely new: they’re Hapa. We have stretched the boundaries of creativity to develop dishes that defy all the rules while holding true to our roots. We hope you will find our menu innovative, uninhibited, and distinctly fun! Incomplete parties will not be sat until complete.

topReview.highlightedText: Great service, ambiance, and food

name: Root Down
description:
Hello!

Root Down and the Edible Beats Family (Root Down, Linger, Ophelias, Vital Root and El Five) are very grateful to welcome you back into our restaurant.

Our menu continues to feature eclectic, globally-influenced seasonal cuisine, with a focus on organic, natural and locally-sourced ingredients.

Our interior dining space has the classic vibe of a neighborhood restaurant, while our large main patio offers picturesque views of the near neighborhood and downtown skyline.

We are open for inside dining and to-go, and patios are open at full capacity.

We look forward to seeing you again, we MISSED you!

topReview.highlightedText: Moving to Denver

name: Jovanina's Broken Italian
description:
Jovanina's is now OPEN and following state and local guidelines for safe and healthy food service! We can't wait to see you! If reservations are not available online it is because we have a max capacity during this time.

Jovanina’s offers a fresh, modern take on Italian cuisine sourcing the best local and regional ingredients by the season. Handmade pastas and our rustic, wood-fired ovens are the heart of our menu. We provide vibrant, vegetable-forward dishes, seafood, steaks, and chops, presented in a spirited, inviting setting. We pride ourselves on hospitality and consider ourselves amongst the best of Denver when it comes to taking care of our guests. Our bar is focused toward classic crafted cocktails, barrel-aged spirits, and seasonal liqueurs. We offer a local beer selection and an extensive wine list housed in our wine cellar Sotto Voce.

topReview.highlightedText:
I took my parents for dinner last night and it was simply fantastic. The service is top notch and my mom couldn't stop raving about her bucatini.

This is our 2nd visit back and it will not be the last!

name: Venice Ristorante & Wine Bar
description: Venice Ristorante & Wine Bar in Downtown Denver provides first class Italian cuisine! Facilitating all of your event needs, from private receptions, corporate events, anniversaries and birthdays. Our amazing wine list showcases 800 Italian wines and 300 worldwide wines.

topReview.highlightedText: This was a great find. My first time there. I will definitely go back. Great service, excellent food, great selection of wines. The manager came by several times to say hello and check on things. Great location. We had asked to sit outside. They were thoroughly cooperative and well set up for that.  Great in every way.

name: Earls Kitchen + Bar - Downtown Denver
description: If you have lofty expectations for an Earls in the mile-high city, Earls Glenarm Denver Restaurant will not disappoint. Let us direct your attention to the atmosphere: warm, welcoming but with a bit of an edge. There's the fact we seem to be getting a bit of a rep for our parties, where we've hosted up to 350 people at one time. For a slightly more intimate feel, try our private wine room with unique wine displays. Then there are the two large patios that look out onto the 16th Street pedestrian mall, one upstairs and one at ground level for two distinctly perfect views of summer. Let's not forget the contemporary, fresh Earls menu. The 24 big-screen plasma TVs. The smiles that greet your arrival. The feeling of knowing you made the right choice for a good night out with your family and friends. C'mon, tell us you're not just a little bit tempted? There's so much more the best thing to do is join us and discover it for yourself. We are located just off the corner of 16th St & Glenarm.

topReview.highlightedText: We stopped in before a concert and we were surprised at how good everything was.  The dry rubbed ribs were outstanding.  A couple of us ordered the Thai Chicken Curry.  Before  it arrived we were thinking we should have shared an entree, but it was so good we all devoured our whole meal.

name: Linger
description:
Hello!

Linger and the Edible Beats Family (Root Down, Linger, Ophelias, Vital Root and El Five) are very grateful to welcome you back into our restaurant.

Our menu continues to feature diverse international offerings, that combine farm-to-street sensibility with our spin on traditional ethnic eats.

Overlook the energy of the lower highlands neighborhood from our large scenic rooftop, or enjoy our unique, multi-level space from the dining room or bar.

Our full dining space is open, including our rooftop patio. We sincerely apologize, our outdoor seating is not available to be reserved ahead of time.

We look forward to seeing you soon, thank you!

topReview.highlightedText: Wonderful food and great service.  We loved the sharable plates and got to try quite a few different menu items, definitely not bad price wise either, less than we both expected. Definitely recommend the espresso martini!

name: Ace Eat Serve
description:
Ace features three unique spaces, housed in the old Storz Garage space at the corner of 17th & Pennsylvania. Like its sister restaurants, Steuben’s, great attention was given to the design of Ace. Repurposed and recycled materials are used throughout the space to create an industrial design and comfortable setting that compliments the history of the building. Ace was a recipient of the 2012 Mayor’s Design Award.

Ace serves Asian inspired dishes conducive to sharing, drinking and hanging out. Voted as Denver’s Best Bartender by 5280 magazine, featuring house made sodas, fresh juices, Asian beers and a craft cocktail menu.

Ace is a place to eat, drink, play, and hang in another unique and creative destination in Uptown, Denver, Colorado brought to you by Secret Sauce F&B group.

topReview.highlightedText: the only negative- music was too loud- made it difficult to hold a conversation with the large group we had there...otherwise- amazing!

name: Tamayo Restaurant
description: Located in Historic Larimer Square, Tamayo is a chic spot with a vast rooftop deck with sweeping views of the mountains. The innovative Latin menu is carefully crafted by world-renowned Chef Richard Sandoval who is often hailed as the “Father of Modern Mexican Cuisine.” Savory & authentic, the upscale Mexican cuisine at Tamayo will make any meal an unforgettable experience. With a collection of over 100 tequilas and agave-based spirits, Tamayo is also a hotspot for margaritas & hand-crafted cocktails.

topReview.highlightedText: The margaritas were some of the best I have had.  Service was awesome and the food was absolutely delicious!  I will be back and I strongly recommend this restaurant!

name: Panzano
description: Award-winning Panzano offer the best in contemporary Northern Italian cuisine featuring local, organic, sustainable ingredients with uncompromising service and an award-winning wine list in a stylized urban setting inspired by the Italian streetscapes and terracotta tile roofs of Renaissance Florence.

topReview.highlightedText: Went there for my birthday while on vacation and heard happy birthday from multiple workers. Food was excellent and unique in a very good way.

name: ELWAY'S Downtown
description:
ELWAY'S Downtown offers 100% USDA Prime steaks, hand-cut on the premises, an award-winning wine selection and a comfortable, memorable and attentive dining experience. Enjoy the NFL Sunday ticket in our bar and lounge. We offer multiple private dining options to accommodate 6 to 100 people, ELWAY'S Downtown is the perfect setting for any occasion.

We are currently closed to in-person dinning. Take out and third party delivery are available by calling the restaurant or through Grub Hub and Door Dash.

We look forward to welcoming you back soon.

topReview.highlightedText: Great food and atmosphere! Had a great time and the service was amazing. Highly recommend 👌

name: Ultreia
description:
We are a Spanish and Portuguese restaurant with a lively atmosphere, serving plates from the Iberian
Peninsula that are meant to be shared. Gin tonics and sherry adorn the cocktail menu along with Basque ciders.

topReview.highlightedText:
Most importantly, the food was excellent. Both the croquettes and the bacon wrapped dates were a must have. The service was adequate, although I suspect our server was new to industry.

The only letdown (and the reason this is not a 5* review) were the drinks. The restaurant hints at specializing in gin and tonics and neither of the G and Ts I ordered were worth it. Whoever is running the bar must believe in spirit forward cocktails, to the exclusion of any of the advertised supporting flavors, and in one case the tonic! Similarly, the sangria as nothing more than a glass of low quality red wine on ice… no fruit flavors period. My recommendation, enjoy the food, order a decent glass of wine and hope they bring the bar program into the 21st century at some point in the future.

name: Humboldt Kitchen + Bar
description:
Humboldt Kitchen & Bar is all about bringing our community together for enticing craft cocktails, a bite to eat and authentic hospitality. With a chef-driven menu featuring both small plates and elevated entreés, seasonal craft cocktails, unique local beers and a carefully curated wine list, Humboldt Kitchen + Bar is the ideal place for celebrating, commiserating or sharing some well-deserved time with friends. Executive Chef Brett Bowen brings traditional dishes with bold flavors, for a menu that is both adventurous and familiar.

Everything from our cocktails and food to our atmosphere and service are designed for lively conversation and friendly informality. Settle in, relax and enjoy our modern neighborhood kitchen and bar.

topReview.highlightedText: Fantastic calamari!  Went for Sunday brunch & everything was great.

name: Of A Kind
description: The coasts of California and the Mediterranean inspire the clean, fresh flavors at Of a Kind. You may opt for our unique made-to-order pita program paired with clean vegetable salads, select from a menu of hummus options, savor a hearth-fired leg of lamb, or dig into a robust yet delicate pasta. Pair it with an herbaceous rendition of a classic cocktail, a curated wine or local beer.

topReview.highlightedText: Food was absolutely delicious.  Jonathan and Kalen were FABULOUS!  10/10 service

name: Kona Grill - Denver
description: Welcome to Kona Grill Denver at Cherry Creek Shopping Center, with convenient valet parking right at our main entrance. Enjoy your local paradise after work, a day of shopping, or before catching your next movie. Fresh, wild caught fish is flown in daily to craft award-winning sushi, while contemporary American entrees are prepared from scratch in-house. Happy hour on the beautiful, shaded patio is a must. And don’t leave until you’ve tried one of the handcrafted cocktails, ice cold draft beer, or a glass of wine selected from the extensive drink menu. The restaurant’s diverse menu and contemporary ambience provide the perfect venue for special occasions like bridal showers, baby showers, birthday celebrations, business meetings, date night, or just any occasion really.

topReview.highlightedText: The sea bass was the best entree I’ve had in a long time….loved the stir fry rice as well….will definitely go back for more of the same.

name: Blue Agave Grill - Denver
description:
Blue Agave Grill is a local, independent, and Colorado grown restaurant! We are full service dishing up contemporary southwestern cuisine with a full bar and over 120 tequilas. We feature a from-scratch kitchen with many gluten free options as well as a large selection of margaritas, house infused tequilas, and homemade sangria. From made-to-order guacamole to our vibrant atmosphere, come on down and try a flight of our favorite margs and tequilas.

Happy Hour
Monday, Wednesday - Friday 3:00pm to 6:00pm / All-day Tuesday
-$5 Margaritas
-$4 Drafts
-$3 Bottled Beer & Wells
-$2 off all Glasses of Wine

Brunch Menu available Saturdays and Sundays from 11:00am to 2:00pm, full menu available all day!
Featuring house-infused bloody mary’s and Downtown Denver's most affordable BOTTOMLESS mimosas!

topReview.highlightedText: Steak Rojo was delicious

name: Urban Putt Denver
description:
**Reservations are for dining only. The mini-golf is first come, first serve. Online Reservations can be made for up to 6 people. For larger reservations please contact the restaurant directly. Multiple small reservations may not be seated together.**

Welcome! Thank you for choosing Urban Putt. We are Denver's finest indoor mini-golf, restaurant, and bar. Our dining room serves up classic American fare with a twist. Enjoy a meal before or after you experience our unique, imaginative mini-golf with a craft cocktail.

topReview.highlightedText: Fun venue and great social setting to be with friends, whether a couple or a small group. The appetizers were really good and they have great beer options to choose from too. I would definitely go again.

name: D Bar Denver
description:
The D in D Bar stands for Drinks, Dining, and Dessert.

Drinks: We have an excellent wine, beer and D Bar concoctions menu that suits all price ranges and occasions. We even have a wine made just for us called Mr. Cupcake by award winning wine maker, Charles Smith!! Time for some after work fun? Join us for Nibbles and Sips Happy Hour!

Dining: D Bar isn’t based on one particular type of dining. As chefs, we pull from what we personally enjoy eating. Thus, our menu is based on our childhood favorites, inspiration from travels, and simply just things we like to eat!

Dessert: Our passion and background is pastry! We have designed D Bar with a unique dessert bar! It's the best seating in the house as you watch pastry chefs create beautiful plated desserts right before your eyes!

topReview.highlightedText: Great food and service!

name: Ruth's Chris Steak House - Denver
description:
Now Open: We look forward to serving you soon.

Ruth's Chris Steak House in Denver, CO serves the finest USDA Prime beef available, broiled at 1,800° and served on 500° plates, so your steak stays hot, juicy and delicious from first bite to last. Enjoy our New Orleans-inspired appetizers, USDA Prime steaks, fresh seafood, signature side dishes and homemade desserts. All this while you enjoy our warm, inviting atmosphere and Ruth’s Chris’ genuine hospitality. So whether you’re a regular or have just been wondering what all the buzz is about, Ruth's Chris is the perfect excuse to enjoy the perfect night out. Dinner is served nightly, reservations are suggested and private dining and offsite catering may be arranged.

topReview.highlightedText: Had dinner by myself at the bar while in town. Was treated very well. Service was outstanding…George took excellent care of me.

name: Del Frisco's Grille - Cherry Creek
description:
Del Frisco’s Grille is a stylish, modern restaurant with a vibrant ambiance where life is celebrated around the table. Boasting premium American classics infused with fresh, seasonal ingredients, the Grille’s thoughtful menu features Del Frisco’s Prime, hand-cut steaks and craveable, shareable dishes such as the signature Cheesesteak Eggrolls. With an award-winning yet accessible wine list and hand-crafted cocktails, Del Frisco’s Grille takes guests through a social culinary journey with each experience, no matter the occasion.

Our patio provides al fresco dining at one of the best restaurants in Cherry Creek.
*Reservations are accepted for indoor dining only. Patio seating is available on a first-come, first-served basis.

topReview.highlightedText: My wife and I both had the half shaved beef sandwich and ceasar salad.  Both of us thought that they were excellent, especially the dressing on the salad.  We will definitely have them again.  Our wait person was great so we had an excellent experience.

name: Fogo de Chao – Denver
description: Fogo de Chao is the leading Brazilian steakhouse specializing in fire-roasting high-quality meats since 1979 utilizing the centuries-old Southern Brazilian cooking technique of churrasco. Please join us in our dining room and patio, or bring the Fogo Experience to you with Fogo To-Go, Butcher Shop or Catering for Pick-Up or Contactless Delivery.  Visit www.fogo.com to make a reservation or place an order.

topReview.highlightedText: Always a great experience here.

name: Stoic & Genuine
description: Welcome to Stoic & Genuine! Please contact the restaurant directly for dining availability.  Denver’s iconic multi-coastal seafood, oyster house and granita bar committed to impeccably fresh, sustainable, and creative seafood preparations set in the grand ambiance of Denver's newly renovated historic Union Station. An exhibition kitchen opens up to a fresh raw bar with ever-changing selections of shellfish. The beverage program is centered on a creative granita bar, craft and classic cocktails and a broad grower champagne selection by the bottle and glass. No ocean. No worries.

topReview.highlightedText: One of my favorites in town.  Chef Jen is amazing with her presentation of food and bringing tastes that you will find no where else.  Our server was over the top knowledgeable and was having some fun recommending drinks to us

name: Corridor 44
description: Corridor 44 is Denver's only Champagne bar. Our Champagne list consists of over 115 bottles of Champagne,18 Champagne cocktails & Champagne martinis. We also offer an extensive wine list & a full bar. Our dinner menu offers many small plates, appetizers and also larger dinner entrees.

topReview.highlightedText: Wonderful evening dining outside. Great drinks and food.

name: Sushi Sasa
description: Sushi Sasa is designed to offer Denver the opportunity to enjoy Traditional and "New Style" Japanese cuisine harmoniously beneath one roof. The seasonal, healthy, beautiful and affordable tasting menu compliments the fully functioning sushi bar bridging the gap between East coast innovation and West coast charm. Bilingual chefs man the sushi bar at the rear of the zen-like space and offer up exotic fish and produce from around the world with the heart of the cuisine remaining Japanese. With a wonderful sake and wine list and a cozy downstairs lounge, Sushi Sasa is a perfect place for a business lunch or a nice dinner with friends.

topReview.highlightedText: Wonderful lunch spot! Excellent menu! My favorite sushi spot in Denver because they serve lunch and take reservations.

name: Aquarium Restaurant - Downtown Denver
description: Enjoy our one-of-a-kind Aquarium Restaurant and make a splash with deliciously fresh seafood, steak, chicken and decadent desserts all served in an unbelievable underwater setting. Guests are seated around an elaborate 50,000 gallon aquarium with over 100 species of colorful fish and marine life – you may see a mermaid or two! Aquarium Restaurant offers guests an exciting and unique dining experience in an extraordinary setting.

topReview.highlightedText: Amazing customer service! Amazing time! The kindness of the waitstaff was incredible and we will be back.

name: 100% de Agave
description: Like Tequila distilling, 100% de Agave has taken years to perfect our menu, decor, and location. Downtown Denver has witnessed a menu or experience like what we have waited patiently to provide. Come experience our selection of over 100 premium tequilas, the tastes of old Jalisco, Mexico and the hospitality of our Mexican culture. FREE PARKING AT THE BEAUVALLON.

topReview.highlightedText: No complaints with the service or food. Everyone enjoyed their meal.

name: Brightmarten
description:
Brightmarten is a neighborhood restaurant serving elevated comfort food and drink in a confident, cozy habitat in the heart of the Bonnie Brae neighborhood.

The Brightmarten menu is an imaginative take on New American fare, following the seasons, and sourcing from local distilleries, breweries, growers, and producers.

topReview.highlightedText: Great meal! Great service!!

name: Bao Brewhouse
description:
IMPORTANT NOTES: All "Regular Table" reservations are for the Tea Room. If you want to sit in the Tap Room please book "Counter" or "High Top" section.

Bao Brewhouse is a multi-concept restaurant, the first floor is known as the tap room, in which you will find service via QRL codes or counter service, Chinese street food inspired fare and a local rotating draft list. The second floor is known as our Tea Room, there you will find a more traditional dining experience with a twist. The Tea Room menu and ambiance lend to more curated and intimate affair, with a vast tea selection ranging from herbal to puer, a thoughtfully selected wine list with a focus on natural wine and a tea-centric cocktail program to satisfy even the most adventurous of palates. The Tea room is open from Wednesday through Saturday with a live DJ every night giving the room a not-so-stuffy feeling (we call it high energy fine dining)

topReview.highlightedText: We had such a great time at Bao and can't wait to go back for more. We started with some apps and drinks downstairs and then moved upstairs for dinner and to watch the DJ.  We had so much fun.  We also talked to a manager and they said they are launching a new menu.  Everything was so good we can't wait to hear what they have in store for their new menu.  We will be back very soon.

name: Thirsty Lion Gastropub – Denver, CO
description: Our mission is to evolve the gastropub business by combining the traditional values of European and American pubs, to create a place where friends and family can celebrate life and enjoy handcrafted food, beers and cocktails.

topReview.highlightedText: The food was absolutely delicious (we had the calamari, California roll, and bacon & onion mac and cheese)! There was a mistake with our order, but the waitress was quick to assist/correct it and the manager made sure that the new plate was correct. The Raspberry Drop adult drink was soooo good! I can’t recommend this place enough! :)

name: Fontana Sushi - 534 E. Alameda Location
description: Come join us for sushi and Japanese cuisine. Our Master Sushi Chef, Danny Niu, studied and worked in Tokyo for seven years and brings both classic training and contemporary creativity to his food. Enjoy dining in a casual, welcoming atmosphere and remember to ask about the Chef's weekly specials. There are always a few surprises!  Please do not combine coupon offers.

topReview.highlightedText: Love this place!

name: Citizen Rail
description:
During the Covid 19 Pandemic Citizen Rail offers both indoor dining and dining in our 40' heated tent.
Citizen Rail features regional American classics and contemporary riffs. The concept of grilling over a wood-fire resonates deep within the American culture, and our guests have a firsthand view of the show. An impressive wood-fired grill that incorporates the use of native hard and fruitwoods is the anchor of the restaurant space, kitchen, and menu. At its core, Citizen Rail is a restaurant that connects with the soul and fulfills Denver’s desire for restaurants & bars that are genuine, authentic and reflect the true passion of the artisans behind the stoves.

topReview.highlightedText: Relaxing atmosphere and delicious food.

name: The Saucy Noodle
description: For over four decades the Saucy Noodle Restaurante has been a Denver landmark at the same location at 727 South University Boulevard. The little spot, known to locals throughout the Washington Park, Cherry Creek and Bonnie Brae districts was originally known as Jim Sano's when it was purchased by the Badis family in 1964. Sam Badis, a former Big Band Leader and Denver entrepreneur, held court with a gregarious smile and warm welcome and served up what is arguably the best pizza and pasta in town. Traveling the country in the '60's and 70's Sam would frequently buy unique antiques in small towns and haul them back to the Saucy Noodle to adorn the restaurant's, now famous, red velvet walls.

topReview.highlightedText: Great service, kind staff, and amazing food. My kids love it, too!

name: The Pig & The Sprout
description:
Located in Denver’s thriving Union Station neighborhood, our menu embodies the dual nature of its name. Featuring both hearty and light items, it provides thoughtful, creative seasonal fare for vegans and meat-eaters alike. Even the bar program gives a nod to this split focus – our quirky, sexy cocktails are paired to both palates. We’re proud to source ingredients locally and make items in-house whenever possible.

We designed the space to make guests feel like they’re at a casual get-together hosted by their most stylish friend. Climbing vines, antique books, garage doors that overlook two patios, sleek couches for lounging and community tables for making new friends come together to welcome guests, whether they’re wearing flip flops or a suit (or both).

Please visit our website www.pigandsprout.com for a link to our online gift card store for all the food lovers on your list.

topReview.highlightedText: We were visiting Denver from out of town. The pig &the sprout was the BEST meal we had-by far!  We only wished we had eaten there on the first day- we would have gone back everyday. Lots of delicious sounding items on the menu.

name: GRIND Kitchen + Watering Hole
description: The Cherry Creek garden-level spot has been transformed into a cozy, low-slung bar and dining room decorated with vintage photos and prints, rustic light fixtures made from Mason jars and bright pickled vegetables in quart-sized containers. Although the space is below street level, windows on the south and west walls let in a surprising amount of sunlight, giving a warm glow to reclaimed barnwood and weathered tin siding. The space also includes patio tables to enjoy outside dining.

topReview.highlightedText: Fried chicken sandwich was out of this world.   Craft beer list may be the best in town, and that’s saying something. Brandon is a terrific bartender.

name: The Corner Office Restaurant and Martini Bar Denver
description:
Loosen your tie, kick off your heels and forget all your
deadlines.
The Corner Office is the flirty rendezvous where edgy global
dishes meet chic creative cocktails in the heart of downtown
Denver. Designed with a modern mid-century eye, The
Corner Office features a sexy bar + lounge, bustling dining
rooms, communal table, lively outdoor patio and private
event rooms each infused with intrigue and style. Our friendly
and fun staff is vibrant, personable, and always accessible.
Progressive comfort food mixed with international flavors
give traditional favorites a fresh twist.

topReview.highlightedText:
Amazing corned beef and potatoes. I loved the crispy bits. Eggs were cooked spot on!

Coffee was a little lukewarm and meh.

Denver omelet was delicious!

Excellent for a “hotel” restaurant.

name: Manzo Lobster and Oyster Bar
description:
Manzo Lobster and Oyster Bar is a modern American Seafood Restaurant & Oyster Bar bringing the freshest, most sustainable seafood to the Mile High City. We offer a wide range of Ultra-Fresh, Sustainable Seafood & Lobster flown in Daily.

We do have a covered patio for seating rain or shine!

topReview.highlightedText: Had the branzino - it was amazing. The old fashioneds were great, as well. Servers were worried about being understaffed but service was delivered with a smile and not noticeable to us.

name: Que Bueno Suerte
description:
Que Bueno Suerte is a Mexican restaurant serving the traditional flavors in a distinctive colorful manner. The place has an energetic vibe about it and the hip yet comfortable interior with cozy seating arrangements make this restaurant a wonderful option to enjoy meals with friends and family. The casual dining spot, Que Bueno Suerte has friendly waiting staff and cooperative management ensuring a good experience.

Que Bueno Suerte has a full alcohol bar serving a fine selection of wine, cocktails and beer, etc. to enhance the food experience. Some of the popular food choices at this Mexican food joint include pheasant in blackbean sauce, duck confit in mole sauce, bone marrow, empandas, chiliquas, antojitos, rice varieties and noodle varieties. The place also served mouthwatering dessert choices such as rice pudding and cookies.

topReview.highlightedText: Absolutely wonderful. A band was playing lovely milieux. Our server was so attentive and great.  The restaurant is really. Nice.  Food was delicious. Highly recommend

name: FIRE - The ART Hotel Denver, Curio Collection by Hilton
description: Perched above Broadway, FIRE offers diners beautiful views in one of Denver’s newest restaurants.  Enjoy the elevated dining atmosphere with artfully prepared American fare.  Diners can sample craft cocktails prior to their dinner engagement at the restaurant's bar & lounge or simply take in the stunning works of art housed in the hotel.

topReview.highlightedText: A fun and unique place to eat and have a drink while admiring Denver's beautiful evenings.  Food is tasty, well plated and great service. Enjoy we did!

name: Ship Tavern at the Brown Palace
description:
**Reservations are currently available. Please note, a face covering is required while entering, exiting or moving through the restaurant. Parties must be complete to be seated, and should not arrive more than 5 minutes before their reservation time.**

Welcome to the Ship Tavern at The Brown Palace Hotel and Spa, located on 17th Street in beautiful downtown Denver! We are pleased to offer a varied menu sure to accommodate all appetites! Chef Herwerth and his team source our signature Prime Rib and Colorado Trout, as well as most of our products, locally! Enjoy John Kite live on the piano every Friday & Saturday evening from 7:30 to 10:00 pm.

The Ship's cocktail menu offers hand-crafted beverages, a large selection of beers, including tap and a pleasing spirit list! The Palace Arms' wine list is also available!

In order to accommodate parties of 8 or more guests, please contact us directly 303.297.3111 extension 3315

topReview.highlightedText: Ship Tavern is one of our favorite spots to take out-of-town guests. The history, ambiance, and food never disappoints.

name: Lola Coastal Mexican
description:
Northern Baja-inspired cuisine from celebrated Chef Javier Plascencia, Lola will keep you happily satiated with crave-able dishes unlike any other in Denver.
Order online for curbside pick-up, or book a table for outdoor or outdoor dining. If you're in the neighborhood, stroll up to our window on 16th & Boulder St. to place your order and see what we're selling from The Tequila Shop.

And new to Lola, The Tender Project is a ghost kitchen offering bougie, all-natural, double-dipped chicken tenders and ThighFries with five of the most delicious dipping sauces one could dream up. Order these through the window or for curbside pick-up. You'll thank yourself.

topReview.highlightedText: Expensive cocktails the food was quite good though I really liked the fish tacos

name: Acova
description: Acova is writing the next chapter of one of Denver’s great neighborhoods. An iconic locale in a historic district, Acova builds on the rich story of “The Northside” (now known as LoHi) by breathing new life into an address with soul. Even its name pays homage to its South Broadway sibling restaurant The Hornet, while tipping a cap to its storied Italian predecessor Patsy’s.  The place you bring friends and family from out of town to show them what Denver’s all about. The place you go for that after work cocktail, or your go to date spot, whether it’s your first or 50th date. The place you get the group together on a Saturday night, and where  you recover together on a Sunday morning. Acova is the next Highlands institution, bearing vintage flair and contemporary charm that threads the past into the future. Acova brings you back time and again because you are part of this story now, and Acova is part of yours.

topReview.highlightedText: The food is wonderful and the prices are extremely reasonable.

name: Mizu Izakaya and Sushi
description:
2017 Top of the Town, "Best Japanese Restaurant in Denver"


Dipped in the Japanese arts and architecture, the Mizu Izakaya and Sushi restaurant offers an authentic experience of Japanese culture. The restaurant offers contemporary Japanese dining and a comfortable, young and hip atmosphere. The food is served hot and its assortment of dishes are popular among the locals and are nicely complimented by innovative drinks.



Mizu Izakaya and Sushi restaurant, despite being a Sushi place, has a diverse menu and it offers a variety of Japanese dishes. Some of the dishes include King Mushroom Carpaccio, Grilled Whole Squid, Grilled Lamb Chop and Brussels Sprouts. These are some of the favorite dishes for diners at the Mizu Izakaya and Sushi, a place that diners prefer for the quality of their food.

topReview.highlightedText: Waitress was great, sushi was ok- overpriced in my opinion!

name: The Patio at Sloan's Lake
description: We at The Patio at Sloans are an eclectic group of people who deeply care about what we do.

topReview.highlightedText:
Patio between bar and 17th is perfect. View of lake and not too much traffic.  Excellent old fashioned, different with lots of bitters. 
Shishitos we’re delicious as was the aioli.  Steak and frites with greens prepared perfectly.  Enjoyed everything and Talon was awesome as our server.  Will be back to try more of the menu!

name: Adrift
description:
Adrift is a craft cocktail Tiki bar located on S. Broadway in Denver. We feature modern tropical cocktails and island fare aimed at making you forget that you're no where near a beach!

We specialize in rum, but our drinks don't stop there! We're cocktail enthusiasts with a passion for over-delivering and a tendency to have a great time with all of our guests.

topReview.highlightedText: It was great! Tiki drinks on point, food delicious. We tried the pork belly bao + edamame hummus. Only bummer wa s that we were looking forward to sitting inside, but even with a reservation we had to sit outside where it’s not a decorated.

name: Ash'Kara
description: Ash’Kara will explore the continuous evolution of Israeli cuisine, with ingredients and flavors from across Europe and North Africa.

topReview.highlightedText: We went for the Rosh Hashanah prix fixe menu and everything was fantastic. Our server (Samantha) was the perfect blend of attentive and leaving us to our own devices. Great on checking in, easy to talk to, awesome experience top to bottom. Will definitely be back!

name: Jax Fish House & Oyster Bar - LoDo
description:
Jax Fish House LoDo is open and ready to welcome you for both indoor and outdoor dining and curbside pick-up 7 days a week. Any way you choose to dine, we got you. For curbside pick-up order online! It is easy-peasy, and you can place an order for a future date, too.
Order Online: https://www.jaxfishhouse.com/lodo/
----------
Jax Fish House in downtown Denver works tirelessly to bring fresh caught seafood and fine coastal food to the surrounding landlocked community. The dining experience, whether outdoors or at your home, focuses on sustainable seafood when choosing who to partner with to provide guests only the freshest seafood.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent as always! Love Jax!

name: Williams & Graham
description:
Williams & Graham is a craft cocktail bar hidden behind a bookshelf, offering a rich ambiance, wide variety of drinks, delicious food, and genuine hospitality.

We take reservations everyday of the week and have limited capacity for walk ins due to social distancing protocols. Due to limited capacity and high demand, all reservations will have a set maximum time of 2 hours to enjoy food and drink. Thank you for your understanding as we navigate these challenging times. This is a 21 and up environment, we apologize for the inconvenience but we will not be able to permit any one under age.

We look forward to sharing a drink with you soon!

topReview.highlightedText: Fantastic. The food is excellent and the drinks even better.

name: Shells and Sauce
description: General Manager, Oscar Venegas and Executive Chef Marcus Jimenez are serving authentic Italian American food in the heart of Congress Park.   Shells and Sauce brings Old Country taste to a cozy neighborhood restaurant. If you’re craving home-made lasagna, meat or fish, Shells and Sauce has a variety of savory appetizers and entrees to chose from. We also boast an extensive wine list to pair with anything you choose, and we offer delicious desserts to top off your evening. Whether you sit on our rooftop or in our main dining room to watch our open kitchen, Shells and Sauce is a great place to entertain friends or family in an inviting setting. Step into our kitchen and let us share our passion for food!

topReview.highlightedText: I loved this place! Cute neighborhood restaurant with delicious food and cocktails

name: Spuntino
description:
**We kindly ask that all of our guests be fully vaccinated against COVID-19 before visiting Spuntino**

Our staff is fully vaccinated, will continue to wear facemasks and ask that our guests moving about our indoor space do so as well. We will continue to offer the choice of covered outdoor dining, though do keep in mind that fickle Colorado weather may require us to close our outdoor space on rare occasions.

If you are unable to find the reservation you are looking for, don't hesitate to call us directly - we love to hear from our guests!

If you are booking an earlier reservation (up to 7pm) please respect our need to reseat your table with later reservations.

If you are running late or if your reservation plans change at all, please call. Our business depends on our guests communicating with us and no-shows have a severe impact on us.

topReview.highlightedText: We love Spuntino. The food is always amazing, the staff friendly and knowledgeable.

name: The Fifth String
description: The 5th String is Chef Amos Watts' neighborhood eatery located in the LO HI area of Denver, Colorado. A fun vibrant atmosphere featuring a main dining room, bar room, and patio area.

topReview.highlightedText: We went to the Fifth String for our 11th  anniversary. Service was top notch! Our waiter was very attentive and patiently explained the menu to us. We started with oysters and the tallow candle bread service. Then we ordered from the prix fix menu. I ordered raclette, scallops, and the lemon tart. My husband ordered raclette, fettuccine, and the lavender dessert. Everything was delicious and flavorful. Loved the ambiance as well, perfect for a date night or special occasion. Lastly, our waiter surprised us with two glasses of sparkling wine to toast us for our anniversary-we were so touched. A wonderful place, we can’t wait to go back!

name: Babes Tea Room
description:
Afternoon Tea, Bubbly Brunches, Cafe & Events. A tea party is the ultimate indulgence and the perfect way to share special moments. Delightful and modern, Babe's Tea Room is also a lovely stop-in for a quick salad, sandwich, or pastry with a cuppa!
Event specialist... Bridal Showers, Baby Showers, Birthdays & Books clubs are all welcome.
75 + Loose leaf teas sold by the Oz.
Patio Seating with (really cute) umbrellas + flower pots!
Vino, bubbles, and happy hour specials daily!

topReview.highlightedText: The atmosphere was awesome, our waitresses were  very helpful and very nice. The food was delicious and pretty. We had an amazing time. Highly recommend Babe’s tea for any occasion.

name: Il Posto
description:
An elevated Italian restaurant, where food and wine are in symbiosis, Il Posto is “the complicated simplicity of Italian food and wine." Our food and wine lists represent all of the Italian peninsula; in its history and tradition with clear sophistication, simplicity and creativity.
Your experience at Il Posto will be the ultimate journey for the time that you will spend with us.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent spot for a special night!  Amazing food and friendly staff every time! Absolutely recommend, and can't wait to return! Grazie!

name: LeRoux
description: LeRoux, the newest restaurant from Chef Lon Symensma and ChoLon Restaurant Concepts, showcases contemporary European cuisine in an elegant, intimate atmosphere.

topReview.highlightedText: An absolutely beautiful dining experience at LeRoux.. From the innovative menu, to the friendly and knowledgeable staff- this is a gorgeous restaurant that I would return to time and time again in Denver. Would highly recommend. Make sure to try to the cauliflower creme brûlée and beef tartare. Their wine selection is also top notch. Also, don’t sleep on Sunday brunch!

name: Mimosas
description:
**Please note in the event of inclement weather, we cannot promise to move your party inside if you book an outdoor table due to our current limited seating. We will do our best to make the experience as comfortable as possible, and thank you so much for joining us!**

In the heart of the historic Five Points neighborhood in Denver, CO, Mimosas is a chef-driven, gourmet food concept founded in 2020. It is inspired by a true love for breakfast. The menu is a balance of comfort and innovation, celebrating classic comfort fare with a twist.

Our goal is to share our food with everyone. When guests dine with Mimosas, we strive to provide more than just a meal—we want it to be an experience. Our focus is providing exceptional quality, taste, presentation and service.

topReview.highlightedText: Love this place every time!! Staff is phenomenal and food is great too!

name: Palace Arms at the Brown Palace
description: Experience the reimagined Palace Arms. Dine amongst Napoleonic artifacts, reinvigorated interior, upgraded furnishings and lighting while you explore our locally sourced, farm fresh inspired dinner menu, hand-crafted, specialty cocktail offerings and our Wine Spectator recognized, award winning wine list. Executive Chef, Kim Moyle breathes new life into our iconic Palace Arms with artful plate presentations and delectable dishes with a focus on locally raised premium Angus Beef.
