topReview.highlightedText: Awesome. Great food, great wine, great service. What else could you ask for.... champagne. They have that too. Highly recommend. Will definitely come back when ever we are in Denver.  The ambiance alone was wonderful.

name: Jax Fish House & Oyster Bar - Glendale
description:
Jax Fish House is open and ready to welcome you for both indoor and outdoor dining and curbside pick-up 7 days a week. Any way you choose to dine, we got you. For curbside pick-up order online! It is easy-peasy, and you can place an order for a future date, too.
Order Online: jaxfishhouse.com/glendale
----------
Jax Fish House in Glendale, just east of Cherry Creek, works tirelessly to bring fresh caught seafood and fine coastal food to the surrounding landlocked community. The dining experience, whether outdoors or at your home, focuses on sustainable seafood when choosing who to partner with to provide guests only the freshest seafood.

topReview.highlightedText: Sadly, no Gulf coast oysters on the menu. Very helpful wait staff; very knowledgeable of oyster options and white wine (try the DV Domaine St Michele).

name: Ellyngton's at the Brown Palace
description:
**We kindly ask that guests wear a face covering while entering, exiting or moving through the restaurant. Parties must be complete to be seated and should not arrive more than 5 minutes before their reservation time.**

**Currently, our Sunday brunch is not a buffet; it is offered à la carte. We are hopeful that we will be able to return to a buffet-style brunch later this year.**

topReview.highlightedText: Wonderful experience. Dawa, our waiter, was the absolute best! Eggs Benedict amazing and so was everything else we ordered. The atmosphere is unmatched in this historic hotel. And the Brunch Jazz piano player was the pièce de ré·sis·tance! Request a table near the piano if that’s your preference. I would have preferred being seated closer to the action but the back of the dining area wasn’t bad. Thanks to Jerome for his hospitality and kindness. What a wonderful experience. Would do it over and over again.

name: Kachina Cantina- Denver
description:
Guests and associates who are fully vaccinated are not required to wear a facial covering while on property, however those not fully vaccinated we encourage to continue to wear a mask and social distance while indoors. We operate on the honor system and will not be actively inquiring your vaccination status.

The health and safety of our guests and associates is our highest priority. We have implemented a wide variety of operational changes that go above and beyond guidance offered by the CDC, other public health experts and government officials. We look forward to serving you safely during this time and appreciate your cooperation in helping us do so.

Kachina is a free-spirited, modern cantina providing an escape in the LoDo district of Denver. Kachina’s inspiration is found in the Four Corners region of Southwest America and Baja Mexico.

Curbside carry out available during normal business hours.
Cash is not accepted at this time and we apologize for any inconvenience.

topReview.highlightedText: Our server was so nice and the food was excellent. Highly recommend the blood orange margarita (get the pitcher because you will want more than one).

name: Carmine's McGregor Square
description: Carmine's on McGregor Square is a family-style Italian restaurant located in the ballpark neighborhood. We take pride in making our dishes with the freshest ingredients, sourced locally when we can. Our atmosphere is casual, festive, and friendly. Our servers bring the menu to life, describing dishes and offering advice on selecting just the right combination of food and beverage. Reservations for dining preferred, bar seating available for walk ins.

topReview.highlightedText: Dinner was excellent, but the bread pudding was SO worth the food-coma!

name: Duo Restaurant
description:
Duo Restaurant is a treasure for those seeking a special dining experience tucked in Denver’s hippest neighborhood, Highland. Duo offers a relaxed and unassuming environment attracting diners who might wish to linger over a cup of coffee, a glass of wine at the bar, or to enjoy a hearty meal.

The stylish neighborhood restaurant is elegant and exciting. It’s the kind of place you want to show off to those who think they know where all the hot spots are in the city!

Duo Restaurant offers a seasonal changing menu with the freshest ingredients available from our local farms. Choose from a selection of appetizers or entrees that will satisfy the biggest meat eaters or the most discerning vegetarians.

topReview.highlightedText: Everything was excellent and the service great.

name: Kisbee on the Roof
description: A sparkling lap pool is the focal point of The Jacquard’s rooftop, though the mountain and city views also vie for attention. Kisbee on the Roof is The Jacquard’s elevated bar experience, offering exclusive access to incredible sunsets and a space that is perfect to unwind, reflect, and celebrate the day.

topReview.highlightedText: Lovely rooftop ambiance. Friendly, hard-working servers, tasty salads & "Frose" drink.

name: Red Square Euro Bistro
description: Red Square is a warm and friendly restaurant that offers contemporary Russian and European cuisine.  Our full bar features over 100 vodkas from around the world plus twenty house-made infusions, as well as an extensive wine list.

topReview.highlightedText: Amazing food, excellent vodka, friendly and attentive service.

name: The Original- Denver
description:
The Original, is a new restaurant located within The Rally Hotel, across 20th Street from Coors Field.

The Original reinvents the neighborhood eatery, combining timeless inspiration from classic Americana with inventive and playful modern flair.

The menu, with influences ranging from the 1950s diner to elegant railway dining cars, features familiar and elevated comforts, including a variety of gourmet sandwiches, soups and all-day breakfast options alongside enticing entrées.

topReview.highlightedText:
We had Prime rib and short ribs it was all very good.
Will be going back

name: Wildflower - Denver
description: Highlighting locally sourced ingredients and seasonal fare, Wildflower celebrates the Western landscape, with a veg-forward, shared plates style offering with Italian & Mexican influences.

topReview.highlightedText: This was one of the best dinners we have had in Denver.  The food and presentation was spectacular and the service was impeccable.  The cocktails were crazy good, and the ambiance was such a cool vibe. I can't wait to go back.  You are definitely going to spend a little money there, but it is worth every penny.

name: Marco’s Coal Fired
description:
Marco’s Coal Fired started with the simple idea that passion makes great pizza.  The authentic taste of Italy is served to you through the finest ingredients and traditional techniques of the Verace Pizza Napoletana (VPN).  Only 00 flour, San Marzano tomatoes, all natural fior di latte or bufala mozzarella, fresh herbs and fresh, all natural, non-processed ingredients are acceptable.  Marco's Coal Fired cooks in authentic, Italian hand built wood fired pizza ovens.  
Come taste Marco's Coal Fired's efforts and see if we don’t have you dreaming of warm Neopolitian nights, no passport required!

topReview.highlightedText: One of the best salads and pizza I ever had

name: Rhein Haus - Denver
description:
A Bavarian-inspired restaurant with house made sausages, pretzels, and other authentic eats.

***Kitchen closes at 10PM each night***

topReview.highlightedText: We arrived early and were sat immediately, the staff was AWESOME, service was very attentive and appreciated, Food was very good and my Girlfriend and I will have a Giant pretzel joke for life. Love your restaurant.

name: Sushi Ronin
description:
Sushi Ronin offers a traditional menu focused on Japanese cuisine. A chic sushi spot in Lower Highland, it offers a sleek and contemporary d�cor with pendant lights and bar style seating. Weather permitting, guests can also dine outdoors at Sushi Ronin.



Along with a menu of sushi, udon and soba bowls, Sushi Ronin�s full-service bar offers a variety of wines, cocktails and spirits. Most popular however are its sakes, Japanese beers and whiskeys. It is open daily for dinner with extended weekend hours. You can also stop by for its weekday Happy Hour specials to enjoy deals on drinks and small plates.

topReview.highlightedText: We were on the patio so the noise level was low. The music inside seemed a bit loud. Had requested a patio table but the patio was closed. Arrived and one of the staff kindly set up a table for us...amazing accommodation. A bit pricey, but great sushi!

name: Gyu-Kaku - Denver, CO
description:
We are open for limited dine-in service.

We have updated our operations in accordance with all government guidelines to put your health and safety first.

To maintain a safe environment for you and Gyu-Kaku staff, we ask that all guests understand and adhere to the following:

- Masks are recommended
- There may be limits on party sizes.
- We are serving a limited menu. Not all Grand Menu items will be available during our immediate reopening.
- We only accept payment via credit or debit card. Cash payments respectfully declined.

topReview.highlightedText: Always good, always consistent.

name: Henry's Tavern - Denver
description: Located in downtown Denver, near the 16th street mall Henry's is your local tavern. If you find yourself looking for a sports bar or ale house in the Theatre District, after an event at the Paramount Theatre or Colorado Convention Center or just want to spend time with friends after a Colorado Rockies home game from Coors Field we would love to serve you a beer. We source a number of ingredients for our fresh made-to-order fare from local sources. Our extensive beer list focuses on local breweries with ever-changing seasonal and hard to find specials.

topReview.highlightedText: Henry’s is a must eat for us every time we are in Denver, twice this trip. Food is wonderful, service is excellent and the open air environment is entertaining.

name: Atelier by Radex
description:
Long time Denver-area chef and restaurateur, Radek Cerny, delivers his newest creation, Atelier by Radex, to Denver's City Park neighborhood.

French-influenced with a casual, friendly vibe, Atelier by Radex is a spectacular choice for lunch or dinner.

topReview.highlightedText: We were amazed watching the staff handle everything with professionalism and grace. They were short by two people and still gave us all the attention to make our meal very special. Can’t wait to go back.

name: Foraged- Denver
description:
For[a]ged restaurant is a culinary-inspired concept that will unite craft and cuisine. The For[a]ged brand is committed to offering a menu based on the relentless pursuit of thoughtfully chosen local, international and seasonal ingredients. The restaurant will have three different dining experiences which will include an upstairs mezzanine with a raw bar and intimate seating, two private dining rooms designed for meetings and private events and a large whiskey driven bar/lounge.
First of his field to debut as a Murray Carter Journeyman Bladesmith, Executive Chef Duy Pham will institute the forging of his own Japanese carbon steel knives as part of the concept.
Welcome to For[a]ged.

topReview.highlightedText: Enjoyed a delicious dinner here with my family, who run from vegan to carnivore. Service was excellent and food satisfied. Not cheap, but worth it.

name: ATTIMO
description:
ATTIMO MEANS “MOMENT” IN ITALIAN.
Jon and his wife, Megan, moved to Monforte d’Alba in Piedmont, Italy with their son in 2013, settling on the Ginestra hill and purchasing their own small Barolo vineyard. In Italy, Jon spent his days working and learning in the vineyards and wineries from producers whose families have been making wine in the region for generations. After returning to his native home of Denver, Jon wanted to bring a piece of Italy back with him to share with Colorado. So Attimo was born.

Attimo is about bringing the special moments of everyday Italian life to Denver. Authentic and approachable northern Italian wines and cuisine are the specialty, accompanied by warm and genuine hospitality.

topReview.highlightedText: We always enjoy Attimo.  Amanda waited on us last night, giving us excellent service.

name: Zocalito Latin Bistro
description: Zocalito Latin Bistro now in Denver, Colorado, is home to chef Michael Beary, the man who is doing more than anyone to bring the authentic ingredients and true flavors of Oaxaca to America. Over the years, Beary has traveled widely in the Oaxaca region and now works directly with farmers and food artisans who supply him with rare chile peppers and other ingredients.

topReview.highlightedText: Awesome food and super service.

name: the plimoth
description:
WE LOVE FOOD

We believe in an eclectic yet approachable love for food. Our chefs draw from foundations in classic French and Italian cuisine, finding inspiration in seasonal and local ingredients that offer a modern twist to each dish. Our ever changing menus reflect the efforts of our collaboration with unique purveyors, local farmers, and artisan producers. Join us for an elevated, unpretentious dining experience.

topReview.highlightedText: We have been here a number of times and always have a wonderful experience.  Best restaurant in Denver!

name: Ronin - Congress Park
description: Located in Congress Park Neighborhood, Ronin serves traditional sushi, sashimi and ramen, featuring fresh fish imported daily from Japan.

topReview.highlightedText: Delicious sushi and sake, outdoor patio, quiet neighborhood. Highly recommend.

name: Viale Pizza and Kitchen
description: A down to earth neighborhood bistro-lounge serving New York inspired pizza, traditional Italian fare and much more.

topReview.highlightedText: Always delicious

name: Ritual Social House
description:
Ritual Social House is Cap Hills newest spot. Come experience a taste of the mountains on the hill and try the best pizza and burger in Denver along with a wide selection of small plates, hand rolled pastas, fresh salads, unique bowls and a great cocktail and craft beer selection. We are open 7 days a week for lunch and dinner and host brunch on Saturday and Sunday complete with bottomless mimosas and a full Bloody Mary bar. Happy hour is everyday Tuesday - Sunday 3pm-6pm & again 9pm-close. Monday make it a happy day and join us all day for happy hour.
Come get your new daily Ritual started now.

topReview.highlightedText: The crab cake benny and buffalo hash were the highlights. I also loved the bloody mary! Great place. Thanks, Emily!!

name: The Lobby - Denver
description:
To our lovely Lobby guests:

We are excited to have you back and brunching with us again! Since the times have changed, so have our policies. Please read the following to ensure a safe and enjoyable experience:

We can no longer accommodate parties larger than 8 people.

Reservations are recommended on weekdays since we are unable to have patrons wait within the restaurant or bar. If you arrive early, you may be asked to wait to enter until your reservation time.

Reservations are required on weekends since we are unable to have patrons wait within the restaurant. If you arrive early, you may be asked to wait to enter until your reservation time.

Dining & bottomless mimosa times are limited to 120 minutes on Saturdays and Sundays so we can accommodate as many guests as possible while having limited seating & increased sanitary practices. This time limit begins at your reservation time.

For reservations past 4:00pm on Saturdays & Sundays, please call the store.

topReview.highlightedText: Food is always great as is the service!

name: Mehak India's Aroma
description: Dining at Mehak India's Aroma is an experience like no other.  The ambiance is vibrant and exciting while providing the comfort our customers expect.  The aroma's intrigue your taste buds, inviting you to try all of our delicious dishes. The cuisine strikes a tasteful balance of modern and authentic Indian cuisine.

topReview.highlightedText: Another good experience.

name: Recess Beer Garden
description: Recess Beer Garden is an indoor/outdoor haven for food and drinks in the LoHi Area (Lower Highlands) of Denver. We have 24 beers on tap, as well as a full bar and kitchen.  Enjoy the summer months on our patio where we have cooling misters, picnic tables, and areas for all sized groups.  We specialize in domestic and craft beer, refreshing cocktails, and American bar food with a twist.  Hope to see you soon!

topReview.highlightedText: What a great place, ambiance and outdoor area so cool.  Thought there should be more variety of beer on the menu and better selection of food, but what they have is good.

name: The Family Jones Spirit House
description: The Family Jones Spirit House is a distillery and tasting room featuring crafted spirits and bites. It emphasizes the relationship between distiller, chef, bartender and guest, with a focus on hospitality that makes it a gathering place where all feel at home. Nestled in the space at 3245 Osage St., The Family Jones Distillery occupies the former Mancinellis Market building two doors from Root Down. Designed and built by tres birds workshop, the space pairs industrial elements with rich wood details. The roof was lifted to add a second-floor mezzanine where distillery operations are now perched above a sunken, curvilinear, concrete bar. Guests enter the space through a large, square, wooden door made from reclaimed, on-site materials. Inside, they are met with low-slung seating, deep blue booths and soft lighting. Two-story wooden louvers flank the Osage Street glass facade, offering passive temperature and lighting control, while drawing attention to the well-lit copper still.

topReview.highlightedText: Incredibly atmosphere, amazing drinks, lovely service! Can’t wait to go back.

name: MBP
description: A black-owned and operated upscale restaurant in Five Points, we are dedicated to our community by providing excellent service and cuisine. With various eclectic culinary offerings, a full-service bar, and a large covered patio space with live music events, MBP is the place to relax, dance, and have an exceptional evening. We can’t wait for you to be a part of the MBP experience!

topReview.highlightedText: A wonderful neighborhood gem! The patio is lovely. Service (Kyra) was great - she was knowledgeable and made us feel so welcome. Food was creative and delightful. Can't wait to go back!

name: P.F. Chang's - LoDo
description: P.F. Chang's is a restaurant concept that honors the 2,000-year-old Asian tradition of wok cooking and believes in making food from scratch every day in every restaurant. With a Farm to Wok™ food philosophy at its core, P.F. Chang's chefs hand-roll dim sum, hand chop and slice all vegetables and meats, handcraft every sauce and wok-cook each recipe, every day in every restaurant using wholesome, fresh ingredients. With roots in Chinese cooking, the culinary landscape at P.F. Chang's now stretches across Asia with diverse, culturally inspired recipes including hand-rolled sushi, Vietnamese-style soups and bowls, traditional Chinese dim sum, wok-fired chicken and beef entrées, and family style noodles and rice. All made from scratch every day.

topReview.highlightedText: Everything perfect

name: Campus Lounge
description: Campus Lounge has been a Denver icon for over 50 years in the Bonnie Brae neighborhood.  Recently reestablished, Campus Lounge is your home away from home.  Whether you gather with your family, friends or neighbors, you will enjoy all that we have to offer at this 70s Era Vintage Lounge & Steakhouse.  Relax with a T-bone, Filet or Ribeye while enjoying a fine glass of wine.  Maybe mix it up with a craft cocktail and our House Smoked Chicken or Fried Cauliflower Wings.  And don't forget about our large selection of domestic and craft beer with a juicy Campus Burger.  Hope to see you soon!

topReview.highlightedText: Upgraded menu, great attentive staff - can't miss food & beverage!

name: Kobe An
description: Kobe An has been serving the Denver area delicious sushi and authentic Japanese cuisine since 1979. We were located in Lakewood for 35 years and we just relocated to Cherry Creek.  Our owner, Kimie, came to America from Kobe, Japan to serve traditional as well as today's modern food that is popular in Japan.  All of our entrees come from and are inspired by her family’s recipes.  We have tatami rooms for an authentic Japanese experience.  Our tatami rooms are a unique and fun way to enjoy your authentic Japanese cuisine.   Menu modifications are happily accommodated.

topReview.highlightedText: We sat at sushi bar and were happy with the chef’s creations.  We were a bit disappointed that we were only ones at the bar.  A little too quiet for us.  We would also have liked Omakase.

name: Bubba Gump - Denver
description: Since 1996, Bubba Gump Shrimp Co. has been entertaining guests with a charming down-home style that’s a hit with eaters around the globe. Our menu offers a number of items for the shrimp lover in all of us. Boasting creative seafood dishes inspired straight from the movie Forrest Gump and a fun family atmosphere, Bubba Gump Shrimp Co. will have you running to the nearest location you can find!

topReview.highlightedText: They were out of onion rings and it came with at least half the mean with the group that we had. They only told half the table. They did not substitute with anything and still charged full price. Staff was very nice and had a great time with our group, but the food was disappointing. I hope it was just an off day for the restaurant

name: West 29th
description:
Seating is limited - please make reservations, especially for the patio. If you simply show up without reservations, you may be disappointed, and we really don't want that. Patio parties limited to 5, including children. One table per party.

1:45min. limit per table. Please understand that this is in order to accommodate customer demand and ensure that our business survives this challenging period.

Children must be included in head count.

$25 minimum per person. Dining room and Patio tables are reserved for dinner. You may join us in the bar if you are only having appetizers and/or drinks.

We may not always be able to take take-out orders, as we prioritize our seated guests. Thank you for understanding.

Kitchen closes an hour before our doors close. Please be prompt, so that you have time to enjoy your experience with us!

Thank you! We look forward to serving you!

topReview.highlightedText: Perfect place for three generations of family and friends to gather, share a delicious meal and a cheerful toast. Something on the menu for everyone but not so many choices that anyone gets overwhelmed. Perfect wine selections, cozy atmosphere and excellent service!

name: Coohills
description:
With a focus on local, regional, and farm-fresh ingredients, Coohills Restaurant and Bar is reminiscent of what you might find in casual bars and restaurants in Europe. The open kitchen and uniquely modern interior, designed by award-winning architects Semple Brown, underscores Coohills' style! Located in the Lower Downtown (LoDo) neighborhood, we invite you to pull up to the community table, tuck in at your own intimate table for two or more, or enjoy our outdoor terrace for a spirited drink.

Coohills includes a main dining room, private dining room, community space, bar and beautiful outdoor terrace, providing a breathtaking view of the infamous Colorado sunsets.

Coohills comfortably seats up to 200 people and can host up to 400 people for a stand up reception.

We offer Happy Hour, Dinner Service and are happy to host your upcoming Private Events

topReview.highlightedText: Holly and I celebrated our third wedding anniversary at Coohills last night. Three years ago we were married on the bridge outside, and held our reception there. Last night was perfect. Excellent service and delicious foods and drink. We both are so happy that Tom and Diane’s wonderful destination survives!

name: Dimestore Delibar
description: Dimestore Delibar, located in the heart of LOHI just around the corner from the iconic Littleman Ice Cream Can, and named one of 5280 Magazine's Best New Restaurants of 2020, is an eclectic combination of eatery, craft cocktail bar, deli and full service restaurant offering both in house dining (featuring two large outdoor patios, including our rooftop patio that sports its own independent bar) as well as a multitude of to-go options from our creative menu of sandwiches and small plates, as well as our stocked deli full of house roasted meats, cured delicacies from around the world, and some incredible selections of cheese. Not to be outdone, our house crafted cocktail menu hits on all levels and is both incredibly delicious, as well as delivering great bang for the buck. Our Five & Dime Happy Hour runs Tuesday through Friday, 3-5pm, so come get a drink and a bite and hang out with us!

topReview.highlightedText: Delicious Location, Hip Eats

name: The Nickel - Hotel Teatro
description: Located within Denver’s historic Tramway Building, originally opened in 1911, The Nickel pays homage to the space that was once used to collect fare from customers riding its resident streetcars: a nickel. Just as the building in which The Nickel is housed has a storied past, the dishes found on the menu at The Nickel all have a story. We proudly serve menus that incorporate the highest quality ingredients from farmers, ranchers, distillers and craft producers, and is comprised of dishes that are easily recognizable and feel simple, but eat complex. The restaurant aims to make all guests feel the warmth of familiarity within its doors.  From our friendly and knowledgeable service team, to our sommelier curated wine program, to the centerpiece of our restaurant- The Barrel Bar - which offers house barrel-aged cocktails on tap.

topReview.highlightedText: Menu is simple but the food was good. The drinks were fantastic, and they have a great selection too. The service was also very good, our waiter EJ was awesome, and it’s a very cute restaurant fitting the theme of the hotel nicely.

name: Blue Moon Brewing Company
description:
Come enjoy the gorgeous microbrewery-sized Blue Moon Brewing Company! Along with elevated, global cuisine in a casual environment, we will feature 23 rotating Blue Moon beers. From the original Blue Moon Belgian White that started it all, to our diverse and ever-changing line-up, we have a beer taste for everyone.

A reservation through OpenTable guarantees you a reservation in the restaurant and the opportunity to grab a beer and go on the self-guided tour. We currently do not take reservations for our patio area.

***In order to give all reservations the opportunity to dine with us, tables will be available for a maximum of 2 hours during high volume times.***

topReview.highlightedText: Awesome experience! It was my first time here. Lots of beer choices, many of which you can only taste here. My favorite was the chocolate beer! Great food menu as well.

name: Q House
description:
* Masks are required to enter the restaurant and when not seated at your table.
* We will be taking reservations for the patio (outdoor) and dining room (indoor).
* Outdoor tables are available during booking. Standard tables = Inside.
* We do not have an enclosed patio with heaters, so plan according to the current weather forecast. We likely will NOT be able to move your party inside due to inclement weather.
* Parties of up to 5 will be given 1.5 hours from the time of reservation, parties of 6-8 will be allotted 2 hours. If your party is late, it will cut into your overall time.
* Due to limited space, please account for any children in your party.
* We hold tables for up to 15 minutes. If you are going to be more than 15 minutes late, please contact the restaurant.

topReview.highlightedText: Great meal, from Tongue &Tripe to Ribs, everything was delicious! Duck Lo Mein…..OMG, highly recommend this value driven amazing spot!

name: range
description:
Located within the new Renaissance Denver Downtown City Center Hotel at the historic Colorado National Bank building, range offers cuisine that celebrates the cultural heritage and adventurous spirit of the American West, prepared with a modern day sophistication.

range features a bar offering a wide selection of local beers, liquors and wines, a private dining room and a wood fired oven, in which much of the fare will be prepared. In addition to offering daily featured dishes, the menu changes seasonally and offers a large selection of shareable plates in addition to entrees and side dishes.

range also offers free valet for all guests.

topReview.highlightedText: The food was pretty good but it was overpriced. We received an email saying to arrive in business casual dress. When we walked in, the first person I saw was in a white tee shirt with some logo on it.

name: Su Taco
description: Lively, easygoing taco bar serving up street-inspired tacos, enchiladas, tequila, mezcal, margaritas, cocktails and craft beer in a vibrant, industrial space with a rooftop patio.

topReview.highlightedText: Love the brunch. I take all my friends that are in town visiting here!

name: Kobe An - LoHi
description: Welcome to Kobe An LoHi.   In addition to a full sushi and izakaya menu, our signature dish of “shabu shabu” is a traditional Japanese-style hot-pot meal. The phrase “shabu, shabu” means “swish, swish” for the custom nature of cooking this dish.  We're not your typical hot-pot or fondue restaurant. Our "Shabu Shabu" style transports you across time and cultures to immerse you in a deliciously fresh and evocative world. Enjoy the skills of our chefs and bar staff as they complement this gastronomy of the past with quality sushi, crafted cocktails and small plates with a modern twist.  In our beautiful dining room , or under Japanese lanterns on our patio, come savor not only the food - come savor the swish and the sushi.

topReview.highlightedText: Amazing food. Great new experience with amazing food.

name: Bigsby’s Folly Craft Winery & Restaurant
description:
5-Star Certified, full-production winery & restaurant, inspired by the Roaring 20's. Located in the heart of Denver's hottest neighborhood, the River North (RiNo) Art District.

Our beautifully restored, historic building boasts 30’ ceilings with original beams and 10’ chandeliers. We have a full menu, extensive wine list, an impressive selection of craft beer and specialty cocktails. Now serving brunch on Saturday & Sunday, 10:30am-2:30pm.

You’ll find plenty of free street parking with several nearby garages and the 38th & Blake Light Rail Station is just steps away from our front door. Our winery is the perfect place to enjoy a relaxing meal or host a large group for a special event.

FOR GROUPS LARGER THAN 15 PEOPLE, PLEASE CONTACT CASSIE@BIGSBYSFOLLY.COM

topReview.highlightedText: Great atmosphere! Highly recommend. Thanks for a great experience.

name: Locanda Del Borgo
description:
Authentic Italian Restaurant in a trattoria setting.
We serve genuine traditional Italian recipes with our Chef's personal touch, in a warm and friendly atmosphere.
Our Chef bases his creations on his 25 years experience in the restaurant business.
Our philosophy is to serve free range and naturally raised farm products whenever possible, and we try to support local farmers as much as we can.
Our menu is paired with an Italian based wine list with international accents, including wines from USA, Spain, Australia, Argentina and others.

topReview.highlightedText: FIVE STARS! Phenomenal food - truly amazing food - great ambiance, and the nicest staff! The outdoor patio is perfect - it reminded us of the cute patios we dined in during vacations to Italy! We will be coming back again and again! THE FOOD IS SOOOO GOOD!

name: Bazille - Nordstrom Cherry Creek Shopping Center
description:
Enjoy a view of the exhibition kitchen in a vibrant cafe that delivers our interpretation of bistro cuisine, including soups, salads, sandwiches, pizza and desserts. Beer and wine are available.

We are open for to-go orders with Curbside Pickup. Call (720) 746-4610 to place your order.

topReview.highlightedText: It was a great food

name: El Jefe
description:
Our menu is inspired by the Mexican regions of Yucatán, Oaxaca, and Veracruz. We strive to respect the influences and traditions of these diverse cultures to bring you food that is uniquely El Jefe.

We believe in doing things the right way. Not because it’s trendy or cool, but because it’s right. We change our menu with the grow season, supporting our neighbors and the terroir of Colorado. We are not your average Mexican joint, rather a reflection of our environment and beliefs.

We hand make our tortillas every day. All of our pork comes from one whole hog. Our chefs breakdown the whole animal, for chorizo, appetizers, stocks, soups, and entrees. Nothing is wasted. We do this out of respect for the animal and for the people who raised them for us. Anything we can produce in our kitchen is done by us, with love. No frills, just good food.

We do an amazing brunch on the weekends, and by default or menu is nearly 100% gluten free.

topReview.highlightedText: Delicious food, great service, fun atmosphere. Will definitely visit here again.

name: One Barrel - American Bistro & Wine Bar
description:
One Barrel has prepared intriguing gourmet dinner menus that will delight foodies as well as those of you who just love good-tasting food. We're confident you wont get bored with our selections; we will be serving a rotating seasonal menu with daily specials. The One Barrel standards will allow nothing less than fresh, high-quality offerings, including Colorado ingredients as much as possible.

Due to Covid-19 we will do our best to have all we can in stock but our menu will be limited and on first come first serve. We are taking safety precautions very seriously and asks all our guests to do the same. We're now open for brunch on the weekends, lunch, happy hour and dinner. We are thrilled to be back open and we can't wait to see everyone's smiling faces!

topReview.highlightedText: Had the chicken schnitzel and it was great! Great service and fun bar atmosphere. We’ll be back.

name: Benzina
description: Local neighborhood Italian restaurant serving seasonal salads, family-style appetizers, Neapolitan-inspired pizza, handmade pastas, entrees prepared on a Mibrasa Charcoal Oven, and classic desserts, alongside complementing cocktails, local breweries and approachable domestic and international wines. The restaurant is set in a converted gas station with bocce courts and urban planters alongside an outdoor dining patio.

topReview.highlightedText:
Love this place! Great food, service and ambiance. The pate is to die for, beautiful salads, and a mushroom pizza that is out of this world. Nice wine list  and I love the smaller menu, makes decisions so much easier! 
The service is delightful, so nice to see happy, friendly faces. 
Can't wait to return, we had a wonderful time!

name: Sushi Hai
description:
Like the Highland neighborhood we call home, Sushi Hai is refined, with a funky bite to its elegance. Modern with a Japanese flair, and filled with exceptional art created in the neighborhood, this restaurant has a unique style and provides three floors of seating - and every table feels special. We also offer three private Tatami Rooms, which accommodate 8 to 10 diners in traditional Japanese floor-seating.


We at Sushi Hai welcome you to come indulge your senses.

topReview.highlightedText: We’ve been coming here for about two years and every time it’s better. Highly recommend!

name: Undici Ristorante
description: Updated Italian classics in contemporary surroundings. Old-school elegance, including table linens, sets the stage for Italian classics, cocktails & wines.  Bring your friends, family & co-workers to enjoy a great meal & reconnect. Full bar-Banquet room-Extensive wine selection-Happy Hour 3-6

topReview.highlightedText: The food is absolutely delicious!  The service is spectacular!!  Such a great place!!

name: Brazen Neighborhood Eatery
description:
Brazen Neighborhood Eatery began in 2014, and it has been providing the West Highland area of Denver with high-quality, delicious food. The restaurant offers dinner each night and has brunch on the weekend. Brazen Neighborhood Eatery's outdoor dining is covered by umbrellas at each table and illuminated at night by elegant string lights.

Brazen Neighborhood Eatery has a number of interesting items on the menu. Owner and Chef, Christopher Sargent, brings you fresh oysters on the half shell, tomato braised meatballs, house-made pastas, and rotating large dishes. Some of the items on the brunch menu include the Brazen burger, Brazen ramen and the Chilaquiles.

topReview.highlightedText: The food was fresh, unique and tasty. Our waitperson, JT was exceptional. We’ll be back.

name: Gattara
description:
Uptown’s Italian-American eatery

Executive Chef Thomas Newsted leads an inventive and community-focused team, dedicated to fresh food with will satiate any palate. Gattara’s cuisine features traditional Italian flavors combined with delicious, local ingredients. Enjoy our creative Napolitano-style, house-made pizzas, cooked in front of you in our copper oven in as little as 90 seconds. An expansive cocktail menu showcases Italian-influenced cocktails with feline-inspired names. Relax al fresco on our shady patio, or dine in our playfully mod interior. Gattara is now open for business and is purring with excitement

topReview.highlightedText: Not what you'd expect for a restaurant in a hotel. Stellar Italian food (we had some pizzas) and very kind, helpful servers. Burrata salad was especially delicious. Dessert was the only average part about it. Would definitely recommend this place.

name: The Preservery
description: Open for dine-in! The Preservery aims to build community through great food, music and good old fashioned fun. Located in the beautifully restored warehouse in the Backyard on Blake complex, this restaurant and bar features classic American comfort food with a focus on scratch made, great ingredients and preservation traditions.

topReview.highlightedText: Food and cocktails were pretty good. Loved the ambiance as well.

name: X BAR Denver & Saffron Grill
description: Combining fresh made Mediterranean inspired food and American bar.

topReview.highlightedText: Amazing time and amazing food! Overall great experience!

name: Necio Mexican Kitchen
description: NECIO Mexican Kitchen is inspired by authentic Mexican cuisine from some of the best traditional places in South, central, and Nothern Mexico. Blending flavors to keep those traditions alive is what we are passionate about, and being able to serve our guests with quality dishes that bring the Mexican experience alive. Make yourself at home, unwind, and be prepared to be amazed with Mexican cuisine as never before!

topReview.highlightedText: Best salsa and drinks

name: Kingas Lounge
description:
Here is your best pick for Polish food in Denver! Kinga’s Lounge atmosphere is what makes this Capitol Hill spot special. There’s large plates of Pierogi and Kielbasa sausage, stuffed cabbage rolls and hunter’s stew to satisfy, plus sweet Cheese blintzes to finish off a traditional meal.
***
Humble look from the outside. But walk in and there’s a full bar across from a handful of booths to help grab a cold one to help eat plate after plate.
***
Also featuring long-lasting favorites: Zywiec, Perla & Warka Beers. Zubrowka, Zolodkowa Gorzka & Luksusowa vodka aperitifs and craft cocktails, as well as 30+ organic infused vodka flavors to choose from!

// BRUNCH HOURS: Saturday and Sunday 11am - 3pm
We offer one of the most exciting Brunch experiences in Denver, serving ALL YOU CAN EAT PIEROGI, Bottomless Mimosa and House Infused Bloody Mary and farmhouse plates specials!
Enjoy dining in or our outdoor patio areas:
Our Happy Hour is 7 days a week:
Mon - Fri 4pm - 7 pm
Sat - Sun 3pm - 6 pm

topReview.highlightedText: The service was amazing! She accommodated our ever need. It was not too crowded. The drinks, and prices are reasonable too!!

name: Millers and Rossi
description:
Located in the heart of Denver’s blossoming RiNo Arts District, Millers and Rossi Cocktail Lounge, is a must see destination for anyone who is looking for something a bit out of the ordinary. A unique experience, unlike any other.

Enter through the Ohana Room, our new Tiki Bar. When you’re ready, you’ll slip behind our exotic plant wall and into an extravagant lounge where amazing craft cocktails, our very own Chef’s elegant small plates and adventure awaits you!

Whether you're looking for a private event venue, romantic date night or a unique experience with some friends out on the town, Millers and Rossi is the perfect place to entertain. We'll see you soon.

topReview.highlightedText: We had the charcuterie board. It was very good... It had various berries, nuts, cheeses and meats. The drinks were delicious as well. What we loved most was the chill vibe.

name: Piatti - Denver
description: Hey Denver! We are excited to announce we are OPEN for dine-in! We are taking all  precautions to ensure the safety for our staff as well as each guest who walks into our establishment. We are in compliance with the Colorado Restaurant Association & Public Health and Environment. At this time, we are taking reservations parties of 8-10 people.  For parties larger than 10, please call the restaurant.  For all other sized parties, we are taking walk-ins on a first come, first served basis.   Located in a casual neighborhood, this warm laid back eatery knows its way around authentic regional Italian cuisine. The service is friendly, food is fresh, and the experience is Unbeatable!

topReview.highlightedText: I went there for my birthday. The hostess was very sweet and accommodating to my group. The food was good and the atmosphere was nice too.

name: Bar Red
description: Bar Red is located just east of Colfax and Glenarm, two blocks from the Colorado Convention Center and directly across Colfax from the Golden Triangle. Bar Red offers Authentic Italian cuisine. Happy hour from 4pm-7pm and dinner from 5pm to close. The menu was prepared by Chef Luke McCoy. Chef Luke is classically trained in French and Italian Cuisine. Chef Luke's signature Seared Salmon Risotto is famous amongst regulars. All of Chef Luke's dishes are meticulously prepared with fresh scratch ingredients ...and his house-made Desserts are to die for. The menu changes weekly with many mainstay dishes to please all foodies. Bar Red also features occasional live music and there is never a cover charge. A semi-private lounge room is also available for large parties. The room has customizable seating and includes a working fireplace to complete the romantic, comfortable setting.

topReview.highlightedText: Our Italian dinner was delicious. The music was great and the service was the best. The owner made time to visit with us at our table. We had a wonderful evening!

name: Slaters 50/50 - Denver
description: We’re passionate about burgers, bacon and beer. Known for burgers, bacon and beer, and famed for our 50/50 patty consisting of 50% ground bacon and 50% ground beef. You can find us on the ground floor of The Hub in Denver’s River North Art District. But don’t worry, we offer something for everyone, including salads, healthy bowls, flatbreads, wings, shakes and more.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent spot, great burgers, Lebowski-inspired decor, friendly staff and tasty drinks! Highly recommend.

name: Ironton Distillery & Crafthouse
description:
**With current Denver Covid Restrictions, we are currently only open for outdoor and partial indoor dining, with limited bar service, limited food and cocktail menus. We also have to go food, cocktails, spirits, gift cards, and merch. Thank you!**

From the mountains to the city, there’s an undeniable spirit of adventure that runs through the state of Colorado. Our goal is to capture it with the best ingredients, flavors and experiences this great state has to offer. And just like Colorado, there’s always more to taste, discover and explore. We invite you to do just that at Ironton Distillery and Crafthouse.

topReview.highlightedText: super cool ambiance, food that accommodates my allergies--and with fresh, flavorful ingredients. And, their Rye Whiskey is very good!

name: Little India Restaurant & Bar
description: Catering is a critical component of your event, so we take the same care with our catered meals as we do in our restaurant. Serving the highest quality of food and providing superior service, each dish uses the freshest ingredients and spices imported exclusively from India. Custom equipment made to our specifications ensures we deliver the honest flavors of India and remain faithful to the family recipes handed down for generations. Since 1998, Little India has been serving authentic Indian food in the Denver Metro Area and our chefs, who began their careers in Northern India, have mastered the art of preparing classic Indian cuisine. Residents have voted the Baidwan family’s Little India Restaurant & Bar the Best Indian Restaurant and Best Lunch Buffet for 16 years in a row.

topReview.highlightedText: The lamb vindaloo and the chicken tikka were delicious. We loved the cosmos too. Great service.

name: Serene Cuisine of India
description:
WELCOME TO SERENE CUISINE OF INDIA
DENVER’S NEWEST AUTHENTIC INDIAN RESTAURANT.

At Serene Cuisine of India, we serve Denver diners with a dazzling array of Indian dishes prepared in traditional methods honed over the centuries.

Traditional Indian food almost always uses fresh ingredients and involves making dishes from scratch, which means fewer preservatives and overall healthier food. Indian cooking uses spices like turmeric, ginger, garlic, and green chilies – all of which have medicinal and healing properties. So in addition to being “spicy”, the spices used are actually good for the body and don’t just taste nice.

topReview.highlightedText: We had a lovely dinner of chicken korma, palak paneer, chicken tikka masala and naan. They were all very good and we definitely had leftovers with the 3 dishes. It was a nice place to meet a friend to catch up.

name: Ironworks/Mile High Station
description:
Mile High Station and Ironworks are teaming up with local non-profits and invite you to get out and join us for Mile High Fall Series Supporting LOCAL Bands Under the lights. We will be hosting the fall series inside the Mile High Station located at 2027 W. Colfax Ave, which has 16,000 square feet of space. We have our tables socially distanced, our masks on, our sanitizer ready and cocktail servers ready to serve you! We appreciate any support during this devastating year of 2020.

Our concert series will be running Thursday's & Friday's in October & November. Please check our calendar and bands at milehighsummerseries.com. Door open at 6 p.m., music begins at 6:30 p.m.

We will have drinks specials offered all night and a Food Truck.

We appreciate the support during this very difficult year!!!!

We can't wait to see you and don't forget to wear your mask!

Please support local bands & businesses during this time.

topReview.highlightedText: The outdoor music series was lovely last week. The food trucks and drinks were great. Service was attentive and kind. I'll probably bring a blanket for next time!

name: Barbed Wire Reef
description:
We are a local, award winning food truck that has been a staple in Denver since 2011. After growing our brand from just a pick-up truck and a trailer to 3 food trucks, we opened a restaurant to serve our ever-growing fans and followers.

Our concept specializes in serving wild game and seafood in a fun, casual and comfortable setting. We are a full-service restaurant with a scratch kitchen and pride ourselves in providing great tasting food without a fuss!

We offer a full bar with focus on local breweries and craft cocktails.
Come see us ~ It's guaranteed to be a wild time!

topReview.highlightedText: Great drinks, delicious food and wonderful service.  We love BWR and can't wait to go back.  The prickly pear margarita and chicken tacos were particularly on point for our visit.

name: Little India Restaurant - 6th Ave
description:
Little India on 6th Avenue is a popular Indian restaurant with unique specialties and cocktails. To the delight of hungry patrons, the open kitchen allows the scents of the food being cooked to waft through the dining room. Little India is the definition of a local favorite, having been voted "Best Lunch Buffet" and "Best Restaurant" by local publications that polled both critics and patrons. It also offers takeout and delivery if diners can't come in and sit down.

Little India's award-winning lunch buffet is the perfect opportunity for guests to come in and try a little bit of everything on the menu. Specialties include items baked in the clay oven (tandoori) and several made-from-scratch curry dishes. Little India's desserts are also made fresh, including the bright and tangy mango custard.

topReview.highlightedText: The food was excellent and the service was outstanding. Can’t say enough good things about our server. He was top notch. The tandoori items were a bit dried out but very tasty. Next time we’ll stick with the curries and masalas. Naan was to die for.

name: Ponti Restaurant at Denver Art Museum
description: Welcome to Ponti Restaurant at Denver Art Museum!

name: Angelo's Taverna
description:
AS OF APRIL 4th 2021, THE GREENHOUSES ARE NO LONGER AVAILABLE. WE DO NOT ACCEPT RESERVATIONS. YOU MAY CALL THE RESTAURANT DIRECTLY TO BE ADDED TO OUR LIMITED PRIORITY LIST FOR INDOOR OR PATIO SEATING. 303-744-3366
Angelo's Taverna is Denver's original pizza and oyster bar! We are located in the Capital Hill area of Denver, Colorado. We have been serving the Denver area for over 40 years with homemade pastas, made from scratch pizzas and the freshest oysters in Denver!
MAXIMUM PARTY SIZE IS 10 GUESTS.

topReview.highlightedText: Everything was great! We sat in the greenhouse and that was a really fun experience!

name: Anise - Modern Vietnamese Eatery
description: Anise is a full-service Modern Vietnamese Eatery that is also a fun place to spend time with friends… or meet new ones. Our tag line is “Fresh, Healthy, Fun!” Anise is a fun eatery that happens to be perfectly situated in a historic but artistic area of Denver.

topReview.highlightedText: We've eaten at Anise a couple of times and have found our new favorite Vietnamese! The food is outstanding. The service is great. The owner greets us every time we come. And, as a family with several dietary restrictions, Anise is great about marking what's gluten free or can be made that way. Even though they're not super close to our house, I'm sure we'll become regulars at Anise.

name: Stoney's Bar & Grill
description: We are a locally owned, Colorado themed, sports & music bar in downtown Denver located in the heart of the city.

name: Los Chingones
description:
Hi there! Wanted to circle back and let you that Los Chingones RiNo is open for carryout, delivery, indoor and outdoor seating! Our outdoor seating hours will be from 12PM - 9 PM, Sunday, Wednesday and Thursday. 12PM -10 PM, Friday and Saturday. Understand that seating may be limited and we will do our best to get you in! You can view the menu and place your order at https://www.loschingonesmexican.com/online-ordering/ or stop by the patio (with mask please) and place an order in person.
To learn about our social distancing protocol and COVID-19 playbook, please visit loschingonesmexican.com

LOS CHINGONES, is Chef Owner Troy Guard’s Mexican concept. The space features a 90- seat rooftop bar and open main floor dining room, serving bold, flavorful, Guard-style twists on tapas style Mexican favorites. Los Chingones serves lunch and dinner Monday through Sunday.

topReview.highlightedText:
Was a little weird at first.  All the menus are accessible from your phone.  Social distancing at it best.  Place is usually packed but there was no on to my left or right.  Botha are all spaced and the sitting outside was the same.   

The good. 
Food was amazing.  Had a rosé and milagro magdrit

name: Saffron Grill in LoHi
description:
At Saffron Grill we believe that food is so much more than just fuel. Food is about bringing people together. We believe no one is ever alone in the kitchen. We bring generations to the table for every meal: Grandmothers, grandfathers, fathers, mothers, daughters, and sons.
Food is never just food. It is a door to learning so much more: who we are presently, who we once were in the past, and who we want to be in the future.
That is why each and every dish is prepared with the same ingredients that my mother and her mother before her used. All of our recipes are homemade with fresh vegetables and top quality spices.
We hope you can join us and enjoy our food, culture, and the people you surround yourself with!

name: Former Saint Craft Kitchen and Taps
description: Steps from the Colorado Convention Center and the Denver Theater District is the new Former Saint Craft Kitchen and Taps. Here Former Saint chefs tempt with adventuresome, Colorado tastes and experiences, giving a nod to the bond shared by food and spirits. Copper piping from a glass enclosed keg room draws local craft beer on tap to the center, focal-point bar, back dropped by a Denver Urban meets Colorado Wild locally inspired 16 foot mural. Serving morning, noon, night and spirits daily.

topReview.highlightedText: Food was great, wine was great. Service was sub par. Our waiter was super nice but seemed like she might of been new. Could of played the music a little louder, couldn't tell if the restaurant was modern social place or more of a quite intimate place. Would recommend though.

name: The Delectable Egg
description: Since 1982, Delectable Egg has proudly served the greater metro-Denver area. We strive to offer our guests a unique and memorable dining experience. Here at Delectable Egg we use only the freshest ingredients as well as local products. The Court Place Delectable Egg offers Bloody Marys, Bellini's, and Bottomless Mimosas. The Court Place location also showcases local artwork which changes monthly. Check out our loyalty rewards programs that can earn you free meals and perks.

topReview.highlightedText: We had a large group of 10 and we're seated on time, although we were not allowed to order until our entire party was there. This made sense because they were extremely busy (Sunday morning brunch) so just a heads up. The service was great, all of our orders were correct even with a large group and the restaurant being super busy. The food was great, and the menu has TONS of options. We enjoyed the bottomless mimosas too and they were not stingy about bringing us more. Overall I'd definitely come back!

name: 3 Margaritas - Downtown Denver
description:
With 18 locations in Colorado, 3 Margaritas on 16th St. Mall is sure to be the next shining gem in our line of esteemed Mexican restaurants, serving you great authentic food and providing you
with the best service from our family to yours. From our delicious food to exotic margaritas, we assure the best quality of dining you will experience while visiting the heart of Mile High City. We invite you to visit 3 Margaritas on 16th St. Mall and experience a truly authentic, family operated Mexican restaurant.

With open arms while maintaining 6 feet apart, 3 Margaritas Downtown. Gracias, Amigos!

topReview.highlightedText: Great food and service.  Was able to reserve a table on the patio and felt safe and well cared for.

name: Himalayan Spice
description: We serve authentic Indian food with modern flare......

name: Fortune Wok to Table
description: Authentic Chinese in Cherry Creek. Fine Dining Thursday, Friday & Saturday evenings. Casual counter service during Lunch and Dinner the rest of the week.

topReview.highlightedText: Food and service were amazing!!! Definitely coming back when I’m in Denver! Best Hot & Sour soup I’ve ever had.

name: YumCha
description: Coming Soon!

name: Stoney's Uptown Joint
description:
**We are not using Open Table for reservations at this time! All dine-in is first come first served.**

We are a locally owned, Colorado themed, sports & music bar in downtown Denver located in the heart of the city.

name: Hapa Sushi Grill & Sake Bar- Cherry Creek - Omakase
description:
Hapa Sushi's Omakase Experience is a multi course meal, curated by our executive sushi chef uniquely for your meal. A masterpiece of small courses will arrive at your table during your 2 hour experience. Our chef will prepare plates tableside when possible. Courses will be chosen for their freshness, flavor, uniqueness and beauty. An experience not to be missed.

$150/person
An optional sake pairing can be added for an additional $50.
Deposit Required.
no substitutions. no special requests. no modifications.

name: Little India Restaurant - Wash Park/DU
description:
Little India Restaurant in Denver has been providing quality Indian food to this area of Colorado since 1998 when the Baidwan and Malhotra families came together and started the establishment. Little India Restaurant has proven to be a very popular choice with residents of the area due to the quality of the items on the menu.



Options from Little India Restaurant that are popular include the coconut shrimp, momo dumplings and calamari fried in chickpea butter. Entrées include the chicken ginger kabob, tandoori chicken, lamb chops, shrimp tandoori and fish tandoori. The restaurant has nice ambiance, and it delivers for those who want to stay home.

topReview.highlightedText: The ambiance is incredible. They had wonderful live music there. We went on a Friday and it wasn’t too crowded, but still lively. We also went for Denver Restaurant Week and their offering was incredible. Large portions and amazing flavor.

name: The District
description:
*Serving food until 9pm and the Bar is open until 10pm*
Our mission is to provide everyone a memorable experience with great service, quality food and drink choices in a welcoming, fun atmosphere!
The District masterfully creates an eclectic take on American cuisine from smokehouse BBQ and fresh salad entrees to chef inspired dinner specials, and brunch 7 days a week, there is something to entice your appetite. 
Started by Denver natives, we have partnered with dozens of local breweries, Distilleries, Colorado farms and Denver's iconic Little Man ice cream to bring together the best of what Colorado has to offer.
Come experience the comfort and ambiance of the neighborhood most inviting space with exposed brick and beam architecture, local artist installations, creative mood lighting, great music and roll up garage doors connecting it all to our welcoming outdoor patio.
Adding a fresh vibe of DELICIOUSNESS to Denver’s Restaurant Row, The District aims to satisfy customer’s cravings by combining the perfection of flavors and ambiance. Stop on by!

topReview.highlightedText: Nice local place. Would go back when in Denver.

name: The Broken Cage
description: The Broken Cage is an opportunity to disconnect and enjoy sophisticated cocktails & conversation in a quaint and intimate environment.  Our mixologists use fresh, local and unique ingredients when crafting cocktails. Pick something off our extensive signature cocktail and sparkling libations menus or allow our mixologists to craft something bespoke to your taste.  We've got a full selection of wines, craft beers & spirits.  When visiting be sure to seek out our hidden package store.

topReview.highlightedText: The ambience was great, we had the best vodka blue cheese vodka martini ever.  Will definitely go back.

name: Gerard’s Pool Hall
description: Homage to the rich history of Rocky Mountain cue sport and cocktails, located in the heart of River North.

topReview.highlightedText: Great Sunday morning event with friends and family.

name: Sushi Rama-RiNo
description: We are open daily from 11am - 8pm offering dine-in, take out and delivery through ChowNow.

topReview.highlightedText: I was really impressed by the food and the efficiency of the staff. There was a large variety of sushi at four different price ranges and they were all delicious.

name: Osaka Ramen- RiNo
description: We are open Monday - Thursday 11am -8 pm, Friday 11am -  9pm, Saturday 12 noon - 9pm, Sunday 12 noon - 8pm for dine-in, take out and delivery through ChowNow.

topReview.highlightedText: I always love Osaka, either for dining in or to go on a cold night. Their ramen is tasty and their menu is simple. I like really spicy ramen, so this is my go-to place. If you're looking for an appetizer, try the green beans or tofu.

name: TAG / Burger and Bar at Madison Street
description: TAG BURGER BAR features gourmet burgers and a lengthy beer list from local breweries, all in a cozy neighborhood setting.

topReview.highlightedText: Food as always was great - we ate at the bar and the bartender was great

name: Avanti Food and Beverage
description: Welcome to Avanti food and beverage! We are currently not taking any online reservations. If you have a reservation in place already, we will still honor it. Otherwise, come on in and get seated. Groups up to 8 people are allowed and masks are required. See you soon!

topReview.highlightedText: Love Avanti! We went mid day, during the week and it was pretty quiet but they had everything set up for COVID, so we felt really comfortable being there. The food and drinks were great and the atmosphere was really nice.

name: Red Lobster - Lakewood - Wadsworth Blvd.
description: Red Lobster welcomes you by offering PRIORITY SEATING to reduce your wait time in the restaurant, so you can spend more time doing the things you love. Or, come enjoy a drink at our bar and a Tasting Plate while you wait. Red Lobster is the world's largest and most loved seafood restaurant company, offering high quality, freshly-prepared seafood, sourced in a way that is traceable, sustainable and responsible. We offer lunch and dinner daily, featuring classics like our Ultimate Feast®, Garlic Shrimp Scampi and Parrot Isle Jumbo Coconut Shrimp, and feature limited time flavors and preparations during events like Lobsterfest®, Crabfest® and Endless Shrimp®. And, who can resist our famous warm and cheesy Cheddar Bay Biscuits®? To learn more visit www.redlobster.com

topReview.highlightedText: Dezi was an amazing waitress!  Food was delicious and they are following COVID protocol

name: There-Denver
description: Globally inspired dishes & clever cocktails abound at this watering hole with a bohemian vibe.

name: Mister Tuna
description:
A neighborhood sanctuary by Chef Troy Guard and the TAG Restaurant Group in The INDUSTRY Building off Brighton Blvd **COMPLIMENTARY PARKING** Please park in the garage off of 29th and bring your ticket to host stand for validation.

Mister Tuna, a nod to the nickname of Chef Guard's father, evokes the feeling of a family with shareable dishes cooked over an open wood fire. Whether grabbing a craft cocktail at the bar, digging in to fresh oysters and poke at the chef's counter or hosting dinner with Ohana in the main dining room, Mister Tuna offers a culinary variety fit for every palate in an urban setting.

topReview.highlightedText: This experience was an amazing concept. The menu was a delicious variety. And our server was extremely pleasant.  Chef Troy is a gem!

name: Inga's Alpine Lounge
description:
Ingas Alpine Tavern, in Denver, serves phenomenally comforting cuisine crafted with global inspiration in its contemporary and vibrant eatery. The crinkle cut French fries topped with bacon bits and white cheese queso and the creamy house made spinach and artichoke dip served with veggies and bread make excellent appetizers. Some of Ingas Alpine Taverns specialty entres include the Bavarian plate with Buffalo jalapeno cheddar sausages served with a soft pretzel, beer cheese and mustard, the coconut curry mussels and the Rat Pack pizza topped with pepperoni, sausage, green peppers and red onions and mozzarella cheese, are delicious and show the versatility of the menu. More causal fare, like dressed-up fries and chicken wings, as well as sandwiches, are also popular choices.

Beer cocktails, such as the Elektra king with Pabst Blue Ribbon and pickle-infused vodka, are an Ingas Alpine Tavern specialty that goes well with your meal.

topReview.highlightedText: Great little old school bar with excellent pub food. We just had snacks and drinks, but everything we ordered was excellent. There's nothing fancy at all about this place, and that's what makes it so charming. They have a nice patio.

name: The Lumber Baron Inn and Gardens
description: The Lumber Baron Inn is an elegant bed and breakfast in a Victorian era mansion located in the Potter Highlands district of Denver. We celebrate the Scottish heritage of the mansion and the neighborhood. We offer brunch Sunday, afternoon tea daily, prix fixe dinner Friday and Saturday and several types of social functions including wine, beer, spirits dinners and holiday events. We are available to book private functions for social and business groups

topReview.highlightedText: This place is a hidden gem in the local neighborhood it represents.  I LOVE Scottish breakfast dishes and their oatmeal pancakes are right on point.  Could they publish the recipe for that dish?

name: P.F. Chang's - Lakewood
description: P.F. Chang's is a restaurant concept that honors the 2,000-year-old Asian tradition of wok cooking and believes in making food from scratch every day in every restaurant. With a Farm to Wok™ food philosophy at its core, P.F. Chang's chefs hand-roll dim sum, hand chop and slice all vegetables and meats, handcraft every sauce and wok-cook each recipe, every day in every restaurant using wholesome, fresh ingredients. With roots in Chinese cooking, the culinary landscape at P.F. Chang's now stretches across Asia with diverse, culturally inspired recipes including hand-rolled sushi, Vietnamese-style soups and bowls, traditional Chinese dim sum, wok-fired chicken and beef entrées, and family style noodles and rice. All made from scratch every day.

topReview.highlightedText: A great dinner with excellent service! Exactly what we have come to expect from P.F. Chang’s. Thank you!!

name: Spice Room | Neighbourhood Indian Bistro
description: The Spice Room, established by few Friends in July 2017.  Began its story as a small vegan, vegetarian, and gluten-free options restaurant.  Mr Joshi’s commitment to his family recipes, his integrity with produce and his masterful art of blending spices attracted curry addicts from everywhere.

topReview.highlightedText: Took my mom here for an early dinner and we had the buffet. It was delicious and we definitely had our Indian Food fix! The owner was so nice and welcoming. Great place!

name: Jett Sushi
description: Offering the finest selection of Japanese favorites, Jett Sushi is where friends and family gather to enjoy truly authentic Asian cuisine. Fresh, flavorful, and vibrantly presented, our sushi rolls are delicious and creative, and our Japanese steaks and ramen bowls are irresistible. With a full bar available and an elegant atmosphere for enjoying your meal, we're the perfect spot to enjoy a date night, family dinner, or happy hour drink with friends. If you can't make it in for a meal, we make bringing Jett to your home simple with online ordering and delivery available for your convenience.

topReview.highlightedText: Our meals tonight were as delicious as every other time. Carefully prepared and presented. We dining tonight with a party of 6 an were attentively cared for  and when our server realized one of the people in our party was waiting for their sushi after other meals had been served, he quickly brought her a soup on the house so she wasn't the only one waiting while we dug into our individually and deliciously prepared meals. I would recommend this place for everything from a last minute night out to a planned event. We will definitely be back sooner than later!

name: Africana Restaurant & Cafe
description:
Since 1980, Africana Restaurant has been a destination for authentic Ethiopian food in the Denver Metro area. Our menu features a wide variety of unique flavorful dishes, including many vegetarian options.

We have a full bar with a daily Happy Hour specials with plenty of local drinks and imports of Ethiopian drinks. Check our Events page often to find out when your favorite local band or DJ is going to be featured on our stage. Feel free to move check us out daily should the mood strike.

Just here for the delicious food? Our restaurant is one of the top picks for authentic Ethiopian dishes; so you can enjoy a peaceful meal.

name: Vital Root
description: Vital Root is committed to keeping it real. Real ingredients. Real food. Real passion. People’s food preferences have evolved. They want alternative choices. They want healthier options. They want fun, lively, flavorful ingredients. They want a mind body connection. They don’t want limits. And they want to be inspired. Vital Root is one answer to the omnivore’s dilemma.

topReview.highlightedText:
Perfect for those of us who like Raw and vegan foods - they fully accommodated my food allergies and my daughters 
- we look forward to the final Raw Monday next month (unless we can convince the Chef to do one more month!!!!!!!)

name: Cafe Terracotta
description: Cafe Terracotta is located in the historic Louthan House, just off Main Street in Downtown Littleton. From our Curtice Street Breakfast Burrito, to our Lucille's Mediterranean Salad, Terracotta offers something for all tastes. A hidden gem in the South Metro area, Dinner at Terracotta provides thoughtfully prepared and presented food, accompanied by a unique and creative wine list unlike any other restaurant in the area. Whether you are joining us for a special occasion, or just happen to be in the neighborhood, we aim to make every experience exceptional. Summertime opens our patio, a perfect place to relax and enjoy the beautiful Colorado weather.

topReview.highlightedText: We took some out of town friends here for breakfast! They loved it as much as we do!

name: Shanahan's Steakhouse
description:
Shanahan's is the modern interpretation of the classic steakhouse. From the museum appearance of its exterior to the European lighting design of the interior, the space has art features of glass, steel, stone and granite that provide a timeless ambiance. Comfortable booth banquette seating in our Lounge area is not available to book through the website. 



Shanahan's is a steak and seafood restaurant serving U.S.D.A prime aged Midwestern beef with a signature "Bone-In" cut selection that is not available at most steakhouses. Our seafood is all flown in fresh daily to ensure the highest quality and exceptional flavors. All fish are responsibly sourced from sustainable fisheries which mirror our commitment to the environment.

topReview.highlightedText: My wife and I were in Denver celebrating being newlyweds and we had an exceptional experience. The entire staff was amazing and the food was excellent. I had a New York Strip and she had the crab cake entree and they were cooked to perfection. We appreciate the service provided and will definitely visit again when we come back to town

name: Eddie V's - Greenwood Village
description:
OUR DINING ROOM IS OPEN. CURBSIDE PICKUP ALSO AVAILABLE – We are pleased to open our doors, but delighted to still offer takeout. Please call (720) 826-7488 to make your reservation.

Join us at Eddie V's in Greenwood Village, CO for a stylish and sophisticated fine dining experience. Choose from a varied selection of prime seafood from pristine waters around the world, or indulge in our critically acclaimed center-cut steaks. Complement your dinner with a selection from our wine menu – an award-winning list of over 300 wines curated by our sommelier. Whatever the occasion, from a weeknight dinner to a special private event, let us handle every detail. We'll do the work. You bask in the glory.

Polite Dress Notice - To promote a family friendly and welcoming atmosphere for everyone. We consider gym attire, sweatpants, hats, clothing with offensive languages or images, and exposed undergarments too casual for our restaurants.

topReview.highlightedText: Outstanding !  Beautiful restaurant. Excellent service. First visit and many more to come

name: Ocean Prime Greenwood Village - Denver Tech Center
description:
Ocean Prime is a nationally acclaimed, modern American restaurant & lounge from the award-winning Cameron Mitchell Restaurants. There is a warm & vibrant energy, stunning settings, an impressive menu of seafood & steaks, and genuine hospitality making Ocean Prime the ideal place to socialize, talk business, celebrate & indulge. Made from scratch dishes showcase simple, pure & regional flavors. Our menu features an array of appetizers, salads, seafood, steaks, sides, house-made desserts & handcrafted cocktails.
Located in the heart of Denver Tech Center, OP features a vibrant outdoor terrace & 4 private dining rooms. OP is open weekdays for lunch & nightly for dinner.
We are proud to announce our new, state-of-the-art Air Filtration and Air Purification system has been installed in our restaurant. Our NEW iWave Air Purification system, along with MERV Filters, will eliminate 99.4% of all airborne pathogens, including viruses and COVID-19, maki

topReview.highlightedText: The place is excellent overall.  Servers are well trained.  Food is really good, but somewhat over priced.   If you all improved the cost value some. I think you would be rewarded.  Nice job!

name: Cafe Mercato
description:
Café Mercato, located in Denver, is a brand-new modern Italian restaurant, owned and operated by Giancarlo Macchiarella of Locanda del Borgo

Mercato’s light and airy atmosphere and design permeates throughout the modern space. With a large open kitchen and large wine “library”, you will feel right at home sipping on a glass of select wine while watching the chefs create your meal.

The menu at Café Mercato is based on Southern Italian fare with a lighter approach. All of the pastas and sausages are made in-house, as well as gelato and desserts. Enjoy homemade pizza from our over imported from Italy and other selections from our wood-fire grill. Come visit us with your family and friends for our “family-style” specials, happy hour, or a satisfying Sunday Brunch. Bon appétit!

topReview.highlightedText: a friend asked to have spaghetti instead of potatoes and was told no alternatives allowed.  This seemed odd, disappointing and unprofessional.  Certainly the the cost for these two items seems comparable

name: Simms Steakhouse
description: Enjoy our award-winning menu as you marvel at the breathtaking views of Denver. Our renowned chefs have created a menu from the finest ingredients available. Succulent steaks, fresh seafood, and decadent desserts - there's something for everyone at Simms Steakhouse.

topReview.highlightedText: We planned a birthday dinner for two. I always forget to take pics when we go out for special occasions so I asked the restaurant to remind me! They did! We had a perfect dinner with a gorgeous view and the ambiance was fabulous!  The food was delicious and we started with the bacon app, then had our bread, French Onion soup was delightful and the Lobster bisque was scrumptious. We had steaks, a 10oz filet mignon and a Buffalo Ribeye!  Both were cooked to perfection! I order medium rare which most places have a hard time achieving! Not Simm’s! The crustiness on the outside of the steak and that red juiciness exploded with flavor! The Buffalo Buffalo Ribeye was cooked medium and was tender, moist and delectable. The su gratin potatoes were flavorful and well the green beans were crisp and tasty! Now the service….Edward gets 6 stars! He was truly spectacular! Before we could think of what we wanted he seemed to know! He made our experience at SIMM’s Steakhouse an extremely memorable one! By the way if you’re a wine drinker the Austin Hope Cabernet is a wonderful wine suggested by Edward! He knows his stuff! Thank you again for a wonderful meal and entertaining conversation!

name: Vin Rouge Wine Bar & Tasting Room
description:
Welcome to Vin Rouge Wine Bar & Tasting Room! We specialize in boutique wines from around the globe, local craft beers, and must-have light fare staples like cheese, charcuterie, caviar, and chocolate in the comfort of our cozy neighborhood bar.
Due to current Covid-19 regulations, we are able to serve alcohol until 9:59pm.

topReview.highlightedText: Amazing wine, great conversation with the owners.

name: Le French
description:
Le French is a gourmet, casual-chic French bakery
and bistro located in Denver’s bourgeoning Belleview Station. Le French specializes in high-end pastries and elevated modern Parisian cuisine with global influences, a nod to the sisters’ heritage. Rougui – an award-winning and internationally-recognized chef – helms the restaurant’s kitchen as executive chef. Serving breakfast, lunch, and dinner every Tuesday through Sunday, Le French also offers an afternoon “Delightful Hour,” featuring carted tea service and small plates; a nightly dessert bar experience with after-dinner wines and classic French cocktails; and weekend brunch. The welcoming space features indoor and patio dining; a grab-and-go case with freshly made salads, sandwiches and pastries; and a carry-out counter. Le French is located at 4901 S. Newport St. in the Denver
Tech Center. For more information, visit lefrenchdenver.com.

topReview.highlightedText: Great birthday celebration with friends!!?

name: Ya Yas Euro Bistro - Denver
description: Ya Ya's not only caters to the casual diner but also includes room for business meetings and special occasions. Our menu changes daily to ensure the freshest seafood, best quality steaks and chops, and most exquisite entrees. With an award winning wine list and beautiful patio overlooking the park and water with fountains, Ya Ya's is the perfect place for all occasions.

topReview.highlightedText: Very pleasant as always

name: Hapa Sushi Grill & Sake Bar - Landmark in Greenwood Village
description: The name Hapa is derived from the Hawaiian term that describes a harmonious blend of Asian and American cultures.  Like our name, our food reflects this dynamic combination.  The menu is based on traditional Japanese cooking fundamentals which are then amplified, muted, or mixed with influences from many different styles of cooking until they are something completely new: they're Hapa. We have stretched the boundaries of creativity to develop dishes that defy all the rules while holding true to our roots.  We hope you will find our menu innovative, uninhibited, and distinctly fun!

topReview.highlightedText: Great place for a date, friends meet up or business lunch. Menu has bowl lunch specials and sushi you can choose from! Always is tasty and I highly recommend!

name: Smokin' Fins Grill | Littleton
description: Welcome to Smokin' Fins Grill | Littleton!
