Smokin Fins is a regional restaurant concept featuring a unique menu that blends ocean-fresh seafood, sushi and house smoked specialties such as prime rib and slow smoked pork. Please note that we reserve a large portion of our restaurant for walk ins only, please contact us directly with any questions about availability.

topReview.highlightedText: It was awesome!  We will definitely be back!

name: Benihana - Denver, CO
description: Welcome to Benihana and a dining experience unlike any other! Our guests are seated at communal tables in groups, where your personal chef will perform the ancient art of Teppanyaki. Watch as we slice and dice, preparing a meal that will dazzle your eyes as well taste buds, whether you choose mouth-watering steak, tender chicken or succulent seafood. You can also enjoy sushi prepared by a talented sushi chef and indulge in a specialty cocktail. Benihana Denver is located in the newly-renovated Tamarac Square, just minutes west of I-25 off Hampden Blvd. It is close to Denver Tech Center and not far from world-class shopping at Cherry Creek Mall. Happy Hour is available each Monday through Friday from 4-7 p.m., featuring great cocktails and sushi, plus hot and cold appetizers starting at just $3.00.

topReview.highlightedText: Delicious food - chef was excellent - with reservation waited 55 minutes for the chef - he was on time - restaurant appeared short staffed - turned walk in’s away

name: Bistro Barbes
description: Please be aware that Bistro Barbes is only offering a 4 course Chef's tasting menu for $65 per person. Please contact us if there are any dietary restrictions or allergies because last minutes substitutions may not be available

topReview.highlightedText: This is the best experience in Denver. The food is outstanding! The tasting menu is the perfect amount of food and together with the wine pairings makes for an incredible dining experience.

name: Venice Ristorante
description: Venice Italian Restaurant is an upscale Italian restaurant in Greenwood Village that specializes in authentic Italian food in a Venetian Northern Italian Style. It is a neighborhood gem that is perfect for a night our with family, friends or coworkers.  We have beautiful private dining spaces that can host all styles of events, inquire within about our different banquet menu options. When you're looking for the best Italian restaurant in Greenwood Village, then reach out to Venice Italian Restaurant & Wine Bar today. We hope to see you soon!

topReview.highlightedText: Really great Italian food, excellent service, great restaurant, and a really good wine list.  I brought family from out of town and they loved it.  I really recommend this place and I will return again!

name: The Keg Steakhouse + Bar - Colorado Mills
description:
The Keg Steakhouse & Bar serves the finest cuts of succulent steak, aged for tenderness and grilled to perfection. Prime rib is a Keg specialty, slow roasted, hand carved and perfectly seasoned with special Keg spices. The restaurant also serves delicious seafood, memorable appetizers, crisp salads and decadent desserts. A casual ambiance and friendly, very knowledgeable staff are proud and reliable trademarks of The Keg Steakhouse & Bar. You'll find a truly comfortable and satisfying dining atmosphere accompanied by a fun and up-scale bar setting where guests can enjoy an excellent wine list, signature Keg martinis, and fresh squeezed juice cocktails.

Takeout From The Keg
If you'd rather enjoy around your own table, you can also place an order for takeout online and pickup curbside. Visit our website, or copy and paste this link: www.kegsteakhouse.com/en/takeout.

topReview.highlightedText: Food was terrific and service (Brooklin) was even better.

name: Texas de Brazil - Denver
description:
Texas de Brazil is no ordinary steakhouse. It’s a dining experience like no other.

Here, traditions of Brazilian cooking blend with Texas hospitality to create a lively atmosphere in an upscale setting. Your meal begins with a visit to our extravagant salad area where you can indulge in a wide array of seasonal roasted vegetables, fresh artisan breads, charcuterie, imported cheeses and other specialties.

Then enjoy the rodizio-style dining that has made us famous. An endless parade of gaucho servers visits your table with skewers of freshly grilled beef, lamb, pork, chicken and Brazilian sausage carved directly onto your plate. It’s all served with authentic side dishes of garlic mashed potatoes, Brazilian cheese bread and sweet fried bananas.

To complement your meal, select from our award-winning collection of wines or traditional Brazilian bar creations. And don’t forget to treat yourself to one of our decadent à la carte desserts.
General Manager
Davi da Silva

topReview.highlightedText: Delicious food, little pricey but totally worth  it.

name: Ruth's Chris Steak House - Denver Tech
description:
Now Open: We look forward to serving you soon.

This Ruth's Chris Steak House located in the Denver Tech, Greenwood Village suburb of Denver, Colorado serves the finest USDA Prime beef available, broiled at 1,800° and served on 500° plates, so your steak stays hot, juicy and delicious from first bite to last. Enjoy our New Orleans-inspired appetizers, USDA Prime steaks, fresh seafood, signature side dishes and homemade desserts. All this while you enjoy our warm, inviting atmosphere and Ruth’s Chris’ genuine hospitality. So whether you’re a regular or have just been wondering what all the buzz is about, Ruth's Chris is the perfect excuse to enjoy the perfect night out. Dinner is served nightly, reservations are suggested and private dining and offsite catering may be arranged.

topReview.highlightedText: My sons 37th birthday, he really enjoyed the meal and the waitress was phenomenal

name: Banzai Sushi
description:
We are open but only accepting reservations over the phone during covid -19.

An oasis of Japan in the heart of Denver, Colorado.
Banzai Sushi features the highest level of Japanese
cuisine crafted with a creative touch.



We're the home of "100 Rolls". Select from 100 sushi combinations ranging from the usual to the outrageous. There is a sushi roll here for
every taste. Or choose from our innovative lunch and dinner menus featuring fully cooked selections of fish, chicken or beef. All prepared in the time honored cooking traditions of Japan.

topReview.highlightedText: Just about as good as sushi gets in Denver, and less expensive than that much bigger place…. Very friendly too, they remember us when we come in!  Small place, clean and very nice.

name: ChoLon Modern Asian - Central Park
description: ChoLon, which translates to "big market,” is named after the largest Chinese-influenced market in Saigon, Vietnam. At ChoLon, Chef Lon Symensma brings to life his extensive culinary travels throughout Southeast Asia. ChoLon's menu features inspired interpretations of traditional dishes found across the region, with presentations ideal for sharing. From dim sum or "small bites" to large family style plates, ChoLon offers authentic flavors for the modern palate. The bar and lounge serves handcrafted, artisanal cocktails developed to complement Symensma’s cuisine. The venue is also ideal for business meetings, presentations, large parties and events. ChoLon’s professional staff will deliver top quality service and a memorable experience.

topReview.highlightedText: Really great, tasty food, love the homemade noodles and friendly staff!

name: Del Frisco's Double Eagle Steakhouse - Denver
description: Del Frisco’s Double Eagle Steakhouse embodies the rich tradition of the classic American steakhouse, serving USDA Prime Beef, fresh seafood and premium wines from our award-winning wine selection.

topReview.highlightedText: Oz was excellent with his menu recommendations!

name: Seasons 52 - Lone Tree
description:
OUR DINING ROOM IS OPEN. CURBSIDE PICKUP ALSO AVAILABLE. We are pleased to open our doors, but delighted to still offer takeout. See the menu at Seasons52.com. Please call (303) 799-0252 to make your reservation.

Seasons 52 is a comfortable and stylish fresh grill and wine bar offering a refreshingly balanced approach to food and wine where guests are free to enjoy, knowing any choice they make is one they'll feel good about. The menu changes with the season to feature ingredients at their peak, from whole produce that arrives and is kept 100% fresh, never frozen, to carefully sourced meats and pristine seafood. Entrées are oak-fire grilled or brick oven-roasted, without a fryer in sight, to be flavorful and naturally lighter. The Wine Bar pours world-class wines by the glass and signature cocktails. More at Seasons52.com

topReview.highlightedText: Always awesome!!!

name: Citron Bistro
description: A mix of rustic brick, hardwood floors and modern colors produce a relaxing dining atmosphere to enjoy world foods, with American, Mediterranean and Southwestern flavors. With dishes as Shrimp Nachos, Asian Lollipops, Oven Roasted Feta, Oregano-lemon crusted Lamb Chops, Paella, Cilantro rubbed Trout, Filet Mignon, Tequila Pasta, and our Signature Dessert Creme Brulee Napoleon. Denver's BEST HAPPY HOUR 4-6:30pm ALL WEEK LONG Featuring Delicious Food and Drinks at Great Prices in our bar and patio.

topReview.highlightedText: Excelent food and staff!

name: White Chocolate Grill - Park Meadows
description:
If your preferred reservation time is not available online, please make use of our call-ahead seating program as we may still be able to accommodate your originally requested time. Our outdoor-only seating is available at open-air tables with propane heaters adjacent to them. We no longer have any igloos as they have been destroyed by the weather and wear & tear.

The White Chocolate Grill offers an expansive menu of classic American fare; made from scratch using only the highest quality ingredients. A selection of house-made white chocolate and other desserts complement this offering. Happy Hour is first come first serve in limited tables at limited times.

topReview.highlightedText: Lovely as always

name: Chianti Ristorante
description: Chianti Italian Restaurant is a premium Italian restaurant in DTC (Denver Tech Center). With a small establishment focused on high quality cuisine matched with wine. Our Italian food and wine pairing options are on par with the best restaurants in Denver and the DTC area of Greenwood Village. Our Italian food menu is made to pair elite Italian food and wine to create an experience and ambiance that any guest can enjoy. We also offer delivery and take out. Book your next date night or special event with Chianti Ristorante Italiano.

topReview.highlightedText: We sat outdoors under a large canvas shelter in the parking lot; some how it worked as a wonderful outing.  Wait staff was very attentive, knowledgeable, and professional.  Food was excellent.  Wine pricing seamed a little high, not in line with the food pricing.  Recommend and will go again.

name: Perry’s Steakhouse & Grille - Park Meadows
description:
Located in the Park Meadows Retail Resort, Perry’s Park Meadows is bringing our award-winning menus, iconic signatures, tableside presentations and impeccable service to the Mile High City. Our spacious main dining room can host up to 175 guests, inviting all to join in the Perry’s experience complemented by our lively color palette with details of ravishing glass structures and a warm, inviting ambience that is unmatched in its design.

Perry’s open-kitchen concept allows guests to catch glimpses of chefs putting Perry’s twists on Steakhouse signatures, as guests dine amongst our two-story-high wine tower featuring Perry’s carefully-curated selection from vineyards around the world. Guests can join us in Bar 79 for glasses and bottles of these wines, or raise their glass with handcrafted cocktails on the outdoor patio as they soak up crisp mountain air, all while savoring our full menu.

topReview.highlightedText: Service and food were outstanding as usual.

name: Indulge Bistro & Wine Bar
description: Indulge Bistro & Wine Bar is locally owned and operated by long time Highlands Ranch residents.  We offer a unique and fun environment to meet friends and family and enjoy great food and drinks.  We have an extensive wine list and a full bar.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent good and service!

name: The Fort
description: Situated in the Red Rocks country 17 miles southwest of Denver on Hwy 285, The Fort is a true replica of Bent's Fort, (1833-1849), the first American fur trade post in Colorado. The Cheyenne, Arapahoe, Kiowa and Pawnee traded and intermarried at Bent's Old Fort, creating an economic and peaceful exchange of cultures in an otherwise violent West. The Fort building is on the National Registry of Historic Places, and celebrates the many cultures that traded at Bent's Old Fort. Our menu features "New Foods of the Old West" including the best cuts of buffalo, elk and quail, grilled to perfection. There are vegetarian options inspired by American Indian recipes including Corn Beans and Squash, known as the Three Sacred Sisters. The wine list is awarded the Wine Spectator each year, and the nine dining rooms, with intimate seating, has a  350 seat capacity, with real adobe "beehive "fireplaces that burn wood in the winter and fall months. Romantic. Amazing views of the Valley and Mountains!

topReview.highlightedText: Everything perfect!

name: Comida- Stanley
description: The Comida Cantina is an extension of our Comida Food Truck – located in Aurora (Comida at The Stanley Marketplace). Our Cantina is a full service, sit down, neighborhood joint serving the street food you’ve come to love and crave along with beautifully crafted cocktails, rotating locavore specials and a newsworthy Brunch specials on Saturdays and Sunday. And, just as we always have with the Food Truck, we’ve kept our prices modest while keeping the integrity of our ingredients and efforts high.

topReview.highlightedText: Best place for tacos!

name: La Sandia Stapleton
description:
Chef Richard Sandoval, internationally recognized as the Father of Modern Mexican Cuisine, elevates Mexican cooking to new heights at La Sandia. Inspired by his culinary mantra of ‘old ways, new hands,’ Chef Sandoval reinterprets traditional dishes with contemporary techniques and skillful presentation.

Guests will rediscover classics, such as taqueria-style tacos made with soft, corn tortillas and flavorful fillings such as chicken tinga and adobo marinated pork. Sophisticated dishes such as the Carne Asada and Salmon Adobado will expand visitors’ perception of Mexican cuisine.

With over 250 varieties, La Sandia’s Tequila Bar showcases the diversity of agave-based spirits. House infused Tequilas and Tequila flights are different ways to explore the collection. A menu of handcrafted, Latin cocktails includes Tropical Fruit Margaritas, Mojitos and Sangria. Guests will also enjoy La Sandia’s menu of Mexican beers and list of Latin wines.

topReview.highlightedText: The staff is great, the food could be a little better.

name: The Perfect Landing
description:
The Perfect Landing Restaurant is known as Denver's Hidden Gem Restaurant. At The Perfect Landing Restaurant you can enjoy delicious meals from breakfast to dinner. Steak and Seafood is the specialty here, but there is also a variety of comforting menu items to choose from. Get your meal started right with delectable starters, soups and salads.



Take in the picturesque view of Pikes Peak and Longs Peak just outside the restaurant's windows. Stop in on evenings and listen to the live music as you sip on a drink in our lounge and piano bar. When you're looking for a place to kick back and relax or rock the night away, you can't go wrong with the amazing food, extensive wine menu and live entertainment at The Perfect Landing.

topReview.highlightedText: As always, the experience was great. The service was a little less attentive than usual, but that could have been a result of being busy.

name: Eddie Merlot's Prime Aged Beef & Seafood - Englewood
description: Eddie Merlot's Prime-aged Beef and Seafood starts with U.S.D.A. Prime Beef and the freshest seafood. Eddie Merlot's has created one of the hottest concepts today; the wine bar provides more than 40 wines by the glass and a very extensive reserve wine collection by the bottle. The bar is stocked with all of the finest spirits and after dinner cordials and Cognacs. Eddie Merlot's boasts a contemporary but stunningly elegant interior design and atmosphere.

topReview.highlightedText: As always, Jenny was amazing!

name: Steuben's Arvada
description:
Classic cafe, modern diner, comfort food of the American regional variety, finest & truest self.

We want Steuben's to be a place for everybody. Everybody who appreciates a handcrafted cocktail, fresh Maine lobster in their lobster roll, hand-cut potatoes in their French fries, and ice cream churned in house. Families, friends, neighbors, and first-time visitors to Denver who are seeking out the comfort of a friendly atmosphere, a welcoming smile, and a breakfast, lunch, or dinner that will leave their hearts and tummies happy. Steuben's is a classic café...a modern diner...a place to be comfortable and relax. And when we say comfortable, we mean comfortable. We've got you covered if you're gluten-free, or have a food allergy. We are proud to serve American food, and proud of the fact that the recipes all authentically immigrated here from somewhere else. Regional American fare at its finest and truest self.

topReview.highlightedText:
Server was prompt and attentive. 

Food came out quickly, hot and  very tasty.

name: Farro Italian Restaurant
description: A casual, family friendly neighborhood Italian restaurant that  creates rustic Italian flavors at affordable prices .

topReview.highlightedText: Nice intimate Italian spot...food is right on!

name: Ambli Mexico at Fitzsimons
description: Ambli Mexico brings a global influence to Mexico City cuisine.  This is not Tex-Mex. Ambli offers unique and balanced dishes that are inspired by Chef Ricardos heritage and elevated with an international flare.  All of our cocktails are made with fresh juices and are designed to pair with the flavors of our food menu.

topReview.highlightedText: Brunch was over the top delicious!!

name: DIONYSUS FOOD & WINE BAR
description: Dionysus Food & Wine Bar is an up-sclae restaurant with contemporary American cuisine and extensive wine options for all palates. Our Cruvinet wine dispensing system offers a unique fun experience for any wine enthusiast. Make your way around our dining room and taste up to 120 wines from all over the world. All your senses will be alive with food from our renowned chef, drinks from our expert bartenders and exquisite service in the dining room. We'll see you soon!

topReview.highlightedText:
This was our first time here. We love trying new restaurants to support the art of hospitality and we love Jazz music so it made it even more attractive to try this place out. We were greeted by a very friendly host that took us immediately to our table. The restaurant was clean and the vibe was positive. We each started with a different flight of wine and they were delicious. We got crab cakes and scallops for appetizers. While the flavors were there and plating was beautiful, both were over cooked and took a little while to get to us. We didn’t mind the wait for the food because we were enjoying great company, classic jazz and mouthwatering wine. Our entrees came out just a little over 30 minutes after ordering them. I ordered a ribeye that was described to have and espresso dry rub. To my disappointment the steak was not worth what was being charged for it. It was over cooked and lacked the flavors that I was looking for based on the description. You could tell that they did not take the chill off the steak before cooking it, it had a rubbery chew to it that you don’t expect when ordering a 50 plus dollar steak.  Dessert was delicious and it paired so well with an espresso martini (or two)!
Although the food was not what we would expect from the price, the atmosphere, service and cocktails were well worth the time that we spent there. We agreed as a group that we would be back for happy hour cocktails and Jazz.

name: The Butchery
description:
WE ARE OPEN FOR SERVICE OR TAKEOUT!
Conveniently located near Wadsworth and & 80th Ave, The Butchery is perfect for any occasion. Our menu features consistently craveable dishes that creatively incorporate the highest of quality steaks, chops and seafood. Our perfectly balanced wine list, refreshing cocktail menu and relaxing atmosphere will provide you and your guests a wonderful dining experience.

topReview.highlightedText: The Butchery is a rare  neighborhood treasure with warm service and an elegant environment.  Each steak is prepared perfectly, every time. The Butchery is so easy to love.

name: Early Bird Restaurant- Denver Tech Center
description:
Early Bird provides fresh, creative, Breakfast & brunch the quality of food and beverage executed flawlessly; delivered in an exceptional yet welcoming environment.
A priority of Early Bird is serving original, healthful breakfast and brunch fare with the emphasis being placed on the freshest ingredients to create modest yet flavorful breakfast and lunch dishes.
happy hour 12pm-2pm Monday -Friday (50% OFF Bar drinks )

topReview.highlightedText:
Sunday brunch, and it was delicious. My only “issue”? I’m vegetarian, so I asked for the meat that came with my meal to be brought on a separate plate. That way there wouldn’t be any cross contamination, and my friend could have it instead. I watched our server type it into the order, and it still came out with the meat on the main plate. Fingers crossed, there wasn’t any of the grease on the French toast… I didn’t have the heart to send it back…
Our server, Ashley, was amazing. They were slammed and under staffed, and she handled it well. She was so sincere in her apology for the food being served that way. I will come back and try it again.

name: HiLo an American Eatery
description:
Welcome to HiLo an American Eatery! Chef Greg and his wife Jodi wanted to bring a family restaurant to our Littleton community. Our intention is for every guest to feel like family when they dine with us. Chef Greg prepares every meal as though he were making it for his own family.
Join us for lunch and dinner, Monday – Sunday, featuring our fresh ingredients and made from scratch entrees.

topReview.highlightedText: Wonderful food in a casual setting.

name: Smokin' Fins Grill | Highlands Ranch
description: Smokin Fins is a regional restaurant concept featuring a unique menu that blends ocean fresh seafood, sushi and house smoked specialties such as prime rib and slow smoked pork. Smokin Fins truly is the food and beverage destination with something for everyone! Please note that we reserve a large portion of our restaurant for walk ins only, please contact us directly with any questions about availability.

topReview.highlightedText: Joshua was a fabulous server…great experience

name: Lot One
description:
Our food is filled with flavors from all around the world, keeping families and
friends in mind. We are growing a great deal of produce for our menu via our rooftop greenhouse. This is a great way to keep seasonal vegetables on our menu and introduce kids to real flavors. Our mission is to keep our menu fresh, fluid and relevant with input from patrons. Again, our community is our top priority. We want you to make regular stops at LOT ONE!

topReview.highlightedText: Wonderful!  Make sure you try the BBQ!!!  The new spot next door is available on the menu!

name: Earls Kitchen + Bar - Park Meadows
description:
A mile-high experience in the Colorado Rockies. In the summer, join us on our fabulous new patio, featuring two roaring fireplaces, a vibrant lounge and plenty of sunshine. In winter, think cozy, chic West Coast design. Located at Park Meadows Mall with plenty of exciting adventures nearby.

A global menu with modern versions of ethnic cuisine staples ranging from great appetizer selections, hand-smashed burgers, premium cuts of steak and seasonally grown fresh vegetables alongside breads and desserts that are created and baked in-house daily. It may seem like a little extra work, but our customers are worth it.

Our patio is seated on a first come, first serve basis.

topReview.highlightedText: Nice ambiance. Good value for the money. I would recommend to friends.

name: Table Mountain Grill and Cantina
description: Located in the heart of historic Golden, Colorado, Table Mountain Grill & Cantina takes an innovative approach to contemporary and traditional Southwestern dishes and drinks, while reflecting a love for fresh and native ingredients wherever possible. From its rustic yet sleek décor to its beautiful outdoor main street patio, Table Mountain Grill & Cantina promises to delight any day or night.

topReview.highlightedText: As always the service and food was top notch.  Thanks for another great experience.

name: Indulge Bistro and Wine Bar - Golden
description: Indulge Bistro & Wine Bar is locally owned and operated by long time Highlands Ranch residents.  We offer a unique and fun environment to meet friends and family and enjoy great food and drinks.  We have an extensive wine list and a full bar.

topReview.highlightedText: You guys are awesome- good was excellent

name: Fogo de Chao - Lone Tree
description: Fogo de Chao is the leading Brazilian steakhouse specializing in fire-roasting high-quality meats since 1979 utilizing the centuries-old Southern Brazilian cooking technique of churrasco. Please join us in our dining room and patio, or bring the Fogo Experience to you with Fogo To-Go, Butcher Shop or Catering for Pick-Up or Contactless Delivery.  Visit www.fogo.com to make a reservation or place an order.

topReview.highlightedText: we had an awesome night!! all the staff was so friendly and the food was delicious as always

name: Bella Colibri
description:
We are open for dine-in or outside seating. Please make a reservation on-line.

Bella Colibri celebrates Colorado’s strong ties to Italy and founder Dean Valdez’s Italian family, who immigrated to Colorado from Calabria, Italy in the early 1900s.

The menu features fresh interpretations of Southern Italian dishes, including seafood, homemade pastas, Colorado lamb, steaks and more. All dishes are artfully presented.

The Chef’s Counter offers an up close view of the meticulous preparation and a chance to interact with the chefs as they prepare specialties and practice their craft.

Housed in one of the state’s most historic buildings, Bella Colibri’s elegant décor honors the building’s rich history, while also evoking the atmosphere of Southern Italy. Beautiful artwork depicts Colorado landscapes with a Tuscan feel.

topReview.highlightedText: As always the service was great as well as the food

name: Hideaway Steakhouse
description:
Hideaway Steakhouse is locally owned and operated and ranks as one of the top ten steakhouses in the north Denver suburbs/metro area. The owners take pride in the roots of their foundation which are prime steaks, seafood, exemplary cuisine and impeccable service.

We serve the finest quality USDA Prime Beef. Our hand-cut steaks are aged to 35+ days, seasoned with our special in-house rub and grilled over Mesquite lump-wood charcoal to perfection.

Hideaway offers guests a dining experience equivalent to its outstanding reputation and unsurpassed standard of excellence. Our promise to you is nothing less than exceptional!

We are now open for Dine-In and Takeout. Gift cards are available for purchase, please call us to order: 303-404-9939. Please join our newsletter and watch our FaceBook Page for special events, features and updates. Thank you for your support.

topReview.highlightedText: Amazing food quality preparation and service. Best in the area hands down.

name: Helga's German Restaurant & Deli
description:
Helga’s was created in 1989 as a mother-daughter venture with a small, four-table restaurant. After spending their childhood in Germany, siblings Herbert and Helga have continued the tradition of their mother, Berta. Today, Helga's has expanded but has not departed from its humble beginnings, gathering a large loyal following of wonderful customers. Helga, Herbert and family maintain a warm and friendly environment where you can sit down to an authentic and delicious home-style German meal with family and friends.

In the true spirit of a family-owned restaurant, Helga and Herbert are directly involved in ensuring the satisfaction of each and every one of their customers. Please do not hesitate to ask for either Helga or Herbert or approach them when you see them in the restaurant. They are happy to offer menu or deli suggestions, or even take a moment to just stop by and chat with you in German or English.

Welcome and we look forward to seeing you soon!

topReview.highlightedText: Very nice ambiance. Easy to converse with others at the table. Good food and plentiful - even the smaller portions.

name: Fleming's Steakhouse - Denver
description: Fleming's Prime Steakhouse & Wine Bar is an outstanding choice to enjoy an exceptional Prime steak, glass of wine or handcrafted cocktail. Whether you’re celebrating a special occasion, hosting a business dinner or simply wanting to enjoy an excellent culinary experience  – we will create a safe and memorable evening for you. If you prefer to enjoy your fine dining experience at home, you can order and pay for lunch or dinner online and then pick up curbside or select from one of our delivery partners.

topReview.highlightedText: Fine dining experience, recommend for special occasions

name: Nordstrom Grill – Nordstrom Park Meadows
description:
Nordstrom Grill – Nordstrom Park Meadows features dishes that are reminiscent of classic comfort food, including starters, salads, sandwiches, entrées and desserts. It has the look and feel of a contemporary diner, with full table service. Beer and wine are available at selected locations.

Nordstrom Grill is located on the third floor of Nordstrom at Park Meadows Mall. Conveniently located at I25 and County Line, directly across from the light rail.

We are open for dine-in with limited capacity and to-go orders with Curbside Pickup. Call (303) 645-2721 to place your order.

topReview.highlightedText: Austin was personable, staff awesome.   Husband and I love it here

name: Indulge Bistro & Wine Bar
description: Indulge Bistro & Wine Bar is locally owned and operated by long time Highlands Ranch residents.  We offer a unique and fun environment to meet friends and family and enjoy great food and drinks.  We have an extensive wine list and a full bar.

topReview.highlightedText:
Busy for a Thursday night, both inside and out.  Excellent wine selection, pretty reasonable prices per glass.
Was a bit surprised the staff didn't mask up, but few in the restaurant were either. 
We enjoyed the whole meal and ambiance and will put this on our short list...

name: Marco's Coal Fired - Inverness
description:
Marco’s Coal-Fired started with the simple idea that passion makes great pizza. The authentic taste of Italy is served to you through the finest ingredients and traditional techniques of the Verace Pizza Napoletana (VPN). Only 00 flour, San Marzano tomatoes, all natural fior di latte or bufala mozzarella, fresh herbs and fresh, all natural, non-processed ingredients are acceptable. Marco's Coal-Fired cooks in authentic, Italian hand built wood fired pizza ovens.
Come taste Marco's Coal-Fired's efforts and see if we don’t have you dreaming of warm Neapolitan nights, no passport required!

topReview.highlightedText: Great time! Could tell the service was suffering a bit, likely due to being understaffed. But overall a good experience with awesome food and drinks.

name: Zaika - Littleton
description:
Zaika in Littleton serves authentic and modernized Indian cuisine in a colorful setting with modern elements. Stop in for a quick lunch before heading back to work, or bring the entire family for dinner and drinks from the full bar. The family-owned restaurant focuses on preparing meals with lush, savory spices and serving them with a dedication and passion for each customer to have a great experience. The menu includes vegan, dairy-free and gluten-free options to meet the dietary needs of everyone in the group.

Zaika offers a variety of appetizers for starting the meal, including veggie samosa, momo, chili chicken, onion pakora, cuTO salad and rasila lamb. There is also a daily chef-selection soup for adding to the meal or enjoying on its own. Check out the tandoori offerings for chicken, lamb, salmon and shrimp specialties. Vegetarian options at Zaika include dal tadka, chana masala and paneer makhni.

topReview.highlightedText: Each dish is better than the next! And the staff are wonderfully attentive and gracious.

name: New Image Brewing Co
description: New Image Restaurant and Brewery, located off of Yukon Street and Grandview Avenue in Arvada. We are known for being a hoppy and hazy, sour house. We have unique specialty cocktails & eclectic menu items in a casual, industrial-inspired space in Olde Towne Arvada. We have 16 taps of craft beers and a full bar of wine and alcohol. The atmosphere is laid-back and comfortable, the food menu items are unexpected and innovative. Our friendly and accommodating staff will assist with any questions you have.  Come to our Arvada restaurant today!

topReview.highlightedText: Food and drinks were great. The service was slower than usual, they seemed understaffed.

name: Nonna's Italian Bistro
description:
Nonna’s Italian Bistro serves up home-cooked Italian dishes and local favorites throughout the week. The wine dinner is a popular favorite, but many diners also prefer the standard dinner menu, which offers everything including starters, salads, soups and entrées.

The grilled salmon salad is particularly tasty, as is the pasta fagole and the arrabbiata, which is made with sausage, spinach and peppers. For lunch, enjoy a menu of sandwiches with themes drawn from traditional Italian-Chicago street food. The Italian beef sandwich is always a hit, but you might prefer the Italian combo with beef, sausage and peppers. There is a kids’ menu available, as well as a daily happy hour with discounted wines and snacks.

topReview.highlightedText: Great options and variety! Have never had a bad or disappointing meal at Nonna's. They offer  several gluten free appetizers, meals and even bread. Always an enjoyable experience.

name: Angelina's Fine Italian Dining
description:
Experience the absolute best in New York style Italian Food! Where "It Takes the Best to be the Best!" Visit for the awesome food of course, but you're in for a treat when you get to meet the owner, Bob Travlos.
Bob insists that the food he prepares is fresh and homemade. Bob found his love for cooking while spending countless hours watching and helping his Mother, a through and through Italian, and his Father, a Greek god, cook for their 10 children. Ask him what his "secret ingredient" is and he will tell you LOVE! Angelina's Fine Italian Dining was opened in 1995 in Littleton Colorado. Bob, a gifted Chef and yes, a Brooklyn born, Italian and Greek, Marine Corp veteran. We apologize if you hear an occasional ruckus from the kitchen. Whether you love the classics like Lasagna or Fettucini Alfredo, or if you love trying new things like Scungilli, or Seafood Fra Diavalo, you are guaranteed to find a dish on our extensive menu that you will fall in love with!

topReview.highlightedText:
What a great evening! Angelina’s is a rare find in dining out now a days. The owners greet you at the door as if you’re family showing up at their home for dinner. They told us about the menu and the specials for the evening, which included the Homemade Mozzarella cheese that Bob, the owner and Chef makes everyday.
The Roasted Peppers and sliced tomatoes, with mozzarella cheese drizzled with their homemade Italian dressing was amazing. They also brought out a plate of Garlic bread. It disappeared very quickly. Then our meals arrived all 4 were some of the best Italian food we have had in a very long time. Once the plates were clean except for my Chicken Parmigiana which was way to much to finish because of its size and spaghetti that’s included. No worry though, it was really good the next day at home. The owners stopped by our table frequently to make sure everything was perfect and see if we needed anything extra. Now it was time for dessert. The four of us each ordered a different one. And again they disappeared quickly. We have already scheduled our next visit and can’t wait. It’s been years since we have found a restaurant that cared so much that everything was perfect. 
Thanks Shondra and Bill!

name: Coal Mine Kitchen

address.line1: 9719 W Coal Mine Ave, Unit B

description: We are a locally owned, scratch kitchen serving breakfast and brunch in a casual, fun, friendly, homestyle atmosphere.

topReview.highlightedText: Coal Mine Kitchen is a great little breakfast spot.  Meals are priced well and the quality is good.

name: Famous Dave's - Denver
description:
WELCOME TO THE LONGEST-RUNNING BACKYARD BBQ PARTY IN HISTORY! We serve amazing BBQ to friends and fellow food lovers. Reserve your seat now and join the best BBQ party in Colorado.
MADE-FROM-SCRATCH GOODNESS! A passion for authentic BBQ is behind everything we do. We start with top quality meats, hand-rub them with fresh spices, and slow-cook them to perfection.
FAMOUS DAVE: HE’S THE REAL DEAL! Raised by Southern-born BBQ lovers in a world of street-corner barrel smokers, Famous Dave spent 25 years visiting thousands of BBQ joints. After decades pulling his own all-night cooking sessions, he felt he was ready to open his own BBQ place in 1994.
AMERICA’S MOST AWARD-WINNING RESTAURANT!
Our passion for BBQ is famous! We’re honored to be consistently chosen as America’s favorite BBQ restaurant. We also like heading out to competitions and putting our BBQ up against what the other elite pitmasters are cooking. To date, we’ve won more than 700 awards!

topReview.highlightedText: Love the Thursday rib tips special!

name: Kachina Southwestern Grill
description:
Dine-in is available! We have limited indoor dining seating, heated outdoor patio + winter igloos.

To reserve a winter igloo, we require a $200 food and beverage minimum spend commitment. Regular restaurant menu is offered as well as our specialty winter cocktail list. Reservations must be booked through our event manager by contacting Emily Mintun at 303-410-5024 or emily.mintun@westinwestminster.com

topReview.highlightedText: We had a very nice evening!  Our server, Nick, was informative, knowledgeable, and timely.  Friday night ambience was super!

name: Crawfish Boil Co.
description:
There is power in sentiment. The moment when all your senses come together, to form a memory that envelopes you and transports you to a different place and time. It is Crawfish Boil Co's mission to create this experience with every item on our menu and with every visit to our restaurant.
Crawfish Boil Company's family recipe, fusion cuisine, and cultivating an environment of good food, good drinks, great stories and unparalleled hospitality experience.

topReview.highlightedText: Amazingly good food and very friendly staff. I will be back

name: Namaste India
description:
Specialties
Authentic Indian Food, Nepalese, vegan and vegetarian. Choice for vegan coconut milk based dishes.
20 years of chef experience winning 8 gold medals in Colorado Springs from Little Nepal Restaurant.
No buffets for covid restriction. Let us know how we are doing so we can improve according to your needs.
History: Established in 2013
Our chef has 20 years of experience winning 8 gold medals through his term of cooking at different Indian restaurants throughout Colorado. Manager with 15 years of experience in food industry giving excellent service.

topReview.highlightedText: We were the only people there this time! It was such a lovely way to start our week off! Yummy food that was so good! We ordered the Chicken sag lamb curry and chicken tika masala platter again some cheese stuffed namm and some garlic namm!!! So good!!!

name: Chart House Restaurant - Golden
description: Chart House is a fine dining restaurant serving seafood & steak and famous for their spectacular views. For more than 50 years, Chart House has redefined the ideal dining experience. With 27 waterfront and showcase locations ranging from the historic to the unforgettable, Chart House restaurants specialize in dazzling views, unique cuisine and exceptional service. From fresh fish specialties to slow-roasted prime rib, the renowned chefs of Chart House have tailored a menu that adds a unique touch to local flavors. And the Chart House happy hour is a guest favorite, where guest favor our signature cocktails and delicious bites you are sure to enjoy. Our original Hot Chocolate Lava Cake is the perfect end to a memorable dining experience at Chart House. Chart House offers the ideal setting for your next event. We would be happy to assist you with all the details of your special occasion.

topReview.highlightedText: It was a special occasion, and the staff made us feel that way too.  The food is fantastic, and the service is amazing.  You just don't find service like this anymore.  All the staff were friendly, efficient, and knowledgeable.  I would recommend this restaurant to every one, special occasion or not.  The menu is large and varied, and the chef does not mind substitutions, which I find very refreshing.  The restaurant itself is beautiful too, although the side we sat on had a view of the highway.  Nothing they can do about that, but it wasn't the best layout to take advantage of the Colorado scenery.  The interior of the restaurant and the wonderful staff took our thoughts off that small deficit though.

name: Acreage by Stem Ciders
description:
Acreage, the first culinary venture from Stem Ciders, is a collaboration by Stem and Colorado Farmers, bringing you the freshest ingredients on the front range. Born from an inspiring landscape and dynamic team, Acreage brings the urban cider house experience found in Stem's RiNo taproom, to the countryside with elevated dishes and views that are healthy for your soul.

We are located about 5 minutes from downtown Lafayette with the best view in Colorado, and a huge outdoor space for all ages to enjoy.

Acreage is following mandates by BCPH and are requiring masks unless you are seated at a table and actively eating or drinking.

**Please review the descriptions for the different experiences before making a reservation**
We are still limited on staff and appreciate your patience with us. Please BE KIND to our staff.
If you are looking at an experience, and it's unavailable, it's likely that time is booked, try another time or give us a call to see if we can seat you.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent all the way around.  Can’t wait to come back - a clear day will be amazing too!

name: Willow Creek Restaurant
description:
Willow Creek is located at Evergreen Lake in the heart of Evergreen, a scenic 30 minute drive from Downtown Denver. A wonderful local restaurant experience since 2009, Willow Creek features a beautiful dining room and patio overlooking the lake, glass walled wine room, and a beautiful rock fireplace. Every table has a view! (Private dining room available upon request).
Creative cocktails and an a Wine Spectator Award Winning Wine List, there is something for everyone.
Serving Lunch, Brunch (Sat & Sunday) and Dinner, we make everything in house and resource from local farms and ranches whenever possible. Willow Creek Is NOT your average mountain dining experience.
Reviewed by USA Today as one of the TOP TEN Places in the US to eat Housemade Pasta's (Our Rabbit Dish is not to be missed)

topReview.highlightedText: We loved Willow Creek. Can’t wait to go back!

name: Benihana - Broomfield, CO
description: Welcome to Benihana and a dining experience unlike any other! Our guests are seated at communal tables in groups, where your personal chef will perform the ancient art of Teppanyaki. Watch as we slice and dice, preparing a meal that will dazzle your eyes as well taste buds, whether you choose mouth-watering steak, tender chicken or succulent seafood. You can also enjoy sushi prepared by a talented sushi chef and indulge in a specialty cocktail. The moment you enter Benihana Broomfield you will be captivated by the large saltwater aquariums that adorn the walls. Venture into the dining room to find it bright and airy, with two enclosed, two-table dining rooms that afford private space with sliding shoji doors. Benihana is located in the “Main Street” complex across from Flatiron Crossing Mall. Enjoy Happy Hour, Monday through Friday from 4-7 p.m.

topReview.highlightedText: We love Benihana and always celebrate special occasions there! Awesome food! Wonderful service💜!

name: The Bistro at Marshdale
description:
The historic Marshdale Lodge which was built in the 1920's is now home to The Bistro, where traditional European cuisine meets the quaint locale of Evergreen.
The Bistro at Marshdale offers an unparalleled dining experience. Dine in either of our sun rooms facing the Continental Divide, or nestle up to the warmth of our natural wood burning fireplace. Quench your thirst at our full bar offering Colorado beers on tap. Experience the rustic charm and elegance of mountain dining at its finest. Our traditional Northern Italian cuisine is prepared daily using the freshest organic ingredients and free range poultry when available. We do not use artificials or preservatives. We hope your enjoy your journey and we Serve you Memories of a Lifetime.

topReview.highlightedText: From the first time we walked into the bistro five years ago until now, the dining experience has always been terrific. Supporting our local favorite is important to us, even if it’s take out, always a delight!

name: Joe's Crab Shack - Westminster
description: Joe's Crab Shack is an American chain of beach-themed seafood casual dining restaurants. Founded in Houston, Texas, the restaurant now operates locations all across the United States of America. It serves seafood and American cuisine.

topReview.highlightedText: The food was great, and came out quickly. Being served by the bartender, our service was efficient, but not overbearing. The only issue with the visit was the air conditioning was up too high and we were cold and our food became cold quickly.

name: Bridgewater Grill @ The Golden Hotel
description: Enjoy a wide array of flavors and tastes which you will experience by touring our menu which features culinary creations from our Executive Chef who focuses on Colorado Proud ingredients to bring the best our local partners have to offer directly to your table.  Selections include our Rocky Mountain Miners Salad, a Beet and Ricotta Salad, our House-Smoked Carnitas Tacos, Rosa’s Award-Winning Pork Green Chili, a Salmon BLTA, a variety of craft burgers and much more.  You will have the opportunity to choose from starters such as our House-Made Hummus, Smoked Trout Dip, Crispy Brussels Sprouts and Crab Cakes.  Entrée selections include Bacon Wrapped CO Bison Meatloaf, Coors Beer Battered Cod Fish and Chips, Pan Seared Salmon, and Colorado Gnocchi. There is no better way to complete your memorable experience than with an indulgent serving of our Apple Strudel, Flourless Chocolate Cake, Creme Brulee or Pistachio Cheesecake.

topReview.highlightedText: This would have been higher rated if reservations could be seated outside. Inside, the AC was not working, but it was not uncomfortable. Our server was great and the food was very good, although the chicken had an odd texture (bite) to it.

name: Schnepf's Restaurant
description: Schnepf’s is locally owned and operated neighborhood restaurant serving the highest quality food and drink in an elegant yet comfortable setting.  We focus on high quality regional ingredients and specialize in nose-to-tail utilization. Schnepf’s is dedicated in creating a new category of neighborhood restaurant that maintains the classic attributes of warmth and affordability while delivering superior food and service.

topReview.highlightedText: Our waitress was phenomenal! Great service and even better views.

name: West Main Taproom + Grill
description:
Restaurateur Pamela Briere owns a restaurant and a catering company in Omaha, Nebraska and says she's been thinking of the Parker gastropub concept since she moved to the town more than a year ago. We love to serve people! West Main Taproom + Grill, our newest concept, brings a unique Colorado theme through and through. 54 Colorado Tap Beers to represent the 54 14er Colorado Peaks, a single source of beautiful Colorado Wines, Spirits and an Urban Cuisine Menu with a Colorado flair.

Our mission will begin with our sourcing practices, but will hardly end there! We promise to inspire your dining experience with remarkable hospitality in a polished, rustic, contemporary atmosphere designed to invite and excite in equal measure.

topReview.highlightedText: I love this place. My only comment is I wish they would change up their menu every once in a while. Not sure it’s really changed since they have opened.

name: Red Lobster - Aurora - Alameda Ave.
description: Red Lobster welcomes you by offering PRIORITY SEATING to reduce your wait time in the restaurant, so you can spend more time doing the things you love. Or, come enjoy a drink at our bar and a Tasting Plate while you wait. Red Lobster is the world's largest and most loved seafood restaurant company, offering high quality, freshly-prepared seafood, sourced in a way that is traceable, sustainable and responsible. We offer lunch and dinner daily, featuring classics like our Ultimate Feast®, Garlic Shrimp Scampi and Parrot Isle Jumbo Coconut Shrimp, and feature limited time flavors and preparations during events like Lobsterfest®, Crabfest® and Endless Shrimp®. And, who can resist our famous warm and cheesy Cheddar Bay Biscuits®? To learn more visit www.redlobster.com

topReview.highlightedText: Ambience:  tasteful.  Social distancing:  appropriate.  Service:  attentive.  Food quality:  very good.  Food preparation:  very good.

name: Old Hickory Steakhouse - Gaylord Rockies Resort & Convention Center
description: Old Hickory Steakhouse brings classic American steakhouse fine dining to Aurora with the highest quality prime and dry aged beef. Old Hickory offers charmingly sophisticated cuisine in a striking regional setting. With hand-selected Black Angus beef and filet mignon, along with hand-crafted cocktails, remarkable wines, delectable artisanal cheeses, and flawless service throughout, we strive to create a memorable dining experience for your night out.

topReview.highlightedText: I can’t say enough the food was wonderful and  the wait staff was excellent. Highly recommend this restaurant.

name: Parker Garage
description: Parker Garage is a Chef driven culinary inspired restaurant located right in the heart of downtown Parker. It has been designated as a Parker landmark and was restored back to it's original state in 2014. Executive Chef, Duy Pham, has been an innovator in Denver's dining scene for over 25 years. His intention based menu unites refined dining and local seasonal ingredients.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent choice of entrees.  I had the Bagatini (sp) and my wife had the salmon.  Appetizer was deviled eggs.  Gotta have those. Dessert was apricot cheese cake.  Food had a nice mix of savory and sweet. Great selections of wine and beer.

name: Black+Haus Tavern
description: Welcome to Black+Haus Tavern, a local place to gather with friends for fun, fresh and flavorful food and drinks incorporating local, sustainable and ethically sourced ingredients.  We are looking forward to meeting you!

topReview.highlightedText: This place was amazing. The food, the service and the ambiance.

name: Lodo's Bar and Grill - Westminster
description: Lodo’s Bar and Grill Westminster is a locally owned sports bar/restaurant that is centrally located next to the intersection of 104th Avenue and Federal, near the Legacy Ridge Golf Course. Voted "Best Sports Bar" 2010 & 2011 by Metromix, Lodo's is the perfect place in the Northern suburbs to meet up with friends or catch a game or two – not a bad seat in the house with all the TVs. The 5,500 square foot rooftop patio has impressive views of the Front Range and Boulder's Flatirons with an outdoor fireplace to ward off those chilly nights. Lodo's offers full bar service, exceptional sports viewing and excellent dining options on both its main level and rooftop patio. Lodo's is the perfect place to host your next event. Lodo's serves a broad selection of fine American food. Brunch and the tastiest build your own bloody mary bar (the tastiest, because you build it) every weekend. Happy Hour specials M-F 2-6. Outdoor seating is a request, we cannot guarantee it.

topReview.highlightedText: We are new to the area. Great spot for a burger and a beer. Beautiful deck. Too bad the smoke from western wildfires obscured the view right now. Will come back for sure.

name: Old Capitol Grill
description:
Old Capital Grill, in Golden, serves delicious, rib-sticking home style American fare that makes diners feel like they are enjoying a meal in the Old West. For a tasty start to your meal, try our smoked for hours smoked wings. Some of Old Capital Grill's house specialty entrŽes include the sumptuous rack of pork ribs with tangy barbecue sauce, delicious brisket sandwich, which is thin-sliced roast beef steer on a roll topped with Swiss cheese and grilled onions, or the smoked salmon salad with a tangy honey mustard vinaigrette.

For a sweet end to your meal, try Old Capital GrillÕs decadent chocolate cake.

topReview.highlightedText: We had considered dining across the street, but the noise level was a bit much for our guests... so we were happy to be seated outside at the Old Capitol Grill. Our server clearly had a lot of tables to take care of, but she was extremely accommodating and always smiling. Everyone in our party enjoyed their meal on a gorgeous Golden evening. We will be back!

name: Romano's Macaroni Grill - Church Ranch
description: Inspired by Italian trattoria cuisine, culture and conversation, Romano's Macaroni Grill believes every meal is a chance to celebrate and toast to life, pasta and of course, vino! Every meal is started off right -- with a bottle of wine at the center of the table, encouraging guests to pour as they please while exploring the extensive menu of handcrafted Italian classics. Macaroni Grill restaurants feature an open kitchen that allows guests to see its fresh ingredients and preparation techniques that blend Italian traditions with progressive culinary inspiration, in a polished casual atmosphere.

topReview.highlightedText: Anywhere in the restaurant is very nice.  The ambience is beautiful.

name: Taw Win
description: A new and upcoming one of a kind Burmese and Thai restaurant in a diverse neighborhood of Denver and Aurora. We are family owned and serving up delicious authentic and traditional dishes.

topReview.highlightedText: WOW.  Just fantastic food. Try the Samoa appetizer! Best I have ever had.  Service was excellent and personable.  We stepped out of our comfort area and glad we did.  We will definitely be back.

name: Early Bird Restaurant
description:
Early Bird provides fresh, creative, and quality food and beverage executed flawlessly; delivered in an exceptional yet welcoming environment. 
A priority of Early Bird is serving original, healthful breakfast and brunch fare with the emphasis being placed on the freshest ingredients to create modest yet flavorful breakfast and lunch dishes.

topReview.highlightedText: Simply the best brunch in Denver! The service is great and the food is amazing!

name: Sushi Umi
description: Nigiri, sushi rolls, ramen, hibachi… You name it.

topReview.highlightedText: One of my favorite places in Colorado

name: EAT! Food & Drink
description:
If you’re looking for an inspiring breakfast, brunch or lunch, you’ve found your next favorite Broomfield spot. Enjoy our unique and tasty dishes 7 days a week.

EAT! FOOD & DRINK, Broomfield Colorado’s newest breakfast, brunch and lunch spot, is now open. We strive to deliver fresh and inspiring dishes paired with creative adult beverages. Bring your friends, family and business associates for a casual, delicious meal.

Please be advised on days with inclement weather which causes our patio to close. We cannot guarantee reservation times. We apologize for any inconvenience. Thank you.

topReview.highlightedText: Great spot for a late morning breakfast stop. Energetic and full of good vibes. Plenty of choice and a step up on the usual menu choices.

name: 740 Front
description:
“One of Colorado's 10 most iconic, historic restaurants and a Must Eat” Denver Post, July 2018
Enjoy indoor or outdoor dining (with both tall propane and foot heaters} at 740 Front in Historic Downtown Louisville. Designated historical, 740 is one of Colorado's two oldest remaining saloons; transformed back to its 1904 roots; a traditional American dining saloon with a turn of the century ambiance featuring a magnificent room dominating bar, built in 1880 by the Brunswick Company,. The copper spit trough, once equipped with running water, still exists at the front of the bar. Louisville, notorious for its drinking, gambling, and illegal activities, evidence of the occasional misunderstanding is the .22 caliber bullet hole in the front bar.
The bar offers a selection of craft beers, wines,  handcrafted cocktails and an extensive craft bourbon selection.
Dinner Tue. thru Sat. From casual to fine dining.
“Steaks not well done but done well, Som

topReview.highlightedText: 1st time for 4 of us. We loved the fish, crab cake salad, meatloaf, & manicotti. Too full for dessert, but sounded yummy. The bar from the late 1800’s is art itself. Can’t wait to return!

name: Curry Kitchen Lakewood
description:
Welcome to Curry Kitchen Lakewood! Authentic Indian Cuisine !! We are a family owned Business. Executive Chef Bibek Rauniyar Himself runs the kitchen with other partners ,.
large varieties of vegan dishes like vegan wings , sweet potato masala along with other traditional indian dishes like tandoori , kabab , masala . Dinner For 2 sampler for everyone to try a taste of it. Rack of Lamb (lamb chops) a die to try dish !!

topReview.highlightedText:
Went here for Mother’s Day dinner. This place is BOMB AF! The owner was so accommodating for our three year old daughter with a noodle dish that didn’t have a lot of spice. 

Can highly recommend everything we had. the tomato and coconut soup, garlic cheese naan, Tika masala with chicken, rice pudding. 

We will be back and making this fantastic restaurant a regular visit! Happy to see a new addition to our neighborhood!

name: Joe's Crab Shack - Aurora
description: Joe's Crab Shack is an American chain of beach-themed seafood casual dining restaurants. Founded in Houston, Texas, the restaurant now operates locations all across the United States of America. It serves seafood and American cuisine.

topReview.highlightedText: Great food and fun environment for seafood meals.  relaxed atmosphere.  reasonable cost.

name: Gabriel's Restaurant
description: Gabriel's at the Old House & Gabriel's Bistro Patio - Bar is located in the little town of Sedalia north of Castle Pines. Gabriel's features Italian, European and American dishes from both an a la carte menu served in our Bar and Patio areas as well as our multi-course, dining experience served in The Old House. Our restaurant is housed in the historic, Victorian Manhart home built in the 1890's. The home was converted into Gabriel's in 1986 with the Bistro Patio-Bar and gardens added in the early 1990s. Prices per person average $35 to $55 per person on the Bistro/Patio side and The Old House's multi-course, dining typically starts at $55 per person. Gabriel's extensive wine list and premium back bar offers a huge variety to compliment any dinner. Gabriel's is perfect for all occasions. Indulge yourself and experience the ultimate in elegant fine dining. We are conveniently located between Denver and Castle Rock, just 20 minutes from the Tech Center and 30 from Denver.

topReview.highlightedText: We love dining at Gabriels and sincerely hope a lack of staffing and rising food prices do not cause this restaurant to close.

name: Pino's Italian Kitchen & Bar
description:
Happy Hour 7 days a week. 3pm-6:00pm
At Pino's Italian Kitchen & Bar, family and friends are the main ingredients that make your dining experience even more spectacular.
Pino's truly has something for everyone. Pino’s offers a wide variety of dining choices including top quality steaks, chops, seafood, traditional Italian favorites and very
creative dishes with NY flair. Whatever your fancy, you can find it at Pino’s. Pino’s is a local family owned Italian restaurant. For 15 years we’ve served thousands of families, friends and Colorado visitors. With top-quality Italian dishes and spectacular ambiance, Pino's has become the #1 choice.
If the atmosphere and friendly service don’t seduce you, the wide variety of creative appetizers, entrees and explosive wine list will. Bring your friends, family and appetite for fun, and we’ll handle the

topReview.highlightedText: Love this restaurant, so comfortable, great food and extremely pleasant people serving you!

name: Flagstaff House
description: Partners Scott Monette, Executive Chef and Food Network Chopped Champion Chris Royster and General Manager Adam Monette welcome you to the Flagstaff House Restaurant for unparalleled Colorado dining experience. Located at an elevation of 6,000 feet, the Flagstaff House offers breathtaking views, new American cuisine, a world-renowned wine list and impeccable service. Local and seasonal cuisine take the spotlight in curating our menu. Offered are a three-course or Chef's multi-course tasting menu with the three-course menu available a la carte. The Monette family has owned the Flagstaff House since 1971 and holds many prestigious awards including Colorado's longest holding Wine Spectator Grand Award, Forbes Travel Guide Four Star rating and AAA Four Diamond status. Features include Men's Journal, Bon Appetite, Conde Nast Traveler, USA Today, 5280, Best of Boulder, Eater and many others. We look forward to welcoming you for a special dining experience.

topReview.highlightedText: Flagstaff House offers one of the most special, welcoming dining experiences you'll have - in Boulder or anywhere. The food, drinks, setting and service are all excellent.

name: The Post Chicken & Beer - Lafayette
description:
The Post Chicken & Beer is open and ready to welcome you for dine-in, outdoor dining, curbside pick-up and our very own delivery service 7 days a week!

At The Post Chicken & Beer our motto is Hot Chicken Loves Cold Beer. Our brewers brew beers that are gosh darn delicious, memorable, and something you will want to put in your mouth repeatedly. Featured by Guy Fieri on Food Network's Diners Drive-Ins &; Dives, our bird is better than the rest--humanely raised, all natural chickens are brined for hours, dipped in buttermilk, seasoned with GLUTEN-FREE flour, and then fried to crispy golden perfection.

For curbside pick-up and delivery, order WeDeliver online anytime after 4pm until we close. It is easy-peasy!
Order Online: postchickenandbeer.com/location

topReview.highlightedText: The fried chicken sammy and chicken & waffles are always good!

name: Los Arcos Mexican Restaurant
description: We are a family owned and run restaurant that has been in business since 1978.  We proudly serve homemade Mexican cuisine and invite you and your family to enjoy our family’s hospitality.   We want you to feel as if you were dining in our home by enjoying the ambiance, atmosphere, great food and drinks and all that Los Arcos has to offer.

topReview.highlightedText: Always a pleasure to eat here, great food and great staff.

name: Red Lobster - Littleton
description: Red Lobster welcomes you by offering PRIORITY SEATING to reduce your wait time in the restaurant, so you can spend more time doing the things you love. Or, come enjoy a drink at our bar and a Tasting Plate while you wait. Red Lobster is the world's largest and most loved seafood restaurant company, offering high quality, freshly-prepared seafood, sourced in a way that is traceable, sustainable and responsible. We offer lunch and dinner daily, featuring classics like our Ultimate Feast®, Garlic Shrimp Scampi and Parrot Isle Jumbo Coconut Shrimp, and feature limited time flavors and preparations during events like Lobsterfest®, Crabfest® and Endless Shrimp®. And, who can resist our famous warm and cheesy Cheddar Bay Biscuits®? To learn more visit www.redlobster.com

topReview.highlightedText: Great experience. I hadn't been to a Red Lobster in years and for the price, everything was excellent!

name: Vista Montagne - Gaylord Rockies Resort & Convention Center
description: Transport yourself to Italy and enjoy our seasonally-inspired Italian cuisine. Get lost in a bowl of pasta paired with a glass of crisp, red wine. Breakfast features a buffet while dinner is served a la carte.

topReview.highlightedText: Food and drinks were delicious! Prices were right on point and the food quality was above average! This place did not disappoint in any area! Highly recommended!!

name: Japango Sushi Restaurant
description: Japango, set in a historic building just west of Broadway on the Pearl Street Mall in Boulder, CO, offers a dynamic combination of traditional and contemporary Japanese cuisine. Guests will enjoy a relaxed experience in an award winning space designed by nationally acclaimed architect, Scott Rodwin. In many ways this wildly popular restaurant feels like a direct extension of Boulder itself—sophisticated, casual and healthy. // It’s is the perfect place for a first date, a family gathering, or a night out with friends. In addition to an elegant—yet intimate and unpretentious—dining room, Japango features a large sushi bar, a Pearl Street patio, a back patio with fireplace, an enclosed patio that seats up to 10, and a lively bar and lounge area.  // The full bar offers unique house cocktails, an extensive sake menu and the largest Japanese whisky selection in Colorado.

topReview.highlightedText: super cool place, awesome server, not the best NA drinks i have ever had but they had a good selection otherwise! Definitely would recommend!

name: El Rancho Brewing
description:
Considered by many to be a historic site, the El Rancho Colorado Restaurant was established in Evergreen, Colorado in 1948. The newly renovated El Rancho Restaurant and Brewery is now home to a 10-barrel brewing system, and has 20 craft beers on tap.

On the main level, with an occupancy of 332, guests enjoy dining in the lounge, dining room, the west patio deck, which offers beautiful views of the continental divide. A casual lunch menu ends at 4pm, replaced by a casual-fine dining menu that runs until 9pm.

On the newly-renovated lower level, with an occupancy of 200 inside and 65 outside, The Aspen Room Bar and Beer Garden features live entertainment, cocktails, and limited grill menu.

The new menus at El Rancho Restaurant and Brewery include traditional cooked meals that are made from locally grown and baked goods, and a variety of steaks and wild game. Barbecue is available on the lunch menu, with steaks and fish entrees available after 4pm on t

topReview.highlightedText: Terrific food  & 2) hostesses shorts were too casual & too short for the nice ambiance.

name: Johnny's Italian Steakhouse - Thornton
description:
COVID-19 UPDATE: We are now open for indoor, in-person dining! Due to occupancy restrictions we recommend making a reservation. Overflow seating will be on the patio for walk-ins. We ask that you be courteous of those dining after you and limit your dining experience to 90 minutes. We look forward to seeing you again soon!

Conveniently located off I-25 and 144th in Thornton, Johnny’s Italian Steakhouse is adjacent to The Hilton Garden Inn and features premium steaks, Italian cuisine and seafood specialties in an elegant setting. Guests can choose to dine in one of our cozy private booths, secluded dining areas or in Johnny’s signature Blue Bar. Johnny’s is a nod to the supper clubs of the 40’s and 50’s and brings the Rat pack era to the 21st century!

* Ask about our event space and catering

topReview.highlightedText: From beginning to the end. You won’t be dissatisfied.

name: Piripi
description: Born in Cordoba, Argentina, Owner and Executive Chef of Piripi, Hugo Meyer began his culinary journey in Munich, Germany at age seventeen. Since then, Hugo has owned and operated several restaurants internationally. Through his extensive travels and life in Europe, South America and the Caribbean Hugo has developed a palate reflective of his life abroad. His authentic plates showcase local ingredients. Come join us and enjoy a culinary experience through the eyes of a world traveler.

topReview.highlightedText: Delicious dinner, can’t wait for Paella night.  Yum!

name: Asti D' Italia
description: Set in a comfortable relaxed atmosphere, Asti d'Italia is a fine Italian restaurant with mouth-watering menu items and an approachable comprehensive wine list that creates a memorable experience for any special occasion, or just a simple taste of the Italian countryside.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent service and food. Only problem was they were out of the lasagna, my husband’s favorite. He just had to make another selection.

name: Hapa Sushi Grill & Sake Bar - Pearl St. Boulder
description: The name Hapa is derived from the Hawaiian term that describes a harmonious blend of Asian and American cultures.  Like our name, our food reflects this dynamic combination.  The menu is based on traditional Japanese cooking fundamentals which are then amplified, muted, or mixed with influences from many different styles of cooking until they are something completely new: they're Hapa.  We have stretched the boundaries of creativity to develop dishes that defy all the rules while holding true to our roots. We hope that you will find our menu innovative, uninhibited, and distinctly fun!  Incomplete parties will not be sat until complete.

topReview.highlightedText: Great food but very noisy and chaotic. We’ll certainly go back for the food, but might choose a different time.

name: Roots
description:
Roots has many outdoor and indoor spaces for your visit with safe social distancing in place. Choose from our beautiful outdoor space or our indoor ballroom space.

Roots is about flavors!
Food must TASTE good and it must LOOK good! You will not be disappointed! Roots is owned and operated by 5-Star rated catering company The Gourmet Kitchen. The Gourmet Kitchen has been serving Denver Metro and Front Range since 2002.

Roots is about the environment!
We are committed to environmental sustainability and have processes and company culture in place to minimize our operational footprint. We also have a few raised beds where we grow greens, herbs, and veggies.

Roots is about community!
We are always looking to support our local businesses and communities. Donate here: https://donorbox.org/breathe-delhi

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent meal of small plates with great flavors. Easy to spend $100 before alcohol, but the flavors, ambiance, service make for a lovely evening. A great treat and worth a visit.

name: Jax Fish House & Oyster Bar - Boulder
description:
Jax Fish House is open and ready to welcome you for outdoor dining, curbside pick-up and our very own delivery 7 days a week. Any way you choose to dine, we got you. For curbside pick-up and delivery, order online! It's easy-peasy, and you can place an order for a future date, too.
Order Online: jaxfishhouse.com/boulder
----------
Jax Fish House in Boulder works tirelessly to bring fresh caught seafood and fine coastal food to the surrounding landlocked community. The dining experience, whether outdoors or at your home, focuses on sustainable seafood when choosing who to partner with to provide guests only the freshest seafood.

topReview.highlightedText: Some of the best seafood I've had anywhere. As fresh as you'll find on the coasts.

name: Wine Experience Cafe and World Cellar
description:
Established in 2007, we are a contemporary dining establishment featuring food with an international flair. Thee great chefs that are known for creating exciting wine friendly cuisine that change with the seasons. Owner Eldon Larson has over 30 years experience and has traveled extensively to the world’s greatest wine regions. Relax in our comfortable curved couch area or enjoy several courses in our softly lit dining room. Wine Experience Café boasts an elegant fabric ceiling, contemporary lighting, bay fire place and exciting colors. After dinner you can step into the World Cellar Fine Wine Shop to purchase the wines enjoyed at Wine Experience Café.
**Highlights:
wild boar and green chili wontons, watermelon radish and goat cheese salad, beef fillet au poivre, grilled molasses pork chop, pan-seared sea scallops, fresh market fish, cured meats and artisan cheese. Full Bar, 35 wines by the glass, wine flights, amazing wine list

topReview.highlightedText: Great experience, delicious food. The servers have great recommendations

name: Bitto Bistro
description: The owners and staff at Bitto Bistro believe in the heritage and traditions of food and culture around the world and in supporting the craft of traditional artisan fare. As such, we are pleased to share with you some of the best the world has to offer in Artisan Cheeses and Charcuterie (cured meats, sausages and pates). Our wine by-the-glass and flight list is the largest in the state! Because buying local is also important to us, we source our products from area businesses, farms and dairies whenever possible. We hope you enjoy your time with us. Please sit back, relax and prepare to have a great time!

topReview.highlightedText: Nice  setting and atmosphere. Great service and food.

name: Monarch Chophouse
description:
A whole new twist on a classic steakhouse
Welcome to fine dining done the Monarch way.
Elegance. Sophistication. Luxury. Three words describe the food and the experience at Monarch Chophouse. Monarch Chophouse proudly serves 28 day aged, USDA prime cuts of beef chosen for their superior marbling and flavor, fresh seafood, and Colorado lamb in an elegant atmosphere with unsurpassed service and attention to detail. Experience the art of table-side preparations from traditional Caesar Salad and Steak Diane to our uniquely modern “321 Below” ice cream created using liquid nitrogen amid a dramatic cascade of fog. Complement your meal with wine from our selection of over 330 labels or an expertly mixed cocktail from our intriguing list of spirits. Allow us to arrange an exclusive private dining experience for your group of up to 50 guests.

topReview.highlightedText: New granddaughter.

name: /pôr/ wine house
description:
/pôr/ Wine House is considered to be one of the only premier bars and restaurants Downtown in the city of Louisville. Established in 2014, it was situated behind Bittersweet Café on Main Street. It is now on the corner or Pine and Main st. /pôr/ Wine House has become known for the extensive wine on tap and craft beer lists that are offered. In addition to the impressive bar, customers have an extensive tapas menu from which they can choose their meal. Along with a feature entree menu. Some of these choices include blistered shishito peppers, cheese & charcuterie boards, flatbread pizzas, and homemade desserts from their in-house bakery. Gluten Free and Vegan options available.

/pôr/ Wine House has a sophisticated yet trendy ambiance that is created through the dim lighting, sleek lines and contemporary accent pieces found throughout the dining room. On weekends, customers are treated to live music and entertainment.

topReview.highlightedText: Hanging out with friends

name: Ebert's Terrace
description:
Ebert's Terrace is conveniently located at Green Valley Ranch Golf Club and minutes from DIA! Membership is not required, we are open to the community. Ebert’s is the new gathering place for families, friends and neighbors that builds community and pride in Green Valley Ranch. We offer indoor and outdoor seating and competitive rental rates for private event spaces!
Contact Kelly Tuley at 303-957-4096

topReview.highlightedText: Loved the live music! Service was great. Food was delicious!

name: Coriander Flavors of India
description:
At Coriander, we are aiming to make simplified yet elevated Indian food. The spices, the aromas, the clay oven preparation all weaving together a celebration of senses. Call it comfort food from across the ocean.

Indian food is the labor of love. The rendering of sauces, cloves, cinnamon, coriander, turmeric and many more spices adding this magic to the curries that are the backbone of most of our dishes.

topReview.highlightedText: Great food!  I’m now a fan of Indian food!  They will make the dish as spicy as you want.  Definitely going back!

name: Spruce Farm & Fish
description:
Fresh, straightforward, honest & approachable food. Every time, with our new Boulderad’s Best menu. Patio dining at the Corner Bar | ToGo: 303-442-4880 | Delivery through Doordash | Open daily from 11am – 8pm
--
Spruce Farm & Fish serves creative and contemporary Brunch and Dinner menus utilizing the highest quality ingredients. Guests can indulge in Brunch any day of the week until 3pm. Partnering with sustainable oyster farms and fisheries, seafood at Spruce is flown in daily. Spruce offers rotating dinner specials, including certified angus beef house-smoked prime rib.

The bar offers espresso drinks, an extensive selection of wines, and locally sourced spirits and craft beers. Happy-hour specials are available daily and include seasonal small plates and fresh cocktails.

Want to eat out without going out? Order your food to-go! Give us a call at 303-442-4880. Our top priority is the health and well-being of our staff, guests, Boulder community.

topReview.highlightedText: Really lovely dining room and excellent service!

name: Boulder Cork
description: The Boulder Cork Restaurant has provided quality food and excellent service since 1969. The restaurant is now one of Colorado’s most renowned dining experiences. The casual, yet attentive atmosphere is the perfect place to spend a special evening, be it to relax with friends or entertain business associates. Our banquet facilities can accommodate large groups with the quiet proficiency and superior quality that has become the hallmark of The Boulder Cork. The food is an impressive display of creativity and variety, masterminded by the chef, Jim Smailer. Chef Smailer has created an enticing offering of steaks, prime rib, chicken, pasta, and fresh fish selections; all on the cutting edge of culinary delight. The food is as fresh as the market allows. The true epicurean will agree that our efforts are apparent to both the eyes and the palate, from the appetizer through the handmade desserts.
