topReview.highlightedText: Always been a favorite of ours and this dinner was no exception. Had the prime rib and must say it was the best in recent memory. Very professional wait staff. Our waitperson Teal was excellent.

name: Via Toscana
description:
Relax in a warm, elegant setting and enjoy Italy’s rich culinary traditions. Over 600 wine selections, nightly chef's dinner and specials, and stained glass ceilings throughout.
Offering Specialty Valentines, Christmas Eve and New Years Eve dinners, please visit viatoscana.com to view menu selections.

topReview.highlightedText: New to the area, this was our first time at Via Toscana.  It was our 38th wedding anniversary.  My husband requested a quiet table.  Everything was wonderful.  The table was in a room with only one other couple.  The menu said "Happy Anniversary" at the top.  The waiter was attentive.  The service was excellent, as was the food.  We will be returning in the near future.

name: Carelli's Ristorante Italiano
description:
Enjoy a wonderful dining experience with family or friends at Carelli's. Owner Greg Carelli with help from his father Gene wanted to offer guests authentic Italian cuisine in a contemporary setting that features a large open flame fireplace, mosaic tiles, natural Birch woods, and warm lighting. An appetizer of fresh mozzarella and Beefsteak tomato caprese, lightly breaded calamari or lamb artichoke meatballs will please the palate at Carelli's. Guests can dine on baked jumbo shells stuffed with spinach and ricotta , the classic chicken parmigiana or shrimp scampi. Artisanal pizza, calzones, and paninis. Awsome Gluten-free options are also available.

Carelli's was the winner of the Daily Camera Reader's Choice 2002-2020 award for Best Italian Restaurant and ambiance. It also has won awards from the Denver Post and Boulder Weekly magazines. It has an awesome bar scene and an extensive wine list. Carelli's restaurant features daily fresh fish specials.

topReview.highlightedText: Very nice atmosphere, friendly staff, yummy food and large portions.

name: Centro Mexican Kitchen
description:
Centro is locally owned and operated and open for indoor and outdoor dining, and curbside pickup. Serving soulful, Baja-inspired Mexican food, your senses will be ignited by bright & bold flavors, fresh ingredients, and unique combinations that characterize our Mexican cuisine.
-----

topReview.highlightedText: Came for an early dinner, ended up being happy hour (even better)! Loved the selection of appetizers and bites.

name: Corrida
description: Corrida offers dining inspired by Spain with stunning mountain views from our rooftop location. We offer Happy Hour on our patio from 3-5PM, and dinner service indoors from 5-9PM.

topReview.highlightedText: Incredible views, superb staff, incredible wines, stellar food

name: Union An American Bistro
description:
The cozy, upbeat UNION is the epitome of a friendly neighborhood restaurant, inviting locals and visitors to enjoy the modern American culinary experience. UNION offers creative, seasonal menus served in a warm and comfortable setting in the heart of downtown Castle Rock, using quality ingredients from around the block and around the world.

Online ordering: https://unionamericanbistro.alohaorderonline.com/mobile/splash?

topReview.highlightedText: Our meal was exceptional. Great service!! Definitely one of favorite restaurants!! Never have had a bad meal or experience!

name: SALT - Boulder
description: The philosophy at SALT is simple; a belief that the best food travels the shortest distance from farm to table, that menus should change with the seasons and that the locally sourced ingredients, combined with European technique and innovative thinking make for a truly remarkable experience.  Chef Bradford Heap and his staff have made a commitment to source local, organic and fresh ingredients whenever possible.  The menu reflects this mind-set, simple, yet elegant and delicious.  The wines, while sourced all over the world offer our guests some classic profiles, while introducing them to some new and exciting choices as well as a pre-prohibition cocktails with a twist.  Approachable, but sophisticated.  Enjoy!

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent, bartender and hostess let us pay in advance for anniversary celebration

name: Kokopelli Beer Company
description: Kokopelli Beer Company is the first solely woman owned and operated brewpub in the state of Colorado.  Located in the Solaire Shoppes at 8931 Harlan Street in Westminster Colorado, we are across from the future Downtown Westminster development at Highway 36 & Sheridan.  We enjoy brewing quality and consistent handcrafted ales, and are proud to offer 30 unique taps, including at least 27 of our own, in-house made craft beers covering the style spectrum, as well as a few guest taps of ciders and sour beer.  Our craft beer selections are complemented by select Colorado wines and spirits.  We will happily satisfy your hunger with great appetizers, hand-tossed pizza, artisan sandwiches and salads, and finish off the meal with desserts you would never expect from a brewpub.  Our pint-sized guests love our kids' menu too.  We pride ourselves on being a place where "Friends meet friends and make new ones!"

topReview.highlightedText: Everything was amazing!!! It's one of my favorite place to relax and drink beer and have fun. :)

name: Nanna’s Gourmet Market and Tea Emporium
description:
Nanna’s delivers 4th generation recipes and tea service with tender loving care. Founded in 2009, Karen Renz and her daughter Tobie expanded their online tea shoppe into a retail location where it quickly grew into a popular hangout for the neighborhood. It has now evolved into a tea room that serves cups of tea, scones bangers and mash, crumpets and more. Nanna’s offers over 120 teas and menu items in its shop, including freshly baked scones, clotted cream and preserves from recipes that have been Karen and Tobie’s family for more than four generations.
Nanna’s gives back to the community with special events and requests that people only pay what they can. If you’d like to partner with Nanna’s to give back to the community

name: Sforno Trattoria
description: We strive to give you the genuine tastes of Italy, right here on Boulder’s historic Pearl Street Mall, with our local, natural ingredients. And with our famous mozzarella made in house, Happy Hour 7 days a week, and an original wood burning pizza oven, we have no doubt that you will love coming to Sforno. Join us for a little bit of Italian bliss right here in Colorado, and let us show you what ‘love from the oven’ means to us.

topReview.highlightedText: Everything was great, can’t wait to come back to Boulder and eat here again!

name: Brick House Tavern + Tap - Parker
description: Local restaurant serving up fresh food with a huge beer and cocktail selection. From hand-made burgers, pizzas, and desserts Brick House Tavern + Tap has the best American comfort food to satisfy your cravings! Large groups welcome!

topReview.highlightedText: Longer wait, but expected given the times.  Server handled situation well and was fantastic.   Food good.

name: The Post Chicken & Beer - Boulder
description:
The Post Chicken & Beer is open and ready to welcome you for dine-in, outdoor dining, curbside pick-up and our very own delivery service 7 days a week!

At The Post Chicken & Beer our motto is Hot Chicken Loves Cold Beer. Our brewers brew beers that are gosh darn delicious, memorable, and something you will want to put in your mouth repeatedly. Featured by Guy Fieri on Food Network's Diners Drive-Ins &; Dives, our bird is better than the rest--humanely raised, all natural chickens are brined for hours, dipped in buttermilk, seasoned with GLUTEN-FREE flour, and then fried to crispy golden perfection.

For curbside pick-up and delivery, order WeDeliver online anytime after 4pm until we close. It is easy-peasy!
Order Online: postchickenandbeer.com/location

topReview.highlightedText: Great food and beer. We sat outside and we knew the traffic would be driving by our table. We loved the area and can’t wait to come back. Deviled eggs were great too. Thumbs up

name: Roadhouse Boulder Depot
description: Located in the 125 year old historic Boulder Train Depot, Roadhouse Boulder Depot brings an urban flare to a historic setting and serves as a gathering place for the entire Boulder community.  Operating as a restaurant in the Roadhouse Hospitality Group, Roadhouse Boulder Depot offers a quality “roadhouse” style menu with an emphasis on customer service and community.  As University of Colorado Boulder alumni, the Shipp brothers, Terry, Dan, Mike and John, took their knowledge of restaurants and coupled it with their understanding and appreciation for the Boulder community.  Tying together history, art, and great food, guests can expect a one of a kind dining experience in a true Boulder institution. Roadhouse Boulder Depot is more than a trend, it’s a tradition.

topReview.highlightedText: food and service great; nice option to downtown; outside space nice

name: West End Tavern
description:
West End Tavern, Boulder's iconic tavern and bourbon house, is open for curbside pick-up and delivery 7 days a week from 11:30am to 9pm. Order online and choose WeDeliver for to go. Our foodservice trained staff will deliver it to your car, contact-free, which means you can get booze delivered and your money goes directly to a local business and to our staff...so BONUS.

Or reserve a table for indoor and outdoor dining, 7 days a week from 11:30am to 8pm.

-----------
West End Tavern has been serving up craft beer -- 20 on tap at all times -- for generations in Boulder, CO. For decades this tavern has been a spot for the community to congregate over fine beer and good eats! The West End Tavern hosts wonderful tasting events to broaden the horizons of valued patrons, introducing them to the exciting and dynamic world of craft beer.

topReview.highlightedText: Took some out of town guests here for lunch and a stroll down the Pearl Street Mall.We had a Cobb salad, two orders of burnt ends, the bbq platter, a chicken club sandwich and an order os cooked Brussel sprouts for an appetizer.  Everyone loved their food with the cooked Brussel sprouts being especially appreciated.  Atmosphere was great with a well stocked bourbon wall behind the bar.  Glad I chose this place to eat.

name: Frank's Chophouse Boulder
description:
Frank Day started his restaurant career in the 1970’s in Boulder, CO. Together with his wife Gina, they have created dining experiences focused on bringing their guests together with fun and interesting food and drinks. In that same tradition, Frank’s Chophouse brings you classic fare with a twist, we source only the finest meats, produce and seafood available. Our Tavern menu, available on our patio or in the tavern, offers a refined-casual experience that everyone can enjoy. Our Chophouse menu, available in our dining room, offers a variety of chef-prepared, steak and seafood dishes, perfect for a special occasion or night out in Boulder.

Our team understands your trust in dining with us and we promise to provide a memorable experience. We thank you for your patronage.

topReview.highlightedText: Went here for a date and it was the perfect spot. The menu included a variety of options and price ranges so that everyone can find something that they want. It was a little loud near the start of our meal because there was a table with some babies next to us, but they left and it was pretty quiet afterwards.

name: Bramble & Hare
description:
Bramble & Hare, the original Farmhouse Kitchen and Pub, opened its doors in July 2012. Founded by Chef Eric Skokan and his wife, Jill, as the sister restaurant to their Black Cat Farm~Table~Bistro.

Bramble & Hare has a lively, warm atmosphere in its three charming dining rooms. It is located in the heart of Boulder, CO, just off the historic Pearl Street Mall.

Features a 3-course prix fixe menu with choices for each course, Hand-crafted, seasonal cocktails featuring artisanal spirits and local ingredients show the talent of our incredible bar team who make our restaurant spring to life.

The variety of produce and meats grown on their 425 acre certified Organic farm allows Chefs Skokan and Garza Silva a limitless palette of flavors, colors, and textures from which to build their award-winning cuisine.

Cost: $59+gratuity, tax and alcohol

topReview.highlightedText: Amazing fresh food and a perfect setting for a romantic dinner for two where you can actually hear yourself! The staff was amazing and the bartender even made us a pisco sour to perfection! Good was finger licking delicious and we followed our waiters recommendations to great success! We will be back!

name: Famous Dave's - Aurora
description:
WELCOME TO THE LONGEST-RUNNING BACKYARD BBQ PARTY IN HISTORY! We serve amazing BBQ to friends and fellow food lovers. Reserve your seat now and join the best BBQ party in Colorado.

MADE-FROM-SCRATCH GOODNESS! A passion for authentic BBQ is behind everything we do. We start with top quality meats, hand-rub them with fresh spices, and slow-cook them to perfection.

FAMOUS DAVE: HE’S THE REAL DEAL! Raised by Southern-born BBQ lovers in a world of street-corner barrel smokers, Famous Dave spent 25 years visiting thousands of BBQ joints. After decades pulling his own all-night cooking sessions, he felt he was ready to open his own BBQ place in 1994.

AMERICA’S MOST AWARD-WINNING RESTAURANT! Our passion for BBQ is famous! We’re honored to be consistently chosen as America’s favorite BBQ restaurant. We also like heading out to competitions and putting our BBQ up against what the other elite pitmasters are cooking. To date, we’ve won more than 700 awards!

topReview.highlightedText: Thanks bar tender was great

name: Go Fish Sushi - Broomfield
description:
CAPTIVATING DENVER'S SUSHI PALATE SINCE 2015
—
Go Fish Sushi fits right in amongst the trendy shopping, eating, and drinking destinations on 136th Ave. – packed with personality and local flavors, this restaurant has been a favorite of locals for over a decade. Here you can grab a beautifully prepared Japanese meal, a drink at the bar that serves a variety of wines, local beers, custom cocktails, and imported sakes. Relax for dinner or drinks as you experience the fresh & beautifully decorated sushi. Independently owned and operated, Go Fish Sushi continues to deliver Sushi with an attitude.


If you love Go Fish Sushi located on South Broadway, then you will love the Broomfield location that opened in early 2015. Located in a quiet suburban neighborhood, Go Fish Broomfield brings a casual fine dining experience. This beautiful restaurant offers the same menu, but also has the time to offer more unique weekly appetizer specials with a different range of sushi/sashimi.

topReview.highlightedText: Food is delicious

name: Red Lobster - Wheat Ridge
description: Red Lobster welcomes you by offering PRIORITY SEATING to reduce your wait time in the restaurant, so you can spend more time doing the things you love. Or, come enjoy a drink at our bar and a Tasting Plate while you wait. Red Lobster is the world's largest and most loved seafood restaurant company, offering high quality, freshly-prepared seafood, sourced in a way that is traceable, sustainable and responsible. We offer lunch and dinner daily, featuring classics like our Ultimate Feast®, Garlic Shrimp Scampi and Parrot Isle Jumbo Coconut Shrimp, and feature limited time flavors and preparations during events like Lobsterfest®, Crabfest® and Endless Shrimp®. And, who can resist our famous warm and cheesy Cheddar Bay Biscuits®? To learn more visit www.redlobster.com

topReview.highlightedText: The food is always excellent and in our travels we find the food and service at every Red Lobster to be very consistent.

name: The Fort Patio
description:
We have upgraded our Patio for fine dining. Please make a reservation using our main OpenTable account.

Thank you!
-Fort Management

topReview.highlightedText: Loved the outdoor dining on the patio at the Fort. The food, service, ambience, and overall experience made the evening very special. Wish the weather would permit doing this year round!

name: Buca di Beppo - Broomfield
description: Work up an appetite at Rock Creek Farm Park or Flatiron Market Place, then head over to your Broomfield, CO Buca di Beppo, just off the Denver Boulder Turnpike, on Interlocken Loop for the best Italian food around.

topReview.highlightedText: We love the food we eat at any restaurant when we find one on vacation Yesterdays meal was excellent our waitress was excellent everything about it yesterday was very good thank you We have been eaten there for years and will continue

name: India's Kitchen II
description: Come and try our authentic Indian cuisine and our excellent wine list and exotic beers that compliment the complex flavors and aromas of the Indian cuisine at India’s Kitchen II here in Centennial. Our casual interiors creates a variety of spaces, allowing us to create an intimate dining experience for two or more, as well as larger groups with over 50 seats in both private and open areas. We’re sure to find the right table for you. We also offer All You Can Eat Lunch Buffet @ $10.99 – Daily starting 11:00am to 2:30pm. Our sisters locations are at Parker and Foxfield.

topReview.highlightedText: The food is always consistently excellent. And the portions are generous.  We always leave the restaurant raving about how good it was.

name: Corner Bar
description: Located inside Hotel Boulderado on the corner of Spruce and 13th streets, The Corner Bar is the ideal location for a quick lunch, a lively Happy Hour, a great late-night meal, or the perfectly poured Martini. This spacious restaurant offers indoor and outdoor seating with a large wrap-around patio featuring plenty of room for social distancing and fun.

topReview.highlightedText: Great patio, good variety on menu, ample cocktails & great staff!

name: The Douglas | Kitchen & Cocktails
description:
The Douglas | Kitchen and Cocktails, named after the county in which it resides, features elevated comfort food and a relaxed atmosphere. We serve creatively constructed dishes with locally sourced ingredients that honor the deep roots of Douglas County.
The heart of The Douglas | Kitchen and Cocktails, is found at the table, the people who gather around it and the food we bring to it. Sharing a table with our neighbors contain the moments that shape us and our communities. It’s a tradition that’s been honored here in Douglas County since 1861.

Pull up a chair, we’ve made space for you.

topReview.highlightedText:
Great place that is worth returning!!
Peter

name: Seoul Korean BBQ
description:
At Seoul BBQ in Aurora, you’ll find an exciting mix of barbecue and sushi items that are bound to whet the appetite. With an exciting ambience full of scrumptious sights and smells, Seoul BBQ offers guests a chance to cook their own meals and enjoy a variety of sauces and sides. The restaurant offers an eclectic blend of Korean and sushi items with favorites that include galbi, pork, kimchi, tofu, California rolls and much more.

Seoul BBQ offers diners a unique experience and an opportunity to interact with the ingredients, allowing them to cook various meats at their leisure and enjoy the cuisine of a Japanese-Korean blend. Try rainbow rolls with fried galbi, or cook a soup right at the table for the freshest experience possible.

name: Smokin' Fins Grill - Arvada
description: Smokin Fins is a regional restaurant concept featuring a unique menu that blends ocean fresh seafood, sushi and house smoked specialties such as prime rib on Friday & Saturday nights. Smokin Fins truly is the food and beverage destination with something for everyone. Please note that we reserve a large portion of our restaurant for walk ins only, please contact us directly with any questions about availability.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent food and service.

name: P.F. Chang's - Aurora
description:
P.F. Chang’s is a restaurant concept that honors the 2,000-year-old Asian tradition of wok cooking and believes in making food from scratch every day in every restaurant. With a Farm to Wok™ food philosophy at its core, P.F. Chang’s chefs hand-roll dim sum, hand chop and slice all vegetables and meats, handcraft every sauce and wok-cook each recipe, every day in every restaurant using wholesome, fresh ingredients.

With roots in Chinese cooking, the culinary landscape at P.F. Chang’s now stretches across Asia with diverse, culturally inspired recipes including hand-rolled sushi, Vietnamese-style soups and bowls, traditional Chinese dim sum, wok-fired chicken and beef entrées, and family style noodles and rice. All made from scratch every day.

topReview.highlightedText: Great atmosphere and ambiance. Our server Michael, was warm,  caring, other-centered, smiled a lot, was upbeat made our night out extra special! The broccoli chicken was delicious and the orange chicken was the best we have ever had. Thanks for a great night!

name: Lucky Pie - Louisville
description:
Lucky Pie in Louisville shows that pizza can be every bit as healthy as other cuisines. By using real, quality food from the eatery garden and local Boulder and Denver area farms, each Neapolitan style pizza is true to cultural traditions while being good for you. With all the major food groups involved, it really is a balanced choice.

Custom designed pizza choices include such unique ingredients as brussels sprouts, roasted beets, cipollini onions and smoked mozzarella. When you’re looking for something different, you can also turn to Lucky Pie for great antipasti boards, salads and unique appetizers

topReview.highlightedText: Attentive service, good margs. We didn’t have pizza but certainly will next time. They looked great. Word to the wise for the first time guest, the signage for Sweet Cow is much more prominent. They share the building which I didn’t know.

name: Azitra - Broomfield
description: Azitra Indian Restaurant in Broomfield, CO, offers authentic Indian cuisines with personal, group and business dining accommodations. We offer a richly varied menu of fresh, natural ingredients, wholesome sauces and a combination of flavorful spices that encourage a depth of flavor. Meat lovers will savor our lamb, chicken and seafood entrees whether grilled, tandoori style or simmered in one of our light sauces. We welcome group dinning and individual alike. Make your online reservation today!

topReview.highlightedText: Great food, very friendly staff. We were pleasantly surprised at how good the food was. The staff was very nice and helpful. The decor inside the restaurant is ordinary but we really enjoyed sitting outside.

name: Sonoma'z Wine Bar & Grill
description: Based on freshness, diversity and artistic use of the finest ingredients, Sonoma’z Wine Bar & Grill prides itself on the imagination and creativity found in Colorado-inspired cuisine. Pair one of our signature dishes with a glass of wine from our thoughtfully-crafted beverage menu featuring robust California wines and locally crafted Colorado brews.

topReview.highlightedText: Great place to stop in for a quiet dinner.  Food was geeat and service was very friendly!

name: Zingers Bar & Grill
description:
Enjoy casual elegance while dining on regional favorites at this north Denver restaurant located in the Clubhouse of Todd Creek Golf Club. Offering a relaxing bar and lounge atmosphere to enjoy a quick bite before you tee off or after your round to tally your score.

A full service restaurant with mountainous views and breathtaking sunsets is sure to entertain all family, friends, clients or guests.

topReview.highlightedText: Still consistently good food and even with the staffing shortage that everyone feels they are making it work.

name: Timberline Grill - Ameristar Casino Black Hawk
description:
With its walls of reclaimed timber, intricately carved wooden bar and solid cherry wood furnishings, the Timberline Grill pays homage to the best Colorado craftsmanship. And its cuisine is equally impeccable. When you’re savoring one of our signature dishes, such as cedar plank salmon or roasted prime rib, in front of a roaring fire, it's easy to imagine that you're high up in the Rockies, experiencing the deep peace that can only be found in an isolated cabin. One that serves Chocolate Avalanche Cake, that is.

Guests must be 21 or older to be on the first floor of the resort, including Centennial Food Hall, Waypost Deli, Timberline Grill and Starbucks. We look forward to your next visit. *Guests with reservations in Timberline Grill may go to the front of the casino security line. Please indicate the name of your reservation with security upon arrival.

topReview.highlightedText: Steak was very good but sides could have used some work and bisque was ok but the pieces of shell shouldn’t have been there.

name: Park Center Lounge
description:
At this time, we are not accepting reservations. Tables are first come first serve. Please use the online waitlist below to add yourself to the waitlist (if we are on a wait)
Parties must arrive within 10 min of table ready time.
Due to limited capacity, no parties more than 10 people and a 3 hour time slot will be allowed for dining. If we are not at max capacity and don’t need the table, parties could potentially stay longer. Double-bookings same day is not allowed and will not be honored even if under a different name, only a 3 hour time slot per guest can be guaranteed.
There is a $10 minimum spend per guest during Karaoke hours.

Park Center Lounge is a comfortable place to get excellent pub style/american food and fantastic craft cocktails. Although it sits in a strip mall, the quality of the food is outstanding, the place is clean and has a very warm and classy interior design. It is also the Best Karaoke Bar in Colorado featuring karaoke every night from 6PM on.

topReview.highlightedText: We had a large party. The staff was kind and very helpful. Great food. Good drinks. Sang songs and had a great time.

name: Martini's Bistro
description:
Martinis Bistro offers upscale, eclectic yet approachable dining with a classy, comfortable atmosphere. ​Whether you’re looking to plan a romantic date night, a corporate event, a family gathering​, or share a round of cocktails and appetizers with friends, Martinis Bistro will exceed your expectations.

Come experience excellent service, quality food, and outstanding beverages on the prettiest patio in Longmont or inside our historic, Victorian home. We are eager to impress you.

**PLEASE NOTE - DUE TO LIMITED SEATING AND HIGH VOLUME, REQUESTS FOR SPECIAL SEATING (i.e. the patio, sunroom, etc) IS ON A FIRST COME, FIRST SERVE BASIS PER RESERVATION AND GROUP SIZE. WE APPRECIATE YOUR UNDERSTANDING.

topReview.highlightedText: The menu is evolving with the seasons. We really are enjoying the variety and specials. We had the “Cajun” Snapper and the center cut Flatiron Steak.  There was nothing left to take home!  Our waiter Tony did a wonderful job pacing our dinner experience and also helping us choose wine. We are fortunate to be able to frequent Martini’s. We look forward to our next visit.

name: P.F. Chang's - Broomfield
description: P.F. Chang's is a restaurant concept that honors the 2,000-year-old Asian tradition of wok cooking and believes in making food from scratch every day in every restaurant. With a Farm to Wok™ food philosophy at its core, P.F. Chang's chefs hand-roll dim sum, hand chop and slice all vegetables and meats, handcraft every sauce and wok-cook each recipe, every day in every restaurant using wholesome, fresh ingredients. With roots in Chinese cooking, the culinary landscape at P.F. Chang's now stretches across Asia with diverse, culturally inspired recipes including hand-rolled sushi, Vietnamese-style soups and bowls, traditional Chinese dim sum, wok-fired chicken and beef entrées, and family style noodles and rice. All made from scratch every day.

topReview.highlightedText: Good food, great service. Horrible bass-heavy electronic music - probably won't be back until that changes.

name: Sugarbeet
description: Our locally owned restaurant offers a refreshing collection of Seasonal American Cuisine in an intimate and contemporary setting. Our seasonally changing menu emphasizes our creativity and passion for using the freshest ingredients possible and supporting local growers and ranchers. Join us for a memorable evening of delicious food with friends. In addition to our warm and inviting dining rooms, we have outdoor seating on our patios when weather permits. We can accommodate your next group function and can help you with a personalized menu for your event. We look forward to seeing you soon!

topReview.highlightedText: Sugarbeet never disappoints! The cocktails, cuisine, and quality of service keep me coming back routinely. Ari and Ben are warm, professional, personable, and are doing a fantastic job running Longmont’s best restaurant. Thank you gentlemen for all your hard work through these challenging times in providing your customers a safe place to escape from it all for a few hours for a civilized evening…

name: Roxy Restaurant & Bar - Isle Casino Black Hawk Colorado
description: Refined food in a relaxed atmosphere. Savor seasonal menus featuring fresh, locally-sourced fare. Reservations are recommended.

topReview.highlightedText: The dinner was great, the wait staff was super even though they were a little under staffed on a Thursday night.  We thoroughly enjoyed the meal and the dessert, especially the Tiramisu was amazing.

name: Caprese Trattoria
description:
Welcome to Caprese Trattoria. We are an authentic Italian restaurant with home made mozzarellas, pastas, desserts, and more. Come to join us in a rustic, casual, but modern ambiance. We also have a beautiful large bar and two large patios that will make your experience very pleasant. Looking forward to cooking you an incredible authentic Italian meal. Buon Appetito!
-Chef Marco Monanni & Staff

topReview.highlightedText: It was our first time there and all four of us agreed that the food (and service) was excellent!

name: The Garden Grille at the Hilton Garden Inn Arvada
description: A freshly prepared breakfast is offered daily in the Garden Grille restaurant. We also have a delicious dinner menu. Beverages are served in the cozy Pavilion Lounge and select properties also offer a full bar.

name: Greenbriar Inn, The
description: Opened in 1967, The Greenbriar Inn is an elegant restaurant, tavern and private event space located in the north Boulder countryside and nestled at the foot of the Rocky Mountains. The surrounding 20 acres features two ponds, striking woodland, and thriving vegetable, fruit, and flower gardens. The cuisine focuses on seasonal, American classics and is complimented by a 900 label award-winning wine cellar.

topReview.highlightedText:
It is always a treat to eat at the Greenbriar.   From basic burger (and truffle fries) to the outstanding Halibut, the meals are excellent.  The vegetarian risotto is one of the best I've ever had.  Caesar salad is large enough to split.  Their garden provides wonderfully fresh vegetables and basil.

And the staff is awesome.

name: Flights Wine Cafe
description:
Valentine's Day is a special menu.
$45 per person includes appetizer, salad, entree, dessert and 1 glass of champagne. They can purchase additional drinks, wine, bottles from the Wine Menu.
Our seatings are 4:00 - 6pm; 6:15-8:00pm & 8:15 to 10pm

Same day reservations cannot be made after 2:00pm online. After 2pm call restaurant direct.

A Wine Cafe featuring over 100 wines with over 35 available daily by the glass. Great beers from all over the world & a nice Light Eats menu to compliment your beverage of choice. We are open at our new location (7714 Grandview Avenue, Olde Town Arvada)

topReview.highlightedText: Good fun tasting wine in a small house that has been converted into a wine tasting area that serves small plates of food to compliment the wine tasting.  Come early because it can fill up fast and the noise level makes quiet conversations difficult.

name: Masters
description:
Welcome to Masters! We’re so happy you’re here.

We are currently accepting reservations for inside and outside dining on the patio for parties of up to 8 guests. Walk-in’s are accepted if tables are available.

Not interested in dining in with us? Call us at 303.926.1723*2 with curbside pickup or carry out available,

From our family to yours – thank you for your support

topReview.highlightedText: Great food, great service!  Plenty of staff and very attentive.

name: Crossroads Bar and Grill at The Summit Thornton
description:
The Crossroads Bar and Grille is the full-service restaurant and sports bar at The Summit. We offer comfortable dining on delicious food for lunch, dinner, late night snacks, and anytime in between in a fun, lively atmosphere.

If you’re a sports fan, you’ll find Crossroads to be the ultimate sports bar. There’s not a bad seat in the house with tables for two or a crowd and our full-service bar has a huge selection of beers on tap. Catch your favorite team or sport on one of our big-screen TVs. If there’s a pro game on, it’s on at Crossroads!

topReview.highlightedText: Bowling was great and reasonable price wise. Laser tag was fun. Game room was fun but the prizes were pretty cheap looking. The food was ok except for the pizza. name: Pint Brothers
description:
Pint Brothers Alehouse welcomes you to the family to share our passion for cold beer, delicious bites and great friends.
Pint Brothers Alehouse delivers hand-crafted casual style and flavor in a space that connects the social vibrancy of our indoor beer garden and bustling bar. Pint Brothers does just what our name suggests - it gives you your moment to become family over your pints. Start off with one of our eclectic beers or rotating seasonal brews, tasting flights - or even beer cocktail for the more refined palettes. In addition to hydrated and happy, Pint Brothers will also keep you welcomed and well-fed, offering an honest menu of mastered comfort classics.

topReview.highlightedText:
We came to Pint Brothers as part of Restaurant Week so we had some items not normally on their everyday menu, but their regular menu does look good as well. The food was prepared very well and was delicious! Not your typical menu that you find at ordinary restaurants. 

Only downside is that it is located inside the Marriott hotel in DTC that has paid parking lots for whatever reason (it’s not downtown so paid lots seem ridiculous in this area). name: Farm House Restaurant at Breckenridge Brewery
description:
Farm House Restaurant at Breckenridge Brewery is a cozy restaurant that specializes in handcrafted New American food and beer. The restaurant features multiple dining spaces for guests. Enjoy a meal in the rustic dining room or outdoors on the back porch. There's also a beer garden complete with firepits and games like bocce, corn hole and giant Jenga. Farm House Restaurant is a great place to get away for the day and relax.

Begin the meal with some cast iron bread served with smoky creamed butter and seasonal preserves or try the baked brie, house-made cornbread or stout brined chicken wings. Farm House Restaurant offers a variety of fresh and hearty entrées for the main course. Options include dishes like smoked espresso pork osso bucco, crispy chicken gremolata, NY strip steak, bacon apple bleu mac ‘n cheese and the signature Farm House meatloaf or pot pie.

topReview.highlightedText: We enjoyed everything about our visit. Thanks for making the dinner special.

name: Bj's Restaurant & Brewhouse - Denver West
description: Time counts at BJ’s Restaurant & Brewhouse. Since our humble beginnings back in 1978, we’ve continued to refine our brewhouse experience to make BJ’s a place where you can make the most of any meal. We want BJ’s to be a place where the moment you leave is the moment you plan on coming back. We pride ourselves in our craft and attention to detail. Our guests come here for our award-winning handcrafted beer. They come here for the Southern California twist we’ve put on the Chicago-style deep dish pizza. And they come here for our Pizookies®, our world-renowned dessert. But above all we know people come here to make their good times better. So in many ways we haven’t just crafted a brand, but a mindset. And our guests are the reason for this. And it’s because of them we’re continually striving to make sure every moment they choose to spend with us counts. Welcome to BJ’s, a restaurant with a Brewhouse soul.

Featured by Guy Fieri on Food Network's Diners Drive-Ins &; Dives, our bird is better than the rest--humanely raised, all natural chickens are brined for hours, dipped in buttermilk, seasoned with GLUTEN-FREE flour, and then fried to crispy golden perfection.

For curbside pick-up and delivery, order WeDeliver online anytime after 4pm until we close. It is easy-peasy!
Order Online: postchickenandbeer.com/location

topReview.highlightedText: Great Chicken, excellent craft beer, the side dishes were awesome and the blueberry handpie a la mode was fantastic.

name: Black Cat
description:
*Reservations are limited and released weekly each Monday at noon for the following week.

Upon arrival, you will be greeted with hors d’oeuvres and aperitif at our historic farmstead. Explore the restored, historic farm buildings, greenhouse, and working organic farm, or find a private spot to relax.

Dinner is served at private tables in the historic blacksmith barn, garden cabanas, or beneath the patio pergola. The farm hosts up to 10 people per table. ( For larger parties please visit our website for our Guide For Private Events)

You will enjoy three courses, family-style, based on the day's bountiful harvest. Fresh salads from the garden, tomatoes still warm from the sun, and heritage pork or lamb roasted over plum wood embers are some of the flavors that await. Wines from our award-winning list, as well as craft beer selections, are available by pre-order delivery.

Cost:$125/pp
7 PM arrival time

For More Details: www.blackcatboulder.com
farmdinners@blackcatboulder.com

topReview.highlightedText: This was our 2nd time eating at the Black Cat Farm (since the restaurant stopped serving due to COVID) and we will definitely be back for more. I'm vegan and my wife is gluten free. The staff did a wonderful job preparing a delicious ensemble of dishes that left us both with big smiles and full bellies. Perhaps the best part of the experience is the amazing setting. Meals are served in romantic little glass-walled structures among the flowers and vegetables of the working farm. We just learned that the farm is open year round with individual wood stoves heating each structure. Will definitely come back in the winter to experience the farm in the snow. Highly recommend Black Cat Farm for a special treat!

name: Jill's in the St Julien Hotel
description:

Located in Boulder, Colo., a noted food destination that is home to one of the nation’s top Farmer’s Markets, Jill’s

Interim Culinary Director Michael Griffith and Chef de Cuisine Steven Yacovetta sources its ingredients through partnerships with local farms, creameries and ranches, its own on-­site garden and Boulder’s seasonal Farmer’s Market – conveniently located across the street – where the chefs procure the freshest herbs, vegetables and fruits. These ingredients are used to create scratch-­made food, including pasta, bread, pastries, sauces, jus and more.

Our rooftop terrace is the perfect spot to enjoy the golden hour and incredible views of the sun dropping behind the Rocky Mountains. Let our friendly staff serve you at one of our abundant outdoor tables. You can't beat a Colorado night at the Upper Deck.

Diners will be able to choose from the favorites when visiting the restaurant. Whether you want samosas to start or some pakora, naan or various kabobs, you will find many choices. There are many soups and salads, and entrŽes range from tandoori meats and kabobs to kormas, curries, masalas, saags, vindaloo and many other classics. Specialty options include butter chicken, shahi dal and goat dishes. When you crave authentic Indian cuisine in a vibrant setting, head to India's Kitchen.

description:
This 1930's-style restaurant balances a sophisticated and intimate dining experience with a casual and friendly atmosphere. Specializing in seafood and steak, the Chop House serves a traditional upscale menu and features weekly specials. The restaurant boasts an extensive wine and martini list, including our popular Moscow Mule, as well as local vodkas, whiskeys and liqueurs.

The Chop House is a gem found nestled among the brick buildings lining Historic Downtown Loveland. Reservations are always encouraged, especially for large parties. The Chop House's Roosevelt Room is perfect for hosting private events, such as seminars and business meetings or holiday parties and rehearsal dinners. Unique menu selections are provided specifically for Roosevelt Room guests to ensure their night is exceptional. The Chop House is the perfect place to celebrate with family and loved ones.

topReview.highlightedText: Everything was spot on. From the smiling hostess to the server and food it was all great.

name: Dickens 300 Prime
description:
Originally built in 1881 by William Henry Dickens a relative of the famous author Charles Dickens, William Henry came to the area in 1860 as a young man, the son of Mary Allen.
 
When he built the opera house he was one of the largest land owners of the time. The parcel that the building sits on was given to his father by Ulysses S. Grant, the president.
 
His goal with the opera house was to bring society and culture to a growing community. He furnished it with lavish sets.
 
The building also housed the original Longmont college in 1885 until a building was completed on Atwood Street.

The site survived the devastating fire which destroyed much of downtown Longmont and has continued to operate under many business ventures since.

She concentrates on beverages and orders and the enjoyment of her tables. Abby was solicitous without hovering. She made my day by allowing me to substitute one of the offerings on the Chef's Choice menu. Everything on this seasonal offers was an amazing blend of natural flavors enhanced but not overwhelmed by spices. The soft shelled crab was tender without being greasy. The speck crumbs and pistachio bits in the chilled melon soup were perfect. The steamed halibut was very tender and not rubbery. The only drawback to the evening was being seated near a table of six men who became louder as the alcohol increased. Not frat party loud but I had to raise my voice more than once to be heard by my husband seated across the table. This is always awkward for a restaurant. I am sure something would have been said should the volume continued to increase. Please patronize this restaurant to reward all the hard work and attention to detail that makes it very special. And please use your inside voices.

name: Grand View Dining Room at the Garden of the Gods Resort & Club
description:
RESERVATIONS REQUIRED

With a backdrop of the famed Pikes Peak, Grand View Dining Room serves up extraordinary flavors and culinary artistry, along with personable, attentive service. This restaurant offers healthy options, daily features, and special prix fixe menus.

Grand View Dining Room is one of the city’s best restaurants. It’s the perfect place to celebrate any moment, entertain clients, and enjoy time with family.

topReview.highlightedText: Not a more beautiful place to have lunch in the City!

name: Red Lobster - Lone Tree
description: Red Lobster welcomes you by offering PRIORITY SEATING to reduce your wait time in the restaurant, so you can spend more time doing the things you love. Or, come enjoy a drink at our bar and a Tasting Plate while you wait. Red Lobster is the world's largest and most loved seafood restaurant company, offering high quality, freshly-prepared seafood, sourced in a way that is traceable, sustainable and responsible. We offer lunch and dinner daily, featuring classics like our Ultimate Feast®, Garlic Shrimp Scampi and Parrot Isle Jumbo Coconut Shrimp, and feature limited time flavors and preparations during events like Lobsterfest®, Crabfest® and Endless Shrimp®. And, who can resist our famous warm and cheesy Cheddar Bay Biscuits®? To learn more visit www.redlobster.com

topReview.highlightedText: Greyfood and great service

name: La Vita Bella
description:
Welcome to La Vita Bella, the place to be if you aspire to experience the good things in life.

La Vita Bella, located in the heart of the historic district, features farm to table fare, unique craft cocktails, biodynamic wine, local brews, events and live music. Our menu offers Contemporary American cuisine featuring locally sourced ingredients. Executive Chef LeRoy Alvarado prepares his dishes from scratch and cooks to perfection. Our grassroots ambitions are to cultivate resourceful, local business relations to help grow Longmont's economic origins... the farmland. This creates a connected sustainable ecology that can be experienced in all of our seasonal dishes. When you dine with us, you are invited to slow down, and enjoy "The Beautiful Life".

topReview.highlightedText: Exceptional! Our new favorite spot!

description: Coming Soon!

description: Coming Soon!

description: Coming Soon!

name: P.F. Chang's - Littleton
description: P.F. Chang's is a restaurant concept that honors the 2,000-year-old Asian tradition of wok cooking and believes in making food from scratch every day in every restaurant. With a Farm to Wok™ food philosophy at its core, P.F. Chang's chefs hand-roll dim sum, hand chop and slice all vegetables and meats, handcraft every sauce and wok-cook each recipe, every day in every restaurant using wholesome, fresh ingredients. With roots in Chinese cooking, the culinary landscape at P.F. Chang's now stretches across Asia with diverse, culturally inspired recipes including hand-rolled sushi, Vietnamese-style soups and bowls, traditional Chinese dim sum, wok-fired chicken and beef entrées, and family style noodles and rice. All made from scratch every day.

topReview.highlightedText: Great spot for lunch. Got a beautiful booth, overlooking the mountains. Service was great. Food was delicious, and the "lunch portion" option was plenty of food to fill us up. We had not been here for a while, and both of us commented that we need to make this back into the regular rotation of where we dine.

name: Blue Agave Grill - Fort Collins
description:
We are a full service restaurant serving contemporary southwestern cuisine with a full service bar. We are a scratch kitchen with many gluten free options as well as a large margarita selection, house infused tequilas, and homemade sangria. Our outdoor seating accompanied by fire pits surrounds the historic art museum in old town Fort Collins CO. From guacamole made to order to our vibrant atmosphere, come on down and try a flight of our favorite drinks.

Happy Hour
- Monday thru Friday 3pm to 6pm
- $5 Margaritas
- $3/4 Beer
- $2.00 off all Wine
- $3.00 Wells

Brunch Menu!
Saturdays and Sundays from 11am-2pm, full menu available at 11am in addition.
With house-infused bloody Maria’s and BOTTOMLESS mimosas!

topReview.highlightedText: So many interesting food and drink options, great happy hour specials, super service. Our new favorite restaurant!

name: Jax Fish House & Oyster Bar - Fort Collins
description:
Jax Fish House is open and ready to welcome you for both indoor and outdoor dining and curbside pick-up 7 days a week. Any way you choose to dine, we got you. For curbside pick-up order online! It is easy-peasy, and you can place an order for a future date, too.
Order Online: jaxfishhouse.com/fort-collins
----------
Jax Fish House in Fort Collins works tirelessly to bring fresh caught seafood and fine coastal food to the surrounding landlocked community. The dining experience, whether outdoors or at your home, focuses on sustainable seafood when choosing who to partner with to provide guests only the freshest seafood.

topReview.highlightedText:
I recognize and appreciate all the restaurants have endured through the last year and a half.  My friend was a bit disappointed that the menu items had decreased on the happy hour menu.  Yet, it’s the new world we’re living in.
Still my favorite restaurant even though happy hour is all I can afford.  I want to support you as often as I am able.

name: Cowboy Star - Colorado Springs
description:
As a new addition to the University Village lifestyle center of Colorado Springs, Cowboy Star is dedicated to providing an unmatched attention to detail and a level of service that immediately sets us apart. Cowboy Star guests are the number one priority and guest satisfaction is the base upon which our entire concept is built.
Our level of service is only matched by our celebration of regional American heirloom recipes offered with genuine neighborly hospitality. We are committed to supporting local and regional farmers, fishers and producers by cooking food that recaptures the simple and pure tastes found in locally grown, natural and organic ingredients. We strive to raise awareness of a more sustainable food future, while helping to restore a sense of community that brings us back to a more homegrown time.

topReview.highlightedText: We all ate different things and they were are good and the presentation was very good.  I would come back and try another item on the menu.

name: Ambli Global Cuisine - Colorado Springs
description: Ambli Global Cuisine is thrilled to be in University Village Colorado (UVC).  We started the Ambli concept over 8 years ago and we have always had the consumer mindset at heart.  We have created an elegant and beautiful restaurant to take you on an exquisite journey.  The Ambli family has a genuine passion for food and service.   Our globally inspired Food and Cocktail programs are approachable, unique, flavorful and balanced.  You’ll find influences from Indian, Asian, Mediterranean and Latin American cuisines.   Ambli is the Place Where Food and Culture Meet and the Conversation Begins.

topReview.highlightedText: Our second visit didn’t disappoint. Grace and several other staff were amazing and they remembered us from our first visit. I believe we have had the entire menu minus the seafood & sushi due to food allergies.

name: Exotikka Indian Cusine
description:
Exotikka delivers the rich, exotic spices from India straight to your plate for a truly unique flavor experience. Curries, Tikkas, & Naan's made right in the Entertainment District of Lone Tree, CO.
Our 20 years Experienced chef From Nepal and Cooked at London For Over 15 years. The One and Only Madhav Shrestha came to denver in 2012 and opened a restaurant name as Mehak's Aroma at cherry creek Denver Downtown and ran for 2 years before opening Exotikka Indian Dining as owner with two other partners. Bibek Rauniyar who is young Enthusiast Restaurant Owner of Namaste India Arvada (ESTD 2013) and Focused on Providing Excellence Restaurant experience for all Our Patrons with Delicious Indian Food. Jaskaran Thiara as 1st Partner came in with his eager and passion for opening an indian restaurant which he could give an authentic and Modern feeling for all patrons at a same time.

topReview.highlightedText: Quiet atmosphere and very good food.  Did not feel rushed and pace of service was very good.  Will definitely return.

name: Chef Tasting Menu at Urban Village
description: Coming Soon!

topReview.highlightedText: The chef tasting was a wonderful way to try and experience Indian food.    The chef was very nice and funny and personable and delivered our food numerous times and explained the dishes.   I’m going to go back for my birthday dinner with family in s few weeks.

name: Cascades - The Stanley Hotel
description:
Cascades, a Classic American Restaurant and Steakhouse, is housed in the historic 109-year old Stanley Hotel. Join us for lunch or dinner in our dining room. The menu features wild game, beef, seafood, burgers, sandwiches, pasta and Colorado specialties. We also offer delectable desserts.

Our bar and lounge offers seasonal cocktails and a whisk(e)y menu with over 1,000 varieties. Ask our bartenders to help select a distinctive flight! The wine list offers a selection of sparkling, white, and red varietals to please your palate.

topReview.highlightedText: Nice experience but is  close to bar which may be very noisy

name: Ember
description:
IMPORTANT! PLEASE READ THE FOLLOWING STATEMENTS:
NEW!
Ember will no longer be offering a la cart dining. Instead, we are happy to announce a brand new three course prix fixe menu. Three courses: $60/person or, you may choose two courses for $50. A-La-Carte dining is available in the bar.

topReview.highlightedText: Great ambiance and merriment!

name: Bonny and Read Fresh Seafood and Steaks
description: Colorado Springs first Fresh Seafood Restaurant. We offer Lobster, steam Clams, oysters and some of the best Colorado beef in the state.

topReview.highlightedText: The  lobster roll, lobster-stuffed cod, and calamari appetizer were all extraordinary, tasty, and fresh! Service was perfect and polite. And I love the wall art!

name: Tiller's Kitchen & Bar
description: Welcome to Tiller’s Kitchen and Bar, a contemporary Colorado kitchen where we think Colorado first in everything we do. At Tiller's you will find an approachable, unique menu that highlights the areas best farmers, artisans, and producers.

topReview.highlightedText:
Great meal with my wife. We had a few special requests ant the staff was very accommodating.  Our server was very attentive and the ambiance of the place was exactly what we were looking for.  I started with some lovely appetizers and drinks.  Amazing mac and cheese dish and delicious halibut sandwich.

Truly enjoyable experience. Thank you to the staff and crew.

name: Vintage
description:
Classic French-Inspired Brasserie.

If your desired reservation time is unavailable, please try calling the restaurant. We may be able to secure a booking.

We apologize for the inconvenience, but we no longer accept online reservations for brunch. Please call to book a table.

topReview.highlightedText:
We treated ourselves to brunch on Monday and we’re so glad we did! The menu features dishes you probably wouldn’t go to the trouble of preparing for yourself… Especially for breakfast… I loved the prosciutto wrapped asparagus  w/poached eggs and hollandaise sauce, perfectly caramelized onions, sautéed mushrooms … and baguette… such a scrumptious  meal!
My partner really enjoyed his eggs Benedict as well…
We live on the western slope of Colorado so we don’t get to Vail very often… But next time we’re in the area we’re definitely coming back to vintage!!

name: Colorado Mountain Brewery
description:
Stop in for a nice cold beer at Colorado Mountain Brewery and you will quickly notice that the food being offered is out of this world as well. This has turned into quite the lunch and dinner spot within the Colorado Springs metro area. The fish and chips, along with spicy chicken wings, are just two of many menu items at Colorado Mountain Brewery that will go well with your favorite beverage.



Colorado Mountain Brewery is a great place to hang out with your friends watching the big game. The list of beers on tap will impress even the most discerning of tastes in the group.

topReview.highlightedText: We enjoy great ambience/environment, good beer and food all with friendy and excellent service!  Keep up the great work!

name: BJ's Restaurant & Brewhouse - Westminster
description: Time counts at BJ's Restaurant & Brewhouse. Since our humble beginnings back in 1978, we've continued to refine our brewhouse experience to make BJ's a place where you can make the most of any meal. We want BJ's to be a place where the moment you leave is the moment you plan on coming back. We pride ourselves in our craft and attention to detail. Our guests come here for our award-winning handcrafted beer. They come here for the Southern California twist we've put on the Chicago-style deep dish pizza. And they come here for our Pizookies®, our world-renowned dessert. But above all we know people come here to make their good times better. So in many ways we haven't just crafted a brand, but a mindset. And our guests are the reason for this. And it's because of them we're continually striving to make sure every moment they choose to spend with us counts. Welcome to BJ's, a restaurant with a Brewhouse soul.

topReview.highlightedText: Beer is always good, the Rib eye dips were great as was the double pork chop, the mushroom burger was good too although the bun was a bit dry.  We'll be back!

name: Four by Brother Luck
description: Four by Brother Luck- A new American Restaurant focusing on Four Course tasting menus. Bravo TV Celebrity Chef Brother Luck is influenced by the IV key sources who supply our ingredients; the hunter, the gatherer, the fisherman, and the farmer. These people are truly the beginning of every dish we imagine as the seasons change. The seasonal menus have been set up in four quadrants, each quadrant being a self- guided four-course menu tasting for one person. A guest can either stay with the pre-set tasting menu or can utilize all four menus to create their own custom four-course tasting experience.

topReview.highlightedText:
We live in Denver and made a special trip for an evening to dine at Four for our first visit. We were really impressed. We requested outdoor seating and it was a beautiful evening and the people-watching was so much fun- with families lining up for ice cream a few doors down. 
We eat at good restaurants frequently and Four was simply a cut above- gourmet food beautifully presented with unique combinations and tastes.  Stand-outs were the scallop ceviche, lamb roulade as well as the chocolate mousse dessert.

Thank you!

name: La Bella Vita
description: This restaurant is owned by a native Italian Chef Giuliano Casulli from Bari and offers Colorado Springs a true mix of Northern and Southern Italian cuisine on La Bella Vita’s menu.

topReview.highlightedText: Amazing Server!!

name: Swiss Chalet - Woodland Park
description: Built in 1962 with spectacular views of Pikes Peak, the Swiss Chalet offers continental cuisine prepared thoughtfully. Enjoy lunch or dinner Tuesday through Sunday either in our quaint dining room or comfortable patio.

topReview.highlightedText: Love the ambiance at Swiss Chalet. We come back here time and time again. The staff are friendly, professional and knowledgeable. Our meals have always been excellently prepared and enjoyed. We drive well over an hour one way just to treat ourselves to this upscaled cuisine. This last time we brought our daughter and son-in-law to introduce them to this delightful place and they were wowed!

name: Glen Eyrie
description: Escape the ordinary and create memories that will last a lifetime! Attending tea in the Glen Eyrie Castle is a unique and historic experience.  This place leaves you in awe and invites you to be a part of something much bigger than yourself.

topReview.highlightedText: Second time here for tea. Usually not my thing but I love it here. Our server, Robin, was great. We wanted for nothing. This is a don't miss when in Colorado Springs,

name: Cabin Juice at Gravity Haus
description: Cabin Juice is the place where you come to swap tales and plan your next adventure. We offer a seasonal menu highlighting ingredients from sustainable farms, finely crafted cocktails and family-style dishes. Located at the Base of Peak 9, Cabin Juice offers casual counter service for breakfast and lunch and a seated dinner service every night of the week. We here at Cabin Juice are big on having fun, while maintaining a standard of excellence when it comes to the guest experience.

topReview.highlightedText: Very nice apres HH.  Enjoyed the elk and black cod.  Food was fresh and not heavy so a break from Breck comfort food.

name: Jax Fish House & Oyster Bar - Colorado Springs
description:
Jax Fish House and Oyster Bar Colorado Springs is OPEN for INDOOR and PATIO dining as well as curbside carryout service and delivery. ***Please note whether the table you are booking is inside or outside. Tables booked outside cannot be moved inside unless space is available at the time.***

Please visit jaxfishhouse.com/colorado-springs to order from our menu AND Post Brewing AND The Tender Project.

We currently allow only service animals for both inside and outdoor dining.

topReview.highlightedText: Pleasantly surprised with this trip to Jax! We have dined there before but for whatever reason this experience stood out the most. It was a fairly busy and rainy Thursday night but the wine was flowing, the oysters shucked, and the fish was prepared exceptionally well. Our server Priscilla was fabulous. We will gladly be going back.

name: Red Gravy
description:
Red Gravy offers upscale casual modern Italian fare.
Chef/Owner Eric Brenner spent his first decade in the industry inside Italian kitchens. Talking up St. Louis' wide-ranging Italian eatery scene, which gets as specific as regional specialties, he says he's wanted to have a place like this since he was 18.
"We're going to start very simple and accessible," he says, "we'll play to the crowd and start a dialogue, then grow the menu with community input."
"Simple," includes dishes like his tomato bisque, with which only has five ingredients. "It's all about the perfect balance. And that gets back to the essence of good Italian food: quality ingredients, very few, in perfect balance." Other examples include his St. Louis-style, thin-crust pizza, best compared to a flat-bread.

topReview.highlightedText: We were seated at our reservation time. Greeting by host and server several times. Great food and wine selection. Was recommended and will recommend to family and friends.

name: BoLD Restaurant and Bar
description:
BoLD serves an elevated American breakfast and brunch, followed by a Mediterranean-inspired lunch, happy hour and dinner.

We're open from 8:00 a.m Monday-Friday and 7:30 a.m Saturday and Sunday for breakfast and brunch, serve lunch from 11:30, happy hour runs from 2:00-6:00 and dinner's from 5:00-9 p.m. We only accept reservations in the evening - at any other time of day, please phone ahead.

topReview.highlightedText: This place is a gem. I’m Greek, have grown up eating a lot of the food on this menu and they put their own twist on a lot of my faves. The spanakopita and the bakalava are amazing and nothing you’ve ever seen b4 :)

name: Montauk Seafood Grill
description:
Serving dinner nightly 5-930pm.

All reservations require credit card information only kept on file in the event guests no-show or cancel within 24 hours. In the case of cancellations we only ask for as much communication as possible to avoid a $25/per person cancellation charge. Email us at montaukvail@gmail.com or leave a voicemail if needed to let us know 970-476-2601.

Reservations are taken for inside dining rooms only. Patio tables are ONLY available on a first come, first served basis. Patio diners cannot be guaranteed a table inside if inclement weather is in the area.

For parties greater than six please call us at the restaurant during business hours or send an email to montaukvail@gmail.com

Where the oceans meet the mountains.
Est. 1987, serving FRESH seafood from all corners of the globe & high quality Colorado steaks.

topReview.highlightedText: Great food.

name: Twist - Breckenridge
description:
Twist is located in Breckenridge's downtown historic district. We offer a locally sourced seasonal menu that can change daily based on what's available and what looks fresh. Our menu is eclectic American with an emphasis on fish and game. We are chef owned and operated and love making people happy by serving delicious food.

So bring your friends and family, and let them enjoy what's a little bit off the map when it comes to ordinary cuisine. Twist is something a little different and very special, and we can't wait to welcome you!

topReview.highlightedText:
We had a 4:30 scheduled dinner.  Our first visit.  Our host Sarah and waiter, Rick, was 5⭐️ 
The service was as exceptional as the food.
We celebrated a birthday and decided we’d give as our gift,  a return visit to Twist…ASAP 😀

name: South Ridge Seafood
description:
Since 1998 South Ridge Seafood Grill has been serving the finest seafood in the Colorado Rockies. Our menu relies heavily on the freshest available seafood but also includes hand cut steak & fresh Colorado ingredients.

Located on Main Street in La Cima Mall, South Ridge Seafood Grill is a perfect spot for drinks & appetizers or a multi course dinner served by Summit County’s finest waitstaff & bartenders.

After a day of skiing or a summer hike through the Rockies, our Happy Hour always includes oysters on the 1/2 shell, peel & eat shrimp, Colorado micro brews & great value wines.

topReview.highlightedText: This was one of the best dinners I have had out in a very long time.  Everything was perfect!!

name: Sushi Rama- Lone Tree
description: We are open daily from 11am - 8pm offering dine-in, take out and delivery through ChowNow.

topReview.highlightedText: Mid afternoon meal and was overall a good spot to satisfy my sushi craving. Not even knowing I came in after 3pm which was happy hour. Never been in a sushi restaurant like this but they explained and it is very easy to understand the concept and pricing structure. Will come back

name: Famous Steakhouse
description:
BEST OVERALL RESTAURANT | BEST STEAK | BEST FINE DINING | BEST CHEESEBURGER (LUNCH) - Colorado Springs Independent & Colorado Springs Gazette

Colorado Springs’ finest upscale steak house and lounge located in the center of downtown. Dine in an elegant and classic steak house environment. Award winning prime steaks, fresh seafood, premium wines and piano bar provide a provocative mix of atmosphere and entertainment. Featuring 30+ Colorado spirits and wines as well as local craft brews.

topReview.highlightedText: The steak was cooked perfectly. Service was great.

name: Sonny Lubick Steakhouse
description: Sonny Lubick Steakhouse is a locally owned and inspired polished casual steakhouse. We have a beautiful main dining room, a private dining room called The Coach's Room, and a casual bar/lounge area.

topReview.highlightedText: From the moment we walked in until the moment we left, I was absolutely baffled by the ambience.  From fresh flowers you can really smell, romantic lighting and a candle at every table, to the absolutely delicious food, every single aspect of this restaurant set the bar higher than anywhere else I've been. They deserve the same respect they give, which is absolutely outstanding. This is going to be our go-to spot for our anniversary, and I can't wait until next time!

name: Bent Fork Grill - Loveland
description: The Bent Fork Grill is quality, flavor, hospitality, art, architecture, scent, warmth, relaxation, sound, and fun. With our award winning menu of diverse American classics, casual elegance and eclectic wine list, the stage is set for our staff to deliver an experience that will melt away the stress, stimulate the palate, and leave you wanting more.

topReview.highlightedText: Everything was perfect!! Got to sit outside and enjoy the water feature! Tatiana our server was fabulous!

name: MacKenzie's Chop House
description: We serve only the finest steaks, chops and seafood combined with innovative cuisine in an upscale, nostalgic environment. MacKenzie’s is perfect for a special occasion or casual gathering and features the finest service in the greater Colorado Springs area. Our cutting edge wine list, extensive martini menu and fine array of single malt scotches all add to the Chophouse tradition.

topReview.highlightedText: The steaks, salads and dessert we split were fabulous.   We had a longtime reservation as we were visiting the area but we were sat in the bar.

name: Prime 25
description:
Prime25 is a modern interpretation of the classic steakhouse, with valet parking two levels of dining and sipping experience. A warm, contemporary touch with a mix of copper, rich wood, glass & steel. Open kitchen serving U.S.D.A prime aged beef with bone in selection. Our seafood is flown in daily to ensure the highest quality of exceptional flavors. We Pride ourselves with superior foods and high quality service with a well-educated team on wines and champagnes.

Upstairs there are private dining rooms for parties or events and a sexier more glamorous take on a lounge. Sit back and enjoy our handcrafted one of a kind cocktails, outside dining and views of the mountains. We are located between downtown & the Broadmoor Hotel. Call 719-216.9344 for details

topReview.highlightedText: Absolutely amazing! Our new favorite!

name: Alpenrose Vail
description:
Where guests become friends..
With lovely prepared dishes from traditional recipes to fine classics and specialties with a touch of international culinary inspiration.
We serve simple tasty home-style cuisine with hearty goulash, dumpling specialties, Kässpätzle and a savoury snack plate as well as a sweet finish with a selection of traditional Alpine desserts like Marillenknödel, Dampfnudeln, Palatschinken or apple strudel.
For families and get-togethers with friends try our Walliser tomato fondue at long, comfy family tables and for our little one's we offer a special kid's menu.
Warmth, hospitality and enjoying life - Welcome to Alpenrose!

topReview.highlightedText: Charming presentation and fun environment.  Delightful cocktails

name: Pepper Tree Restaurant
description: The Pepper Tree restaurant has been a tradition for fine dining in Colorado Springs since 1983. Serving steaks, seafood, lamb, veal and more, the Pepper Tree is legendary for impeccable cuisine, ambiance, service and breathtaking views of the city. The Pepper Tree"s signature Mango Chutney Pepper Steak and other specialties, including Chateaubriand and Steak Diane, are prepared or finished table side.

topReview.highlightedText: We went for our 38th anniversary at our favorite Restaurant. We both had Pepper Steak. Salads with Dill vinaigrette. I had an onion soup and my wife had the melon lobster appetizer. We topped it of with a huge New York cheese cake. Josh and the great team at pepper tree are the finest people you will ever meet. Their service is impeccable and their attention to detail to ensure your experience is memorable is always consistent. We have been coming here for years and will continue to do so. When it comes to special occasions or a company dinner where you want to impress clients you cannot go wrong with the Pepper Tree.

name: The Farmhouse at Jessup Farm
description: Set in an 19th Century home, The Farmhouse at Jessup Farm is a casual restaurant focused on elevated country and healthy farm fare. With a ¼ acre and chicken coop in our backyard, The Farmhouse is proud to offer seasonal menus, made from scratch daily.

topReview.highlightedText: Great food and friendly staff

name: Hana Matsuri Sushi
description:
Hana Matsuri offers entrées including Kobe beef zabuton, New York strip steak, filet mignon, chicken breast, Scottish salmon, lamb loin chop, scallops and single or twin lobster tails. You won't find a menu as long as your arm at Hana Matsuri, but what you do get will be cooked to perfection and your choice of two sides including truffled mashed potato, grilled asparagus, grilled mixed vegetables, french fries, cauliflower puree, house salad or baked sweet potato.

Tempura dinners are also available at Hana Matusuri, served with salad or soup. Noodle dishes are also on offer, and come with salad. If you're just looking for a light lunch or a snack, you will find a wide range of offering at the sushi bar.

topReview.highlightedText: Great food and service!! Love all the sushi options and at the end get the Mochi ice cream!

name: Paella's Restaurant & Bakery
description: Seafood Paella!!!! Yummy !!! Come to Paella’s Restaurant and taste a piece of Spain here in Winter Park.

topReview.highlightedText: This is a restaurant where the staff works very hard to please you. The food was delicious. Excellent value. Maybe the best place to eat in Winter Park now.

name: Beasts and Brews
description:
Enjoy a variety of self pour local brews, perfected classic cuisine, and witness an unforgettable view of the mountain landscape.
Restaurant & Taphouse
You’ll love dining at Beasts and Brews. Our selection of beer, wine, and spirits in our self-pouring taps is the first thing you’ll notice in our rustic, yet sophisticated restaurant. The best seats in the house are placed strategically on our gorgeous patio facing an incredible view of the mountains, next to our roaring fire pits. Inside seating has the same phenomenal view through our open-concept windows. Chef Noah has outdone himself with the quality of food. You’ll find delicious cuisine from classic burgers, tacos, and mac n cheese to short ribs and rib eye.
Butcher Shop
The Beasts of Beasts and Brews started as an idea of integrating a butcher shop inside of the restaurant itself. We are dedicated to serving locally-sourced, fresh meat. When it comes to purchasing meat, you have two major options—a butcher, or a nearby supermarket. We can offer the freshest, high-quality meat that will leave your taste buds begging for more and of course, we’re always available to give you some quick tips on how to best prepare it.
Event Space
Beasts and Brews event space provides an upbeat and welcoming atmosphere. Our event space is perfect for company happy hours, birthdays, wedding receptions, parties and so much more. Reserve the event space today for your next dose of good times!

topReview.highlightedText: Great restaurant. All the beers on tap are super affordable, fun to have all the choices too. Decent food.

name: The Blue Fish-Breckenridge
description: The Blue Fish serves the finest sushi, sashimi, rolls, and Asian inspired cuisine, with an emphasis on quality and freshness. The Blue Fish also offers an array of Asian inspired hot dishes, salads and artisan desserts. Compliment your meal with uniquely crafted cocktails, or with a selection of fine wine, sake and beer. Exceptional service in a lively atmosphere gives guests an unforgettable experience that has made The Blue Fish an award-winning restaurant for 20 years.

topReview.highlightedText: Terrific Happy Hour Menu. The patio is worth a visit before the snow season arrives.

name: Carlos' Bistro
description:
In the beginning there has been one word in Carlos’ Bistro, Beautiful. The excellence and the experience of the best in Colorado Springs. Carlos (Owner, Executive Chef, and Matradee) provides a warm and welcoming experience to all of our customers, making everyone feel special at home and relaxed.

We are proud to now offer Japanese kobe and wagyu steaks plus burgers and kobe sausages made with kobe, wagyu, and prime meats at Carlos' Bistro as the state of Colorado is now a member of the Japanese Kobe Club.

topReview.highlightedText: Food was excellent, a bit pricey but worth it, and the service outstanding. Menu is huge…something for everyone. Presentation was lovely and unique. They are attentive to the details and very friendly. Carlos asked our names when he seated us and our server, Stephanie, addressed us personally all evening long. Impressive!

name: El Segundo
description:
Outside seating is on a first come, first served basis and weather permitting. Outside opted for diners cannot be guaranteed inside seating due to inclement weather, we appreciate your understanding.

El Segundo is a high-energy, fast-paced, sophisticated semi-traditional taqueria & tequila bar, in the middle of Vail Village.
El Segundo is the second restaurant from the Montauk team. Chef Dimitri Souvorin and restauranteur, Cameron Douglas invite you to the newest hot spot in Vail Village. Chef Dimitri’s creative menu ranges from Mexican standards to Asian fusion to Americana. Our bar will boast over 100 tequilas, with signature cocktails and flights that will feature delicious tequilas both well-known and obscure. Whether you are seeking a quick casual bite, drinks with friends or a big night out, El Segundo is the place to be.

BOOKING SEPARATE RESERVATIONS DOES NOT GUARANTEE TABLES WILL BE SAT TOGETHER.
Please call 970-763-5470 for parties o

topReview.highlightedText:
We love El Segundo and one secret favorite is the Tres Leches!!  
Keep up the great work!  You are one of the few restaurants who have managed so well during this employee shortage and Covid.  It can't be easy!
Great job!  You are still nice to your customers! :)

name: Gunbarrel Brewing Company
description:
Crafted with passion by brewer Jamie Fox and his wife Marie, Gunbarrel Brewing Company is to be located in Boulder, Colorado.


Enjoy a vast selection of craft beer in the spacious taproom or in the pastoral beer garden. Have a blast with your friends playing corn hole, giant beer pong, pool, pinball, giant jenga and so much more in the game room.


Food trucks for lunch and dinner daily. Large selection of snacks and non-alcoholic beverages.


Projection football games, livestream concerts, educational events and more. See website calendar or facebook for details.


Book our private event space for your next meeting or party.

topReview.highlightedText: Amazing beer and staff 🙏

name: Jay's Bistro
description: Locally owned and operated, Jay's Bistro takes pride in sourcing its products from responsible producers and retailers.

topReview.highlightedText: Great food great and friendly service.

name: Siena at The Courtyard
description:
Please call for Reservations

Welcome to Siena at the Courtyard in downtown Castle Rock, Colorado, a fun casual Italian/American gathering place. Always fresh and seasonal, our eclectic menu features brick oven pizza, steak, seafood and pasta. Our menu is complemented by a 50+ bottle wine list and specialty martinis. Enjoy a cozy meal by the fireplace in the winter or soak up the sun on our patio during the spring and summer. We offer happy hour every day with food and drink specials. We also have a private room for parties, meetings, and family events. Siena is celebrated year round for its cuisine, hospitality, setting and service.

topReview.highlightedText: Service was good. Food and atmosphere, less than mediocre.

name: Hearth Restaurant and Pub
description: Hearth, in Downtown Windsor, is a warm and inviting gastro-pub and pizzeria to share in food, drink and laughter. Our historic building, built in 1902 now renovated, reveals its classic industrial feel, exposed brick and large windows. The wood burning oven is the focal point of our dining room atop the second floor that offers panoramic views of Windsor Lake and the Rocky Mountains. A 16 tap beer system featuring craft beers, wide-ranging wine list and craft cocktail list are offered at Hearth. Please come join us with friends or family and experience this distinctive Hearth away from home!

topReview.highlightedText: Waitress knew her stuff and kept it sweet and simple. Menu was eclectic but not overwhelming.  Something for every budget. Beautiful view of Windsor Lake and a really neat pizza oven in plain view which I feel is kind of the heart of the restaurant.
