name: Ristorante Di Sopra
description:
Ristorante Di Sopra is an upscale Italian dining experience.

The sister restaurant to award-winning Paravicini’s Italian Bistro. Located in Old Colorado City, with panoramic views and rooftop patio dining available.

Ristorante Di Sopra will feature Chef Franco’s creative genius on Italian classics with seasonal specialties.

The Wine list boasts over 100 bottles, classic cocktails, and an extensive craft beer selection.

Whether it be inside the modern styled dining area, or on the second story patio with breathtaking views of Pikes Peak and the surrounding mountains, you are guaranteed to be impressed at Ristorante Di Sopra.

MANGIA!

topReview.highlightedText: Was our first visit.  The food and atmosphere were great.  We got there and it was still light outside.  Want to come back at night to enjoy the pretty lighting. Also would like to come back with friends and sit outside to enjoy the view.  Our server was very  good and Albert is a true asset to the business!

name: Slope Room
description:
Slope Room is an Alpine Bistro focused on the connection between Rocky Mountain farmers and ranchers. Pasture-raised, sustainable proteins, and locally sourced produce will be front and center at the sophisticated yet cozy restaurant and bar. The room will pay homage to the sexy and dangerous allure of the Old West with a decidedly modern twist on the traditional new American Steakhouse menu.


The space will feature a full service Unravel Coffee Shop with both Grab & Go options and fast-casual counter service for Breakfast and Lunch.

topReview.highlightedText: We loved the food and cocktails. Excellent side options for your entree and great apps - we will 100% be back

name: License No. 1
description:
License No. 1 in Boulder, Colorado has been in business since 1969 and carries a rich history. The restaurant has an extensive drink menu that dates back to that same time, while also offering many great food options for hungry diners. License No. 1 is a casual restaurant with an upscale flair and offers an excellent dining choice for a group of friends.

Those looking for a great meal at License No. 1 can try many options. Some of these include chopped chicken Waldorf salad, steak and fries, roasted prime rib sandwich, smoked trout dip, deviled eggs and the L1 burger.

name: Fall Line Kitchen and Cocktails
description: Located on Bridge Street next to the Gorsuch Building, Fall Line Kitchen and Cocktails serves satisfying New American cuisine in a modern alpine setting.  Using locally sourced ingredients whenever available, Chef Nicole Hoffman provides diners with a new perspective on traditional dishes.  The dining room is decorated with a collection of Slim Aarons photographs that celebrate "attractive people doing attractive things in attractive places".

topReview.highlightedText: We had a beautiful dinner with excellent service.  Steak and pork chops were so good!!

name: Outworld Brewing
description: A Sci-fi/Fantasy-themed brewpub.  Enjoy Small plates, Shareables and Entrees from our restaurant menu.  Dine in the upper level, open space mezzanine or in one of the taproom "Escape Pod" booths.

topReview.highlightedText: We took a chance on this after looking for brew pubs while traveling through CO ~ what a nice surprise! Great food, thoroughly enjoyed my flight of beers, and the service was exceptional.  We'd definitely go back.

name: The Grand Bistro at Grand Z Casino Hotel
description: The Grand Bistro is a classic American fine dining bistro where quality ingredients are prepared by culinary experts to create a memorable dining experience.  From hand cut steaks to our made from scratch sides, we have something for everyone to enjoy. Our knowledgeable staff will provide impeccable service and are happy to assist you in choosing a bottle of fine wine from our climate controlled wine room located at the entrance of the restaurant.

topReview.highlightedText:
Our server, Breana (might have spelled her name wrong) was very sweet.  She was very attentive and apologetic when there was a mix up with our food.  We understood and the supervisor bought on our cocktails and took off $20 due to the mix up. 

Food was great and service was top notch. 

Definitely would go back.

name: Streetcar520
description: Stretcar520 is an eclectic New American eatery located in the Trolley district in the heart of downtown Colorado Springs. We serve delicious food and offer exceptionally good vibes... Take the ride!

topReview.highlightedText:
Parents weekend at USAFA 🇺🇸
Went 2 nights in a row the food was that good!
Kimchi fries were delicious, as was the Bodah bowl!

name: La Tour
description: La Tour Restaurant has been voted the best restaurant in Vail since 2006 by the Vail Daily Readers Poll and is conveniently located in the heart of Vail Village directly across from the west-end of the Vail Village Parking Structure. Chef Paul Ferzacca’s modern French-American cuisine is famous in the Vail dining scene. Utilizing the best organic, natural and sustainable products available, La Tour is known as the restaurant where the chefs eat.

topReview.highlightedText: Absolutely wonderful. Service was spot on. Great wine list.  Dover Sole was to die for .

name: Urban Steam American Bistro
description:
An irreverent espresso bar, full service bistro & cocktail lounge located near downtown Colorado Springs. Proudly serving classic European & Australian style espresso drinks and unique coffees from around the world in our pour over bar. Serving Breakfast/Brunch every damn day until 2pm daily, with a light lunch from 11am to 3pm, and dinner service 3pm until 10pm Tuesday thru Saturday.

We are located in a converted warehouse in the Mill Street neighborhood, just southwest of Downtown Colorado Springs, stop in and say hello, enjoy our espresso, waffles and whiskey selection, and stay for good times!

topReview.highlightedText: Our sever Christian made the whole night.

name: Monte Jade - Gaylord Rockies Resort & Convention Center
description:
Currently closed.

Discover the culinary diversity of Asian Inspired cuisine at Monte Jade, where you are encouraged to share plates and conversation in our relaxed environment.

topReview.highlightedText: Our waiter last night was fantastic!  He remembered all of our names, suggested great beer, sake & dishes.  I will definitely come back to Mont Jade.

name: Colorado Mountain Brewery at the Roundhouse
description:
Colorado Mountain Brewery is a restaurant and brewery located in Colorado Springs. This is a place that is serious about it's quality cuisine and refreshing house brewed beer. We have 6 flagship beers along with monthly specialty and seasonal brews.

The menu is classic bar food, kicked up a notch. Appetizers include the bison poppers, jalapeños stuffed with cream cheese and ground buffalo, wrapped in a thin pastry and dipped in amber ale batter and flash fried. Another fusion item that takes the best of different cultures are the venison eggrolls, which are eggrolls filled with venison, sweet potato, cheddar cheese, peppers, onions and black beans with a blueberry BBQ dipping sauce. In addition, diners will find a variety of sandwiches, pizzas, burgers and more.

topReview.highlightedText: Everyone was very friendly. Gabby our server was exceptional!

name: Elway's Vail
description:
Elway's Steakhouse, located in The Heart of The Vail Village.

Our approach is simple: deliver the finest and freshest every day.

Aged USDA prime beef is the star at Elway’s whether your preference is a thick porterhouse, tender filet or a juicy rib-eye. Our culinary team shops for seasonal and interesting ingredients, then plans the ever-changing menus. This allows us to incorporate menu options with limited seasonal availability. Adding choices in portion size, flavor profiles and culinary styles – from the familiar to ethnic and contemporary – allows us to blend a menu always full of chaise and variety. In our ever-changing menu, you’ll always find a great mix of old favorites and exciting new options.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent fillets, wedge salad and Olathe corn side dish.

name: El Padrino Mexicano
description: Locally owned and operated Family Mexican Restaurant. Located on the north side of Colorado Springs close to I-25, powers corridor and north gate to Air Force Academy. Come in and try our fresh made food and hand shaken margaritas. With happy hour daily from 3-6 pm. Many gluten free and vegetarian options. Dine in with full service bar or get food to go for pick up. We also do catering. Large private party room and patio with view of AFA and fire pit.

topReview.highlightedText: I had a lovely time.  I ordered a lunch item at dinner and they made it for me.  It was a chicken fajita. The chicken was tender and moist.  Í will definitely be going back. The outdoor space looked awesome. It was really windy the night we were there so we chose to sit inside.  It has a fire pit that looked very inviting and now I want to go back when it's lit up.

name: Palomino Mexican Restaurant
description:
**COVID 19 UPDATE**
Due to limited occupancy to allow social distancing your reservation will reserve your table for an allotted amount of time. Your table will be reserved for 1 hour 15 minutes for parties up to 4; and 1 hour and 30 minutes for parties of 6 or more. Please remember a face mask is required to enter the building and while you are up and walking around.

Welcome to Palomino! We invite you to indulge your senses with some of the best, fresh from scratch authentic and healthy Mexican food that northern Colorado has to offer. Whether you live in Loveland, Fort Collins, Windsor, Greeley or Evans, we offer catering service when you need us to come to you and our full menu "To Go" for your convenience.

topReview.highlightedText: One of my favorite places!!

name: Northside Kitchen
description:
Northside Kitchen offers Homestyle Contemporary American Cuisine in a comfortable modern mountain setting. From Slow-Roasted Prime Rib and Wild Salmon, to Lobster Risotto and Braised Lamb Shank, Northside offers a full service dinner menu every night of the week!
Northside is also famous for our bakery. Come join us for a hearty breakfast or lunch and fresh baked donuts. Every night our bakery staff makes fresh donuts, pastries and breads. Get here early, they sell out quickly.

topReview.highlightedText: Had a delicious dinner at Northside Kitchen. Excellent service!

name: Matsuhisa Vail
description:
If your desired reservation time is not available online, please call the restaurant at 970-476-6628.

Featuring Chef Nobu Matsuhisa’s signature new-style Japanese cuisine, Matsuhisa Vail is located in the Solaris Plaza in the heart of Vail Village. Our dining room is open from 5pm nightly. Takeout available nightly from 5-9:30pm.

To ensure we are adhering to the health and safety guidelines, and to reopen as safely and responsibly as possible, we are requiring guests entering our premises to wear protective face masks.

-----------------

Chef Nobu Matsuhisa’s fusion cuisine draws influence from his classical training in Tokyo and his life abroad in Peru, Argentina, and around the world, showcasing signature dishes such as Yellowtail Sashimi with Jalapeño, Black Cod Miso and White fish Tiradito.

topReview.highlightedText: Great dinner casual sushi after jazz concert

name: Ristorante Ti Amo - Vail
description: Established in 1995, located in Eagle-Vail halfway between Vail and Beaver. Featuring authentic northern Italian cuisine, served in an atmosphere reminiscent of little Ilaly. The dress code is casual however the fare is anything but. Featuring dishes such as Pasta Fritta, Insalata Griglia, Petti di Pollo alle Fragole, and Risotto Pescatore. Recognized by locals and visitors alike as one of the best restaurants in the valley. A must during your visit.

topReview.highlightedText: Fantastic meal. Great staff. Great value.

name: Dat's Italian
description:
Outdoor Seating is for an enclosed and heated romantic dining den. These dens are available for reservation by selecting the Outdoor Seating option. Dat’s Italian is a family-owned and operated Italian restaurant. We pride ourselves on serving some of the best and most original Italian food in the Colorado Springs area.
We offer outdoor heated pods.
We would love to cook, serve, and share our dishes with you!
Popular menu items include chicken cacciatore, sausage and peppers pasta, eggplant, chicken, veal
parmesan, and the classic spaghetti and meatballs. Make sure you ask for some of our house-made
mozzarella to go with your delicious meal! We have a full bar with an extensive wine list.
Inspired by the Italian generations before us, our food is a labor of love. When you come to Dat’s Italian! You’ll feel like you’re part of our family! We strive to make our restaurant a pleasure for you to visit and know that our commitment and dedication shows through our food!

topReview.highlightedText: Nice little place to grab some food! Great staff, nice atmosphere, and food was delicious.

name: Smokin Fins - Fort Collins
description: With a passion for food and a focus on quality, we built Smokin Fins, where Fort Collins could count on perfectly smoked meats and fresh seafood and sushi. Our modern rustic dining room reflects the community we serve and the simple presentation of our well-executed recipes. Every dish we serve is made with the best ingredients out there, and we source locally produced goods when we can. Not to mention, our cocktails are creative, and our staff is friendly, making us the total package. Please note that we reserve a large portion of our restaurant for walk ins only, please contact us directly with any questions about availability.

topReview.highlightedText: We went here for my birthday and it was great! Our server was attentive, friendly and took good care of us. The food was great, we took advantage of the happy hour and shared 4 different kinds of sushi, an appetizer of Kickin shrimp and the two toned chocolate cake (not sure if I got that right but it was delicious) . We loved all the different sushi we had but our favorite was the Fins Gokana. I would definitely recommend Smokin Fins to anyone who loves great food, a cozy atmosphere and amazing service.

name: The Melting Pot - Colorado Springs
description: Colorado Springs favorite celebration restaurant. "The Melting Pot is pure entertainment," declares the NY Times. Whether it's a romantic dinner for two or a gathering of friends for a bridal or baby shower, Girl's Night Out, or birthday The Melting Pot has the recipe to make all your occasions special. Relax in our inviting, warm atmosphere and let our attentive servers guide you through our selection of fondues, sauces and fine wines. Winner of an "Award of Excellence" from Wine Spectator magazine.

topReview.highlightedText: Fun experience.

name: The Salt Creek Steakhouse
description:
The Salt Creek Steakhouse is located in the heart of the Breckenridge historic district. Since 1997 we have consistently set the benchmark for great Steaks, mouth watering BBQ (cooked slow and low) fresh fish, poultry and vegetarian fare.
Our restaurant is one of the few quality establishments in town capable of catering in house to large groups and special events.
Our extensive, yet reasonably priced, wine list has garnered the Wine Spectator award of excellence every year since 1998.
For the finest food, superb service set in an authentic old western style ambiance the Salt Creek Steakhouse is your Breckenridge destination.

topReview.highlightedText: It was really great.

name: Red Lobster - Longmont
description: Red Lobster welcomes you by offering PRIORITY SEATING to reduce your wait time in the restaurant, so you can spend more time doing the things you love. Or, come enjoy a drink at our bar and a Tasting Plate while you wait. Red Lobster is the world's largest and most loved seafood restaurant company, offering high quality, freshly-prepared seafood, sourced in a way that is traceable, sustainable and responsible. We offer lunch and dinner daily, featuring classics like our Ultimate Feast®, Garlic Shrimp Scampi and Parrot Isle Jumbo Coconut Shrimp, and feature limited time flavors and preparations during events like Lobsterfest®, Crabfest® and Endless Shrimp®. And, who can resist our famous warm and cheesy Cheddar Bay Biscuits®? To learn more visit www.redlobster.com

topReview.highlightedText: My son is heading back to college out of state this week.  We ate to celebrate our last Sunday Dinner tradition for awhile.

name: Juniper Restaurant in the Vail Valley
description: Experience The Confluence of Seasonal and Contemporary Cuisine on the Eagle River, just minutes from Beaver Creek and Vail Resorts.

topReview.highlightedText: Michael did an excellent job taking care of us!  Thanks for a terrific evening!

name: Meritage at the Omni Interlocken Resort
description: The word Meritage was originally coined as an American expression of excellence – a term that combines "Merit" and "Heritage" in a definition of the finest blended American wines. Meritage, the restaurant, stands as a perfect symbol of a commitment to excellence. With its floor-to-ceiling windows framing Long's Peak and the Flatirons, Meritage offers American cuisine.

topReview.highlightedText: The omlets were amazing being made to order. Loved our server Marco very attentive enjoyed the mimosas! The shrimp was also amazing all we wanted-new York could have been cooked better a bit dry. Enjoy prim rib more the staff very friendly as a whole!

name: Copper Sky Distillery
description: From craft spirits to craft cocktails, Copper Sky Distillery's goal is to create something worthy of saying, "you've got to try this!" Visit the distillery for a tour or to share a cocktail and conversation at our tasting room in Longmont, Colorado.

topReview.highlightedText:
This is a must!!  Small but quaint with Oliver - knowledgeable and great service! 
We went for my husband’s 50th and it was great!  He got a flight of locally made moonshine and whiskey and loved it!  The girls got amazing raspberry drinks!  They’ve done it right - barrels, table clothes but unpretentious.  Great lighting, dumpling foot truck.

name: Momma Pearl's Cajun Kitchen
description: Momma Pearl's Cajun Kitchen serves Southern Louisiana Cajun dishes prepared by Chef Robert "BB" Brunet and his staff. All recipes are made from authentic Cajun recipes Chef BB learned from his mother, "Momma Pearl".  Voted "Best Cajun Food" three years running by the Colorado Springs Gazette and Independent Newspapers.  Catering Available.  Visit www.MommaPearls.com

topReview.highlightedText: This is possibly the best Cajun restaurant north of NOLA.  The food tasted as good or better than being in NOLA.  The staff is friendly and very happy and upbeat making the enjoyment even better.  The atmosphere also made you feel like NOLA.  I know there are other restraints that try like lost Cajun but this is the best.  Worth the drive from wherever you are in the state.

name: Mishawaka Amphitheatre Restaurant
description:
**Currently, Mishawaka is restricted to outdoor dining with heaters or take out**

Enjoy a front row seat of the Poudre Canyon with a burger and a beer at the Mishawaka. Our featured Craft Micro Brewery is Odell Brewery, located in Fort Collins, CO. Odell Brewery is our craft beer partner featuring Mish Ale, but we have a full bar with many choices of craft beers, wine and spirits. There is no better spot to share what Northern Colorado has to offer, so bring up your friends and relax for the afternoon. Give yourselves a taste of mountain air, sunshine, the rushing river, as well as a great burger and Odell beer on tap. Outdoor seating available weather permitting in winter season with patio heaters and blankets available.

Mishawaka Amphitheatre has a full service restaurant available. Enjoy a meal on our beautiful deck and watch the big horn sheep grazing on the canyon hill side or enjoy our indoor seating with large bay windows that offers the same river and wildlife view.

topReview.highlightedText: Great laid back hangout. Beautiful on deck by the water. Tons of bees so we had to move inside but not much you can do about that. All around cook place to go!

name: Flatz
description:
Our dedication to sourcing local ingredients combined with seamless execution forges an experience worth coming back for multiple times over.

Due to COVID-19 the main dining room is closed and we are offering a limited dinner menu. The lounge and patio is open for seating with parties no larger than 8. For the safety of the guests and staff, masks are required at all times while inside unless you are sitting at a table.

The highly regarded Flatz Restaurant is an urban establishment located just miles from the foothills of the Rocky Mountains that emphasizes a ‘Food Forward’ approach to each dish we serve. Quality ingredients, community partnerships, and a desire to provide excellent service drive our actions. In each decision we make, creating an intriguing experience where food is at the forefront of our mind.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent Mother's Day Brunch!  All of the food was delicious and good quality, especially the jumbo shrimp cocktail.

name: Simmer
description:
Our aim at Simmer is simple – providing you with the honest-to-goodness pleasure of eating and drinking while you relax in your favorite neighborhood bar. Whether you’ve come for the food, drink, or both, we hope you will feel right at home.

When you step into Simmer, you’ll be greeted with a friendly smile. We’ve fashioned a warm, comfortable dining room that spills over into a spacious outdoor patio, complete with an open fire pit and tranquil water feature. Enjoy “Happy Hour in the Round” during the warmer Colorado seasons when we open up our overhead doors at the back of our bar, creating 360° of indoor/outdoor seating.

Whether you are looking for an upscale décor restaurant for a date night, a casual vibe for a business lunch, or a laid back ambiance for a fun night out with friends, Simmer is the choice in West FOCO.

topReview.highlightedText: Absolutely wonderful.  We celebrated our 30th Anniversary. Loved the peach menu!  Will be back!

name: Silverheels Bar and Grill
description: Located on Main Street in Frisco, CO and open year round. We specialize in Colorado cuisine, hand cut choice steaks, fresh Rocky Mountain trout, seafood, burgers, and much more. *Please call us for a reservation at our sister sushi restaurant, Kemosabe 970-668-0345.

topReview.highlightedText: First of all, our waiter was Jon Walsh and h was excellent with his knowledge of the dishes and his recommendations (ask for him).  The snow crab "wantonadas" that he recommended were awesome (our only problem was that we ordered 6 and should have gotten 9.  My wife had lemon pepper trout and I had the southwestern trout and both were GREAT.  We usually try different places when we travel and return to the best on our last night-we'll be at Silverheels before we go home!

name: Lucky Dumpling
description: Lucky Dumpling is an Asian American Fusion restaurant created by Chef Brother Luck. A great place to find handmade dumplings and contemporary dim sum.

topReview.highlightedText:
Great dumplings & Little plates 
Sat outside- not a great patio with homeless and street noise

name: Greeley Chophouse
description: The Greeley Chophouse is an upscale, casual restaurant in downtown Greeley Colorado.  We specialize in all natural, locally produced steaks, lamb and pork as well as fresh seafood.  We serve dinner only in a refined 1930"s atmosphere.  We have  a full bar service with a variety of wines, cocktails and draft beers.  Please come and enjoy your special occasion, business meeting or night out with us!!

topReview.highlightedText: The establishment is fantastic and my fiancé and I enjoyed every moment we were there. Heather, our server, was spectacular, every one who worked there was spectacular. There was a server next to us who had a seven top (they were rude and arrogant) but the server handled them to a T.

name: Namaste India
description:
French - Indian fusion cuisine.
Our experienced, French Michelin Trained Chef works with a very passionate and creative team which works very hard to give all the patrons the best culinary experience, where you will be able to taste progressive Indian cuisine and classic French dishes. We believe in giving excellence on every plate and creating memorable experience for our guests.

topReview.highlightedText: This is a very ambitious menu! We were so impressed we returned for another dinner before we left WP. We tried the sole, the epitome and the elk. The elk was my favorite. It was perfectly seasoned and cooked. The Opera Cake was amazing. We were given complimentary macarons and a bottle of bubbly in honor of my birthday. Our waiter was charming, helpful and attentive. Next time we will try the French tasting menu and the Indian tasting menu.

name: Grouse Mountain Grill
description:
Award winning contemporary American cuisine featuring local ingredients including fresh summer produce from our local garden plots. The restaurant enjoys a spectacular setting with panoramic mountain views. Stellar service, an extensive wine list filled with special international bottles, patio seating and a seasonal schedule of live music round out a memorable evening. A crackling fireplace and ski slope views provide winter dining a very special setting.

Whether you're in blue jeans or resplendent evening attire, or whether you prefer a cold beer or a legendary French Burgundy, we welcome everyone to enjoy one of the most exciting and rewarding dining experiences in Colorado.

topReview.highlightedText:
Another fantastic dinner at Grouse Mountain
The entire staff is incredible parred with delicious appetizers, entree and dessert! Big thank you for consistently delivering a wonderful meal

name: La Bottega - Vail
description:
Please make sure to let the restaurant know if the number of guests in your party changes, at least 12 hours in advance. Failure to cancel or correct your reservation according to our reservation terms, will result in your credit card being charged a fee of $40/person.

La Bottega has been a mainstay for both locals and tourists alike since 1997. Having started as a sandwich and deli operation, La Bottega has grown into one of the top destinations for dining in the Vail Valley. La Bottega offers authentic Italian cuisine with the Chef Stephen Virion having worked in Tuscany and the Veneto regions of Italy. His wife, Elisabetta, is from Asiago, Italy and has crafted the wine list to compliment the cuisine. La Bottega's Wine Bar is a great place for apres ski or to just have a glass of wine with friends from our award winning wine list. Of course our famous sandwiches and our stone oven pizzas are still

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent wait staff and food!

name: Russell's
description:
Russell's is more than a steakhouse, it is a dining experience!

Serving certified Angus beef, fresh seafood, shrimp, weiner schnitzel and Alaskan King Crab legs to name a few. A delightful bottle of wine will compliment your dining experience.

Enjoy a friendly, relaxing atmosphere with wonderful creekside dining. Come and join us and discover your own reason to visit us again and again.

Russell's combines a unique charm with great food that creates an incredible dining experience you will not forget.

topReview.highlightedText: We have enjoyed dinner at Russell’s many times before. Last evening was made even more enjoyable through the thoughtful service we received from our server, Pam. Thanks for a great evening.

name: Basil & Barley Pizzeria Napoletana
description:
Welcome to Basil & Barley Pizzeria Napoletana!
Your Authentic Neapolitan Pizzeria certified buy the International True Neapolitan Pizza Association.
Basil & Barley is proud to offer authentic Neapolitan Pizzas, made in the time honored traditional method that originated in Naples, Italy, and passed from generation to generation around the world.
In addition to our hand-made signature pizzas, Basil & Barley offers a distinctive menu of classic Neapolitan fried starters, salads, wings, stone-baked pasta and homemade desserts, as well as a broad selection of draft beers and wines.
Featuring fine dining with full table service, our friendly staff and charming atmosphere are second to none. In the spirit of Italian hospitality, we welcome everyone to our restaurant.

topReview.highlightedText: Everything was delicious! Never been disappointed.

name: Snake River Saloon and Steakhouse
description:
**If Open Table is not able to accommodate your reservation please call 970-468-2788 for select availability**

Opened in 1975, the Snake River Saloon & Steakhouse in Keystone, CO provides a casual spot for groups, couples, and families to come together for delicious meals, liquid refreshment and musical entertainment. Equal parts restaurant and old time saloon, the Snake River Saloon features local and well-known live bands and a popular happy hour by the fire.

With a comprehensive array of mixed drinks, beer and wine, the Snake River Saloon also features fine foods for diners of all ages. Appetizers feature American standards and unique choices, like smoked trout. Entrees include steaks, pasta dishes, heartier beef options, fish and other specialties. A comprehensive kid's menu & hand crafted desserts rounds out the wonderful choices available.

topReview.highlightedText: Fabulous service, food and ambiance. True supper club style! Crab legs are huge and abundant and fantastically tasty!

name: Brakeman's Burgers
description: Craft Burgers, Pizza and Milkshakes located in Colorado Springs at The Old Depot Building.  Offering Outdoor Patio seating with a Fire pit on the Patio.

topReview.highlightedText: nice place.. excellent job on the remodel. food is great!

name: Mood Tapas Bar
description: Enjoying tapas with friends and family is what Mood is all about!  Our delicious and diverse small fares, and robust wine selection make for the perfect dining occasion for any group.  Located across from Acacia park in downtown Colorado Springs!!  Check out our website for additional booking options.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent risotto and everything else

name: Vin48 Restaurant Wine Bar
description:
Vin 48 offers an ever-changing rustic American menu to satisfy discriminating palates with small and large plates featuring local organic ingredients.

Chef Hays’ food is complemented by our eclectic, carefully chosen wine list. An Enomatic preservation system allows us to present over 40 wines by the glass and half glass. We also serve hand-crafted cocktails and beer from our full bar.

Vin 48 Resaurant Wine Bar

topReview.highlightedText: Food was outstanding, the wine, a Barolo, was exquisite !

name: Austin's American Grill - Harmony Road
description: Austin’s American Grill is the quintessential taste of Colorado. With two great Fort Collin’s locations—one in the heart of Old Town and another on Harmony Road, we’ll have you wondering why mom’s food never tasted so good and when you can come back for more. Savory roasts and chicken cooked over an open flame in our front-of-the-house rotisserie. All-natural buffalo seasoned to perfection. Cornbread baked in iron skillets and drizzled with honey and butter. Signature cocktails sweetened with fresh-squeezed fruit juice. Plus, our decadent desserts are made fresh daily, giving you an excuse to stop in for a slice that reminds you of home. So grab a friend and make plans to meet at the red umbrellas. There’s a reason Austin’s is one of Northern Colorado’s favorite destinations.

topReview.highlightedText: Decent food but nothing spectacular.  Don’t bother with the cheesecake dessert, it was disappointing; it came in a small jar with loose crumb topping that was a mess.  More like tasteless pudding.

name: The Emporium: An American Brasserie
description: Located on Walnut Street in Old Town, The Emporium is easy to get to with plenty of street and garage parking available.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent meatloaf in very pleasant setting. Definitely going back.

name: Springs Orleans
description:
Springs Orleans is dishing up local favorites and Cajun Classics! We are the hottest restaurant and bar in Downtown Colorado Springs.

Whether you are craving a burger, a salad or some amazing Étouffée, Springs Orleans has something to please everyone.

Executive Chef Shyann Aguilar has created a menu that is as affordable as it is delicious. From your appetizer to your dessert - which is made fresh in house daily, you won’t be disappointed.

Laissez le Bon temp rouller!

(As they say in Nawlins - Let the Good Times Roll! )

topReview.highlightedText: The food was absolutely delicious. Worth every penny. All the staff was very friendly. We ate outside and that was a lovely area.

name: Traverse
description: The Lodge at Breckenridge's signature dining establishment, Traverse Restaurant and Bar's culinary team demonstrates skill and creativity, providing an innovative variety of daily fresh selections and expertly prepared meals featuring local and sustainable ingredients.

topReview.highlightedText: Wonderful small venue with excellent food and incredible views up the Blue River valley.

name: Up The Creek
description: Up the Creek Bar and Grill has been family operated since 1988. In our effort to serve only great, healthy, sustainable food we source our ingredients locally as much as possible, and use additive free, grass fed and environmentally responsible products.  Try some of our hand muddled specialty cocktails, local micro brews, or enjoy a bottle of wine from our extensive list.

topReview.highlightedText: Absolutely love this restaurant! Food is amazing and location is perfect! Been here 5 times in 3 weeks!

name: The Great British Food Company
description: Owner Steve Jones, and head chef Miles Sanchez are excited to present our vision to you and all our guests. We know that you want dining out to be more than just a meal. From the moment you arrive, we work to ensure you have that memorable experience.

topReview.highlightedText: Always great food and service. Check it out.

name: Coyote's Southwestern Grill
description:
Fresh Southwestern Food Daily!
“We invite you to the Lucio’s kitchen for two decades of southwestern inspired flavors that have been inspired through multiple family generations. From our unique catering to our food delivery services, if you can’t make it to us, we will make it to you!””

topReview.highlightedText: Always good at Coyotes! Our favorite place to go !

name: On the Rocks Bar & Grill at Arrowhead Golf Club
description: Located in Arrowhead Golf Club's beautiful clubhouse with panoramic views of the Rocky Mountains, the On The Rocks Bar & Grill offers lunch and dinner seven days a week in an upscale but casual ambience, and can also be used for special events hosted at the club. Ranging from mouth-watering burgers and piled-high sandwiches to salads, wraps, pastas, and an eclectic list of delicious entrée items that changes seasonally, all of the club's food is prepared fresh daily on-site by the executive chef and culinary team.

name: Gurkhas Restaurant
description: From the rich cream based curries of INDIA to the fresh distinctive flavors of Nepal, Gurkhas’ chefs bring 15 years of experience to each of our entrees. Come in tonight for an experience and tastes that won’t be forgotten.

topReview.highlightedText: Used to have to drive to Golden for this quality of food.  So glad Longmont finally has a good Nepalese restaurant!

name: Lancelot Restaurant
description:
Lancelot is Vail's original prime rib house and has been serving the same slow-roasted favorite since 1969. Today, Lancelot offers a delicious array of carefully prepared steaks and seafood in addition to our time honored tradition. Our wine list features selections from around the world, with an emphasis on California and Napa Valley.

Locally owned and operated, we are a small team and strive to treat our customers like family. Serving dinner Monday-Sunday at 5:30p.m. The bar is open at 5:00p.m.

topReview.highlightedText: Lancelot continues to be one of the top restaurants in Vail Village.   Always renown for their prime rib, yet all of their entrees are great.  Some of the best fish dishes in Vail!  The staff is the best in Vail.  No attitude, just great service!

name: Mirabelle Restaurant
description:
Mirabelle is a boutique restaurant located in the Vail Valley and believe to be the first home site in Beaver Creek. It’s unique and romantic setting is the home of Belgium Master Chef Daniel Joly. His unique and contemporary cuisine uses the best natural and organic ingredients available. Chef Joly takes great pride in his work but if you ask him what gives him the most satisfaction of all his awards and accomplishments he will simply say that awards and peer recognition are great but a customer complimenting him for a great dining experience is the best of all.
We are open 6 days a week, Monday thru Saturday, during May and June. Please call after 2 pm if you have any questions.

topReview.highlightedText: The lamb was amazing. The service was impeccable. We love Mirabelle!

name: P.F. Chang's - Colorado Springs
description: P.F. Chang's is a restaurant concept that honors the 2,000-year-old Asian tradition of wok cooking and believes in making food from scratch every day in every restaurant. With a Farm to Wok™ food philosophy at its core, P.F. Chang's chefs hand-roll dim sum, hand chop and slice all vegetables and meats, handcraft every sauce and wok-cook each recipe, every day in every restaurant using wholesome, fresh ingredients. With roots in Chinese cooking, the culinary landscape at P.F. Chang's now stretches across Asia with diverse, culturally inspired recipes including hand-rolled sushi, Vietnamese-style soups and bowls, traditional Chinese dim sum, wok-fired chicken and beef entrées, and family style noodles and rice. All made from scratch every day.

topReview.highlightedText: Their system for open table was down. They also were closing early due to staffing. I felt bad for everyone as they are doing the best they can.

name: Yama
description: Nestled in the Vail Village, this sophisticated sushi and Japanese restaurant offers an intimate and fun dining experience. This upbeat, chic restaurant focuses on fresh fish and a variety of specialty cocktails.

topReview.highlightedText: Best sushi in town

name: Track 10
description: Colorado Style Urban Kitchen and Bar located in The Old Depot Building in Downtown Colorado Springs. Featuring locally sourced meats and produce as well as sustainable seafood.

topReview.highlightedText: Nice atmosphere, good food, friendly staff.

name: WYLD
description:
Take a step on the WYLD side and join us for an elegant evening indulging in premium abstract culinary presentations. Our Chef driven signature restaurant features locally farmed meats and vegetables accompanied with seafood sourced from a range of top destinations. With a hyper-seasonal influence, Chef Jasper and Chef Manuel will lure your palate into the various seasons of Colorado. Complimented with a sophisticated wine list, a night in WYLD is sure to be an unforgettable evening for family and friends

*Hours of operation are subject to change. Please call for more information.

topReview.highlightedText: Amazing food, impeccable service !

name: Pepi's Restaurant & Bar
description:
PEPI’S RESTAURANT & BAR located in the heart of Vail. Known for its Austrian continental cuisine.
WE ARE OPEN SEVEN DAYS A WEEK ; LUNCH 11.30 TO 3.00PM DINNER 5.30 TO 9.00PM FRIDAY AND SATURDAY 5.30 TO 10.00 (970) 476-4671

topReview.highlightedText: Had a wonderful meal together with our son and husband. We are from Switzerland and were craving European food. My jaegerschnitzel was excellent. As a starter we shared the tartar and escargots. Equally delicious.

name: Bol – Restaurant & Cocktail Lounge
description:
**OPEN TABLE IS FOR DINING RESERVATIONS ONLY. FOR BOWLING RESERVATIONS, PLEASE VISIT BOLVAIL.COM OR CALL 970-476-5300. **

*We have a $50 no show policy - if you need to make changes to your reservation please call the restaurant*

Located in Vail’s newest village center, Solaris, Bol offers an experience unlike any other. Bol is a full service restaurant offering fresh, contemporary takes on worldly flavors with creative twists on classic American cuisine. Bol has a custom cocktail menu and over 200 labels of wine to chose from. Guests may dine in the chic, modern dining room, at the sixty foot bar, or in the bowling lounge while they bowl. Bol brings a metropolitan vibe to the mountains and has a high standard of service to reflect just that!

topReview.highlightedText: This is a very fun place. I was told when we stopped by the day before our reservation that we would have no problem getting an outside table because our reservation was early enough (6pm) that was not the case . We also mentioned at that time that we wanted to bowl a game or 2 and nothing was said to us about reservations for that. Very disappointing. The food was delicious and the service good too.

name: CONTINENTAL DIVIDE WINERY
description:
Voted Colorado's Best Winery Experience and a double First Place winner in the Best of Summit awards, Continental Divide is the highest altitude winery in the world. Experience Colorado wine and join us for a unique and memorable wine tasting experience. EFFECTIVE NOVEMBER 20 BY STATE LAW ALL SEATING IN ALL ESTABLISHMENTS IN SUMMIT COUNTY IS OUTDOORS ONLY. COME ENJOY OUR OUTDOOR PATIO WITH PRIVATE FIREPITS AND HEATED TABLES. Our indoor area is open for wine to go in our Wine Shop.

We offer a variety of wine tasting flights, wine by the glass, and wine by the bottle. Vsitors can enjoy cheese and charcuterie plates from our neighbor the Breckenridge Cheese Shop or appetizers from BOLD restaurant while wine tasting. We do not offer full meal service in the winery.

We follow strict COVID-19 sanitation and safety protocols and kindly ask all visitors to wear masks except when eating or drinking.

topReview.highlightedText: Awesome wines. Easy access to the cheese boards right across the street!

name: Sushi Nama
description: Our mission at Sushi Nama is to deliver fresh, simple and innovative sushi to Colorado using only the best ingredients with all hand cut and prepared dishes.  We deliver outstanding customer service to our guests within an exquisite dining environment

topReview.highlightedText: As always a fantastic meal with fresh sushi!

name: Colorado Craft Social
description: Colorado Craft is a modern restaurant concept designed to showcase the best of Colorado’s breweries, distilleries, farms and purveyors.

topReview.highlightedText: The wagyu burger is where it's at!!

name: Millonzis Restaurant
description: Coming Soon!

topReview.highlightedText: They were very short-handed.. only 2 people in the kitchen and 2 waitresses. And even so, the waitress was extremely pleasant and the food was excellent. It was an enjoyable evening.

name: Los 3 Garcia's Mexican Restaurant - Conifer
description:
Welcome to Taqueria Los Gordos - your local restaurant with authentic food and great happy hour!

Three brothers from a humble farm in Los Altos de Jalisco, Mexico, uprooted their lives to pursue the American dream. The three brothers’ pursuit became more than just hard work and determination when they opened their first restaurant.


In March of 2013, they celebrated one-year anniversary of their third location, Los 3 Garcia's Mexican Restaurant, in Conifer, where locals and mountain vacationers enjoy delicious, family-inspired Mexican meals.

name: Center Stage
description: Named Center Stage for it's strategic location overlooking blue waters and perfectly framing Longs Peak and Mount Meeker, Hole 16 sits just outside of our relaxed dining and bar area - also named Center Stage. Showcasing exhibition kitchens to encourage culinary interaction, Center Stage offers a more causal yet refined experience serving comfort food, homemade brick-oven pizzas and Colorado craft beers to enjoy around the 40-person bar.

topReview.highlightedText: The service was excellent, the food was great, and the view is awesome. We will be back soon.

name: The SteakHouse
description: The Steakhouse has been lauded as having the “Best Steak Dinner” in Cripple Creek and one of the best steakhouses in Southern Colorado. The Steakhouse is a hidden gem only an hour away from Colorado Springs.

topReview.highlightedText: So happy to see specials. I had the seafood type stew. So glad that it is going to be on the new fall menu. The steaks were very flavorful and perfectly cooked.

name: Idlewild Spirits Distillery and Restaurant
description: Idlewild Distillery Pub is a restaurant and distillery that serves craft cocktails with our home distilled spirits and delicious food made from scratch!

topReview.highlightedText: Great distillery; excellent whiskey with huge assortment of cocktails. Food was great too! Highly recommend!

name: Michael's Italian Restaurant
description:
Coming Soon
Michael’s Italian is a family-run restaurant in beautiful downtown Breckenridge. We are proud to serve fresh and authentic Italian cuisine.

topReview.highlightedText: Vacation group

name: Hooked
description:
HOOKED is a blend of our travels far and wide, which enable us to bring unique seafood preparations from around the world to your palate. The wood interior of our beautiful Beaver Creek location is recycled from our forest to invite you in to our local surroundings; our fresh fish is brought to you from our dedicated fisherman and their families from around the world; and our eclectic group of culinarians create unique meals and one-of-a-kind experiences that will leave you...HOOKED.
Whether your home is on the beach, or in a high-rise in the Big Apple, you'll find yourself asking how fish can be this fresh in the middle of the Rocky Mountains. The answer: Our passion for great food, along with hard work and mind bending logistics.
Join us to experience the freshest seafood this side of the beach, and GET HOOKED!

topReview.highlightedText: This was my second time at hooked, and did the whole fish experience again. The first time was great, this time not so much. They rushed us through dinner, we were getting new courses while still finishing the first one. Although it was Oktoberfest, it was not busy and there was no need to speed us out of there - especially for the money we were spending. I am sure we will be back and have a better experience.

name: Cliff House at Pikes Peak
description:
The Best in Colorado Fine Dining.
The Cliff House Dining Room has gained national renown as one of Colorado’s premier dining destinations. We are proud recipients of the distinguished DiRoNA Award, AAA Four Diamonds,and "Best of Award of Excellence" Wine Spectator MagazineOur wine list is the largest in the Region with over 800 offerings.
Led by our visionary Executive Chef Chris Lynch, our elite culinary staff will astound your senses with a creative symphony of tastes, smells and textures. His award winning dishes will amaze you with their modern twists combined with his fearless utilization of cross-cultural techniques and fresh Colorado ingredients.

topReview.highlightedText: The duck was excellent! Service was great!

name: Splendido at the Chateau - Beaver Creek
description:
Splendido at the Chateau offers wonderful Rocky Mountain dining featuring hearty yet refined American-European cuisine. In summer, enjoy a cocktail or dine outdoors on our flower filled deck and enjoy great views of Beaver Creek Mountain. As the sun sets and the mountain chill sets in, retreat indoors and get cozy next to our lovely, double-sided, wood burning fireplace. Splendido offers entertainment by Peter Vavra, Kathy Morrow and Micky Poage in the piano bar.
Splendido can comfortably accommodate a range of events including wedding receptions, family celebrations, cocktail parties, as well as business and corporate dinners with private facilities for catered meetings and seminars.

topReview.highlightedText:
Another fabulous experience at Splendido! Love it here - I believe it's the best restaurant in Colorado bar none. 
My only issue is that the prices are kind of crazy in some areas. The lamb entree' at $78 seems pretty crazy, and I am allergic to some of the ingredients in my order, and they said they would replace them with other choices, and then charged me an additional $8 for fingerling potatoes, which I thought was rather out of line. 
But other than that, the atmosphere, the dining room decor, the amazing friendly attentive service are all great - and the chef does a beautiful job with the dishes. And don't miss the chocolate souffle!

name: Moot House Restaurant and Pub
description:
Moot House Restaurant and Pub in Fort Collins, Colorado offers brunch, lunch and dinner menus, as well as an extensive beer menu. The environment here is casual and comfortable, and Moot House Restaurant and Pub also offers special menus for kids and those with gluten intolerances.

House favorites for dinner at Moot House Restaurant and Pub include pan-seared chicken, 90 schilling bratwurst and fish & chips. Some popular entrŽes include pork schnitzel, grilled salmon, Guinness short ribs and prime rib. Beers on tap include ciders, fruity and sweet options, sour beers, bright and crisp selections, hoppy beers and other selections based on flavor profiles, making it easy to find a beer to suit your taste.

topReview.highlightedText: Friendly staff and team members helped make dining experience nice

name: Windy City Pizza and Pub
description:
We're a favorite in Breckenridge for pizza, beer, and all the good times that come along with them.
Reservations for parties 6 guests are less are 70 minutes, 7 - 10 guests are 85 minutes. Please, call if your group requires a longer visit.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent food!!

name: Jing Asian Fusion | Sushi & Raw Bar
description:
A favorite of locals and guests alike, Jing (formerly Asie) features a unique menu of modern Asian fusion, contemporary sushi, sashimi, and raw bar dishes. Fresh ingredients, creative cuisine, and an inviting atmosphere that inspire warmth and happiness. Jing delivers an authentic Asian experience right in the heart of downtown Aspen.

Beloved for his original approach to Asian dining, Chef Frank Lu’s techniques and artistry are showcased in signature dishes such as the roasted Peking duck, 13 - flavor fresh whole lobster, tomahawk steak, and spicy ginger-miso crispy whole fish.

If interested, you should reserve these signature dishes ahead of time, as we often run out: Peking duck, 13 - flavor fresh whole lobster, Kobe beef Tomahawk, and whole fish.

Please inquire about catering events.

topReview.highlightedText: The sushi is fine, but there is probably better in town. The miso is good, but the portion is pretty small for 8 bucks a pop. Except for the California roll or maybe a veggie roll, all of the other rollls are 22 and up. These are the fancier rolls that would normally be under 15 at most sushi restaurants, but some are like 36. Our server was spectacular though. So nice and attentive…which can sometimes be an issue in this town unless you’re dressed like a multi-millionaire with an attitude of entitlement.

name: Acquolina-Aspen
description:
ACQUOLINA: Mouth-Watering.

Acquolina is an informal, yet elegant Trattoria & Pizzeria where you will find fine food and a fun atmosphere! We strive to provide an authentic Italian experience from plate, to glass, to environment. Please eat, drink, and enjoy! Our expansive menu, all Italian wine list, and warm service team will give you a place to return to and share with friends and family.

Open nightly for takeout 5:00pm till Close. See you soon!

Please note we do 1 hour and 30 minute turns on all tables, restaurant, bar counter and patio as well.

topReview.highlightedText: Fantasti!  Loved the suggested wine pairing to our meal!

name: Bistro 28 @ Pole Creek

address.line1: 51 Pole Creek Golf Course 5827 County Rd

description:
As of 9.1.21, Bistro 28 is adjusting its operating hours. On Monday's and Tuesday's Bistro 28 will ONLY be serving grab and go snacks, cold sandwiches, hot dogs and brats until 8pm. The bar will be open for drinks. No Lunch or Dinner Menus are available on these two days.

NEW Hours of Operation:
Breakfast: Not available
Lunch served 11am-4:30pm Wednesday-Sunday
Dinner served 4:30pm-8pm Wednesday-Sunday
*Hours subject to change*

Book through Open Table or email jesse@polecreekgolf.com

Bistro 28 features unique made-to-order cuisine infused with international flavors, using local and organic produce whenever possible and no meal is complete without a delicious homemade dessert by Chef Kai Brosze.

topReview.highlightedText: Enjoying a delicious dinner on the Bistro 28 outdoor patio is a favorite activity for our family when we vacation in Winter Park, CO!!

name: Briarhurst Manor
description:
Only a few minutes drive west of Colorado Springs, Briarhurst Manor is located in the tiny valley of Manitou Springs. The stately Victorian manor house was built in 1872 by the founder of Manitou Springs, Dr. William Bell of London, England.
Our restaurant seats up to 500 guests and features casual yet elegant dining in nine intimate rooms, an extensive menu and wine list complete with five course dinners featuring domestic and game meats, fresh seafood, pastas, poultry, specialty salads, vegetarian, and handcrafted desserts. The finely grained pink sandstone Tudor manor displays the architecture and landscaping of an English country house complete with the bubbling Fountain Creek passing through the estate. There is also an unrivaled view of Pike's Peak.

topReview.highlightedText: Great service by a very knowledgeable waiter, Bryon!  Loved the unique food and artistry!  Will return for sure!!!

name: Leonora
description:
When it comes to playful sophistication, restaurant Leonora is a staple. Named for Leonora Carrington, a famous Mexican surrealist painter and novelist, this hidden gem honors her legacy with edible works of art composed of fresh, organic and locally-sourced ingredients.

Leonora offers an inviting dining experience inspired by the French Alps, Spanish Pyrenees, and our own Colorado Rockies. The menu is designed as a tapas experience, one where diners embark with shareable small plates, pintxos and cheese & charcuterie before progressing to larger plates which revere alpine flavors including Colorado lamb pops, local steaks and more. For a traditional dish with a Vail flair, try Chef Tyson's fried chicken with barrel-aged Fresno hot sauce. Flavorful dishes are simply prepared and thoughtfully paired with wines from around the world.

Our outdoor patio has been enclosed and is now heated for the winter season. Come check out the future of dining out!

topReview.highlightedText:
Our experience at Leonora was exceptional. The food was wonderful, tapa style so we were able to work our way through the menu. My favorites were the passion fruit ceviche, mushroom bolognese, cheese cake, and lamb lollipops. 

The service was just as amazing as the food, Cam made the best drinks and Garrett went above and beyond to help us pair the perfect wines with our plates.

Highly recommend 👌

name: The Empire Lounge and Restaurant
description:
SEE YOU SOON!

To our valued guests-

After much consideration we have decided to temporarily suspend operations at the Empire until April 17th. Our family is so grateful for your continued support, and even as the rest of the world is changing around us, you remind us why we love our guests and community.

As this closure is only temporary, it’s a good opportunity to reach out to our Government, and help support our employees that may need a little extra assistance. By urging your Local and State Representatives to work hard to create a stimulus package, debt relief fund, or by issuing aid so everyone can return to their normal lives. 250,000 Coloradans are counting on you, and together, our voices can create a difference!

We will be posting updates on social media of our progress and potential reopening, please stay tuned. We will come back stronger than ever, and we can’t wait to have you as our guests.

Thank you from the entire Empire family!

topReview.highlightedText: I was excited to check this spot out after their summer renovations and we had such a nice dinner.  I really enjoyed the gazpacho soup after a hot day.  It was really balanced and delicious.  The roasted romaine salad was excellent as well.  Sierra helped us out and did and amazing job.  I loved this experience and will be back again soon!  The burgers here are outstanding!

name: Tandoori Kitchen
description: Tandoori Kitchen is a collaboration between Colorado’s greatest Indian chefs and local restaurateurs. All fans of Indian & Himalayan cuisine in the Lafayette area can enjoy classic dishes and excellent service provided by their new local Indian Restaurant. Tandoori Kitchen will serve traditional Indian dishes that will be familiar to Indian food fans. They will also serve classical Himalayan cuisine that will be most recognized by Himalayan food fans.

topReview.highlightedText: We had the nicest Valentine’s Day dinner here! The food was delicious and the service fantastic....and they gave roses to the ladies. 💕😉

name: Bully Ranch
description:
Bully Ranch, a restaurant located inside the Sonnenalp Hotel in Vail, is a casual dining experience that focuses on Southwestern and American food presented in a western style ambiance. The traditional fare at Bully Ranch is hearty, flavorful, and has a little bit of something for everyone.

The main staple of Bully Ranch is its selection of burgers and sandwiches, such as the 7X Colorado Wagyu burgers, the BFC - Bully Fried Chicken. The menu also offers a variety of soups and salads, as well as full entrees of ribs, fajitas and chicken pot pie.

topReview.highlightedText: Wonderful time at BR as usual - Sigi took great care of us, and food was delish!

name: Betula Aspen
description: Betula is the new endeavor of French chef Laurent Cantineaux and Venezuelan architect and restaurateur Juan Carlos Pérez Febres, co-owners of Bonito, a restaurant in the French West Indies Island of St. Barth. Betula offers French Pan-American cuisine with  the  show case of Rotisserie selection; a combination that was  mastered flawlessly by Chef Cantineaux  and known for his innovative cuisine crafted with French techniques and his experience in the America for over 20 years.

topReview.highlightedText: One of the best restaurants period. Excellent food and service in a beautiful atmosphere. I'd highly recommend multiple appetizers and the crudos. We had the special "fish ribs" which was incredibly delicious, innovative, and adventurous for such a high end restaurant. Props to the chef.

name: Kenichi Aspen
description: Thank you for visiting Kenichi, Aspen's premier contemporary Asian cuisine and world class sushi.  Known for its exciting sushi bar, bustling dining room, and hip bar scene. Locals favorites include Dynamite Lobster, Black Cod Misozuke, Asian BBQ Ribs, and Yellowtail Serrano Sashimi.  Enjoy our private Rockstar booths and Aspen's only private Tatami Room for larger parties. We also offer a world class selection of Japanese Sake, Fine Wines of the World, an exceptional variety of Japanese Whisky, Mexican Tequila, and other fine spirits.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent food and service. Thank you very much!

name: Left Bank Restaurant
description: The Left Bank Restaurant has been a Vail staple for over 48 years. A classic French restaurant, The Left Bank serves the finest and freshest cuisine prepared from scratch daily.  Select an amazing wine at a fair price from our world-renowned wine list to accentuate your meal experience.  Bordeaux, Burgundy, Rhone, Champagne, and a vast selection from around the world will surely please your palate.  Join us for a journey through the French countryside while tucked in the Rocky Mountains!

topReview.highlightedText: We enjoyed a lovely dinner creekside.  This is our favorite Vail restaurant.

name: Jose Muldoon's
description: José’s has been a staple of the Springs’ downtown scene for over forty years. The menu features authentic Mexican & Tex-Mex fare, fantastic margaritas and a variety of dietary offerings. We serve our famous cuisine using only freshest ingredients, all prepared daily. José Muldoon’s, named after the legendary bandito, features inviting fireplaces and an indoor/outdoor bar, and our award-winning patio. José’s service staff is always friendly and efficient. We are proud to be the favorite Tex-Mex destination in Colorado Springs.

topReview.highlightedText: What a great place to celebrate my daughters graduation from college.  Excellent food, service and atmosphere.

name: Cafe Diva
description:
Open seven days a week for dinner services, Cafe Diva is the place to go for a fine dining experience. It features a range of menu items created by Executive Chef Kate Van Rensselaer Rench, including offerings for vegetarians, vegans and those gluten sensitivities. Cafe Diva offers year round classics like Crab and Tomato Bisque and Venison Tenderloin as well as a variety of creative seasonal dishes.

Cafe Diva also features an extensive wine list and a date night menu, making it an ideal place for a romantic evening with that special someone. It has a garden-side outdoor patio for guests to enjoy the weather along with their meals.

topReview.highlightedText: Delicious food, always great service. Love the new outside seating.

name: Paninos Eastside
description: The Pride of Paninos Restaurant began in 1974 when Everetta-Lou & Tony Frasca opened the first location in downtown Colorado Springs. From day one, Paninos Restaurant has been owned & operated by the Frasca Family. Whether its your first time in or you are one of our regulars, the Paninos Family & Crew would like to Thank You for your patronage.

topReview.highlightedText: The food was delicious.  The service was great and our server (James I believe was his name!) was wonderful!

name: Ellina
description:
Ellina is a cozy, intimate restaurant located in the heart of Aspen.
Nestled in a stone walled dining room for the perfect backdrop in winter and fall, in the summer the large outdoor patio offers al fresco dining in the shadow of Aspen Mountain.
Known for our homemade pastas and modern Italian fare, we also mix it up with an authentic taco menu.
Wine is our passion, and Ellina's worldly wine lists offers over 2500 choices, with a particular love and focus on the wines of Italy.

topReview.highlightedText: Best restaurant in Aspen! Definitely try the artichoke bruschetta and the Espresso Martini for dessert. Owner Jill is amazing and long-time server Honey is our favorite. Thanks Ellina!

name: Duemani
description:
We are an approachable and refined restaurant, situated in the heart of Aspen. We are driven by the desire to create great tasting uncomplicated food of exceptional quality- it’s the Italian way. Where the ebb and flow of new flavors and traditional foundations come together! Highlighting contemporary Coastal Italian flavors, composed seafood dishes and prime grilled meats. Let us fill your table, providing exceptional service, memorable moments, and unique culinary experiences.

Our dining room is inviting, with candles glowing, incorporating elegant design and craftsmanship. The intimate private dining area surrounds groups with wine filled walls and custom walnut furniture, accommodating up to 18 people. A sure favorite for locals and tourists alike!

topReview.highlightedText: Great food, great service, atmosphere outside was really nice.  Sit outside if weather permits.

name: Beano's Cabin
description:
Beano's Cabin is open!

Masks are required on the shuttle per CDC guidelines. Beano's is a cashless facility.

Your dinner reservation includes the complimentary shuttle service. Shuttles depart every 30 minutes from the Beaver Creek Chophouse beginning at 6 p.m.

To book your horseback ride please call the reservations office directly at (970) 754-3463.

5 course prix fixe meal is $119 per person, 3 course kids prix fixe meal is $62 per child.
Price does not include beverages, tax or gratuity.

Whether you are a seasoned rider or looking to get in a saddle for your first time you are sure to enjoy our horseback ride to dinner! We have partnered with the Beaver Creek Stables to provide a horseback ride guided by an experienced wrangler. This beginner-friendly ride is the ultimate Coloradan way to arrive for your memorable evening. Price for horseback ride is $75 per person plus 18% gratuity.

*Guests riding horses must be at least 7 years old and weigh less than 250 pounds.

topReview.highlightedText: We were married at Beano’s and haven’t been able to go back much even though we live in the valley because of COVID. Something about this experience just brings me to my happy place. The service is impeccable. The menu is terrific, with creative turns on classic cuisine. A thorough wine list — we enjoyed a 2013 Mathiassen Bordeaux blend. But take this advice: get the pork belly, always. It’s in a class of it’s own.

name: Old Elk Distillery
description: Legendary entrepreneur Curt Richardson is eager to start and grow companies. Stemming from his passion to create a legacy bourbon brand with unsurpassed quality and taste, Curt turned to the Greg Metze, a Master Distiller with 38 years of experience specializing in developing bourbon whiskeys. This collaboration produced an innovative and delicious bourbon, which transcends tradition. Here in our tasting room in Fort Collins, Colorado, guests can experience exclusive whiskey flights, world class cocktails, elevated wild game bar fare brought to you by our spirited, knowledgeable and engaging staff. Welcome to the herd!

topReview.highlightedText: Great vibe, amazing whiskey collection and delicious elk dishes. In the heart of Ft. Collins.

name: Beaver Creek Chophouse
description: Located slopeside, at the base of the Centennial Lift in Beaver Creek Village, the Beaver Creek Chophouse sits amidst all of the action and all of the beauty of Beaver Creek Mountain. Serving a comprehensive lunch menu, featuring an assortment of soups, salads, sandwiches, and hot entrees, in addition to an incomparable dinner selection filled with fantastic steaks and fresh seafood; this restaurant melds delicious cuisine with stunning views, a welcoming staff and a luxurious atmosphere to create an unparalleled dining experience.

topReview.highlightedText: Magician was a fantastic addition to our dinner experience!

name: The Fitz
description:
The Fitz is an iconic alpine restaurant located in Manor Vail Lodge that offers a unique setting with a menu that is crafted with the freshest Colorado ingredients. A great place for families, groups, and couples to gather in comfort and style. Experience this one-of-a-kind Vail dining establishment.

Restaurant reservations recommended by booking online through OpenTable or by phone at 970-476-4959.

topReview.highlightedText: We enjoyed a lovely meal before a show @ GRF Amphitheatre.

name: French Alpine Bistro - Crêperie du Village
description:
Please call 970-925-1566 ext 0 for reservations between 11:30am - 4pm for Lunch and 6pm - 9pm for Dinner. We look forward to dining with you.

Aspen Restaurant Recipient of Multiple Accolades French Alpine Bistro- Crêperie du Village Recognized Nationally Cosmopolitan culinary connoisseurs searching for the elusive triad of a successful dining experience: excellent food and romantic atmosphere.
The Austrian owner has poured her heart and soul into creating an atmosphere that is best described in one German word: gemütlich. The carefully chosen artifacts and candlelight combine to make this the perfect place for a romantic rendezvous, intimate rehearsal dinner or wedding party. According to owner Karin Derly, "We envisioned this as a place for people to create happy, lasting memories." Many many satisfied customers from around the world agree that French Alpine Bistro is a charming hideaway, surrounded by the Rocky Mountains, for lovers to share an intimate meal.

topReview.highlightedText: This is my wife and I’s favorite restaurant in town. Epic date night spot.

name: Aurum Food & Wine - Steamboat Springs
description:
Aurum Steamboat is open for indoor & outdoor patio dining, 7 days a week with Happy Hour 4:30 to 6pm, and dinner service at 5pm. Curbside To Go orders are available 7 days a week 5pm to 8pm, (www.aurumsteamboat.com).

Reservations are recommended. In accordance with the Center for Disease Control’s current guidelines, all vaccinated patrons and staff have the option of wearing their mask while indoors.

For outdoor patio reservations..., should it rain, we cannot promise an indoor table. We will do our best, but if an indoor table is not available..., please be prepared for us to box your food to enjoy at home.

We appreciate timely arrival for your reservation. If you are more than 15 minutes late, we may need to cancel your reservation in order to accomodate subsequent reservations.

Please visit aurumsteamboat.com to book reservations, view our new Spring menu, updates, and special dates. We look forward to seeing you soon!

topReview.highlightedText: Beautiful seating by the river. Pleasant music. Tasty and imaginative menu. We like it so much we made another reservation during our stay in Steamboat!

name: The Fifty-Niner
description: The Fifty-Niner is a one-of-a-kind experience in Colorado Springs. It is the only hidden speakeasy game cafe in the City and quite possibly the state. You will book a two-hour time block for your table and select a game from our extensive board game library. Then, you just sit, sip, munch and play the old fashioned way.

topReview.highlightedText: Amazing place! What a gem with amazing food and drinks. The drink presentation was beautiful and they were absolutely delicious. We will be back!

name: Paninos Westside
description: The Pride of Paninos Restaurant began in 1974 when Everetta-Lou & Tony Frasca opened the first location in downtown Colorado Springs. From day one, Paninos Restaurant has been owned & operated by the Frasca Family. Whether its your first time in or you are one of our regulars, the Paninos Family & Crew would like to Thank You for your patronage.

topReview.highlightedText: Amazing, kind and timely service, DELICIOUS food with generous portions, and fair prices!

name: Austin's American Grill - Old Town
description: Austin’s American Grill is the quintessential taste of Colorado. Savory roasts and chicken cooked over an open flame in our front-of-the-house rotisserie. All-natural buffalo seasoned to perfection. Cornbread baked in iron skillets and drizzled with honey and butter. Signature cocktails sweetened with fresh-squeezed fruit juice. Plus, our decadent desserts are made fresh daily, giving you an excuse to stop in for a slice that reminds you of home. So grab a friend and make plans to meet at the red umbrellas. There’s a reason Austin’s is one of Northern Colorado’s favorite destinations.

topReview.highlightedText: Locally owned, very good service, always a wonderful salad there!

name: Maya – Avon Vail Valley
description:
Carefully crafted, yet bold flavored. Rooted in tradition, yet adventuring into contemporary tastes. Chef Richard Sandoval blends the earthy flavors of his native Mexico with worldly ingredients and creative cooking techniques to create the Modern Mexican Cuisine at Maya. Our hospitality is warm and Latin. We welcome you to linger over drinks, rediscover Mexican classics – mouth-watering guacamole, tacos with authentic fillings and fresh-made tortillas – and savor the Chef’s signature dishes.

FRIDAY AFTERNOON CLUB RETURNS JUNE 25th 2021!

topReview.highlightedText: Veronica was our server.  She was outstanding!  Very nice & happy to accommodate anything we needed!!

name: Gashouse Restaurant
description:
Due to weather issues patio tables are not available to reserve, please request them and weather permitting we will get you out there

Specializing in Rocky Mountain cuisine and seafood. Unique Rocky Mountain Log Cabin atmosphere with great food in a casual environment. Kid friendly and locals’ favorite since 1983. Serving lunch and dinner daily starting at 11 am. Daily Happy Hour with 30% off all drinks and apps, Beautiful garden patio dining dining available. Come check us out and find out why we are the Valleys favorite spot for over 30 years.
OpenTable reservations are not available during lunch, please contact the restaurant directly.

topReview.highlightedText:
Labor Day Burgers?  
Why not the best in the Vail Valley ?

For our romantic end of summer celebration, our table on the patio was ideal. Great food, great service, great ambiance. 

Thank you for a wonderful experience.

name: Toscanini
description:
We are open for Summer 2021 dinner service starting at 5 p.m. Toscanini will be closed Mondays and Tuesdays except 4th of July week and Labor Day weekend. We will be hosting Après from 3pm-5pm on our patio and in our bar. Full Dinner menu will be available starting at 5pm until close. We recommend reservations. Full parties seated only. We will only hold tables for 10 minutes and day of cancellations will incur a $25 per person charge. We are reintroducing seating in our lounge and bar. Our biggest priority this summer is still your safety and we are continuing our procedural changes to make sure our guests and employees feel safe this summer!

**Toscanini is a cashless facility. Please plan accordingly.**

Located in Beaver Creek Village next to the ice rink, Toscanini combines Colorado ingredients with modern culinary interpretations of old world cuisines.

2021 Summer Season (May 28th - October 9th).

topReview.highlightedText: Love this location and the new changes on the menu, delicious!

name: Crossroads Tavern and Grill at The Summit Interquest
description:
Full-service restaurant and sports bar at The Summit. We offer comfortable dining on delicious food for lunch, dinner, late night snacks, and anytime in between in a fun, lively atmosphere.

If you’re a sports fan, you’ll find Crossroads to be the ultimate sports bar. There’s not a bad seat in the house with tables for two or a crowd and our full-service bar has a huge selection of beers on tap. Catch your favorite team or sport on one of our big-screen TVs. If there’s a pro game on, it’s on at Crossroads!

topReview.highlightedText: Taylor was our server, and she was quite friendly and made us feel at home.

name: Mambo Italiano- Steamboat Springs
description: Mambo Italiano, located in the heart of Steamboat Springs, offers a unique and unforgettable dining experience year round. With a fresh new menu, (don’t worry we kept the old favorites!) and an award winning wine list, helpful staff and lively atmosphere, Mambos is “always delicious, always fun, and always a great choice.” Providing a full range of menu selections from old family recipes and chef inspired specials to extensive gluten free and seasonal options, come and see why locals voted Mambos “Best of the Boat.” Come hungry and leave happy, Mambos is Steamboat’s Italian hot spot!

topReview.highlightedText: We had cocktails, beer and wine for Happy Hour as well as pizza and salads. Everything was excellent and such a great deal!

name: Crossroads Tavern and Grill at The Summit Windsor
description:
Full-service restaurant and sports bar at The Summit. We offer comfortable dining on delicious food for lunch, dinner, late night snacks, and anytime in between in a fun, lively atmosphere.

Full-service restaurant and sports bar at The Summit. We offer comfortable dining on delicious food for lunch, dinner, late night snacks, and anytime in between in a fun, lively atmosphere.

If you’re a sports fan, you’ll find Crossroads to be the ultimate sports bar. There’s not a bad seat in the house with tables for two or a crowd and our full-service bar has a huge selection of beers on tap. Catch your favorite team or sport on one of our big-screen TVs. If there’s a pro game on, it’s on at Crossroads!

topReview.highlightedText: Great environment,  friendly staff, fair pricing, above expected service

name: Vail Chophouse
description: Located slopeside, at the base of the Gondola in Lionshead, the Vail Chophouse sits amidst all of the action and all of the beauty of Vail Mountain.  Serving a comprehensive lunch menu, featuring an assortment of soups, salads, sandwiches, and hot entrees, in addition to an incomparable dinner selection filled with fantastic steaks and fresh seafood; this restaurant melds delicious cuisine with stunning views, a welcoming staff and a luxurious atmosphere to create an unparalleled dining experience.

topReview.highlightedText:
Another fantastic night with Phil Long on the patio. I doesn’t get any better than his music, entertainment and hospitality. He visits tables “while on break”…. He just flat out gets it. 

The steak and mushrooms were delicious and the Chophouse Old Fashioneds are top shelf. 

We live in Albuquerque and vacation once a year in Vail. The Chophouse is the first reservation I make and of course it’s got to be a night that Phil is playing. 

Check it out… you’ll start your own tradition!

name: Fratelli Ristorante Italiano
description:
Fratelli Ristorante Italiano is an award-winning Colorado Springs establishment that provides the traditional flavors of Naples, Italy to diners for a fine dinner and happy hour at the ROMAN BAR. A fine dining restaurant that allows guests to linger over a delicious meal, a bottle of wine and a house made Italian dolci! Fratelli Ristorante Italiano is a local favorite.



The menu at Fratelli Ristorante Italiano includes appetizers such as Scampi al pesto, the perfect way to prepare for a plate of Veal Marsala or Gamberi Puttanesca. The Roman Bar serves cocktails, wines, martinis and limoncello shots alongside lighter fare such as Tuscan bruschetta. Finish your meal with a serving of tiramisu or Italian cheesecake and an Italian espresso.

topReview.highlightedText: food ok. had veal marsala. veal was chewy and tough. light flavor of marsala. pasta ragu as a prima made with italian sausage, did not expect the spiciness of the ragu which is not characteristic of northern Italian. ricotta cheesecake excellent. make sure you make a reservation, there are limited number of tables. atmosphere good and quiet. need more servers...

name: Bésame
description:
You don’t have to go far for the tastes of Cuba, Argentina, Portugal and Spain-just head downtown to Steamboat at BÈSAME. Featuring Latin Fusion Cuisine and food from the Hot Zone. Enjoy tapas, shared plates and entrees such as paella, whole fish, lamb burger, jerk chicken to name a few. BÈSAME is a rich and romantic experience with the fun and liveliness of an old world familia dinner.

For more information about our dining experience visit us at besamesteamboat.com.

topReview.highlightedText: Great ambiance-energetic but not too loud. Wonderful hostess and great server. The Tipsy Carrot cocktail was probably the best cocktail I have ever had. Unfortunately the food overall was just okay. Brussels sprouts were incredible. Shishitos were good as always, but the Camarones lacked salt.
