The grilled bread was put in the plate and got mushy from the sauce. I ordered the Picadillo which sounded really delicious, but lacked any memorable flavors. It also came with a fried egg on top (not in description) which was rubbery. (I personally don't care for fried eggs except for breakfast and I don't want them to come as a surprise topping.) My husband had the Arroz Con Pollo which had potential except the chicken was dry. Oh well...

name: New Belgium Brewing - Fort Collins
description: A neighborhood taproom with a familiar name, New Belgium Brewing Fort Collins is open for outdoor seating with food provided by our local food trucks. Located in the heart of Fort Collins, NBB is the 4th largest craft brewery in the U.S. and a Certified B Corp. The brewery has donated over $26 million to charitable causes since 1991. New Belgium is famous for its flagship beer, Fat Tire Amber Ale, along with year-round favorites like Voodoo Ranger IPA, Mural Agua Fresca Cerveza, and La Folie Sour Brown Ale; as well as an award-winning wood-aged sour program and innovative limited release beers. To learn more about the full product lineup and New Belgium’s Human Powered Business model, visit NewBelgium.com.

topReview.highlightedText: Enjoyed the beer…was able to sit and relax after a busy week exploring. Definitely would go again.

name: Steakhouse at Flying Horse
description:
Situated within The Club at Flying Horse, featuring sweeping views of our Tom Weiskopf designed golf course, Pikes Peak, and the Front Range. The Steakhouse at Flying Horse is a contemporary restaurant in a beautiful Tuscan style villa.

Enjoy The Steakhouse dinner menu with delicious appetizers, featured prime and grass-fed steaks and chops, fresh seafood and chicken dishes along with innovative side dishes. Accompany any dish with a hand-crafted cocktail from our full-service bar or bottle of wine from our extensive list of old and new world wines. Our exquisite selection of homemade desserts is the perfect ending to any meal.

We also offer guests delightful options for breakfast, lunch and Sunday brunch.
Breakfast and lunch is served Monday through Saturday
Sunday Brunch is served from

topReview.highlightedText: Exceeded my expectations! Carleigh was Amazing and so was ShawnMac at the bar!

name: Pine Creek Cookhouse
description:
Pine Creek Cookhouse is located at the base of stunning Elk Mountains in Aspen. The only thing as fantastic as the views is the gourmet food served at lunch and dinner. The summer menu and a winter menu each reflect the cuisine that matches the season.

The summer dinner menu at Pine Creek Cookhouse includes a number of wild game options including an elk chop and buffalo tenderloin. This is a great time to enjoy wild salmon, rainbow trout and other fresh flavors. The winter menu has the warm-you-up options such as a warm apple crisp, herb roasted Colorado chicken and stuffed acorn squash. Be sure to check before you go as Pine Creek Cookhouse is a seasonal restaurant.

topReview.highlightedText:
We all enjoyed our meal very much. In town visiting my son. We always try to make lunch or dinner Pine Creek Cookhouse. The trout is my favorite. Very generous portion too. The guys got the Buffalo Cowboy Chop. They were very happy! For appetizer we had the smoked trout that was excellent and the Elk Momos with a perfect amount of spice. Service was great. Waiters very nice. Manager came over to chat and make sure all was good. We ate inside. Dining room was beautifully lit for an amazing night. 
Can't wait to come back.

name: Romano's Macaroni Grill - Colorado Springs
description: Inspired by Italian trattoria cuisine, culture and conversation, Romano's Macaroni Grill believes every meal is a chance to celebrate and toast to life, pasta and of course, vino! Every meal is started off right -- with a bottle of wine at the center of the table, encouraging guests to pour as they please while exploring the extensive menu of handcrafted Italian classics. Macaroni Grill restaurants feature an open kitchen that allows guests to see its fresh ingredients and preparation techniques that blend Italian traditions with progressive culinary inspiration, in a polished casual atmosphere.

topReview.highlightedText: Hadn't been to a Macaroni Grill in years.  Was glad that we stopped in.  Great service and the "build your own pasta" was excellent.  Will be back.

name: Jose Muldoon's - East
description:
Please contact the restaurant directly to set up a reservation. We are excited to bring Jose Muldoon’s, which has been a staple of the Springs' downtown scene for over thirty years to the east side. The menu features authentic Tex-Mex style Mexican fare, the best margaritas and a variety of burgers, sandwiches, salads and vegetarian entrees. We serve our famous cuisine using only the freshest ingredients, all prepared daily.

José Muldoon's, named after the legendary bandito, has been modeled with a modern southwestern look, inviting fireplaces, an indoor/outdoor dining section including a bar, HD television visible from any spot in the bar area and semi-private banquet dining. José's service staff is always friendly and efficient. We are proud to be the now more easily accessible favorite Tex-Mex destination in Colorado Springs.

topReview.highlightedText: Great service and food still a great place after being closed for a while

name: Flame Restaurant
description: As Four Seasons Vail’s signature restaurant, we want FLAME to focus more on “fun dining” rather than traditional fine dining. Locally sourced and seasonally inspired dishes combined with unique steak cuts and tableside experiences provide guests with an interactive dining adventure you can’t get just anywhere.

topReview.highlightedText: This is a fabulous steakhouse right in the heard of Vail Village. We loved the food and the service was wonderful! If you can get Javier, certainly request him! He is awesome! We are foodies, and love to hit up high end restaurants. This place was delish!

name: Ludwig's
description:
Come and enjoy breakfast and dinner at Ludwig's Restaurant at the Sonnenalp Hotel in Vail!
Start the day off right with a bountiful European style breakfast served in the beautiful glass enclosed Ludwig’s terrace overlooking Gore Creek. End the day enjoying our creative cuisine in a truly unique and charming Bavarian setting.

topReview.highlightedText: Sunday brunch was wonderful.

name: Yampa Valley Kitchen
description:
YVK is uncompromising in its selection and sourcing of ingredients.
We only use local, organic, or sustainable foods of the highest quality.
This includes everything, down to the salts, oils, and spices we use.
Instead of the commitment to use organic or local foods “ when available ”,

Please note : We cannot guarantee outdoor seating.

Please indicate in your reservation if you have guests in need of handicap accessible seating as we do have an upstairs service space.

topReview.highlightedText: Love the vibe at Yampa Kitchen and the food is amazing!!

name: Meeker's Colorado Kitchen & Bar
description:
Meeker’s is proud to offer delicious meals for curbside pick up to maintain social distancing. Our breakfast will be available between 7am-11am and lunch/dinner served between 11am-9pm. Please call us 970-353-1883 to place your order.


Meeker’s, A Colorado Kitchen & Bar, is the culmination of community & culinary ingenuity. We seek foods less traveled. Ron Jackson is redefining farm-to-table, bringing food less traveled to Colorado’s burgeoning culinary map. In his role as Executive Chef at Meeker’s, his focus is on merging locally sourced ingredients with classic preparations, specializing in Rocky Mountain & classic American cuisine.

The 150 seat restaurant & bar includes a private dining room that hosts 16 and an expansive park side patio that seats 50. A wall of glass opens up to views of Lincoln Park bringing the outdoors into the bar. Complimentary Parking available in shared parking lot of the DoubleTree by Hilton at Lincoln Park Greeley.

topReview.highlightedText: CHASE is an outstanding waiter!  He made this birthday celebration a perfect evening for a small group!  Thank you CHASE!

name: Jimmy's An American Restaurant & Bar
description:
Jimmy's is located in the downtown core of Aspen with mountain views and serves the finest in steaks and seafood in an upscale but unpretentious atmosphere. If your desired reservation time is unavailable online or if you have a party larger than six, please call 970-925-6020 for availability.

Jimmy's delivers a world-class wine list featuring more than 1000 discerning selections from around the world and has earned Wine Spectator’s “Best of Award of Excellence." Jimmy’s is committed to a sustainable approach to drinking and dining through programs such as offering straws upon request, composting and waste reduction.

The next-level bar program features Japanese and Scotch whiskies and is augmented by Jimmy Yeager’s expertise in agave-based spirits tequila and mezcal. Jimmy's is one of the Top 4 Restaurant Bars in the US Spirited Awards and one of the “Top 50 Bars in the Nation” by Food & Wine.

topReview.highlightedText: So sad to see this Aspen gem close! Best wishes to Jimmy on his next chapter!

name: Sakaba
description: Quietly sophisticated with a generous nod to tradition - the Ritz Carlton Bachelor Gulch's newest food and beverage outlet is Japanese dining in its purest form. Sakaba serves only the highest quality, and freshest fish and ingredients paired with the Vail Valleys finest Sake list, Japanese beer and spirits, while maintaining the craft cocktail tradition of its former namesake.

topReview.highlightedText: Outstanding! Some of the best sushi we've had in Colorado! Service was fantastic!

name: Ore House at the Pine Grove
description:
Celebrating our 50th year, The Ore House continues as the area's longest dining tradition. The converted 110+ year old barn showcases Steamboat's ranching history while serving savory hand-cut Certified Angus Beef® steaks and chops, seafood, salad bar, and craft cocktails. All entrees include bread service, salad bar, and (2) side choices. An attentive staff will add to your evening as you enjoy the rustic atmosphere of this local gem. Available outdoor seating (seasonal), 3 open flame fireplaces (seasonal), bar seating at either of (2) bars, Private Dining options, and the ability to host events from 15 to 115 guests allows this iconic establishment to fulfill all your dining needs. And be sure to save room for dessert!
Reservations strongly recommended.

*Centrally Located Near The Base of The Ski Area
*Ample Parking
*Kids Menu
*Sunset Menu (5:00-6:00 Nightly)
*Weddings, Receptions, Reunions, Celebrations
*Locally Owned

Thank You for considering The Ore House at The Pine Grove

topReview.highlightedText: Very good food  but pricey. Have been to this restaurant many times.

name: Tempranillo
description: Welcome to Tempranillo Restaurant, where internationally acclaimed Chef Javier Gonzalez-Bringas, along with his partner and wife Laura, offer a daily menu of drinks, tapas, dinner and lunch.  Gonzalez-Bringas, a Madrid Native, combines an old-world style with a new-world flair in his signature cuisine.  The name Tempranillo, itself, pays homage to one of Spain's premier grape varieties, and true to its name the restaurant features a selection of over 100 hand-chosen wines.  The atmosphere at Tempranillo is notable for its rich colors, dual fireplaces, and community gathering table-all reflecting the equally rich depth of flavors and influences which are at the heart of the restaurant's origins.  "Our desire is to create a brilliantly charming place in the community where people can gather and enjoy the dance with exists between the flavors of Spain and Italy"

topReview.highlightedText: Same as previous visits; fabulous food & wine, attentive service and lovely patio!

name: The Met Kitchen
description: The Met Kitchen offers something for everyone! From share plates to entrees and everything in between. We have a 16 bottle Enomatic Wine machine along with a fantastic selection of Colorado beers and spirits. Call with any questions (970) 748-3123

topReview.highlightedText: Met had been recommended to us by friends. We really enjoyed the meal. We have already added Met to our dining rotation. And we will bring family and friends.

name: Till South
description:
TILL South is personalized fine dining in a modern, upscale setting. Our thoughtfully curated menu features modern gourmet cuisine, as well as an extensive wine bar and specialty cocktails.

After 9pm, we will only serve small plates and appetizers.

topReview.highlightedText: Great food and service. Always a pleasure to dine here.

name: Primrose - Steamboat
description: Chef-driven cuisine, featuring hand-cut steaks, jet-fresh seafood, curated wines and crafted cocktails - Primrose is Steamboat's newest upscale, "mountain casual" hot-spot with something inspired for everyone in your group...or just the two of you, for the perfect date night! Soul satisfying, Mountain certified.

topReview.highlightedText: We went for happy hour. The drinks were delicious, had 2 appetizers (get the burrata!!) and the burgers. Everything was excellent. Was also the best service we have had in steamboat. Excellent!!

name: Luna's Tacos & Tequila
description: Luna’s scratch kitchen always strives to serve the highest quality natural ingredients, sourced locally when possible. Luna’s features an innovative menu that pays homage to mexican flavors with a respect for authenticity and a passion for creativity. Our salsas, sauces, and fresh-squeezed juices are hand-made fresh daily in house. The bar serves only the best tequilas, imported and local craft brews, Mexican-style beer, and offers the finest craft tequila-based cocktails.

topReview.highlightedText: Had a great night last night at Lunas! Service and food was great! Thank you!

Table 79 Foodbar is open for indoor & outdoor patio dining, 5 days a week, Wed to Sun., with Happy Hour 4:30 to 6pm, and dinner service at 5pm. Curbside To Go orders are available 5 days a week 5pm to 8pm - www.table79steamboat.com.

description:
The Periodic Table is open for indoor & outdoor patio dining, 5 days a week, Wed - Sun, with Happy Hour 4:30 to 6pm, and dinner service at 5pm. Curbside To Go orders are available 5 days a week 5pm to 8pm - www.periodic steamboat.com.

topReview.highlightedText: Came to the best restaurant in Steamboat for our 35th wedding anniversary. We had planned on sitting outside, but an hour before our reservation, the skies opened up and rained like hell. Called Jenny and she switched our table to indoors. Ruby was our waitress, and as usual, she was the best - making wonderful suggestions for appetizers and wine. We ordered the baked salt fish of the day, and I still think it’s the best I’ve ever had. At the end of the meal we declined dessert, but they made for us to go - so sweet of them! I think Periodic Table is only open until the 26th of this month - go before they close for mud season. I’ll definitely be back before the close. I love this place!

name: Bosq
description:
This summer, Chef Barclay Dodge has created an exciting and intimate tasting menu experience. Choose any 4 or 5 items to create your own tasting menu, or opt for a 7 course daily set menu that reflects the progressive culinary inspiration of our kitchen. Tasting menus are priced a $130, $150, and $190.

Established in 2016, Bosq uniquely offers innovative and inspired cuisine sourced from local farms and backyard foraging. Bosq is passionate about the tradition of agriculture in the Aspen Valley. Chef Barclay Dodge creates an alchemy of flavor through his dishes, breaking down flavor profiles and textures to celebrate the essence of the ingredients.
Chef Dodge draws from the best of his local farms to bright, bold flavors of global street markets. His plates are accessible and consistently thoughtful.
Barclay is inspired by the origin of culinary and cultural practices of a place, from local farms for its seasonal brightness to the bold flavors of global street foo

topReview.highlightedText: I’ve been here many times and it always exceeds expectations! Food and staff are amazing.

name: Black Diamond Bistro
description: Whether you are drawn to the ambience of a wood burning fire, 180 degree views of Beaver Creek Mountain, après deals second to none or simply wanting something familiar, the Black Diamond Bistro will delight.  We offer a Contemporary American menu, what some might call ‘Comfort Food’.  We are proud to source as many organic and local ingredients as possible, including natural Colorado chicken and top choice Angus beef and make all of our dressings and sauces in house.  Order up a local Colorado craft beer or spirit or peruse our  approachable boutique wine list but either way, …stay, enjoy and relax.

topReview.highlightedText: Love it here.. the servers are fantastic as is the food!

name: E3 Chophouse | Steamboat Springs
description:
E3 is committed to maintaining sanitary conditions at the Chophouse. Please help us with social distancing and know that we are taking every measure to protect our customers and staff during this time. Let us know how we can enhance your experience! Thank you!

Created by the LaRoche family in 2013, E3 Chophouse is a dining experience not to be missed. Located on the magnificent Yampa River in Steamboat Springs, Colorado, E3 ranch raises the best seasonal, all-natural beef products available.

Our menus change frequently, allowing us to provide a variety of choices for our guests. Enjoy daily specials: jet fresh fish, wild game cooked to perfection, or, of course, our humanely raised, hormone and antibiotic-free beef and chops. Sides and salads have been designed to be large enough to share. Complete your meal with decadent desserts prepared by our pastry chef.

topReview.highlightedText: The service was great, cocktails were amazing. The view was fantastic. But the food was over priced, the food wasn’t bad, it was just super expensive for what it was. I think happy hour is the way to go at this place.

name: Joe's Crab Shack - Colorado Springs
description: Joe's Crab Shack is an American chain of beach-themed seafood casual dining restaurants. Founded in Houston, Texas, the restaurant now operates locations all across the United States of America. It serves seafood and American cuisine

topReview.highlightedText: Our waitress gave us some good menu suggestions and answered all of our questions patiently and thoroughly.  We ended up ordering  a bucket of mixed king crab 🦀 legs and smaller ones to share with potatoes and corn.  It was delicious but a bit pricey for what we got - no drinks either.  The corn was super soggy so we couldn’t eat it - we prefer ours crunchy.  Super attentive and skilled waitress who checked with us often but in a non-intrusive way.  Bus staff very attentive to clearing finished plates and asking about our meal.  Restaurant manager checked in with us as well.

name: Vista at Arrowhead
description: VISTA AT ARROWHEAD - Specializing in Colorado cuisine, seafood, meat and vegetarian dishes. Upscale dining with Vail's Piano Man, Micky Poage performing nightly. Chef David changes his menu seasonally always using the freshest product available. Vista's award winning wine list is known for its affordability. “WINE SPECTATOR’S AWARD OF EXCELLENCE”, AAA Three Diamond Award

topReview.highlightedText:
I now know why it was almost impossible to get a reservation at Vista this summer.
Great food and great service

name: Carl's Tavern
description:
DASHING GOOD LOOKS AND A COOL FOREIGN ACCENT. OH, AND HE COULD FLY TOO!

THE ADVENTUROUS SPIRIT OF CARL HOWELSEN IS OUR INSPIRATION AND CARL’S TAVERN IS A PLACE FOR ADVENTUROUS SPIRITS TO CALL HOME. THE HOSPITALITY IS GENUINE. THE BEER IS COLD. AND THE FOOD IS MADE FROM SCRATCH.

SO RAISE A GLASS TO THE MAN WHO TURNED WINTER INTO A PLAYGROUND, AND SKIS INTO WINGS. THEN GO AHEAD - RAISE ANOTHER FOR YOURSELF. WELCOME TO CARL'S.

topReview.highlightedText:
Pleasantly surprised. Great happy hour! Great service! Reasonable prices.
I would recommend this restaurant.

name: Mawa’s Kitchen
description:
NEED TO KNOW - WE ARE LOCATED IN THE ASPEN AIRPORT BUSINESS CENTER - ACROSS FROM THE ASPEN AIRPORT
Dine in our newly renovated dining room with UV Blue Light Air Ventilation Technology to make our Guests comfortable while dining. Our Patio is open during the summer months, weather permitting. Our 24-hour cancellation policy applies; please visit our cancellation policy! We only seat complete parties/ tables.
Mawa’s Kitchen is the destination for fresh, hand-crafted and seasonal cuisine, situated in the heart of Aspen Airport Business Center. Locals call it the “Hidden Gem of Aspen”. It is located just a few steps away from the Aspen Airport. We are driven by the desire to create fresh, seasonal, hand-crafted, uncomplicated food of exceptional quality- it’s the French/ Mediterranean way. Reserve your table today!

topReview.highlightedText:
Incredible dinner with old friends visiting from out of town. Our meal and the ambience of the outside dining was just perfect. My wife and I have frequented Mawa's for several years; we've had wonderful breakfasts and lunches countless times. This was our first dinner, and we're wondering why we waited so long.

We think what Mawa and Daniel have done with this restaurant is soooo good.

name: Casa D'Angelo Aspen
description:
Coming Soon!

At our restaurant, you’ll experience food prepared according to Old World traditions straight from the heart of Italy – the birthplace of our founder, Angelo Elia. Born in Salerno, Italy, Angelo was first taught to cook by his mother in their home kitchen. Both of his parents (his father was a local butcher) instilled in him the importance of using only locally gathered meats and fish, growing garden-fresh herbs, and baking breads from scratch. Angelo hand-selects the freshest, seasonal ingredients and artfully prepares them in an inviting setting of warmth and sophistication. A carefully curated list of wines has been masterfully chosen to create an extensive wine list from every region around the world. Whether it’s for an elegant night out or a gathering with family & friends, Chef Angelo Elia looks forward to inviting guests for an authentic Italian Tuscan-style meal in a setting that feels like home.

topReview.highlightedText: Wonderful evening!!! This is quite a new restaurant in Aspen.  I checked out the other reviews before making a reservation also there was no menu available to look preview.  The restaurant has modern decor with nice views of the ski hill. There is an outdoor patio, but we didn't sit out there.  The food was outstanding and they had creative appetizers. While not a cheap restaurant, we completely enjoyed ourselves, and it was worth every penny.  The only caution is that the elevator is via the alley, not the front entrance. My husband was on crutches from an injury. There are also 5 steps down to the restroom, unless there is an accessible restroom elsewhere.  We would highly recommend this restaurant! Looking forward to next time-

name: BR Sushi Colorado Springs
description: Coming Soon!

topReview.highlightedText: A delicious, fun and enjoyable experience made even better by professional and extremely attentive staff. Food was very tasty and the spacing of tables during these trying times was comforting. Will definitely go back.

name: Truffle Pig
description:
You won’t find a more convenient place to apres or dine after a day on the slopes than Truffle Pig, which is located at the base of the ski area, adjacent to One Steamboat Place and the gondola.

Featuring casual American Alpine Cuisine crafted from the freshest ingredients, Truffle Pig offers the most indulgent Apres Ski scenes around, including an inviting atmosphere, live entertainment, compelling drink specials and mouth-watering menu items.

As the evening approaches, settle in for an experience that fits your personal desire. A quiet romantic dinner or a festive meal with family and friends, all prepared by a talented culinary team.

Contact Truffle Pig about inquiries for parties and events at this ideal venue
www.trufflepigrestaurant.com

topReview.highlightedText: Outstanding service and great food! Outdoor patio is wonderful and shaded - bring a jacket for when sun sets.

name: Twenty One Steak
description:
A restaurant should reflect the best in a community.

Twenty One Steak is Pueblo’s finest restaurant. Start with our spectacular location on the Historic Arkansas Riverwalk, coupled with our skillfully planned and prepared menu, impeccable service and casually elegant atmosphere you can be sure your dining experience will be memorable. Executive Chef Michael Degenhart has immersed himself in creating meals reflecting his vast knowledge and professional favorites. Chef Degenhart has reached out to local purveyors and partnered with vendors offering the highest quality products. Expect only the finest quality beef, fish and other culinary compositions.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent!!  Food and service are world class!  Best In Colorado for sure!

name: Bluebird Bistro
description: Bluebird Bistro features fresh locally sourced ingredients all freshly prepared in our style of “Modern Mountain Cuisine.” From amazing burgers to brick-fired pizzas you are sure to find the perfect meal after a day of skiing. Open for lunch, dinner, and take-out 7 days a week. Please be aware of limited capacity due to COVID-19 restrictions.

topReview.highlightedText:
The service was wonderful.
Loved the Mushroom pizza and the grilled half chicken.
Pimento cheese was a first and I loved it.

name: The Slogar
description:
Summertime is here! LARGE PARTIES (anything over 9 people) CALL 970-349-5765 - very important: do not make 2 separate reservations, you will not sit together If it looks like there is no space through OpenTable, give us a call! I bet we can find something for you The Slogar has been offering family style, skillet fried chicken dinners in CB since 1984. Handmade baking powder biscuits, old-fashioned mashed potatoes, & chicken gravy have been a CB tradition for both locals & visitors alike. Steak, ribs, & vegetarian options also available. Ian & Ayla Scott have been the owners of The Slogar since 2018. They bring charm, experience, & a whole lotta love to your table. Creating a Colorado Creole Brunch has been very successful and fulfilling for the two, as they love sharing they're love for the Big Easy! Enjoy a crafted cocktail at the bar with a bar snack from our parlour menu! We'll see you soon at Cluckingham Palace.
DINNER RESERVATIONS - YES
BRUNCH RESERVATIONS - NO

topReview.highlightedText: Delicious food with wonderful portions! Friendly staff and fun atmosphere

name: Gessner
description:
Food and drink celebrate the culinary heritage of the Colorado Rockies. This delicious blend of cultures echoes Vail’s own heritage, modeled after the Alpine town of Zermatt, Switzerland.

Gessner restaurant and bar, is open breakfast through dinner, showcasing authentic flavors from the Colorado Rockies.

topReview.highlightedText: Great food, great service! We had the trout and it was incredible!

description:
*If you are unable to book a reservation through Opentable please call the restaurant (970) 516-7908. Or check out our website for MORE times and availability.

Fun-filled supper club offering delicious food and specialty cocktails.
Lounge area designed for private events, dancing & DJs.
Executive Chef Byron Gomez
Master Sommelier Jonathan Pullis

topReview.highlightedText: Really loved this venue! Food was creative and delicious the ambiance was impeccable. Our server was kind, attentive and the sommelier Jonathan was also fantastic he truly went above and beyond. This is a must visit in Aspen!

name: Bear Den Aspen
description:
*Open for dine-in, outdoor seating, take out and pick-up, 8am to 9pm. Take out and pick-up is online only through the following link: https://www.toasttab.com/beardenaspen/v3

A vibrant gourmet bistro located in the historic Lily Reed cottage in downtown Aspen, open year-round from 8am to 10pm. Decadent brunch, après and gourmet dinner, craft cocktails and unique wines. Organic, made from scratch, locally owned. Vegetarian and Gluten-Free options available.

topReview.highlightedText: The osso bucco was incredible.

name: Tahk Omakase Sushi
description:
**If you are interested in sitting at the sushi bar for our Omakase experience, please visit our website at www.tahksushi.com to make reservations or call us at 970-439-0444. Seating for the Omakase bar is limited and fills up fast so we do recommend making reservations in advance! We have a 10 minute grace period so if you are running late please give us a call otherwise you will not be able to join in on the Omakase experience.**

Tahk Omakase Sushi is a sushi restaurant, that offers Nigiri, Sashimi, specialty and classic rolls made with fresh, high quality fish from the Toyosu Market in Japan. Our Nigiri and Sashimi options change daily, please contact us directly for todays fresh catch! We also offer small hot plates, Japanese Sake, beer, classic wines, and a full bar. Our restaurant is two stories and we offer an elegant cocktail lounge/Omakase bar on the main level. A typical evening of dining with us at minimum is 90 minutes to 3 hours, depending on the size of your party.

topReview.highlightedText: The food was unique and delicious. Very high quality, seasonal fish. The pickled wasabi is a must!

name: 8th Street Steakhouse
description:
On vacation and looking for a unique dining experience the whole family will love? See what the locals have been raving for over 25 years with this downtown Steamboat tradition boasting the best chef in town, you! The 8th Street Steakhouse has the finest dry-aged handcrafted steaks from Colorado Buffalo, Prime-grade NY strips, 18 oz. Bone-in Ribeye, bacon-wrapped filets to Wagyu Kobe Beef. With steaks starting at $16.95, including unlimited salad bar and Texas toast, you’ll still have room for our famous 8th Street Tater for dessert. This is truly a restaurant not to be missed!!

With a magnificent Western ambience, our restaurant is focused around our two 20-foot lava rock grills where our patrons season and sauté their steaks to perfection. With the help of our friendly staff making sure their wine is filled and steaks turn out perfect, it’s no wonder we've been a steamboat tradition for over 25 years. Let us make your steamboat dining experience one to remember tonight!

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent.  Birthday celebration and the service was outstanding!  Thanks for helping make this a special evening.

name: Clark's Oyster Bar Aspen
description:
Clark's Aspen is the 2nd location of McGuire Moorman's popular neighborhood oyster bar set in the historic & beloved former Little Annie's location. The Clark's team has worked to uphold much of the charm of the previous tenant including fully restoring it's oak bar. The restaurant also features a bustling open kitchen and alpine version of Clark's dock side aesthetic.

Learn more about McGuire Moorman Hospitality and their family of restaurants at www.mcguiremoorman.com.

topReview.highlightedText:
Oysters were excellent. The Clams and mussels were superb. The crab cake was the best I’ve had since Etta’s in Seattle. 
Not inexpensive but worth it.  The place to go for seafood in Aspen.

name: Plato's Restaurant
description:
Plato's Deck will undergo maintenance , April 19th-May 16th. The restaurant will remain open for indoor dining, take-out and knock-and-drop room delivery.
We offer our Casual menu 7 days a week from 11am-9pm
Cancellations made less than 24 hours in advance will be subject to cancellation fees


Bask in the golden sunset as you dine on the finest and most inspiring Harvest menu in the city at Plato's Restaurant. You will discover local and regional fare as flavorful as the surroundings. Our exceptional culinary team selects the perfect seasonal ingredients to make your meal a truly memorable one.
Please call or check platosaspen.com for all current offerings and guidelines.

topReview.highlightedText: Amazing everything

name: Toro Kitchen and Lounge Viceroy Snowmass
description:
There's more to food than simply eating a meal. It's a thing that happens, one of importance, that we all share, savor and enjoy together. Experience the ritual that is Latin contemporary dining at TORO Kitchen & Lounge, one of the most innovative in Snowmass Village restaurants at Viceroy Snowmass.

Fill your table and delight in the flavors of a Pan-Latin inspired menu from acclaimed chef and restaurateur Richard Sandoval. TORO Kitchen & Lounge will feature a Pan-Latin-inspired menu, drawing inspiration from the flavors of Latin American regions. From grilled steaks to fish, all dishes are made from the finest and freshest products available. Whenever possible, we source organic, sustainable, and grass-fed products locally from Colorado.

After dining, don’t miss the hand-crafted cocktails and barrel-aged spirits at TORO Kitchen & Lounge. With a stonewood granite bar top from Brazil and accenting lighting, it guarantees the right vibe to end the day.

topReview.highlightedText: My girlfriends and I were staying at the beautiful Viceroy Snowmass and made plans for a special dinner at Toro.  They were so flexible with us when we needed to change the time.  We arrived to be greeted by an amazing host and hostess - seated immediately.  There wasn't a moment in time where we didn't feel completely taken care of by this wonderful staff.  The food was delicious - the best meal we had in Snowmass or the surrounding area, hands down.  It's the kind of place you talk about how good it was the next day.  We will be back!

name: Shamrock Brewing Company
description:
Located just two blocks from the Courtyard Marriott Hotel and the Convention Center in the heart of historic Pueblo, Colorado, Shamrock Brewing Company is the only Pueblo restaurant to offer a distinct dining alternative. Consisting of equal parts Irish pub, craft brewery, and restaurant makes Shamrock Brewing Company a truly unique Pueblo restaurant experience. We believe great beer, excellent food, and good friends go hand in hand. The food is great, the beer is world class, and the craic is outstanding! Craic (pronounced crack) is a Gaelic word, meaning a fun, friendly and exuberant atmosphere.

Whether for business or pleasure, Shamrock Brewing Company in Pueblo, Colorado is the place to meet. Our antique mahogany bar is warm and inviting. We offer an extensive list of top-shelf Irish and Scotch whiskeys, an ample wine selection, and specialty cocktails; but our passion is craft beer.

topReview.highlightedText: Friendly place

name: 221 South Oak
description:
221 is offering takeout at 221southoak.com. We also offer catering services in the privacy of your home.
221 is set in a tastefully refurbished historic home nestled in the trees on South Oak Street, just steps from the Gondola. For years, 221 South Oak has been renowned for its intimate atmosphere, incredible food, extensive wine list, friendly service and uncompromising quality.
Chef/Owner Eliza serves cuisine classified as Modern Bistro with an eclectic blend of flavors and styles.
A mélange of seafood, game and beef, with accompaniments that range from Deep South to Calypso to Classical French to Californian Cuisine to Creole, there is a dish for any adventurous palate.
Full Vegetarian Menu is available.
Wine and Delectable Pairing Classes are available weekly.
Patio Seating is wonderful and is first come first serve.

topReview.highlightedText: Many meals over many years They never don’t impress

name: Alpine and Antlers at Beaver Creek Lodge
description:
In the Beaver Creek Lodge with stunning mountain views, this beautiful and cozy retreat offers American-Mediterranean fusion with an artful twist. Enjoy re-imagined classics like our delicious bone-in Pork Shank with expertly mixed cocktails and CBD infusions to start or cap off your day of skiing, biking or hiking.

Whether fueling up for the next adventure or de-thawing by the fire pits after an active day, Alpine and Antlers delivers views, service, and food with an altitude.

topReview.highlightedText: Our waiter Jeremy was great and everyone did a great job to make our anniversary feel special

name: Allred's Restaurant

address.line1: Gondola Station, St. Sophia Station c/o 565 Mountain Village Blvd

description:
Allred's has resumed dine-in service, at a limited capacity, for dinner service only. Due to the capacity limitations, Allred's will be operating with a prix fixe menu and two seatings each night. Reservations are strongly encouraged.
1st Seating: 5:00pm - 6:30pm
2nd Seating: 7:00pm - 8:45pm

Allred's is Telluride's elegant and unique dining experience. Renowned for its culinary excellence and extraordinary service, Allred's offers our guests an award winning Wine List, with an emphasis on exceptional wines from France, Italy and the United States. Exquisite views and a rustic ambiance unite to create a unique dining experience at 10,551 feet above sea level! Allred's Contemporary American cuisine is available daily for dinner throughout the Summer and Winter seasons. Keynotes: Incredible views overlooking the Town of Telluride 1800ft below, creative American dishes with International overtones, a Private Dining Room, and an Award winning wine list.

topReview.highlightedText: As always, absolutely amazing!

name: Cosmopolitan - Telluride
description:
The Cosmopolitan is open seven days a week for indoor dining, outdoor dining, and takeout.
Happy hour is 4-5pm on the outdoor deck only. Outside seating is first-come/first-serve by the host, weather permitting.

Thank you for your trust in us to dine at the restaurant...safely...during the pandemic.

Chad Scothorn, Owner and Executive Chef, has received national attention and praise for his original cuisine. Truly authentic, all menu items are made entirely from scratch, including the house baked bread, sauces, desserts, and even the ice creams. Cosmopolitan offers an extensive wine list with local, domestic and international wines, and delicious craft cocktails.

topReview.highlightedText: Great, as always. Best in Telluride

name: The National
description: The National is an elevated gathering place that offers unconventional yet approachable dining experiences.

topReview.highlightedText: We don’t often eat expensive meals out because we can cook a lot of what we buy; however, the National was worth the money and ambiance. Flavors were great and went above what we expected.

name: Izakaya Carbondale
description:
Thank you for visiting Kenichi Izakaya Carbondale. An Izakaya is a type of informal Japanese pub. At sake breweries during the late 18th century, people in Japan began using sake kegs as stools and snacks were served. This small plates menu was designed to encourage sharing amongst friends and family. Food is prepared in multiple kitchens and arrives as it is ready to ensure freshness. We make the majority of our menu in house, from scratch, and use locally sourced ingredients whenever possible.
We offer full sushi bar, kitchen and bar.

topReview.highlightedText: Great and unusual ramen.

name: Backcountry Pizza & Tap House
description: Backcountry Pizza & Tap House is proud to offer Boulder, Colorado's best gourmet pizza, chicken wings, and the widest selection of draft microbrews. With 60+ beers on draft, new rotating taps daily, and more than 300 bottles, you'll have no trouble finding the perfect beverage to enjoy with our wide array of appetizers, pizza, and entrees.

topReview.highlightedText: Awesome food, great service loved it!😊

name: BJ's Restaurant & Brewhouse - Boulder - 29th St
description: Time counts at BJ's Restaurant & Brewhouse. Since our humble beginnings back in 1978, we've continued to refine our brewhouse experience to make BJ's a place where you can make the most of any meal. We want BJ's to be a place where the moment you leave is the moment you plan on coming back. We pride ourselves in our craft and attention to detail. Our guests come here for our award-winning handcrafted beer. They come here for the Southern California twist we've put on the Chicago-style deep dish pizza. And they come here for our Pizookies®, our world-renowned dessert. But above all we know people come here to make their good times better. So in many ways we haven't just crafted a brand, but a mindset. And our guests are the reason for this. And it's because of them we're continually striving to make sure every moment they choose to spend with us counts. Welcome to BJ's, a restaurant with a Brewhouse soul.

topReview.highlightedText: I tried a new item (new to me at least) on the menu, the Enlightened Asian Chopped Salad, and it wasn't that great.  So many of BJs other salads are sooooo much better.  Well, now I know not to order that again!

name: Willow Creek Bistro - Ritz Carlton Club
description:
Willow Creek Bistro at The Ritz-Carlton Club, Aspen Highlands is a casual restaurant that specializes in contemporary American cuisine. The restaurants interior is designed to provide a modern take on the classic ski lodge, complete with plush comfortable seating, stone walls and amber colored accents. The dining room provides a fantastic view of the neighboring ski slopes and the restaurant features both indoor and outdoor seating options. Willow Creek Bistro also features a full-service bar.

Begin the meal with an order of the restaurants famous house smoked wings, hand made flatbreads or popular appetizers like the Colorado lamb meatballs and truffle parmesan sweet potato fries. Willow Creek Bistro offers creative entree options like wild game elk and buffalo meatloaf with asparagus and Harrisa-agave glaze, and classics like massive cheeseburgers or seared Salmon.

topReview.highlightedText:
Straight up hidden gem in Highlands.  Simple menu that they crush!  Quinoa salad with grilled salmon and the best pho in Aspen to start, and Buffalo short rib absolutely insane.

Bartender Lulu is a pro while also being an absolute riot.

name: The Edge Restaurant and Bar - Snowmass
description: The Edge Restaurant and Bar at the Timberline Condominiums is offering wines by the glass, draft beers, craft cocktails, and food specials. Chef Jason DeBacker, German background influences an alpine menu with flavors from Germany, Austria, Switzerland, France, and Italy that will delight your taste buds. We invite you to savor our fondue accompanied with cuts of baked bread, fresh green apples, vegetables, and sausage. Other signature items include our homemade German wurst and schnitzel.  The Edge's menu has gluten-free and vegetarian options.  Reservations are available on Opentable.com.

topReview.highlightedText: The food is wonderful, service was fabulous. We love this restaurant.

name: Joonas Aspen
description:
Aspen's first wine and tapas restaurant. Topping the menu are tapas, or pintxos, such as Iberico cured meats and Spanish cheeses, Gambas al Pil Pil and Hamachi Tiradito. Joonas features an extensive selection of wines, tequilas and mezcals.

The eccentric and unique design is created by co-partner Bridger Smith. With touches of modern and antique, the ambience is cool and quaint. Antique glass windows and brick from the historic Crystal Palace Hotel are incorporated in the space. There is a 16ft light structure that mimics the constellations of the Southern Hemisphere, as seen from co-owner and restauranteur Alia Joonas's home in Mauritius.

topReview.highlightedText: Love the ambience. Dark cool wood glass metal downstairs.  Variety of seating from big wood tables too high tops to hidden corner rooms with bottles of wine against the wall. But the lighting was such that each table highlighted to have an intimate dinner experience, but good music in the background.  The food was excellent, delicate flavors.  Lots of tapas options as well as full entrées. The halibut was so tender and perfectly cooked. Chicken Tinga had a great flavor.  Even they are Marconi almonds and olives were delicious to nosh on and the lobster appetizer was to savor the flavors!

name: New Sheridan Chop House
description: A lively main street steak house offering a selection of the worlds finest steaks, eclectic fresh seafood and daily specials. Executive Chef Mike Moran focuses on the highest quality local ingredients prepared with Gourmet American flair. Paired with an award winning wine list, the New Sheridan Chop House is sure to please the most discriminating palates. 970-728-9100 www.newsheridan.com

topReview.highlightedText: I have been to this restaurant many times over many years and it has never been anything but great. The bison ribeye was over the top. Ordered it rare and it was wonderful!

name: Allegria - Carbondale
description:
* If you do not see the availability you are looking for please contact us. We would love to accommodate you.
Italian - European casual bistro with in the heart of the up and coming food town of Carbondale. Venetian style decor from local artists with open kitchen. We are using slow cook methods in food preparation with local seasonal ingredients. Our special menus are changing daily whatever can be gathered and harvested in the valley and surroundings. The wine list is hand selected and changes frequently with new and exiting old and new world wines as well a full service bar is available. We are catering through out the valley with in-house cooking, Butler service for all occasions, family, formal, entertaining. We are a truly family operated restaurant with the next generation already in the kitchen and service occasionally. We as a family are truly committed to your pleasure in dining and your experience in visiting Carbondale. Come and visit - Enjoy Allegria.

topReview.highlightedText: Great restaurant. Amazing food. Great service!

name: Devil's Kitchen - Hotel Maverick
description:
Devil’s Kitchen cuisine is rooted in fresh regional ingredients and provisions sourced through our longstanding relationships with local farmers, herdsmen, and artisans.

Informed by the daily harvest and served alongside a thoughtfully curated collection of exceptional craft cocktails, Devil’s Kitchen cuisine is constantly evolving with the seasons and celebrates the foods indigenous to Colorado’s Grand Valley.

topReview.highlightedText: Our waitress was amazing, the food was amazing, the whole evening was perfect!

name: Living Room - W Aspen
description:
Directly nestled mountain side, the indoor/outdoor Living Room is a one-of-a-kind restaurant and bar located at W Aspen. Our Executive Chef serves up globally inspired, yet locally-sourced bites and shareable plates hand -crafted with care and dedication each evening. Shake it up with a mix of thirst quenching cocktails that have a hint of flavor from many different cultures around the globe to ensure an evening full of magical memories and delighted taste buds.

For parties over 8, information regarding cabanas, and all other inquiries please email us at waspendining@whotels.com.

topReview.highlightedText: Great roof deck hang out. Food was just ok. Waitress was great.

name: Slopeside Grill
description: Slopeside Steamboat is a family friendly restaurant in Steamboat Springs, CO at the base of Mt Werner.   A great place in the winter to soak up the local Steamboat scene, while still in your ski boots or taking a rest after a summer hike.  This popular ski-in restaurant has local dogs playing outside, while their owners relax listening to live music, sharing pitchers of beer, and dining on classic American cuisine. Be sure to visit the Dulce Vida Tequila Ice bar this winter and enjoy the unrivaled Sunday Brunch with live music all summer long. See you at Slopeside Steamboat.

topReview.highlightedText: Stopped on a road trip.  Very festive.  Reservations suggested since it was busy.  Great service.   Mushroom Swiss burger was one of the best I’ve ever had.  Side salad was fresh and delicious.

name: Soupçon
description:
-American cuisine steeped in classic French technique accompanied by an award winning wine program.
Located in a historic mining cabin off of Elk Avenue, Soupcon offers a formal dining experience in a cozy atmosphere.

Open for Dinner Monday through Sunday
7 pm (reservations required)

*-PRIX FIXE 5 COURSE TASTING MENU ONLY-*

topReview.highlightedText: We went to Soupçon to celebrate an anniversary and it was as lovely as expected. The ambiance is all Crested Butte and the food and service are entirely top-notch. Soupçon is not a place you go to for "value' - is a special restaurant unlike any other.

name: The Artisan at Stonebridge Inn
description: In winter, cozy up in the lounge, relax at the bar, or sit down to one of the finest dining experiences in Snowmass. In summer, enjoy the Colorado sunshine and dine al fresco on the secluded outdoor patio. An extensive wine list, innovative cocktails, and a selection of Colorado's finest craft brews on tap compliment the menu of mountain favorites. Considered one of the best deals in Snowmass, the always-tempting bar menu offers items between $9 and $15 per dish. Join us on Monday evenings for our Grill Night (5:30pm-9pm), featuring our Burger and Beer special!

topReview.highlightedText: Good food, Reasonable prices, and despite the lack of help the service was fine! We will return

name: Silver West Feedstore
description: We are a new restaurant, we will fill out this description shortly! thank you

topReview.highlightedText:
Quick, friendly service
food was excellent 
ambience was good

name: The Winery Restaurant
description:
The Winery Restaurant has been an icon among western Colorado restaurants for over 35 years. The restaurant makes its home in a 95 year old building that used to house a horse drawn fire station. A gas lamp lit, grapevine canopied alley frames this romantic location perfectly. The beautifully remodeled building contains flowered stain glass windows, barn wood and bricks.

Steve Thoms acquired the restaurant in late June of 2004 after taking a couple of years off from his previous restaurant. His mission at he Winery is simple: Show the restaurant and its patrons the attention that they deserve. Use only top quality ingredients, and establish The Winery as the premiere restaurant in the Grand Junction area.

The Winery provides a variety of steaks, chicken, pork and fresh seafood specials nightly in an atmosphere that can not be rivaled anywhere!

topReview.highlightedText: We went here for our anniversary dinner and they did not disappoint😊 Great food, great service ❤️

name: Mateo
description: Mateo is a casually elegant, bustling, neighborhood Provencal restaurant.  The cuisine features seasonal menus with organic fare sourced from local farmers.  Mateo offers a dynamic wine list & breathtaking full-service bar.

topReview.highlightedText: I had a reservation and was seated immediately, waiter came right over and told what beers were on tap.  We each ordered an entree, I the had that skin in boneless chicken in a butter sauce which is consistently amazingly delicious.  My friend has the steak Whitbeck enjoyed very much.  Fries were crispy and hot.  No dessert but another excellent meal at Mateo.

name: Wooden Nickel
description: The Wooden Nickel continues to provide consistent, top-quality, products complemented by a dedicated and friendly staff. We welcome you to enjoy your evening with us and hope to see you many times in the future!

topReview.highlightedText: We were up for a good steak dinner after a long day hiking, and the elk did not disappoint. Live music from Rachal VanSlyke was a lot of fun. Joe our witer was great and a good conversationalist. Only marked down  a star because the baked potato was small, and "loaded" only came with some bad cheese and sour cream.

name: Little Mammoth Steakhouse
description:
Little Mammoth Steak House is family owned and family oriented restaurant tucked away in the heart of Snowmass Village.
We offer a variety of chicken, pork, lamb and fish dishes, but of course, ultimately, steakhouse is all about the beef. That is why our steaks are done right, with bold flavors, high quality and our signature, served on Himalayan salt blocks.
Come in and see why the locals call us the best kept secret of Snowmass!

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent food and even better service! This is real gem for Snowmass! Finally great steak house in this beautiful town. Wine choice by Diana was the best ever! Highly recommended!

name: Ristorante Ti Amo - Eagle
description: Coming Soon!

topReview.highlightedText: Food & service was amazing.  Staff was very attentive and friendly.  WE'll be back.

name: Steak House No. 316- Boulder
description:
A classic style steak house located in downtown Boulder, Colorado.
We are updating our hours and online availability, so please contact us directly for reservations for now! Thank you.

name: Avanti Boulder
description: After the grand opening in September, explore your culinary options after picking up one of our twenty draft beers, classic cocktails, or affordably priced wines. Find us for a beverage at one of two large bars (main level and rooftop) or grab a seat in our lounge, dining area, or rooftop deck and one of our many cocktail servers will find you.

name: Haymaker
description:
Haymaker Patio and Grill will open Thursday, May 13th
All Day Menu 11am-8pm
Turn Window 7am-8pm
Happy Hour 2:30pm-4:30pm
Fish Fry Friday Starting June 11th 5pm-9pm
Prime Rib Dinner Starting June 12th 5pm-9pm

topReview.highlightedText: Great service with Tyler our waiter!

name: Park East Restaurant
description: We are proud to have been voted “Best of Pueblo” in the following categories: Best Prime Rib, Pueblo Cheiftain 2010, Best Cocktail, Best Girls Night Out, Best First Date, Best Steak and Best Fine Dining, Pueblo Chieftain 2012. We were also named Best Martini, United Way Taste of Pueblo 2009. In 2013, we were also voted into the following categories: Best Night Out with Friends, Best Cocktail, Best Fine Dining, Best Steak and Best Restaurant for a First Date.

topReview.highlightedText: Food was delicious and service was excellent. Highly recommend

name: Ken & Sue's
description: Be Our Guest!  Owners Ken & Sue Fusco welcome you to their casual, fine dining restaurant.  Enjoy great food and great service, all in a comfortable atmosphere.  Their Modern American Bistro menu has something for everyone.  We promise you'll feel right at home at our place whether just enjoying a night out on the town or a special occasion. ***We're Sorry, No Pets, Service Animals Excluded***

topReview.highlightedText: Had such a great dinner on the back patio. Service was spot on and the drinks and food were delicious!!!

name: Sidework
description:
Sidework is a cozy 1950's styled American lounge in an intimate setting that offers a full menu composed of sharable plates, craft cocktails, fresh home brews and an extensive, well curated wine list.

Due to Covid restrictions, we currently have limited outdoor dining available for a limited number of parties each night but we are offering all of our menu items to go. We do not have any indoor seating available at the moment which greatly limits our capacity to serve guest.

Please call us or visit our website for more details. If you have made a reservation through OpenTable, please expect a call from us regarding your reservation as there is no indoor dining available in San Miguel County. Please do not plan on anything until you have heard from us. Thank you for your patience and we hope to see you soon.

Cheers,
Sidework

topReview.highlightedText: We had the creole eggplant caponata, black garlic hummus, and smoked salmon dip. It was all amazing. Next we had the corn and crab bisque and it was so damn good 10/10. Then the red snapper over polenta which was incredible. Good for sharing with others.

name: La Marmotte
description: La Marmotte, located in historic downtown Telluride, specializes in classic French cuisine and wine. We are open Friday, Saturday, and Sunday for lunch from 12-3 with dining a la carte and for dinner seven nights from 530-9 with an $80 three course menu. Please visit our website www.lamarmotte.com for more details or call 970.728.6232. Have a great day.

topReview.highlightedText: All good, thanks for the outdoor dining!

name: Hotel Boulderado
description: Join us for special events and holidays on Hotel Boulderado's Mezzanine and Ballroom. Hotel Boulderado's special events and annual holiday traditions are not something to miss featuring seasonal chef-inspired menus. The Mezzanine is set in the historic wing under a beautiful stained-glass canopy overlooking the charming lobby. The spacious, sunny Ballroom is located in the north wing along Broadway and Pine Streets.

topReview.highlightedText: Mothers dat

name: Oskar Blues- Boulder
description:
The Oskar Blues Pearl St. Taproom is now open for business! Swing on over and check out our draft list that features 48 tap beers from Oskar Blues Brewery, Cigar City Brewing, Perrin Brewing Co, Wasatch Brewery, Squatters Craft Beers, plus a carefully curated selection of guest taps. On top of the draft lineup, the Boulder Taproom also has an insane selection of beer to go, including fresh Crowler® fills, from OB and our homies at Cigar City, Perrin, Wasatch, and Squatters.
We offer a full menu featuring Oskar Blues takes on classic pub food, including some of the best burgers, wings, and pizza in Boulder!
We have one of the largest, southwest facing patios on Pearl St., with iconic views of the Flatirons. Music happens every Tuesday, Friday & Saturday night inside the taproom, so you can hang on the patio and listen to some jams.

name: Almresi
description:
Almresi - something more than a restaurant. 
The European rustic  mountain cottage  offers daily Lunch&Dinner in a cozy exceptional atmosphere.  
Be inspired by our welcoming staff and  join us  for daily Après Ski and  Happy hour!

Almresi is also an excellent place for celebrating a great mountain Birthdayparty, Rehearsal Dinner or even a lovely Wedding.

Where the Alps meets the Rockies.

topReview.highlightedText: Long time locals and this is one of our favorite restaurants in vail. The decor and atmosphere are too cute and the food is even better. We always get the meat and cheeseboard. It’s the best one you’ll ever have. I also, without fail, always get the pork shank. The meat just falls off the bone. I highly recommend!

name: Mountain Social Bar & Lounge
description: A premier après-ski destination, Mountain Social offers refined spirits, handcrafted cocktails, and light fare with a sweeping backdrop of Aspen Mountain. The space offers tribute to the elegant wilderness of Lake St. Regis, which inspired founder John Jacob Astor IV to open his first hotel near Central Park in 1904.

topReview.highlightedText: Chef Carlos was outstanding to accommodate our vegan diet.

name: Black Iron Kitchen and Bar
description:
Black Iron Kitchen and Bar is currently offering Delivery Services, To-Go Services, and covered heated outdoor dining.
Black Iron Kitchen and Bar is Telluride’s best après ski lounge, and modern mountain cuisine experience. Our chef and staff cultivate menu items with the farmers, local purveyors and artisan growers, and connect with the land and food that fuels our passion. Black Iron offers something special for those special dietary requirements, such as a wide selection of gluten free and vegetarian dishes.
Comfortable for the entire family, the Black Iron interior is warm woods, dark steel, and natural stone, providing a modern yet casual dining environment. Located rinkside in Mountain Village, signature dining “fire-tables” accent the outdoor plaza, the perfect spot for people-watching and liquid restoration after a hard day on the slopes.

topReview.highlightedText: Greatest for outdoor dining with fantastic ambience, gas warmers if necessary (and they look great even if not needed for heat!), and exceptional servers and service. One of our favorites not only on mMountain Village (where it it the best, hands down) but I Telluride as well.

name: The Cabin in Steamboat Springs
description: The Cabin features complimentary parking, weekly seafood specials, and happy hour at the Steamboat Grand Hotel. The vast menu spans fresh salads, entrees, sandwiches and burgers.  Truly something for every taste. It’s a place that is all about fun, value, quality ingredients, served with a hearty helping of Steamboat’s warm hospitality and friendly service.

topReview.highlightedText: They did a kind job accommodating our toddler

name: Barrio Social
description: Coming Soon!

name: Silver Sage
description: Chef David Gutowski’s seasonal Colorado cuisine centers on an uncompromising commitment to beautiful ingredients and expertly executed preparations resulting in a concentrated depth of flavors.  When paired with genuine, graceful hospitality and breathtaking sunsets over Castle Peak, Silver Sage offers a thoughtful, distinguished dining experience.  While only available to Red Sky Ranch membership for lunch, the restaurant warmly opens its doors to the public for dinner during the stunning Colorado summer season.

topReview.highlightedText: This place has an amazing view but needs a new chef. No one at our table had anything that they considered wonderful. The wine list was robust but some of the wines were probably not properly stored. For appetizers, the crabcake and tuna we’re both good. Of the entrees we tried: Seabass, salmon the best was a steak. Would not recommend either the Seabass or salmon.

name: La Tour Crystal Cabins
description:
Welcome to La Tour Restaurant's Crystal Cabins--our premium, private seating. La Tour is a French Restaurant located in the heart of Vail. Chef-owner Paul Ferzacca is committed to providing you with the best in everything. Honored with Wine Spectator's “Best of Award of Excellence”, a food rating of “Extraordinary” in Zagat, and winner of TripAdvisor’s Certificate of Excellence three years in a row. La Tour has become one of the most acclaimed restaurants in Vail.
Each Cabin is heated and seats up to four guests. Outdoor Crystal Cabin reservations will be allotted 2 hours for the Crystal Cabin seating.

topReview.highlightedText: Service started off a bit slow, but definitely got better and attentive. Food was very good. The outdoor seating in the private structures was fun and unique.

name: Three Peaks Grill
description:
TPG is a chef owned restaurant offering creative contemporary cuisine. Steamboat’s largest dining room features fireside dining with 210 degree mountain views. The eatery has a display kitchen and raw bar featuring fresh oysters and seafood. TPG also offers hand cut CAB steaks, creative salads and house-made desserts. Our bar and lounge offers fine libations, wines and hand crafted cocktails in a casual, comfortable atmosphere. Non-alcoholic, vegetarian and vegan menus available.

TPG is considering implementing a new C- 19 policy in the future for entry into the restaurant.
Guests would be required to show picture ID & proof of vaccination, or a negative C-19 test result within 48 hours of the reservation for all guests 12 and older. We will notify you when this may go into effect.
Thanks for your support and understanding as we strive to provide a safe environment for our customers and staff.

topReview.highlightedText: Brought my parents here

name: 4 Eagle Ranch
description:
Summer Wagon Ride Dinners
$80 13 and over - $45 4-12 - Free under 3yo (not including tax, gratuity, and bar)

Includes musical entertainment, horse-drawn wagon rides, a delicious buffet, and a cash bar is available for alcoholic beverages and sodas. Other activities include horseshoe pits, cornhole, steer head roping, and volleyball available.

Wagon Ride Dinners is the perfect event for the entire family, with something for everyone to enjoy.  Whether you just sit on one of the many porches to enjoy the view of the Sawatch Mountain Range, throw a couple of horseshoes, or dance to the music, 4 Eagle Ranch is eager to have you experience this family-friendly event.

Seating time subject to availability.

CANCELLATION POLICY
Cancellations MUST be made 48 hours prior to reservation DATE or the guest will be charged the FULL amount of the evening.

topReview.highlightedText: Super fun and relaxing night!  Food was yummy and the views are awesome!

name: Slow Groovin BBQ Snowmass
description:
In Colorado, not only do we have the beautiful mountains for inspiration, but we have flexibility in our quest for great barbecue. We are not expected to adhere to a certain style of BBQ by critics or long standing regional traditions. This allows us to adopt our favorite tastes from hot spots across the country and to create a unique blend that is Colorado BBQ.

Our mission is to create an atmosphere that embraces the important things in life: Family, Nature, Community and of course ridiculously good BBQ. We take pride in every item on our menu. So kick back and Slow Groove your way into something to remember.

topReview.highlightedText: You walk in and this doesn’t look like a place that will serve great food. But don’t judge this place by its cover. Great wings, nachos, and entrees. What a find!

name: 626 on Rood...Modern American Cuisine and Wine Bar
description: In our charming space, each day begins with stoves being lit, wine glasses being polished, and staff tasting wine. Here, we’ve cultivated a ripe passion for providing sustainable, eclectic farm-to-table fare and an unparalleled wine list that spans the globe. Our work with local farmers culminates in an abundance of seasonal dishes that are as much an expression of place as they are an immersive sensory experience. At 626, all are welcome, tradition is respected, and the novel is explored. Unwind, imbibe, and savor.

topReview.highlightedText: A MUST if you are visiting the Grand Valley! 626 outdoes themselves, every, single, time! From the moment you walk in the door, you can expect an excellent experience. Food is always creative and extremely tasty. If something isn't right, they take the extra steps to fix it. Incredible selection of beverages from cocktails, beer, to all sorts of wine! Always enjoy eating here!

name: Elk Ave Prime - Crested Butte
description:
Elk Ave Prime is located in the heart of downtown Crested Butte on Elk Avenue. We feature hand carved Prime and Wagyu steaks, Colorado lamb, Elk, Buffalo, fresh Seafood, farm to restaurant garden salads and more.

We feature many beers on tap, most of which are Colorado born, as well as the largest wine selection in the valley. You can enjoy any of our drinks from our outdoor patio or cozy up next to our fireplace, great after a long day of skiing.

Elk Ave Prime is one of the largest venues in Crested Butte, ideal for large parties or wedding receptions.

topReview.highlightedText: So happy to have Elk Prime open again and with most of the original menu in tact.  Our server, Dara, was great and gave us time to be leisurely.  The Brussels sprouts appetizer was fantastic and none of our plates had anything left on them after our entrees.  We shared the side dish of Mac and cheese and it was plenty to feed 4.  Great night dining out!

name: Atina Bar + Grille
description:
(Formerly known as Patina Bar and Grill)
Carbondale Colorado's premier American Bistro serving dinner and cocktails and brunch on weekends. We also cater and can host your next private event.

topReview.highlightedText:
Appetizers were great
Food was great
Service was great!

It's a win!

name: Timber Room
description: Cap a thrilling day on the mountain with an intimate ending at Timber Room with a loved one or small group of friends. Toast to the moment with expertly crafted whiskey-forward cocktails and our extensive champagne selection around a warming fireplace or the commanding bar. When it’s time to dine, elevated small plates meant for sharing have a touch of Old World flair, whether it’s Devilish Eggs with shaved black truffle or a Timber Room baked potato topped with crème fraîche and Russian osetra caviar. Sophisticated, yet always approachable modern mountain dishes range from line-caught wild salmon with lemon caper butter to Rocky Mountain elk loin with local huckleberry jus.

topReview.highlightedText: Exceptional! Quickly becoming our favorite in town and Mountain Village

name: Velvet Buck
description: Come enjoy Chef Carlos delicious menu influenced by Colorado mountain cuisine with a slight French flair. Our restaurant, located inside the St. Regis Hotel, offers generous spacing between tables and parties.

topReview.highlightedText: Great for some apres Ski food in the St Regis

name: Altezza at The Peaks
description: Altezza restaurant at The Peaks Resort & Spa offers casual mountain dining with regionally sourced ingredients and panoramic Telluride views from both the restaurant and outdoor deck. We welcome you to savor breakfast, and all day menus in relaxed comfort with genuine hospitality. The Altezza to-go menu presents a wide variety of items to enjoy in the privacy of your room or anywhere else in the resort (available daily from 11:00 a.m. to 9:00 p.m.)

topReview.highlightedText: Food was well prepared and the selection was good.  We will go back again.

name: The Village Table
description: The Village Table opened in Spring 2013 features a vibrant menu of mediterranean food from Spain, Italy and France as well as American classics. Enjoy Johnny Gerona's creative cuisine, a 30  yr. local, former head chef at La Marmotte, owner operator of Pacific St. Market (a locals favorite) Creative  specials offered daily for lunch, apres ski and dinner. Menu items include many healthy entrees, salads,  and gluten free items available. The newest restaurant in the Mtn. Village is casually elegant  and unique. 100 bottle wine cellar with many well priced  and delicious choices To go, catering on and off premise special events available. Conveniently located in the Mtn. Village core next to the conference center and the climbing rock. Do not miss this restaurant during your next visit to Telluride. 970 728 1117

topReview.highlightedText: Always delicious this year. Have you eaten there four times in the last six months and every time was great. Nice to sit outdoors and indoors is great because tables are reasonably spaced. Awesome bartender and super servers. Could eat the trout once a week! Wish they would bring back Nina’s flan But the chocolate mousse is close second on the dessert menu.

name: Floradora Saloon
description: Whether you’re craving a juicy burger or fresh salad, we’ve got it all here at Floradora Saloon. Our restaurant’s unique menu features mouthwatering options for appetizers, like the honey-baked Brie or the locals favorite jalapenos poppers. We also offer and array delicious soups and salads, the Diablo bowl is a must after a long day in mountains. Our platters include salmon fish tacos, blackened tofu or the popular fish and chips. We also offer a large selection of delicious whiskey, locals beers, distinct wines and cocktail.

topReview.highlightedText: The pistachio crusted honey brie cheese wedge with apples and cibatta was AMAZING! All the food was so tasty and fresh!! Highly recommend this restaurant.

name: The Creede Hotel and Restaurant
description:
Arp’s at The Creede Hotel features classic American dishes along with international comfort food. Our specials each night highlight a different culinary tradition; Italian, Asian, German, Cajun, and more. Situated in the beautiful Rocky Mountain wilderness, we find some magic in a whimsical tour of the world on our plates! Our bartender has themed special drinks to pair with our nightly specials. Our goal is to prepare the familiar flavors of home and also explore international favorites with an elegant touch.

**PLEASE NOTE: If you'd like to reserve the cabaret, please make sure to book via our OpenTable experience or call the CRT. The reservation times for for the cabaret shows only for 5:15-5:45 pm. **

topReview.highlightedText: A really fine meal by any standard, delicious, perfectly cooked and assisted by an excellent house crafted drink of the day.  Followed by an outstanding Creede Repertory Theatre production.

name: Primus Restaurant
description:
Wild Game, Fresh Seafood, Uncompromising Quality

WE ARE BACK OPEN FOR DINE IN! Due to limited capacity, reservations are STRONGLY recommended.

We are so happy to welcome you back into our Dining Room!

topReview.highlightedText: We found this place by accident. The entire restaurant is only 9 feet wide what they do with that space is just amazing. The chef prepared some of the best meals we’ve had in years and the cocktails made with fresh ingredients (fresh squeezed juice) were really good. Service was excellent, food was excellent and I would highly recommend this place.  ’d be surprised if they don’t start to get booked up every single night because of the quality of their food.

name: WET Deck - W Hotel Aspen
description:
Come soak it in at WET Deck, the hottest summer spot in Aspen. WET Deck is complete with a pool, a hot tub, fire pits, DJ’s, 360 mountain views, and a full bar. It’s the place to see and been seen.

WET Deck rooftop restaurant and bar opens 11AM daily to in-house guests and the local public.

There is a $35 beverage and food minimum for non-hotel guests (per guest). In-house guests and neighborhood cardholders are exempt from the minimum B+F spend.

The WET Deck Cabanas (aka Daydream Lounge) are now taking reservations for Fridays, Saturdays, and Sundays. All other days are on a first come, first serve basis. See below for more information on how to reserve your own Cabana. WET Deck currently has four (4) Cabanas available: two (2) day beds and two (2) lounge couches.

Cabana rates: $250 per Cabana

Cabanas include:
all day access
infused water
2 specialty cocktails
2 Cool Haus ice cream treats

To make a reservation, email: waspendining@whotels.com

topReview.highlightedText:
Awesome rooftop spot, so much fun and great drinks! Liked most of our food but the Hummus was not too great. For sure raw Chickpeas not roasted, had a weird flavor… also very thick likely no tahini or barely any, would be better off serving Sabre. Not a horrible spread, just not hummus…

Waiter tried to charge us $250 for our cabana which we never ordered / requested. Got that taken care of. A bit offended they tried to charge for it (website also says Cabana comes with drinks, dessert…etc which we didn’t get which made it even worse). Seems new and I’m sure it will be great with a little work and time.

name: East by Southwest
description:
Take Out is AVAILABLE

East by Southwest is offering take-out food at this current time. We are open noon-8pm Monday thru Saturday and 4pm-8pm Sunday. Please call us at 970-247-5533 to place your order. We are back, so come in and get your FAVORITE Mojito and more!

topReview.highlightedText: Our waitress Olivia was awesome but she couldn’t help the slowness of the food coming out and the untimely ness. My tempura meal( not appetizer) came out at least 10 minutes before the rest of the tables food ( which was sushi). That part was annoying. Other than that , the food etc was great.

name: Sow's Ear
description:
The Sow’s Ear, established in 1986, is located in the Silverpick Lodge along US HWY 550, 24 miles north of Durango and one mile south of Purgatory Resort.

We feature “Refined Rustic” cuisine. That’s short hand for local, seasonal and prepared in house. What Grandma made but with a wider variety of ingredients, prepared for the 21st century pallet and lifestyle.

We are known for the Best Steaks on the Mountain, elk, quail, wild boar, miso salmon, fresh salad (we grow our own sprouts in house) and homemade dessert We bake bread fresh daily and even can our own fruit for dessert. We also offer vegetarian and gluten free items from our vegan Garde Manger.

Nestled between the Hermosa Cliffs, Engineer Mountain and the Twilight Peaks, the Sow’s Ear is well appointed and intimate, yet with four massive windows there’s not a bad seat in the house. Come join us at the Sow’s Ear Restaurant for dinner and libations and a most pleasant dining experience in the heart of the Rockies.

topReview.highlightedText: Really a great place.

name: The Tunnel
description: Chef Mark Krasic and his team are looking forward to sharing the Tunnel experience with you and your guests. Join us for our 6 Course prix-fixe, co-mingled dining with other guests for the full experience. We create 3 new fused menus per season. The price per guest is $110. We also have an optional wine pairing for $50/person. We will have 2 seating times for the remainder of the season at 6:45 and 7 p.m. If trying to book the day of, please call us for availability, to make your reservation at 970.708.3663. Please note there is a 72 hour cancellation policy, due to the size of our very intimate, private venue. You will receive a text from us the day prior to your reservation for detailed directions, confirming any food allergies and the password.

topReview.highlightedText: The shared table was really fun!

name: The Grill at Grand Z Casino Hotel
description: Coming Soon!

name: Siam's at the Inn
description:
Indulge Your Senses
Chef – Inspired traditional Thai cuisine & Asian influenced dishes. Dinner served nightly using the freshest specially sourced ingredients. A culinary experience enhanced by striking mountain sunsets and a cocktail menu unlike any other in Telluride.

topReview.highlightedText: Menu has changed from my prior visit but it’s still good food.  No outdoor dining was disappointing.

name: The West End Bistro at The Hotel Telluride
description:
The West End Bistro is presently open for in-house dining, take-out and delivery. You will find all of your favorite appetizers with a twist, fresh dinner specials made daily, a diverse children’s menu, and homemade tavern fare using fresh, local ingredients.
Make your reservation or place your order on-line or over the phone 970-369-1188.

topReview.highlightedText: Shane is great! The food is amazing. The value is the best in Telluride!

name: The Roost
description: Brought to you by Chris & Michele Redding, the owners of Cuckoo's Chicken House & Waterin' Hole and The Animas City Theatre, The Roost opened June 12, 2018, offering affordable, casual dining in a fun, downtown location. The Roost offers a wide variety of appetizers, salads, sandwiches, and entrees.  Pair your meal with a glass of wine, craft beer or signature cocktail.  Finish your meal with one of Nana Pat's Cookie Dough Brownies ala  mode, you'll be glad you saved room for dessert!

topReview.highlightedText: Everything and everyone one was fantastic!

name: No Coast Sushi
description:
Sustainable Sources, Superior Quality

Our restaurant is urban modern with an active up-beat vibe.

We at No Coast Sushi value our resources and environment by purchasing our fish from purveyors who pledge to only fish in-season, in-stream, without nets. We also purchase some fish, such as Salmon, from sustainable ranches in New Zealand. We fly fish in three days a week from our main fish purveyors: Honolulu Fish Co. (Hawaii) and Seattle Fish Co. (Washington).

In our kitchen we use hormone, antibiotic free meats for our cooked dishes.
