We also purchase locally grown produce when in season and continue to pledge to buy more each year and create more Vegan/Vegetarian options. Our chefs and bartenders make 99% all of our items in-house, including our sauces and drink mixes.

We care about our food, quality, presentation and your enjoyment.

Please join us and experience what Modern Japanese can be.

topReview.highlightedText: Delicious food, amazing service,  wonderful evening!

name: Seven Rivers Steaks Seafood and Spirits
description:
Join us where Seven Rivers meet to create an amazing authentic steakhouse experience. Deep wood tones in our lounge and restaurant as well as unique lighting features, create the feel of a historic casino steakhouse combined with the modern wonder of culinary advancements. Chef Bill and Chef Gary will wow you from the exhibition kitchen, creating unique steak and seafood combinations. Prime cuts, local/organic vegetable and ingredients, and the knowledge and some secrets from Chefs who have traveled the world.
Join us in the lounge for happy hour and then head into the main Seven Rivers dining area for an evening that is like no other in the Four Corners.

topReview.highlightedText: Nice great food and wine

name: Alpinist and the Goat
description:
Fondue, Raclette, Filet Mignon, craft cocktails, extensive wines in an intimate setting above a gallery on Main Street Telluride. For dessert, we offer all you can eat, self-serve chocolate and caramel fondue bar with Neal's homemade ice cream and biscotti, all butter shortbread, pound cakes, fresh whipped cream, fruits and other delicious dippers.
Now serving $9 lunch!

topReview.highlightedText: Booked a table on the street and the views down Colorado Avenue were spectacular. Great backdrop to the tasty cheese and filet board. One had the gluten free ciabatta bread and even the rest of the party good not believe it was gluten free. Wishes the menu would have mentioned there was meat in the potato dish on filet board for the vegetarian among us. Minor glitch though in such a wonderful evening.

name: Mamma Silvia’s Italian Kitchen
description:
We craft traditional Italian cuisine inspired by Mamma Silvia’s family recipes. We cook from scratch to order “al momento” using the best ingredients with attention to detail. We ask for your patience, please keep in mind that quality can’t be rushed. Thank you for joining us in sharing Mamma’s love of cooking for family and friends.

Buono appetito!

topReview.highlightedText: Great food. Great wine selection. And great service.

name: Angry Chicken CS & Juicy 88 Hotdog
description: Korean Fried Chicken & street food finally coming to the Springs! Come try our deliciously crisp, one of a kind Fried Chicken, trendy Korean style corn dogs, and fresh fruit juices which you can't find anywhere else in Colorado! When you're looking for a quick bite, tasty refreshments, or a welcoming dine in experience, reach out to Angry Chicken CS & Juicy 88 Hotdog! We hope to see you all soon!

name: Chef. llc. DBA Totem Post Supper Club
description: We are a underground supper club, locations are subject to change. themes constantly change and we are a donation based service and there is never a charge for the food. The price donated is legally considered a contribution, donation or membership fee.

name: Caroline's- Wine Country Inn
description: Whether you prefer informal or formal, dinner will is based on fresh, sustainable local foods paired with local wines. Tapestry Lounge features signature cocktails, wine and beer along with small plates and an informal menu. The more formal Victorian dining room, Caroline’s, focuses on fresh Colorado foods such as lamb and beef along with fresh, local produce prepared in the classic French tradition.

topReview.highlightedText: The food was creative and featured the local peaches.  Staff was friendly, professional and knowledgeable.

name: Tomboy Tavern
description:
Located slope-side at the base of the Village Express (4) in the Mountain Village core, the Tomboy Tavern offers craft beers from across Colorado, an extensive array of unique and world-class whiskies, and a meticulously curated wine list. Elevated American fare highlights our lunch menu, while dinner is characterized by an approachable yet upscale dining experience. Tomboy offers inside and outdoor patio dining adjacent to the mountain slopes (great views!) in Mountain Village Core a few steps from the Gondola. A private dining room is available; please speak to our manager to reserve.

Hours of Operation are as follows.
Lunch: 11:00am - 5:00pm
Dinner: 5:00pm - 9:00pm
Bar: 11:00am - 11:00pm

topReview.highlightedText: The suggest Tavern but the dinner menu is nothing like a Tavern menu.  Seemed like a disconnect on the image the lunch menu is very Tavern like where dinner could expand to add some higher end Tavern type food like a steak or a nice pasta/ seafood dish but the need to keep the burgers and wings to go with the image at dinner.   It was a turn off

name: Spoons Bistro & Bakery
description:
This is no ordinary restaurant. While you savor your meal, know that you are supporting HopeWest, a nonprofit dedicated to profoundly changing the way our communities experience aging serious illness and grief – one family at a time.

Spoons also supports our local producers by using the freshest local ingredients. Our talented chef has an extraordinary gift for creating dishes sure to become timeless favorites. Whenever possible we support Pear Blossom Farms, Ferris Mushroom Farm, Quality Meats, and other Valley producers. We are proud to showcase Enstrom’s ice cream, giving you the opportunity to experience the locally owned and world famous toffee.

At Spoons our philosophy is simple – fresh, local, from the heart. Our food not only boasts local flavor but also handmade quality. Everything from our savory soups to our decadent desserts are made in house from our heart to yours.

topReview.highlightedText: Very nice dining on their huge patio. Food was amazing (we had macadamia nut encrusted halibut), wine is from a local winery and service was terrific!

name: Timber & Torch
description: We believe the view needs to be as enticing as the food. And when you head to Timber & Torch, located at the base of the mountain, you’ll see what we mean.  Timber & Torch is Steamboat’s version of dining al fresco when we roll up the doors and bring the outdoors inside. The inviting, mountain-inspired atmosphere and Steamboat themed menu at Timber & Torch combine to create the perfect spot to enjoy some time in the Rockies.

topReview.highlightedText: Cathryn (?) on the waitstaff was so hospitable and she took great care of me and my partner. The entire waitstaff are so cohesive, fun, friendly, and hardworking! The food was amazing in variety and quality!

name: Nayarit Restaurant South
description:
Voted "Best Mexican Restaurant" in Durango for four consecutive years!
Extensive menu offering authentic Mexican classics including a local favorite street tacos, a taste of Nayarit Mexico through our seafood menu, and award winning margaritas.
Note: We will not be accepting reservations on Friday nights. Walk-ins only. We apologize for the inconvenience!

topReview.highlightedText: Was greeted promptly and seated quickly.Waiter was very informative and did a great job! Fajitas and Margaritas were awesome!!

name: Buffalos - The Ritz Carlton - Bachelor Gulch
description:
~Buffalos is temporarily closed for the office season. We are excited to welcome you back on June 18th, 2021!

Ideally situated at the base of Chair 16 in the heart of Bachelor Gulch, the traditional gastropub serves hearty, casual fare utilizing only the finest fresh, organic and local Colorado ingredients. Enjoy flavorful, simply prepared dishes paired with an array of regional draft beers in a family-friendly, mountain setting.

Waitlist:
If you are on the waitlist and a table becomes available, you will be called by the restaurant. If you do not answer, we will leave a voicemail indicating the amount of time we will hold the table for. The table will be released to the next party after that time frame.

No-Show Policy:
We do ask that you inform of us of any cancellations. If you do not arrive for your reservation and do not inform us in advance, you will be charged $50/person fee.

topReview.highlightedText: Leo was great!

name: Palisade Café and Wine Bar
description:
Palisade is loved for its unique charm and wonderful community, but you can't forget about the variety of fresh local produce and of course wine. The Palisade Café and Wine Bar brings all these elements to the table to create a delicious and fresh menu. We offer local/regional Colorado wine to accompany dishes prepared with as many local ingredients as possible for the season.

We allow for some reservations, but do hold some tables for walk-ins. If you don't see your desired times, please call or stop in!

topReview.highlightedText: The Palisade Cafe is AWESOME ! The new owners have really done an excellent job with everything!!!  Highly recommend the restaurant !!!!  It’s a favorite for sure 😍

name: Ania's Table
description: Chef Ania is an award winning Culinary Institute of America graduate.  Chef Ania's menus reflect precise techniques and ingredient driven dishes.  Having spent the last decade cooking for some of Napa Valley's best wineries all of Chef Ania's dishes are intended to be paired with wines.  Some signature dishes include Aged "Liberty Farms" Duck Confit, "Flannery Beef" Steaks and Imported Dover Sole.  Chef Ania's husband, Kenny Koda, runs K-Bar at Lumiere Hotel.  Kenny is a veteran sommelier who started his career in the 90s at the legendary Harmon's Restaurant in Telluride.  Ania's Table & K-Bar are unique dining and drinking experinces in Telluride.  K-Bar offers Telluirde's most eclectic collection of wines, beers, and liquors.   The wine list is driven by the Alpine regions of Italy and France, and Napa Valley.  K-Bar is open for drinks 7 days a week 4 to 9PM.  Seating is limited, reservations are recommended, but walk-ins are welcome.  Dinner at Ania's Table is by reservation on

topReview.highlightedText:
Had heard good things about this small restaurant, run by a couple, Ania and Kenny, and decided to give it a try.  She runs the restaurant and he manages the bar and wine list.  They only accept 8 dinners each evening.

Ania’s Table is a real find.  Both the food and wine selection are exceptional.  I ordered the Olathe Corn and Tomatoes, the Duck Confit and Peach and Brioche Bread Pudding.  Everything was really good.  The Duck Confit was exceptional.  I really enjoyed the Bread Pudding, but Ania’s favorite is the chocolate tort, which I will order next time.  Kenny paired each course with a wonderful wine.  He really knows Austrian and Italian alpine wines amongst others. He maintains an exceptional wine list.

I hesitated to post this review as the restaurant is small and such a find.  But I did so in fairness to Ania and Kenny.  But not until I first made two future reservations, including one over the holidays.

name: Elevated
description:
At Elevated mountain lounge and club, you can enjoy our hand crafted American small plates, cocktails or a glass or bottle from our ever-evolving wine list. The ambiance and the friendly, engaging staff will bring you in while the food and drinks will have you coming back.
We are a mountainside hidden gem, come see us before the secret gets out.

topReview.highlightedText: Casual place. More Apre ski than restaurant. Food very good. Tried  the Lobster Mac, crab cakes, and Caesar salad. All were very good. Friendly atmosphere. Had the smoked old fashion which was very good as well. Portion size was good. Best bet is to order a couple of dishes and share.

name: Telluride Sleighs and Wagons
description:
Summer 2021 updated 4/23/2021
We will only be offering PRIVATE Wagon Ride Dinners or Lunches for the season. Private transportation will be provided from a location of your choice.
Pricing: Base rate for up to 6 guests $1,200.
Additional kids $125 and additional adults $175 up to 14 guests.
There will be no comingled groups.
There will be a 1:00 PM and 5:30 PM ride available Tuesday-Saturday
*WE HAVE A CANCELLATION POLICY. PLEASE REVIEW ON OUR WEBSITE*

Located on the historic Aldasoro Sheep Ranch on Last Dollar Road, guests enjoy stunning views, exceptional food in our canvas sheep camp tent. The tent is heated by a wood-burning stove and guests dine family-style at our custom build farm table. You will hear stories about the Aldasoro familys five generations of history in the Telluride area and eat food influenced by the Basque country where the family is from.

topReview.highlightedText: Outstanding!  Great service, food and experience!!!

name: Jake and Telly's Greek Taverna
description:
In 1997, brothers Telly and Jake Topakas moved to Colorado from Philadelphia and opened Jake and Telly’s Greek Taverna, then simply known as Jake and Telly's Bar and Grill. Though at the time the brothers were relatively young, they were third generation restaurateurs and had gathered much second hand experience and knowledge from their father, uncle, and grandfather about the restaurant business.

They soon noticed that many of their customers were enjoying the Greek specials they were offering over the standard American-style menu items and thus began the transition from a bar and grill to the only full-service Greek restaurant in Colorado Springs.

A few years into the business, Telly and Jake became interested in carrying a better variety of Greek wines and began educating themselves about wine and food pairings in general.

topReview.highlightedText: Good food, great servers, great atmosphere! I understand why this restaurant is award winning!

name: Aspen Grille- Colorado State University
description: The Aspen Grille is a student-run restaurant, and part of the hospitality management department at Colorado State University.  We try to provide laboratory environment for our students, while maintaining excellent quality of food and service.

topReview.highlightedText: Outstanding professional service, with grace and respect. Food was delicious. Bravo all around!

name: Whistle Pig Brewing Company
description: Whistle Pig offers a full-menu with delicious, mouth-watering entrees and appetizers that the whole family can enjoy! Whistle Pig’s distinctive craft beers are created with the finest, natural ingredients which are inspired by Colorado’s culture, history, and lifestyle. We have 7 fresh, onsite crafted flagship beers plus a variety of seasonal, session, and experiential beers on tap. Our brewery is a family-friendly environment with Gazette’s award winning, dog-friendly outside patio area that provides a fabulous view of Pikes Peak regardless of the season.

topReview.highlightedText: great food good beer, better than expected. Never been there before will go back.

name: 39° Restaurant
description:
39 Degrees at W Aspen, takes you on a culinary jaunt along the 39th parallel to the Far East. Making stops in vibrant destinations such as Beijing, Seoul and Tokyo, giving Chef Siao the Latitude to indulge palates with global flavors rotating with the seasons.

To book, parties of 6 or more please contact our reservation line @ (970) 431-0800 ext: 199

topReview.highlightedText: We ended up in one of the bubbles and it was AMAZING.  The staff was excellent, the chef came out to say “hi” and the food was delicious.  I would highly recommend it - we’ll be back!

description: Red Lobster welcomes you by offering PRIORITY SEATING to reduce your wait time in the restaurant, so you can spend more time doing the things you love. Red Lobster is the world's largest and most loved seafood restaurant company, offering high quality, freshly-prepared seafood, sourced in a way that is traceable, sustainable and responsible. description: Hotel Colorado Restaurant and Bar, helmed by Executive Chef Franz Garcia, features an array of breakfast, lunch, and dinner options that will delight your senses (and your taste buds). Don't forget, you can also enjoy lunch and dinner in our courtyard (open seasonally and weather permitting).

topReview.highlightedText: Breakfast was great. The ambiance was good and the server was attentive.

name: New Orleans Feast
description:
Stone Table Dinner New Orleans Feast POP UP
Hosted by Sauvage Colorado Cuisine

Stone Table Dinners is a collective of chefs and lovers of food. We live and work on the Front Range of Colorado and have deep roots and affection for Lyons.  Stone Table Dinners allow independent chefs to combine our passions, talents, taste, and love of feeding people into a unique experience for all. From traditional, and not-so-traditional tasting menus to family style spaghetti and meatballs to South Asian specialties, our dinners will please any palate. Hosted at The Stone Cup, Lyons' Front Porch, in their cozy and elegant new event space.

description:

description:
Italian Chalet-styled restaurant and private members club overlooking Aspen Mountain. We feature contemporary Italian cuisine.
We are no longer booking online reservations. Please call 970.920.7277 to book your reservation over the phone.

topReview.highlightedText: Absolutely wonderful. Start to finish it was perfect.

name: Owashi Sushi & Kitchen
description: Serving excellent sushi to the Eagle area.

topReview.highlightedText: Excellent sushi and EXCELLENT service by Erica!  We will definitely return next time we are in town!

name: T&T Grill
description:
Don’t forget your cowboy hat for this wild, family-friendly ride. Load up in the gondola and bundle up under blankets as you head up to the top of Thunderhead Lodge. Bite into mouthwatering BBQ and after you enjoy a delicious, homemade dessert, you and the family will be ready to learn to line dance with a local Steamboat band. This is a toe-tapping, BBQ-loving, dance-friendly Steamboat experience you won’t want to miss..

The Western BBQ offers evening dining most Friday, Saturday, and Sunday nights. Gondola boarding times are available at 6:00pm, 6:30pm, and 7:00pm.

topReview.highlightedText: This place was a hit with our kids and adults.  The band entertained the kids while they danced and played.  Adults were able to talk and visit.  Food was amazing for a Buffett style.  We were very impressed.

name: Venga Venga Cantina and Tequila Bar
description:
Venga Venga, meaning “Let’s go, let’s go!” was created by acclaimed Chef & Restauratuer Richard Sandoval. Savor authentic Mexican food served alongside a collection of 75+ tequilas and mezcals.

Located right off the slopes in Snowmass Village, Venga Venga’s casual & fun atmosphere is is welcoming to all. Cozy up by the fire pits on the outdoor patio with panoramic mountain views while enjoying handcrafted margaritas & table-side guacamole.

Our lunch & dinner menus feature fresh Mexican fare including street tacos, sizzling fajitas, creamy enchiladas and more. ¡Venga Venga!

topReview.highlightedText: We were surprised at the family atmosphere inside the restaurant, but pleasantly surprised by the food and atmosphere outside. Excellent salsa, entrees and margaritas!

name: Collective Vail, a Retreat at 4 Eagle Ranch
description:
Join us for an exquisite, private chef, outdoor farm to table dining experience to take full advantage of the beautiful Vail Valley. Enjoy a the sunset with a three course meal prepared table-side. Our fine dining chefs will personally cook your private or group dinner while you sit back and enjoy the beautiful ranch views.

Reservations only. This is a private location / catering facility only. We do not accept walk ins. Note- fixed cost of $150 per adult for a 3 course, private chef dinner and wine for purchase. Please notify for children meals in advance.

name: Whitewater Bar & Grill
description: The Whitewater Bar & Grill, Royal Gorge Rafting & Zipline tours make the perfect combination to any Colorado vacation! The Whitewater Bar & Grill is a rustic western style bar & grill with all of the perfect amenities. relax before or after your rafting & zip line tour, enjoy the amazing scenery of the surrounding Sangre de Cristo mountain range and enjoy a cold beverage, a delicious meal or just come in to relax.

topReview.highlightedText: Great place, nice staff.  Could you a slight update as the restaurant next door is very updated, but the food is great.

name: 773 Prime
description: Located in the clubhouse at TPC Colorado, 773 Prime brings a new fine dining experience to Northern Colorado. Chef Martin Woods prepares modern cuisine rooted in classic technique. Please join us for dinner Thursday through Sunday from 5pm-9pm.  Reservations are required.

topReview.highlightedText: It was great xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

name: Fiestas Cafe & Cantina
description: Susan and Mariano  use old family recipes brought to Colorado by Susan's  great-grandparents and Central Mexico, tradition to Mariano to create great Southwestern cuisine. Among the favorites are chicken enchiladas in a white jalapeño sauce and blue-corn enchiladas served Santa Fe style with an egg on top. Handmade corn tamales are stuffed with pork and smothered in a classic New Mexican-chile sauce. The eatery in Edwards Plaza is brightly decorated with New Mexican folk art and paintings. More than 20 tequilas keep the bar—and patrons—hopping.

topReview.highlightedText: We went as a group of 11 and had great food and service!  Will go again in the future.

name: Strip & Tail
description:
PLEASE CALL FOR A RESERVATION

Strip & Tail is a surf and turf restaurant located in Winter Park, Colorado. Husband and wife duo Rhonda and Steve draw on their years of hands-on experience to bring diners delicious dishes and unmatched service every time.

When you dine with us, we go above and beyond to ensure your satisfaction. We love what we do, and our tasty food and welcoming atmosphere reflect that. In order to share our passion with even more folks, we also offer catering. We'll happily cater your wedding, corporate meeting, or other special events.

Our goal is to create a fun, relaxing environment for diners to enjoy our delightful dishes. With four TVs and a comprehensive sports package, we're the perfect place to enjoy the big game. We also have a spacious outdoor deck area, so you can enjoy our scenic surroundings while digging into your favorite meal.

topReview.highlightedText: Genuine local place - food’s always great.

name: La Nonna
description: "La Nonna", Italian for grandmother, reflects our passion for Italian food, wine and creating memories with friends and family.

topReview.highlightedText:
Our last night in Vail and La Nonna did not disappoint. My wife and I shared an appetizer, pasta dish, and veal scallopine. Each dish was excellent. Appetizer was the mussels. Sauce was light and perfect for dipping their delicious bread. We had the seafood pasta with a light tomato sauce. Sauce was not too tomatoey and seafood in the pasta was very nice. The octopus was not too chewy.
The veal dish was very good. I was expecting a more traditional scallopine preparation. It was more like a veal parmesan. So if you are inclined to order it make sure you get what you  expect. 
Finally we had the pear tart for dessert. All I can say is that we loved it!
Portions were just right for splitting. 
We had a very nice time there. Wait staff was knowlegadable, and support staff took care of all the details.

name: 503 West
description: 503W is an award winning restaurant + bar in Colorado Springs specializing in uniquely handcrafted food and drinks using fresh, natural and local ingredients. Locally-minded. Locally owned.

topReview.highlightedText: Wonderful drinks and food

name: P.F. Chang's - Loveland
description: P.F. Chang's is a restaurant concept that honors the 2,000-year-old Asian tradition of wok cooking and believes in making food from scratch every day in every restaurant. With a Farm to Wok™ food philosophy at its core, P.F. Chang's chefs hand-roll dim sum, hand chop and slice all vegetables and meats, handcraft every sauce and wok-cook each recipe, every day in every restaurant using wholesome, fresh ingredients. With roots in Chinese cooking, the culinary landscape at P.F. Chang's now stretches across Asia with diverse, culturally inspired recipes including hand-rolled sushi, Vietnamese-style soups and bowls, traditional Chinese dim sum, wok-fired chicken and beef entrées, and family style noodles and rice. All made from scratch every day.

topReview.highlightedText: Great food with excellent service. Lunch servings are perfect.

name: The Welsh Rabbit
description:
The Welsh Rabbit Cheese Bistro -- a place to start, finish, or linger!
We have always described ourselves as "one part Cheese Shop, and one part Cheese Bistro." Now The Cheese Bistro has taken on a life of its own, while still expressing our values of quality, simplicity, a slow pace, and friendship.

topReview.highlightedText:
We had a wonderful time. The staff (chef/waitstaff/etc.) were all fantastic and extremely helpful. The food completely blew us away in how good it was. The “Down the Rabbit Hole” special was completely unexpected and wonderful. I will order that every time going forward.

Kudos to Emily (our server) for her recommendations.

name: Sunset Lounge
description:
Sunset Lounge features all-weather and open-air lounge areas atop The Elizabeth Hotel. Sunset Lounge is open to the public and is able to accommodate groups and events.

Sunset Lounge features an exquisite outdoor space with unrivaled sunset views and front range mountain views. Our beverage program pours a list of craft cocktails, plus wines by the glass and by the bottle.

Imbibe in style and relax in a sophisticated atmosphere. Our rooftop deck is truly the perfect place to unwind while savoring the finest of drinks and views in the Old Town neighborhood.

topReview.highlightedText: The Sunset Lounge has wonderful ambiance. The staff is extremely knowledgeable and personable. The food and beverage options are high quality. We were seated right next to the live music, which was wonderful from a music aspect, but made it a little more difficult to have conversations.

name: Dale Street Bistro
description:
Dale Street Bistro Cafe offers fine food at an affordable price. Most dinner entrees under $20. Most lunch entrees under $10. Our 19th century rooms offer a variety of dining experiences.



Our sunroom, fireside, and art galleries provide a unique and enjoyable dining experience for you, your friends, your family, and your business associates. A wonderful, wonderful patio.



Call or visit us today and make the most of your dining experience. Join us for breakfast, lunch and dinner.

topReview.highlightedText: This Cozy little Victorian restaurant is a hidden gem.  My wife was out of town so I thought I would give it a try as it is in my college neighborhood and I had it recommended to me by a couple who are regular customers.  The trout was outstanding.  The bread pudding with whiskey (I think) sauce was not like my mother made when we were kids.  Don’t miss it!  The price, $17, was fair although the evening was , nevertheless, expensive as I ended up purchasing a piece of original art from their quite expansive gallery.  I had a great table by the Van Briggle fireplace and hated to leave (maybe that was also due to my inevitable return to an empty house!).  Don’t let the construction at the college across the street get in your way, there is parking (well hidden) behind the building.

name: Panhandler's Pizza
description: Panhandler’s Pizza is not only Fort Collin’s BEST pizza restaurant but we are also the oldest! Since 1975, Panhandler’s has served our unique pan-style pizza by the slice or as a whole pie.  Each pizza starts with a pastry-like dough which has be baked lower and slower than a regular pizza.  They take longer but they are worth the wait!! Each pizza is topped with our secret sauce and 100% real, whole-milk Mozzarella cheese loaded with fresh quality toppings and even sausage that is about the best Italian Sausage you can find made here locally.

description:
WELCOME TO SPENCER'S : The Best Mountainside Dining on Peak 9

Spencer's is located right at the base of Peak 9 in Breckenridge, Colorado - at the Beaver Run Resort & Conference Center.

Please note: there is a 5.5% resort fee at Beaver Run Resort.

name: Giampietro Pasta & Pizzeria
description:
Giampietro Pasta & Pizzeria in Breckenridge, CO is a long-time provider of delicious pizza and Italian specialties to diners in the community. Everything is made on the premises, including the pizza sauce, salad dressings and dough, and menus include the regular lunch and dinner options, in addition to a family style to-go menu.

Diners at Giampietro Pasta & Pizzeria will be able to choose from a range of courses and options. The appetizers feature classics like calamari or bruschetta, but also unusual options like a whole roasted artichoke or a fried olive dish. Large salads, hefty sandwiches and main dishes of pasta or meats ensure appetites are easily satisfied. The pizza menu at Giampietro Pasta & Pizzeria is extensive and desserts are a must, especially the layered butterscotch or the panna cota.

name: Squeaky B's
description: Quality. We are not fans of frozen or processed foods. We raise our own Angus Beef at our ranch in Franktown- always all natural, no antibiotics or hormones.  We serve all natural and free range Colorado chicken, and our Premium Artisan brats are hand crafted by Colorado's finest butchers. When seasonally possible, we source all of our farm fresh salads locally, and we make our own hand cut fries! Try an Extreme Milkshake or Champagne Float! Full Bar.  Great Wine and Beer Selections.  Family Friendly and Pet Friendly Patio in the Summer!  Trivia Thursdays great for all ages!

topReview.highlightedText: The delicious food at Squeaky B's is topped only by the friendly and superb service.  The staff goes out of their way to make you feel welcome and at home.

name: Caspian Cafe
description: Bringing wonderful dishes from the Mediterranean to a Colorado Springs Restaurant, Caspian Café is sure to please the palate with amazing flavors prepared by Chef Daniel White. Dishes represent the full range of the Mediterranean from French and Greek Classics such as Steak Nicoise and Gyros to Middle Eastern Dishes such as Falafel and Shish Taouk. Full service bar and private dining area available for banquets. Evening reservations recommended.

topReview.highlightedText: Absolutely delicious!!! Big hit with the whole family!!

name: Zaika Indian Cuisine- Colorado Springs
description: Zaika means flavor. We serve authentic Indian flavors with modern flare. We are a family serving with passion and dedication to our customers. Plus our carefully crafted menus, modish yet sophisticated ambiance are there to give you a great Zaika experience every time. Come on in to take a culinary plunge in lush spices and savory delights at Zaika!

name: BJ's Restaurant & Brewhouse - Colorado Springs
description: Time counts at BJ's Restaurant & Brewhouse. Since our humble beginnings back in 1978, we've continued to refine our brewhouse experience to make BJ's a place where you can make the most of any meal. We want BJ's to be a place where the moment you leave is the moment you plan on coming back. We pride ourselves in our craft and attention to detail. Our guests come here for our award-winning handcrafted beer. They come here for the Southern California twist we've put on the Chicago-style deep dish pizza. And they come here for our Pizookies®, our world-renowned dessert. But above all we know people come here to make their good times better. So in many ways we haven't just crafted a brand, but a mindset. And our guests are the reason for this. And it's because of them we're continually striving to make sure every moment they choose to spend with us counts. Welcome to BJ's, a restaurant with a Brewhouse soul.

name: Vino Giù
description:
Vino Giù

A Unique Wine, Water, and Chocolate Experience
Vino Giù is a beautifully designed venue that offers your palate a tantalizing experience on every level. Our wine, water, and chocolate venue serves premium-quality wines and chocolates, a unique crystal infused gem water bar, and delicious artisan cheeses and charcuterie that will take your taste buds on an amazing adventure. Our collection of wines are made from the finest grapes sourced locally and around the world and handpicked by our Sommelier. Located in beautiful Estes Park, CO, Vino Giù is the perfect gathering place if you’re looking for more than just wine tasting or a place to unwind. Vino Giú is an experience!

name: Ollie's Pub & Grub - Breckenridge
description:
UPDATE: We are currently serving on a walk-in first come first served basis, no reservations accepted. Stop by anytime and join us for a great local experience at the Best Restaurant in town.

Located in the heart of Downtown Breckenridge, Ollies Pub & Grub has been a locals favorite for many years. With water and mountain views from inside and outside is the perfect place to enjoy the amazing scenery Colorado has to offer. Voted twice as the Best Sports Bar in Summit County, whether you're in town with your family and young children for a couple days or have lived in Summit County your entire life, people feel welcomed and comfortable every time they visit us.

Ollie’s is classic American bar fare that far exceeds peoples expectation of “Bar food”. Large portions mean no one goes hungry!

topReview.highlightedText: Came here on a Saturday night and they had no issue seating 8 people. The food & drinks were pretty good!

name: La Plaza Inn
description:
We strive to create a unique dining experience with Chef Tim leading our culinary staff.
Chef Tim brings artful food that is featured on the separate Daily Chef’s Menu, which highlights fresh and unique ingredients.

topReview.highlightedText: We love La Plaza, it is a wonderful, relaxing place and we go there frequently. People are great there, the owner is awesome and really cares about her customers.

name: Red Lobster - Grand Junction
description: Red Lobster welcomes you by offering PRIORITY SEATING to reduce your wait time in the restaurant, so you can spend more time doing the things you love. Or, come enjoy a drink at our bar and a Tasting Plate while you wait. Red Lobster is the world's largest and most loved seafood restaurant company, offering high quality, freshly-prepared seafood, sourced in a way that is traceable, sustainable and responsible. We offer lunch and dinner daily, featuring classics like our Ultimate Feast®, Garlic Shrimp Scampi and Parrot Isle Jumbo Coconut Shrimp, and feature limited time flavors and preparations during events like Lobsterfest®, Crabfest® and Endless Shrimp®. And, who can resist our famous warm and cheesy Cheddar Bay Biscuits®? To learn more visit www.redlobster.com

topReview.highlightedText: The fish and chips and the parrot bay shrimp were outstanding.   The linguine was just okay, but then this is a seafood restaurant, not Italian!  As usual the biscuits were to die for!  The only disappointments were COVID related...   lack of selection on the salad (only one choice, one dressing), and not being able to have a drink in the bar while we waited for our table.  So I guess that’s more a comment about COVID!

name: The View Restaurant - Mountain Lodge
description: The View Restaurant in Mountain Lodge in Telluride offers up some of the most delectable cuisine in a fantastic setting that gives you stunning views of the natural splendor of Colorado.

topReview.highlightedText: Gorgeous view of ski mountains with an amazing fireplace centered in the middle of dining area. Food was excellent.

name: Burger Theory
description:
Introducing Burger Theory, located at Holiday Inn Hotel & Suites Durango Central. Our casual restaurant offers an extensive menu of burger creations and Colorado craft beers! We have 13 HDTVs conveniently placed throughout the restaurant, offering a great sports watching experience. The friendly ambience of our restaurant is inviting for both individual travelers, families and locals alike.

Call us for dinner To-Go from 5pm - 9pm! - We'll be sure to make it just as enjoyable at home!

topReview.highlightedText: Burger was good but messy. Burger not put together correctly. Lettuce and tomato placed under meat and made it slick which mafe it fall apart. Otherwise it was great.
